a|अ
I. The letter a¤, the first of the alphabet and the short vowel inherent in every consonant. See अकार. <BR>II. The pronominal theme which occurs in the declension of इदम् and is considered as a substitute for इदम् and एतत् qq. vv. <BR>III. ind. (निपात) A particle, a shorter form of न (see also अन and अना); it is used<BR> ^1 In composition with nouns, when it implies<BR> ^a. Negation.<BR> ^b. Privation or prohibition.<BR> ^c. Diminution (i. e. a little).<BR> ^d. Deterioration.<BR> ^e. Similarity or comparison; in a few instances it has apparently become an expletive; cf. e. g. कुप्य and अकुप्य, उदार and अनुदार, एडमूक and अनेडमूक. If the noun begins with a vowel, it assumes the form of अन्, as अ and अन्त form अनन्त; this rule is neglected sometimes, if the vowel following the अ happen to be a ऋ; e. g. अ and ऋणिन् form अनृणिन् and sometimes अऋणिन्.<BR> ^2 In conjunction with an inflected verb, when it implies blame or reproach; e. g. अ करोषि वै त्वं जाल्म ‘how badly thou dost (it), fool’. Accord. to an artificial E. from अत्, kŕit aff. ड. <BR>IV. ind. (निपात) An interjection of pity. <BR>V. 1. m. (अः)<BR> ^1 Vaiśwánara (in an Upan.).<BR> ^2 Brahman (m.).<BR> ^3 Vishńu.<BR> ^4 Siva. 2. n. (अम्) A name of the (neuter) Brahman.

aRNin|अऋणिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णी-णिनी-णि) Free from debt or obligation; also अनृणिन्. E. अ neg. and ऋणिन्.

aMsh|अंश्
r. 10th cl. par. (अंशयति or अंशापयति- p. p. अंशित) To divide, to distribute.

aMsha|अंश
I. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 Dividing, distributing.<BR> ^2 A part.<BR> ^3 A share or portion.<BR> ^4 A fraction.<BR> ^5 The numerator of a fraction.<BR> ^6 A degree (of latitude or longitude, &c.).<BR> ^7 The name of an Áditya.<BR> ^8 (In music.) See अंशस्वर. Also confounded with अंस q. v. E. अंश्, kŕit aff. घञ्, or perhaps more correctly, अम्, uń(?) aff. श. <BR>II. m. n. (-शः-शम्) The shoulder, the shoulder blade. (In this sense the word is more correctly written अंस q. v.)

