akarmabhoga|अकर्मभोग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) The renunciation of reward for virtuous actions, the liberation of the soul from the fruits of action, that is, its absorption into the divine essence which releases it from future transmigration and from the trammels of matter, bestowing the highest state of future bliss. E. अ neg. and कर्मभोग.

