akavaari|अकवारि
m. f. (-रि-री) (ved.) Explained either as I. Tatpur. 1. Not having contemptible enemies--or--2. Having obtained superiority. E. 1. अ neg. and कव-अरि (enemy). 2. अकव and अरि (going to, obtaining); or as <BR>II. Bahuvr. Having enemies who are not to be despised. E. अकव and अरि (enemy).

