axaagra|अक्षाग्र
Tatpur. n. (-ग्रम्)<BR> ^1 The fore part of a car.<BR> ^2 The axle or bar to which the wheels are attached. E. अक्ष and अग्र.

axaagrakiila|अक्षाग्रकील
Tatpur. m. (-लः) The pin of the axle of a carriage, the linchpin, also one at the extremity of the pole. E. अक्षाग्र and कील. See also the following.

axaagrakiilaka|अक्षाग्रकीलक
m. (-कः) See the preceding. E. अक्षाग्रकील, taddh. aff. कन् or as Tatpur. अक्षाग्र and कीलक.

axaara|अक्षार
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः) Natural salt, salt which is not factitious. E. अ neg. and क्षार. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not containing factitious salt. See अक्षारलवण and अक्षारालवण. E. अ priv. and क्षार.

axaaralavaNa|अक्षारलवण
n. (-णम्) I. Tatpur. Natural salt, as river salt &c.,  which has not been obtained artificially. See क्षार and लवण. E. अक्षार (which is explained as अ neg. and क्षार artificial(?) and लवण, or better: अ neg. and क्षारलवण (Dvandva): neither क्षार nor लवण. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Such food as may be eaten during a season considered impure or improper for the performance of religious duties, as a season of mourning &c. (See अशौच.) It is said to consist of cows milk, ghee, rice, kidney-beans, barley, sesamum, and sea or river salt. The word occurs also written अक्षारालवण. E. अ priv. and क्षारलवण (Dvandva), sc. अन्न.

axaaraalavaNa|अक्षारालवण
Dvandva. n. (-णम्) See the preceding, under II. E. अक्षार and अलवण.

axaanti|अक्षान्ति
Tatpur. f. (-न्तिः)<BR> ^1 Impatience, intolerance.<BR> ^2 Envy, impatience of another's superiority or success. E. अ neg. and क्षान्ति.

axaavapana|अक्षावपन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A dice-board. E. अक्ष and आवपन.

axaavaapa|अक्षावाप
