ag|अग्
r. 1st cl. par. (अगति-आग-अगिता.--Caus. अगयति.) To wind or move tortuously. See अक्.

aga|अग
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Not going, not moving. 2. m. (-गः)<BR> ^1 A mountain.<BR> ^2 A tree.<BR> ^3 The sun.<BR> ^4 A water jar(?).<BR> ^5 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the numeral seven. E. अ neg. and ग. See अगच्छ, अगम and नग. <BR>II. m. (-गः) A snake. E. अग्, kŕit aff. अच्.

agachCha|अगच्छ
