angaNa|अङ्गण
n. (-णम्) A court, or yard. See अङ्गन.

angati|अङ्गति
m. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 A name of Brahmá.<BR> ^2 A name of Vishńu.<BR> ^3 Fire.<BR> ^4 A Brahman, who maintains a sacred fire &c. See अग्निहोत्रिन्. E. अङ्ग्, uń. aff. अति. See अङ्कति.

angada|अङ्गद
Tatpur. I. m. (-दः) A proper name of<BR> ^a. a son of Lakshmańa, the brother of Ráma and king of Ángadi, the capital of a country near the Himálaya;<BR> ^b. a son of Gada by Vŕihatí;<BR> ^c. a celebrated monkey, one of the heroes of the Rámáyańa, the son of Bali. <BR>II. f. (-दा) The female elephant of the south or according to others, of the north. See अङ्गना. <BR>III. n. (-दम्) A bracelet worn upon the upper arm. E. अङ्ग and द.

angadviipa|अङ्गद्वीप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) One of the divisions of the world. E. अङ्ग and द्वीप.

angana|अङ्गन
