angula|अङ्गुल
I. m. (and according to one authority also n.) (-लः -लम्)<BR> ^1 A finger.<BR> ^2 The thumb.<BR> ^3 A finger's breadth, as a linear measure, viz. a measure of eight barley corns joined side by side in breadth or of three grains of rice in length. Twelve angulas make a vitasti or span, and twenty-four a hasta or cubit.<BR> ^4 (In astronomy.) A digit or one twelfth part of any dimension, subdivided into sixty vyangulas. E. अङ्गुल is considered by the gramm. authorities as a substitute of अङ्गुलि, as which it ought to occur only at the end of certain Tatpur., derived then with samásánta aff. अच् and at the end of certain Bahuvr., derived with samásánta aff. षच्. In both cases it is a neutre. The native dictionaries however state as above. <BR>II. m. (-लः) A proper name of the sage Cháńakya. E. अङ्ग्, uń. aff. उलन्(?).

angulapramaaNa|अङ्गुलप्रमाण
