angulitoraNa|अङ्गुलितोरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Three semicircular lines drawn across the forehead, with sandal or ashes of burnt cowdung &c., a sectarial mark, especially of the followers of Śiva, more commonly termed Tripund́ra. E. अङ्गुलि and तोरण the ornamented arch of a gateway, to which the mark made by the fingers upon the forehead may be compared.

angulitra|अङ्गुलित्र
Tatpur. n. (-त्रम्) See the following. E. अङ्गुलि and त्र (what protects).

angulitraaNa|अङ्गुलित्राण
Tatpur. m.(?). n. (-णः(?)-णम्) A piece of leather or thin iron, worn on the thumb or finger by archers to prevent the bowstring from injuring it. E. अङ्गुलि and त्राण.

anguliparvan|अङ्गुलिपर्वन्
