anguliiyaka|अङ्गुलीयक
n. (-कम्) A finger ring. E. अङ्गुलीय, taddh. aff. कन्. See also अङ्गुरीयक.

anguliisambhuuta|अङ्गुलीसम्भूत
Tatpur. m. (-तः) A finger nail. E. अङ्गुली and सम्भूत.

anguShTha|अङ्गुष्ठ
Tatpur. m. (-ष्ठः)<BR> ^1 The thumb.<BR> ^2 The great toe.<BR> ^3 A thumb's breadth, as a linear measure which is said to be a measure of six barley corns. This seems, however, not to be correct, because twelve angusht́has are given by the same authority as equal to a Vitasti or span. See अङ्गुल. E. अङ्गु here said to mean the hand, and स्थ.

anguShThamaatra|अङ्गुष्ठमात्र
m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्री-त्रम्) Having the size of, being as little as a thumb. E. अङ्गुष्ठ, taddh. aff. मात्रच्; but, more properly, a Bahuvr. composed of अङ्गुष्ठ and मात्रा.

anguShThamaatraka|अङ्गुष्ठमात्रक
m. f. n. (-कः-त्रिका-कम्) The same as the preceding. E. The preceding, taddh. aff. कन्. 

anguShThya|अङ्गुष्ठ्य
m. (-ष्ठ्यः) The nail of the thumb. E. अङ्गुष्ठ, taddh. aff. यत्.

anguuSha|अङ्गूष
m. (-षः)<BR> ^1 An ichneumon.<BR> ^2 An arrow. E. अङ्ग्, uń. aff. ऊषन्(?).

angya|अङ्ग्य
m. f. n. (-ङ्ग्यः-ङ्ग्या-ङ्ग्यम्) Belonging to, being in the body, the limbs &c. See the meanings of अङ्ग. E. अङ्ग, taddh. aff. यत्.

aNGgh|अङ्घ्
r. 1st cl. átm. (अङ्घतेआनङ्घे-अङ्घिता &c.).<BR> ^1 To go.<BR> ^2 To go swiftly.<BR> ^3 To begin moving.<BR> ^4 To begin.<BR> ^5 To blame, to censure.<BR> ^6 To despise. See also अंह्, of which it seems to be the fuller and original form.

aNGgha|अङ्घ
See E. of अङ्घारि.

aNGghas|अङ्घस्
n. (-ङ्घः) Sin. E. See अंहस्, of which it seems to be the fuller and original form.

aNGghaari|अङ्घारि
Tatpur. m. (-रिः) The enemy of sin or evil, a vaidik epithet of Soma and of one of the sacrificial fire altars. E. अङ्घ, an abbreviation of अङ्घस् (see also अघ), and अरि.

aNGghi|अङ्घि
m. (-ङ्घिः) The same as the following. The correctness of this form seems very doubtful.

aNGghri|अङ्घ्रि
m. (according to some also n.) (-ङ्घ्रिः-ङ्घ्रि)<BR> ^1 A foot.<BR> ^2 The root of a tree. E. अङ्घ्, uń. aff. क्रिन्. See also अंह्रि, of which this word seems to be the fuller, original form. All words meaning ‘foot’ have also the meaning of ‘root of a tree’.

aNGghripa|अङ्घ्रिप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) A tree. See अंह्रिप. E. अङ्घ्रि and प.

aNGghriparNii|अङ्घ्रिपर्णी
Bahuvr. f. (-र्णी) A plant (Hedysarum lagopodioides). See the following and पृश्निपर्णी. E. अङ्घ्रि and पर्ण, fem. aff. ङीप्, the leaves rising from the root.

aNGghrivalli|अङ्घ्रिवल्लि
Bahuvr. f. (-ल्लिः) A plant (Hedysarum logopodioides Rox.). Also अङ्घ्रिवल्ली. See the preceding and the following. E. अङ्घ्रि and वल्लि.

aNGghrivallikaa|अङ्घ्रिवल्लिका
Bahuvr. f. (-का) A plant (Hedysarum lagopodioides, Rox.). E. अङ्घ्रिवल्लि, samásánta aff. कप्.

aNGghriskandha|अङ्घ्रिस्कन्ध
Tatpur. m. (-न्धः) The ancle. See also अंह्रिस्कन्ध. E. अङ्घ्रि and स्कन्ध.

ach|अच्
I. r. 1st cl. See अञ्च् I. (The forms अचति-अचते- p. p. अचित- in the meaning of ‘to go’ and अचते-आचन्त- in the meaning of ‘to bend’ belong only to the Vedas.) <BR>II. As latter part of a compound, see अञ्च् II.

achakra|अचक्र
m. f. n. (-क्रः-क्रा-क्रम्) I. Tatpur. (ved.) Not moving, not vacillating, immoveable. E. अ neg. and चक्र. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Having no wheels. E. अ priv. and चक्र.

achaxurviShaya|अचक्षुर्विषय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) What is not attainable by sight, invisible. E. अ neg. and चक्षुर्विषय.

achaxuShka|अचक्षुष्क
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Having no eyes. E. अचक्षुस्, samásánta aff. कप्.

achaxus|अचक्षुस्
I. Tatpur. n. (-क्षुः) A bad or contracted eye. E. अ neg. and चक्षुस्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षुः-क्षुः-क्षुः) Having no eyes, blind. E. अ priv. and चक्षुस्.

achaNDa|अचण्ड
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ण्डः-ण्डा or -ण्डी-ण्डम्) Gentle, not passionate. <BR>II. f. (-ण्डी) A tractable cow. E. अ neg. and चण्ड.

achatura|अचतुर
m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) I. Bahuvr. Having not four, being devoid of four. E. अ and चतुर्, samásánta aff. अच्.  <BR>II. Tatpur. Not dexterous, not clever &c. See चतुर. E. अ neg. and चतुर.

achara|अचर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Immoveable. E. अ and चर.

achala|अचल
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Immoveable, fixed. <BR>II. m. (-लः)<BR> ^1 A mountain.<BR> ^2 A pin or bolt.<BR> ^3 A name of Śiva.<BR> ^4 A proper name, viz. the first of the nine ‘white Balas’, a class of deified persons peculiar to the Jainas.<BR> ^5 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the numeral seven. <BR>III. f. (-ला)<BR> ^1 The earth.<BR> ^2 One of the ten Buddhist earths(?). E. अ neg. and चल.

achalakiilaa|अचलकीला
Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The earth. E. अचल and कील.

achalatviSh|अचलत्विष्
Bahuvr. m. (-त्विट्) The Kokila or Indian cuckoo. E. अचल and त्विष्.

achaladhRti|अचलधृति
Bahuvr. f. (-तिः) The name of a metre which consists of four lines, each of them having sixteen short syllables. It is called also Gítyáryá. E. अचल and धृति.

achalabhraatR|अचलभ्रातृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) A proper name: a Bráhmańa of Oude, of the Haríta family, who became a convert to the Jaina doctrine and then one of the eleven chiefs of the gańas or assemblings of the Jaina Ŕishis. E. अचल and भ्रातृ.

achalamati|अचलमति
Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) The name of a Rákshasa. E. अचल and मति.

achalaadhipa|अचलाधिप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) The king of mountains, the personified Himálaya; also analogous compounds, as अचलेन्द्र, अचलेश्वर, &c. E. अचल and अधिप.

achaapalya|अचापल्य
Tatpur. n. (-ल्यम्) Firmness, steadiness, consistency. E. अ neg. and चापल्य.

achaaru|अचारु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रुः-र्वी-रु) Inelegant, not beautiful. E. अ neg. and चारु.

achikkaNa|अचिक्कण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Not smooth, rough &c. See चिक्कण. E. अ neg. and चिक्कण.

achit|अचित्
(ved.) I. Tatpur. m. (-त्) One who does not perform the ceremony of the अग्निचयन q. v., one who is impious. E. अ neg. and चित् (collecting). <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्) Without understanding, foolish. E. अ priv. and चित् (understanding).

achita|अचित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) I. Gone. (Only in the Vedas.) E. अच्, kŕit aff. क्त, with ágama इट्. <BR>II. Tatpur. Not collected &c. See चित. E. अ neg. and चित.

achitta|अचित्त
m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) I. Tatpur.<BR> ^1 Not thought, inconceivable.<BR> ^2 Unperceived, not expected. E. अ neg. and चित्त (thought). <BR>II. Bahuvr. Without intellect, insensible, inanimate. E. अ priv. and चित्त (intellect).

achitti|अचित्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Want of intellect, infatuation, foolishness. (ved.) E. अ neg. and चित्ति.

achintaa|अचिन्ता
Tatpur. f. (-न्ता)<BR> ^1 Absence of thought or consideration.<BR> ^2 Disregard. E. अ neg. and चिन्ता.

achintita|अचिन्तित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unthought of, unexpected.<BR> ^2 Disregarded. E. अ neg. and चिन्तित.

achintya|अचिन्त्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्त्यः-न्त्या-न्त्यम्) Inconceivable, unimaginable, incomprehensible. <BR>II. m. (-न्त्यः) A name of Śiva. E. अ neg. and चिन्त्य. 

achira|अचिर
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not long (in time), brief, momentary. Adverbially are used: अचिरम्, अचिरेण and अचिरात्, in a short time, soon, directly. In composition with a participle, अचिर means ‘not yet a long time, not long ago, recently’. See f. i. अचिरप्रसूता, अचिरमृत. <BR>II. f. (-रा) A proper name: the mother of Śánti, the sixteenth Arhat or Jaina saint of the present Avasarpińí. E. अ neg. and चिर.

achiradyuti|अचिरद्युति
Bahuvr. f. (-तिः) Lightning. E. अचिर and द्युति; ‘its light being of short duration’.

achiraprabhaa|अचिरप्रभा
Bahuvr. f. (-भा) Lightning. E. अचिर and प्रभा. See the preceding.

achiraprasuutaa|अचिरप्रसूता
Tatpur. f. (-ता) A cow which has recently calved. E. अचिर and प्रसूता.

achirabhaas|अचिरभास्
Bahuvr. f. (-भाः) Lightning. E. अचिर and भास्. See अचिरद्युति.

achiramRta|अचिरमृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Recently deceased. E. अचिर and मृत.

achirarochis|अचिररोचिस्
Bahuvr. f. (-चिः) Lightning. E. अचिर and रोचिस्. See अचिरद्युति.

achiraaMshu|अचिरांशु
Bahuvr. f. (-शुः) Lightning. E. अचिर and अंशु. See अचिरद्युति.

achiraabhaa|अचिराभा
Bahuvr. f. (-भा) Lightning. E. अचिर and आभा. See अचिरद्युति.

achetana|अचेतन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 Devoid of reason or feeling, insensible (especially as an attribute of matter and inanimate objects).<BR> ^2 Unconsicous. E. अ priv. and चेतना.

achetas|अचेतस्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ताः-ताः-तः) The same as the preceding. E. अ priv. and चेतस्.

achetaana|अचेतान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not reflecting, thoughtless, infatuated. (ved.) E. अ neg. and चेतान.

acheShTa|अचेष्ट
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Motionless. E. अ priv. and चेष्टा.

acheShTataa|अचेष्टता
f. (-ता) Fainting, syncope, loss of sense or consciousness. E. अचेष्ट, taddh. aff. तल्.

achaitanya|अचैतन्य
n. (-न्यम्) I. Tatpur.<BR> ^1 Ignorance, especially spiritual.<BR> ^2 Unconsciousness, insensibility. E. अ neg. and चैतन्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. The material universe or matter in general, as being devoid of reason or feeling and opposed to spiritual being or God. E. अ priv. and चैतन्य. As a Bahuvr. this word may also be used in the three genders.

achodas|अचोदस्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दाः-दाः-दः) Without compulsion, not compelled, spontaneous. (ved.) E. अ priv. and चोदस्.

achCha|अच्छ
I. m. f. n. (-च्छः-च्छा-च्छम्) Clear, transparent. See छ. <BR>II. m. (-च्छः)<BR> ^1 Crystal.<BR> ^2 A bear (see ऋक्ष). <BR>III. ind. (see निपात) A kind of preposition (or गति q. v.) with the meaning of ‘to, unto, before, in front’, or ‘obtaining, taking possession of’. Its use seems to be restricted to the vaidik literature where it appears, for the most part, in the protracted form अच्छा. It occurs only in conjunction with verbs implying motion or speech--especially with अज्, इ, गम्, या, नश्, नु, वा, वच्, वद्--either preceding or following them and requiring the noun which depends upon this combination to stand in the accusative or in  the locative; the latter case, however, is only exceptional.-The word is given also in the form अच्छम्. E. unknown. That which is given is: अ neg. and छो, kŕit affix क, ‘not cutting or injuring sc. the sight’ and would refer only to I. and to II. 1. in the sense of ‘not easily cut’.

achChabhalla|अच्छभल्ल
Tatpur.(?) m. (-ल्लः) A bear. This is sometimes considered as two words. See अच्छ and भल्ल. E. अच्छ and भल्ल.

achChaavaaka|अच्छावाक
m. (-कः) One of the sixteen Ŕitvijs or priests required for the performance of the great sacrifices with the juice of the Soma plant. He is one of the three priests who are subordinate to the होतृ q. v. (see besides मैत्रावरुण and ग्रावस्तुत्) and one of the four priests who receive the third division of the Dakshińá q. v. (See also नेष्टृ, अग्नीध् and प्रतिहर्तृ.) E. वच् with अच्छ in its protracted form, kŕit aff. घञ्.

achChaavaakiiya|अच्छावाकीय
I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Referring to the अच्छावाक q. v. <BR>II. n. (-यम्)<BR> ^1 A Súkta or hymn in which the word अच्छावाक occurs.<BR> ^2 The office or function of the अच्छावाक. E. अच्छावाक, taddh. aff. छ.

achChidra|अच्छिद्र
I. Tatpur. n. (-द्रम्) Uninterruptedness, completeness. E. अ neg. and छिद्र. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्रः-द्रा-द्रम्)<BR> ^1 Uninterrupted.<BR> ^2 Uninjured, unhurt. E. अ priv. and छिद्र.

achChinna|अच्छिन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) Uncut, unhurt, uninjured. E. अ neg. and छिन्न.

achChinnapattra|अच्छिन्नपत्त्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Having the wings uninjured, unbroken (also metaphorically as a vaidik epithet of the इष्टकाः which were arranged in the shape of a bird. See अग्निचयन). E. अच्छिन्न and पत्त्र.

achChuptaa|अच्छुप्ता
Tatpur. f. (-प्ता) A proper name, viz. one of the sixteen Vidyádevís, female divinities peculiar to the mythology of the Jainas. E. अ neg. and छुप्त ‘not touched scil. by sin’.

achCheta|अच्छेत
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Approached, obtained. E. इ, with अच्छ, kŕit aff. क्त.

achChaidika|अच्छैदिक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not always fit to be cut. E. अ neg. and छैदिक.

achChokti|अच्छोक्ति
Karmadh. f. (-क्तिः) Pure speech. E. अच्छ (pure) and उक्ति. This word may also be explained in the sense of ‘allocution’ from अच्छ (the गति), and उक्ति.

achChoda|अच्छोद
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-दः-दा-दम्) Having clear or limpid waters. <BR>II. f. (-दा) The name of a river produced by the Manes Agnishwáttas. <BR>III. n. (-दम्) The name of a lake in the Himálaya, deriving its origin from the river Achchhodá. E. अच्छ and उद (a substitute of उदक).

achyuta|अच्युत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not falling, fixed, firm.<BR> ^2 Imperishable, permanent.<BR> ^3 Not oozing, not trickling, not dripping. <BR>II. m. (-तः)<BR> ^1 A name of Vishńu or Kŕishńa.<BR> ^2 A shrub (Morinda tinctoria). E. अ neg. and च्युत.

achyutaxit|अच्युतक्षित्
Bahuvr. m. (-त्) Resting on a solid ground (a vaidik epithet of Soma &c.). E. अच्युत and क्षित् (dwelling). 

achyutachyut|अच्युतच्युत्
Tatpur. m. (-त्) Shaking or destroying what is fixed (a vaidik epithet of Indra &c.). E. अच्युत and च्युत्.

achyutaja|अच्युतज
Tatpur. m. pl. (-जाः) A class of Jaina deities which belong to the Vaimánikas and are produced by Vishńu. E. अच्युत and ज.

achyutadanta|अच्युतदन्त
Bahuvr. m. (-न्तः) A proper name: the ancestor of the warrior tribe, called आच्युतदन्ति. E. अच्युत and दन्त.

achyutanta|अच्युतन्त
Bahuvr.(?) m. (-न्तः) A proper name: the ancestor of the warrior tribe, called आच्युतन्ति. E. unknown; perhaps the same as the former in a mutilated form.

achyutamuurti|अच्युतमूर्ति
Bahuvr. m. (-र्तिः) A name of Vishńu. E. अच्युत and मूर्ति ‘having an imperishable shape’.

achyutavaasa|अच्युतवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) The religious fig tree (Ficus religiosa). E. अच्युत and वास ‘Vishńu's abode’.

achyutasthala|अच्युतस्थल
Tatpur. n. (-लम्) The name of a place in the Panjab. E. अच्युत and स्थल.

achyutaagraja|अच्युताग्रज
Tatpur. m. (-जः) A proper name of the elder brother of Vishńu, viz.<BR> ^1 Balaráma,<BR> ^2 Indra. E. अच्युत and अग्रज.

aj|अज्
r. 1st cl. par. (अजति. The tenses which require árdhadhátuka affixes, are not to be formed of this radical, वी (q. v.) being then considered as a substitute, of which the formation is to take place. According to others, however, there may be found. perf. आजिथ- fut. अजिता-अजिष्यति- aor. आजीत्- cond. आजिष्यत्. Pass. अज्यते- fut. अजिता-अजिष्यते- prec. अजिषीष्ट- aor. आजिष्ट. Des. अजिजिषति.)<BR> ^1 To go.<BR> ^2 To throw or cast, to impel. With<BR> ^1 अच्छ- To impel to.<BR> ^2 अप- To send away.<BR> ^3 अभि- To impel to.<BR> ^4 अव- To send down.<BR> ^5 आ- To direct hither (trans. and intrans.), to fetch, to scatter.<BR> ^6 आ pref. अभि(अभ्या-) To direct hither.<BR> ^7 उद्- To drive out, to draw out.<BR> ^8 उप- To direct near.<BR> ^9 निर्- To drive out.<BR> ^10 वि- To throw asunder, to scatter.<BR> ^11 सम्- To throw or send together.

aja|अज
I. 1. m. (-जः)<BR> ^1 The mover, the instigator.<BR> ^2 As such, this word occurs in the Vedas, for the most part in conjunction with एकपाद् (q. v.), as an epithet or as a synonyme of<BR> ^a. Indra,<BR> ^b. Rudra, one of the Maruts,<BR> ^c. Agni,<BR> ^d. Púshan or Súrya; in the epic and pauráńik literature as a synonyme of<BR> ^a. Brahmá (see also अजन),<BR> ^b. Vishńu,<BR> ^c. Śiva,<BR> ^d. Káma; in philosophical texts, in its feminine form (अजा) as a synonyme of<BR> ^a. Prakŕiti or Nature,<BR> ^b. Máyá or Illusion, the unreality of Nature or Universe.<BR> ^3 A proper name, viz.<BR> ^a. A descendant of Viśwámitra.<BR> ^b. A prince of the solar race, the son of Raghu and father of Daśaratha, or according to others, the grandson of Raghu, the son of Dilípa and father of Dírghabáhu; or the son of Nábhága and father of Daśaratha.<BR> ^4 A he-goat. This animal was considered as the vehicle of Púshan, the sun, (see अजाश्व) and also as consecrated to Agni and Soma conjointly.<BR> ^5 (In astronomy.) The sign Aries.<BR> ^6 The name of a mineral substance. See माक्षिक and अजनामक.<BR> ^7 A kind of rice, three or seven years old(?).<BR> ^8 The moon(?). BREAḲ. m. pl. (-जाः) The name of<BR> ^a. a sort of Ŕishis in Brahma's heaven;<BR> ^b. a people mentioned in the Vedas. <BR>3. f. (-जा)<BR> ^1 Prakŕiti or Nature.<BR> ^2 Máyá or Illusion  (see अज m.).<BR> ^3 A she-goat.<BR> ^4 The name of a plant, the bulbs of which resemble the udder of a she-goat. E. अज्, kŕit aff. अच्; in the fem. with the aff. टाप्. 1. 4. and 2. 3. implying ‘the quick animal’. <BR>II. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Unborn. This meaning has been applied to अज in the sense of Brahmá, Vishńu, Śiva, Káma, and अजा in the sense of Prakŕiti and Máyá. But see before. E. अ neg. and ज.

ajaka|अजक
I. m. (-कः) A proper name:<BR> ^1 A descendant of Purúravas, the son of Sumantu (or according to others of Sunaha) and grandson of Jahnu.<BR> ^2 A king of Magadha, of the line of Pradyota. <BR>II. f. (-का)<BR> ^1 A young she-goat. (Also अजिका.)<BR> ^2 A kind of disease of the pupil of the eye. See अजकाजात. E. अज, taddh. aff. क.

ajakarNa|अजकर्ण
Bahuvr. m. (-र्णः)<BR> ^1 The ear of a goat.<BR> ^2 A tree (Terminalia alata tomentosa, Rox.); the leaf being compared to the ear of a goat. See also असन. E. अज and कर्ण.

ajakarNaka|अजकर्णक
m. (-कः) A tree, vulg. Sál (Shorea robusta, Rox.). See साल. E. taddh. कन् affixed to the preceding, denoting resemblance.

ajakava|अजकव
m. (-वः) The bow of Śiva. E. unknown; the following is evidently artificial: अज Vishńu, and क Brahmá, taddh. aff. व, Brahmá being placed in the centre, and Vishńu on the upper part. See also अजकाव-अजगव-अजगाव-अजीकव-आजगव.

ajakaajaata|अजकाजात
Tatpur. n. (-तम्) A disease of the transparent cornea of the eye: small tumors like the litter of goats, slightly red, which protrude through the cornea, from which a bloody discharge proceeds mixed with pus. E. अजका and जात.

ajakaava|अजकाव
I. m. n. (-वः-वम्) The bow of Śiva; see अजकव. <BR>II. m. (-वः) A poisonous little animal. <BR>III. n. (-वम्) A sacrificial vessel consecrated to Mitra and Varuna. E. doubtful. Perhaps this word is derived from अजका, taddh. aff. व, III. being explained as a vessel having a piece of wood in the shape of the throat nipples of a goat and II. as an animal poisonous or deadly as the disease अजका.

ajakuulaa|अजकूला
Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The name of a town of the Bodhis. E. अज and कूल.

ajaxiira|अजक्षीर
Tatpur. n. (-रम्) Goat's milk. This word occurs only in the Vedas. E. अज, instead of अजा, and क्षीर. See अजाक्षीर.

ajaga|अजग
See E. of अजगव.

ajagandhaa|अजगन्धा
Bahuvr. f. (-न्धा) The shrubby basil (Ocymum gratissimum). E. अज and गन्ध, ‘smelling like a goat’.

ajagandhikaa|अजगन्धिका
Bahuvr. f. (-का) The shrubby basil (Ocymum gratissimum). E. अजगन्धा, samásánta aff. कप्.

ajagandhinii|अजगन्धिनी
f. (-नी) A plant. See अजशृङ्गी. E. अज-गन्ध, taddh. aff. इनि.

ajagara|अजगर
Tatpur. I. m. (-रः) The Boa, a large serpent. (Boa constrictor.) <BR>II. f. (-री) The name of a plant. E. अज and गर (who swallows).

ajagallikaa|अजगल्लिका
f. (-का) One of the ‘minor diseases’; it occurs in children and consists of small tuberculous eruptions of the form of peas. E. अजगल्ल (cheek of a goat), taddh. aff. कन्. 

ajagava|अजगव
n. (-वम्)<BR> ^1 The bow of Śiva. See अजकाव.<BR> ^2 The southern portion of the three portions into which the path of the sun and other planets amongst the lunar asterisms is divided. See जरद्गव. E. अजग (the meaning of this word is not given), taddh. aff. व. See the E. of अजकाव.

ajagaava|अजगाव
n. (-वम्) See अजगव.

ajaghanya|अजघन्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्) Not the last, not the lowest. E. अ neg. and जघन्य.

ajajiivika|अजजीविक
Bahuvr. m. (-कः) A goatherd. E. अज and जीविका. See also अजाजीव.

ajaTaa|अजटा
Bahuvr. f. (-टा) The name of a plant (Flacourtia cataphracta). Also written अजडा and अज्झटा. E. अ priv. and जटा.

ajaDa|अजड
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-डः-डा-डम्) Not foolish, not stupid. <BR>II. f. (-डा) The name of two plants:<BR> ^1 See अजटा.<BR> ^2 See कपिकच्छु. E. अ neg. and जड.

ajatva|अजत्व
n. (-त्व) The being अजा q. v. Also अजात्व. E. अजा, the long आ being shortened, taddh. aff. त्व.

ajathyaa|अजथ्या
f. (-थ्या) A plant (Yellow jasmin). E. अज, taddh. aff. थ्यन्, ‘fit for goats’. See also यूथि.

ajadaNDii|अजदण्डी
Tatpur. f. (-ण्डी) The name of a plant. See also ब्रह्मदण्डी. E. अज (Brahmá) and दण्ड.

ajadevataa|अजदेवता
Bahuvr. f. pl. (-ताः) The name of the twenty fifth lunar mansion. See पूर्वभाद्रपदा. E. अज and देवता.

ajana|अजन
I. 1. n. (-नम्) Instigating, moving. BREAḲ. m. (-नः) A name of Brahmá. See अज. E. अज्, kŕit aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Devoid of men, solitary. E. अ priv. and जन.

ajanani|अजननि
m. (-निः) Privation of birth; used as an imprecation. Ex. अजननिरस्तु तस्य may he cease to exist. E. अ priv. and जननि.

ajanayonija|अजनयोनिज
Tatpur. m. (-जः) A name of Daksha. E. अजन-योनि and ज ‘born from Brahmá’.

ajanaamaka|अजनामक
Bahuvr. m. (-कः) The name of a mineral substance. See अज and माक्षिक. E. अजनामन् (having the name of Vishńu), samásánta aff. कप्.

ajani|अजनि
f. (-निः) Path, road. E. अज्, kŕit (or uń.?) aff. अनि.

ajanya|अजन्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्)<BR> ^1 Not to be born or produced.<BR> ^2 Not fit for or favourable to men. <BR>II. n. (-न्यम्) A portent, an omen, any natural phenomenon as an earthquake &c. so considered. E. अ neg. and जन्य.

ajapa|अजप
I. Tatpur. m. (-पः) 1. A goat-herd. E. अज and प. BREAḲ. A reader of works considered heterodox. E. अ deter. and जप. <BR>II. Bahuvr. f. (-पा) The name of a particular mantra or mystical formula, otherwise bearing the name of Hansa. E. अ priv. and जप; so called from its not consisting of a जप or a prayer repeated inaudibly, like other mantras, but of a certain number of inhalations and exhalations.

ajapatha|अजपथ
Tatpur. m. (-थः) Probably the same as अजवीथी q. v. E. अज and पथिन्, samásánta aff. अ, ‘like a goat's road’; the taddh. aff. कन् which implies similarity, being considered as dropped in this word. 

ajapada|अजपद
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दः-दा or -दी-दम्) Goat-footed. E. अज and पाद, samásánta aff. अच्. See the following.

ajapaada|अजपाद
Bahuvr. m. (-पादः) Goat-footed. E. अज and पाद.

ajapaarshva|अजपार्श्व
Bahuvr. m. (-श्वः) A surname of Rájívalochana, the son of Swetakarńa. E. अज and पार्श्व; ‘his sides were black like the skin of certain goats, when he was drawn out of the water after having been found exposed by his mother and purified by two sons of Sravisht́há’.

ajapaala|अजपाल
Tatpur. m. (-लः)<BR> ^1 A goat-herd.<BR> ^2 A proper name: according to the Matsyapuráńa, the son of Dírghabáhu and father of Daśaratha. See अज. E. अज and पाल.

ajabhaxa|अजभक्ष
Tatpur. m. (-क्षः) The name of a plant. See वर्वूर. E. अज and भक्ष ‘goat's food’.

ajamaayu|अजमायु
Karmadh. m. (-यः) Bleating like a goat (as a frog). (In the Vedas.) E. अज and मायु.

ajamaara|अजमार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The name of a prince(?). E. अज and मार.

ajamiiDha|अजमीढ
Tatpur. m. (-ढः) A proper name:<BR> ^1 A son of Suhotra and author of vaidik hymns.<BR> ^2 The 26th king of the lunar dynasty, a grandson of Suhotra and son of Bŕihat, or according to others, a grandson of Suhotra and son of Hastin.<BR> ^3 A surname of Yudhisht́hira, the friend of Aja. Also अजमीळ्ह (ved.). E. अज and मीढ.

ajamukha|अजमुख
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-खः-खी-खम्) Goat-faced, having a face like that of a goat. <BR>II. f. (-खी) The name of a female fiend. E. अज and मुख.

ajamodaa|अजमोदा
Tatpur. f. (-दा) The name of several plants:<BR> ^1 Common carroway (Carum carui).<BR> ^2 A kind of lovage (Ligusticum ajwaen, Rox.).<BR> ^3 A sort of parsley (Apium involucratum); this latter application is the one used in the dialects. E. अज and मोद.

ajamodikaa|अजमोदिका
f. (-का) The name of a plant (Ligusticum Ajwaen). E. The former, taddh. aff. कन्.

ajambha|अजम्भ
Bahuvr. m. (-म्भः) A frog. E. अ priv. and जम्भ ‘having no teeth’.

ajaya|अजय
I. Tatpur. m. (-यः) Defeat. E. अ neg. and जय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Unsurpassed, unsubdued, over whom or which no triumph is obtained. BREAḲ. m. (-यः)<BR> ^1 A name of Vishńu.<BR> ^2 The proper name of a lexicographer.<BR> ^3 The name of a river in Rád́ha. <BR>3. f. (-या)<BR> ^1 Hemp.<BR> ^2 One of the female friends of Durgá. See विजया. E. अ priv. and जय.

ajayya|अजय्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-य्यः-य्या-य्यम्) Invincible, not to be subdued or surpassed. E. अ neg. and जय्य.

ajara|अजर
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Undecaying, not becoming old or infirm. <BR>II. f. (-रा)<BR> ^1 Aloes perfoliata. See गृहकन्या.<BR> ^2 See जीर्णफञ्जी, a climbing plant, a kind of वृद्धदारक q. v. E. अ priv. and जरा. With respect to the declension of this word, see जरा and अजरस्.

ajarayu|अजरयु
Tatpur. (ved.) m. (-युः) Undecaying. E. अ neg. and जरयु.

ajaras|अजरस्
Bahuvr. A substitute for अजर in some cases. See जरा.

ajarya|अजर्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Imperishable, undecaying. <BR>II. n. (-र्यम्) Friendship. E. अ neg. and जर्य. 

ajarShabha|अजर्षभ
Tatpur. m. (-भः) The best goat. E. अज and ऋषभ.

ajalambana|अजलम्बन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Antimony. E. अज and लम्बन.

ajaloman|अजलोमन्
Tatpur. m. (-मा)<BR> ^1 Goat's hair.<BR> ^2 Cowach (Carpopogon pruriens). See अग्रपर्णी. E. अज and लोमन्.

ajalomii|अजलोमी
Tatpur. f. (-मी). See the preceding. E. अज and लोमन्, samásánta aff. टच्.

ajavasti|अजवस्ति
Tatpur. I. m. (-तिः) A proper name. <BR>II. m. pl. (-स्तयः) The descendants of the former. E. अज and वस्ति.

ajavaaha|अजवाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) The name of a country. E. अज and वाह.

ajaviithii|अजवीथी
Tatpur. f. (-थी) One of the three divisions of the southern portion (see अजगव or जरद्गव), one of the three portions into which the path of the sun and other planets amongst the lunar asterisms is divided. It comprises the three asterisms Múlá, Púrváshád́há and Uttaráshád́há. E. अज and वीथी ‘goat's road’. See also अजपथ.

ajashRngii|अजशृङ्गी
Tatpur. f. (-ङ्गी) A plant; described as a milky and thorny plant, with a fruit of a crooked figure, like a ram's horn, and used as a medicine for the eyes; vulg. Mera Śringí, and Kankara Śringí (Odina Wodier Rox.). See कर्क्कटशृङ्गी. E. अज and शृङ्ग.

ajastunda|अजस्तुन्द
Tatpur. n. (-न्दम्) The name of a town. E. अज and तुन्द with ágama सुट् ‘like a goat's belly’.

ajasra|अजस्र
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-स्रः-स्रा-स्रम्) Continual, uninterrupted. <BR>II. ind. (-स्रम्) Eternally, continually, always. E. अ neg. and जस्र.

ajahatsvaarthaa|अजहत्स्वार्था
Tatpur. f. (-र्था) A figure of speech, the characteristic of the उपादानलक्षणा q. v. It consists in using a word in an elliptic meaning without depriving it of its primary sense; in such phrases as श्वेतो धावति or कुन्ताः प्रविशन्ति, are to be supplied अश्व &c. in the former, पुरुष &c. in the latter, so as to impart the sense of ‘a white horse gallops’, ‘the men with lances enter’, while श्वेत and कुन्त retain their original sense. See, on the contrary, जहत्स्वार्था.--E. अ neg. and जहत्स्वार्था, scil. लक्षणा.

ajahallinga|अजहल्लिङ्ग
Tatpur. m. (-ङ्गः) (In grammar.) A noun that does not vary its gender, even when it is used attributively. E. अ neg. and जहल्लिङ्ग, scil. शब्द.

ajahaa|अजहा
Tatpur. f. (-हा) Cowach (Carpopogon pruriens). E. अज and ह.

ajaakRpaaNiiya|अजाकृपाणीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) As in the fable of the goat and the shears, viz. approached unreflectingly. E. अजाकृपाणी (Dwandwa अजा and कृपाणी), taddh. aff. छ, implying here comparison.

ajaaxiira|अजाक्षीर
Tatpur. n. (-रम्) Goat's milk. See अजक्षीर. E. अजा and क्षीर.

ajaagara|अजागर
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not wakeful, not awake. <BR>II. m. (-रः) A small plant (Eclipta, or Verbesina prostrata). See भृङ्गराज. E. अ neg. and जागर.

ajaagalastana|अजागलस्तन
Tatpur. m. (-नः)<BR> ^1 The small fleshy protuberance, resembling a nipple depending from the throat of a species of the Bengal goat.<BR> ^2 A term for a worthless, good for nothing person. E. अजा and गलस्तन. 

ajaaji|अजाजि
Tatpur. f. (-जिः) See the following. E. अजा and आजि or अजि.

ajaajii|अजाजी
Tatpur. f. (-जी) Cumin seed (Cuminum cyminum). E. The preceding, fem. aff. ङीष्.

ajaajiiva|अजाजीव
Bahuvr. m. (-वः) A goatherd; also अजजीविक, अजाजीविन् &c. E. अज and आजीव.

ajaata|अजात
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unborn, unproduced, not yet born, not yet produced. E. अ neg. and जात.

ajaatakakud|अजातककुद्
Bahuvr. m. (-त्) A young Indian bull, the hump of which has not yet grown. E. अजात and ककुद, the अ of the latter being dropped.

ajaatavyavahaara|अजातव्यवहार
Bahuvr. m. (-रः) A lad under his fifteenth year, a minor (in law). E. अजात and व्यवहार.

ajaatashatru|अजातशत्रु
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-त्रुः-त्रुः-त्रु)<BR> ^1 Having no enemies existent.<BR> ^2 Having no one existent who is worth being called an enemy. <BR>II. m. (-त्रुः) A proper name or a synonyme of<BR> ^1 Śiva,<BR> ^2 Yudhisht́hira,<BR> ^3 A king of Káśi,<BR> ^4 A son of Śamíka,<BR> ^5 A son of Vidmisára, or according to others,<BR> ^6 A son of Bimbisára and contemporary of Śákyamuni. E. अजात and शत्रु.

ajaataanushaya|अजातानुशय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Having no regret. E. अजात and अनुशय.

ajaataari|अजातारि
Bahuvr. m. (-रिः) A name of Yudhisht́hira. E. अजात and अरि. See अजातशत्रु of which it is a synonyme.

ajaatva|अजात्व
n. (-त्वम्). See अजत्व. E. अजा, taddh. aff. त्व.

ajaada|अजाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) The ancestor of a warrior tribe, called the आजाद्याः E. अज and अद.

ajaadanii|अजादनी
Tatpur. f. (-नी) A small species of prickly nightshade. E. अज and अदन.

ajaani|अजानि
Bahuvr. m. (-निः) Having no wife. E. अ priv. and जानि.

ajaanika|अजानिक
Bahuvr. m. (-कः). See the preceding. E. अजानि, samásánta aff. कप्.

ajaaneya|अजानेय
I. m. (-यः) A horse of a good breed. See आजानेय. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Fearless, undaunted. E. See आजानेय, the initial being made short.

ajaantrii|अजान्त्री
Tatpur. f. (-न्त्री) A potherb (Convolvulus argenteus). See छगलान्त्री. E. अज and अन्त्र.

ajaapaalaka|अजापालक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) A goatherd. E. अजा and पालक. Also used in the three genders m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्).

ajaami|अजामि
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मिः-मिः-मि) Not of kin, not related, not friendly. (In the Vedas.) E. अ neg. and जामि.

ajaamitaa|अजामिता
f. (-ता) The not being of kin, related &c. (In the Vedas.) E. The preceding, taddh. aff. तल्.

ajaayamaana|अजायमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not born. E. अ neg. and जायमान.

ajaavika|अजाविक
Dwandwa n. (-कम्) Goats and sheep. E. अज and अविक, the sing. used instead of the plural.

ajaashva|अजाश्व
I. Dwandwa n. (-श्वम्) Goats and horses (the sing. ased instead of the plur.). <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. (-श्वः) Having goats as his vehicle, a vaidik epithet of Púshan. See अज. E. अज and अश्व.

aji|अजि
f. (-जि) A road. See also आजि. E. अज्, uń. aff. इ.

ajikaa|अजिका
f. (-का) A young she-goat. E. See अजका.

ajita|अजित
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unconquered.<BR> ^2 Unexcelled, unsurpassed.  <BR>II. m. (-तः)<BR> ^1 The proper name of several gods and persons, viz.<BR> ^a. Vishńu.<BR> ^b. Śiva.<BR> ^c. One of the seven Ŕishis who preside during the reign of the fourteenth Manu.<BR> ^d. A name of Maitreya or a future Buddha.<BR> ^e. The second of the Arhats or Jaina saints of the present Avasarpińí, a descendant of Ikshváku and a son of Jitaśatru by Vijayá.<BR> ^f. The attendant of Suvidhi or the ninth Jaina Arhat of the present Avasarpińí.<BR> ^2 The name of a powerful antidote.<BR> ^3 A kind of poisonous rat. <BR>III. m. pl. (-ताः) A particular class of gods in the reign of the first Manu, the same as the जयाः in a former life. E. अ neg. and जित.

ajitabalaa|अजितबला
Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The name of one of the Śásanadevatás, a class of divinities particular to the Jainas, who are supposed to carry out the commands of the Arhats. E. अजित and बल.

ajitavikrama|अजितविक्रम
Bahuvr. m. (-मः) A surname of Chandragupta the second. E. अजित and विक्रम ‘of invincible strength’.

ajitaatman|अजितात्मन्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्मा-त्मा-त्म) One who has not subdued his mind, who has not command over himself. E. अजित and आत्मन्.

ajitaapiiDa|अजितापीड
Bahuvr. m. (-डः) The name of a prince. E. अजित and आपीड.

ajitendriya|अजितेन्द्रिय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) One who has not subdued his senses or worldly desires. E. अजित and इन्द्रिय.

ajina|अजिन
I. n. (-नम्) The hide of a tiger, lion &c., but more especially of the antilope or the black species of it (see अजिनयोनि and कृष्णाजिन) and particularly appropriated to the religious student as a garment, seat, bed &c. <BR>II. m. (-नः) The name of a descendant of Pŕithu, the son of Havirdhána by Dhishańá. E. अज्, uń. aff. इनच्; but it would seem that I. is derived from अज, with taddh. aff. इनच्.

ajinapattra|अजिनपत्त्र
Bahuvr. f. (-त्त्रा or -त्त्री) A bat. E. अजिन and पत्त्र.

ajinapattrikaa|अजिनपत्त्रिका
Bahuvr. f. (-का) The same as the former. E. The former, samásánta aff. कप्.

ajinaphalaa|अजिनफला
Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The name of a plant. E. अजिन and फल.

ajinayoni|अजिनयोनि
Bahuvr. m. (-निः) A deer or antilope. E. अजिन and योनि ‘where the hide comes from’.

ajinavaasin|अजिनवासिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Being clad in an antilope hide. E. अजिन and वासिन्.

ajinasandha|अजिनसन्ध
Tatpur. m. (-न्धः) One who joins together hides, a kind of furrier. E. अजिन and सन्ध.

ajira|अजिर
I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Quick, fast. (अजिरम् is also used adverbially.) <BR>II. m. (-रः) The proper name of a priest who officiated at a sacrifice performed in order to destroy the serpents. <BR>III. f. (-रा)<BR> ^1 A river.<BR> ^2 A name of Durgá. <BR>IV. n. (-रम्)<BR> ^1 A court or yard.<BR> ^2 Air, wind.<BR> ^3 The body.<BR> ^4 A frog.<BR> ^5 An object of sense. E. अज्, uń. aff. किरच्.

ajiravatii|अजिरवती
f. (-ती) The name of a river on which Śrávasti was situated. E. अजिर, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

ajirashochis|अजिरशोचिस्
Bahuvr. m. (-चिः) Having a quick light, glittering, a vaidik epithet of Agni and Soma. E. अजिर and शोचिस्. 

ajiraay|अजिराय्
denom. átm. (अजिरायते) To become quick, to hasten. E. अजिर, denom. aff. क्यङ्.

ajiriiya|अजिरीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Being in or not far from, produced by, possessing or having a court or yard &c. See the meanings of अजिर. E. अजिर, taddh. aff. छ.

ajihma|अजिह्म
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ह्मः-ह्मा-ह्मम्) Straight, not crooked, literally or metaphorically; upright, sincere, honest, direct. <BR>II. m. (-ह्मः)<BR> ^1 A frog.<BR> ^2 A fish(?). E. अ neg. and जिह्म.

ajihmaga|अजिह्मग
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-नम्) Going or moving in a straight line. <BR>II. m. (-गः) An arrow. E. अजिह्म and ग.

ajihva|अजिह्व
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-ह्वः-ह्वा-ह्वम्) Tongueless, having no tongue. <BR>II. m. (-ह्वः) A frog. E. अ priv. and जिह्वा.

ajiikava|अजीकव
n. (-वम्) The bow of Śiva. See अजकाव. E. unknown.

ajiigarta|अजीगर्त
Tatpur.(?) m. (-र्तः) The name of a Ŕishi, the father of Śunah́śepha and son of Súyavasa. E. अ neg. and जीगर्त.

ajiiti|अजीति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Not fading, not decaying. (In the Vedas.) E. अ neg. and जीति.

ajiirNa|अजीर्ण
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्)<BR> ^1 Undigested.<BR> ^2 Undecayed, unimpaired. <BR>II. n. (-र्णम्)<BR> ^1 Flatulency, indigestion.<BR> ^2 Vigour, absence of old age or decay. E. अ neg. and जीर्ण.

ajiirNi|अजीर्णि
Tatpur. f. (-र्णिः) Indigestion, flatulency. E. अ neg. and जीर्णि.

ajiirNin|अजीर्णिन्
m. f. n. (-र्णी-र्णिनी-र्णि) Having an indigestion. E. अजीर्ण, taddh. aff. इनि.

ajiiva|अजीव
I. Tatpur. m. (-वः)<BR> ^1 Non-existence.<BR> ^2 Death. E. अ neg. and जीव. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्)<BR> ^1 Lifeless, dead. E. अ priv. and जीव.

ajiivani|अजीवनि
Tatpur. f. (-निः) Non-existence; used as an imprecation. Ex. अजीवनिस्तस्य भूयात्. E. अ neg. and जीवनि.

ajiivita|अजीवित
Tatpur. n. (-तम्)<BR> ^1 Non-existence.<BR> ^2 Death. E. अ neg. and जीवित.

ajuShTa|अजुष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) (ved.) Not pleasant, not agreable. E. अ neg. and जुष्ट.

ajuShTi|अजुष्टि
Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) (ved.) Unpleasant feeling, dissatisfaction. E. अ neg. and जुष्टि.

ajetavya|अजेतव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) Invincible, not to be conquered or overcome. E. अ neg. and जेतव्य.

ajeya|अजेय
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Invincible, insuperable, not to be overcome or surpassed. <BR>II. n. (-यम्) The name of an antidote. E. अ neg. and जेय.

ajaikapaad|अजैकपाद्
