ajaiDaka|अजैडक
Dwandwa n. (-कम्) Goats and rams. (The singular used instead of the plural.) E. अज and एडक.

ajoSha|अजोष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) (ved.) Having no delight, feeling no satisfaction. E. अ priv. and जोष.

ajoShya|अजोष्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) (ved.) Insatiable, one who is not easily contented. E. अ neg. and जोष्य.

ajjukaa|अज्जुका
f. (-का) A courtezan (in theatrical language). E. अज्, kŕit aff. उकन्(?). Sometimes read अर्ज्जुका, from अर्ज् to earn, to gain. 

ajjhaTaa|अज्झटा
f. (-टा) A plant (Flacourtia cataphracta). E. unknown.

ajjhala|अज्झल
n. (-लम्) A burning coal. E. unknown.

aJNa|अज्ञ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ज्ञः-ज्ञा-ज्ञम्)<BR> ^1 Ignorant.<BR> ^2 Stupid, foolish, unwise.<BR> ^3 Not having the faculty of understanding, as animals or inanimate objects. E. अ neg. and ज्ञ.

aJNakaa|अज्ञका
Tatpur. f. (-का). The diminutive form of अज्ञा. See the preceding. Also अज्ञिका. E. अ neg. and ज्ञका.

aJNataa|अज्ञता
f. (-ता) Ignorance. Also अज्ञत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अज्ञ, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

aJNaata|अज्ञात
