ajra|अज्र
(ved.) I. m. (-ज्रः) Field, acre, plain. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-ज्रः-ज्रा-ज्रम्) Quick. See अजिर. E. अज्, uń. aff. रन्(?).

ajrya|अज्र्य
(ved.) m. f. n. (-ज्र्यः-ज्र्या-ज्र्यम्) Being in the field, in the plain. E. अज्र, taddh. aff. यत्.

anc|अञ्च्
I. 1. (अन्चु-भ्वादि-उदात्त-स्वरितेत्) r. 1st cl. par. and átm. (अञ्चति-ते-आनञ्च-चे-अञ्चिता-अच्यात्-अक्त्वा p. p. अक्त. Pass. अच्यते and अञ्च्यते. Desid. अञ्चिचिषति-ते.--Caus. अञ्चयति).<BR> ^1 To go.<BR> ^2 To ask, to beg.<BR> ^3 To speak indistinctly.--With अप- To go away; caus. to send away.<BR> --उद्- To rise; caus. to raise, to draw up.--उप- To approach.--नि- To go down.--परि- To go round, to turn round.--वि- To approach in different ways; caus. to drive asunder.--सम्- caus. To impel together. BREAḲ. r. 1st cl. par. and átm. (अञ्चति-ते-अञ्चित्वा- p. p.  अञ्चित and अक्न) To bend, to curve. With आ- To bend.<BR> --नि- To bend down.--वि- To bend asunder.--सम्- To bend together, to bend intensely. <BR>3. (अचि-भ्वादि-उदात्त-उदात्तेत्) r. 1st cl. par. (अञ्चति-अञ्च्यात्-अञ्चित्वा- p. p. अञ्चित) To honour, to worship, to treat with respect. BREAḰ. (अन्चु-चुरादि-परस्मैपदिन्) r. 10th cl. par. (अञ्चयति) To make clear or distinct. With उद्- The same. <BR>See also अच्. <BR>II. 1. m. f. n. (-ङ्-ची-क्) Going. BREAḲ. m. f. n. (-ङ्-ञ्ची-क्) Honouring, worshipping. <BR>This word occurs only as the latter part of several, in most instances irregular compounds, the former part of which is, in the classic dialect, restricted to some prepositions and indeclinables; see f. i. अवाञ्च्-उदञ्च्-न्यञ्च्-प्राञ्च्सम्यञ्च्-विष्वञ्च्-तिर्यञ्च्. In the Vedas it occurs also in composition with pronominal and nominal themes, f. i. in विष्वद्र्यञ्च्-देवद्र्यञ्च्-घृताञ्च्. When it has the meaning of ‘going’, the nasal of the root appears only in the nom., voc. and acc. of the sing. and du. masc., in the nom. and voc. of the plur. masc. and neuter and in the acc. of the plur. neuter; in all the other cases and in the formation of the fem. it is dropped. The declension and the fem. formation of अञ्च् ‘honouring, worshipping’ is regular in retaining the nasal of the root. E. अञ्च्, kŕit aff. क्विन्.

anca|अञ्च
m. (-ञ्चः) Going. It occurs only as the latter part of compounds; f. i. in रोमाञ्च. E. अञ्च्, kŕit aff. अच्.

ancati|अञ्चति
m. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Air, wind.<BR> ^2 Fire. E. अञ्च्, uń. aff. अति. See अङ्कति.

ancatii|अञ्चती
