anjisaktha|अञ्जिसक्थ
Bahuvr. m. (-क्थः) (ved.) Having coloured thighs (an epithet of one of the sacrificial animals offered to Indra and Agni in the Aśwamedha sacrifice). E. अञ्जि and सक्थि, samásánta aff. षच्.

anjiira|अञ्जीर
n. (-रम्) The fig tree, also its fruit. See also मञ्जुल and काकोदुम्बरिका. In Bengal, the word derived from this  implies the Guava; the term has, possibly, been borrowed from the Persian. {??}. E. अञ्ज्, aff. ईरन्.

aT|अट्
I. (अट-भ्वादि-उदात्त-उदात्तेत्) r. 1st cl. par. (अटतिआट-अटिता-अटिष्यति-आटीत्.--Caus. आटयति-आटिटत्.--Desid. अटिटिषति.--Intens. अटाट्यते.) To go round about, to roam, to rove, to ramble, to wander about, especially as a religious mendicant. With परि--the same with an intense meaning. <BR>II. (अट-चुरादि-परस्मैपदिन्) r. 10th cl. par. (आटयति) To slight &c. See अट्ट् II, of which it is given as a various reading.

