aTTaalikaabandha|अट्टालिकाबन्ध
Tatpur. (In architecture.) A kind of base; (there are sixty-four different sorts of bases enumerated in architectural works). E. अट्टालिका and बन्ध. (The form अट्टालिकाबन्धम् used as ind., is explained as being derived from अट्टालिका and बन्धम् (बन्ध्, kŕit aff. णमुल्); it may, however, be taken also as the accus. of the former).

