aNumaatrika|अणुमात्रिक
m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्). The same as the preceding. E. अणुमात्र, taddh. aff. ष्ठन्. This word is also explained as ‘consisting of the minute (अणु) mátrás or eight constituent parts of the body viz. bhúta, indriya, manas, buddhi, vásaná, karman, váyu and avidyá.’

