Tatpur. m. (-वः) The becoming an atom. E. अणु, with taddh. aff. च्वि, and भाव.

aNTh|अण्ठ्
r. 1st cl. átm. (अण्ठतेआनण्ठे-अण्ठिता.--p. p. अण्ठित) To go, to go to or towards. See अठ्.

aNDa|अण्ड
m. n. (-ण्डः-ण्डम्)<BR> ^1 An egg.<BR> ^2 A testicle.<BR> ^3 The scrotum.<BR> ^4 Semen genitale.<BR> ^5 The musk bag, regarded as the scrotum of the deer.<BR> ^6 A name or epithet of Śiva (from his being compared to the Brahmánd́a or representing the world). E. अम्, uń. aff. ड.

aNDaka|अण्डक
I. m. (-कः) The scrotum. <BR>II. n. (-कम्) An egg, a small egg. E. अण्ड, taddh. aff. कन्.

aNDakaTaaha|अण्डकटाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) The shell of the mundane egg. E. अण्ड (see ब्रह्माण्ड) and कटाह.

aNDakoTarapuShpii|अण्डकोटरपुष्पी
