atiita|अतीत
I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Passed, gone away.<BR> ^2 Dead, deceased.<BR> ^3 Gone beyond, overcome, exceeded, surpassed. (In this sense अतीत may enter into composition with a word depending upon it in the accusative, f. i. दुःखमतीत or दुःखातीत.)<BR> ^4 Very much, excessive. <BR>II. m. (-तः) The modern name of a class of ascetics belonging to the Dásnámins, one of the principal sects who adore Śiva as the supreme deity. E. इ with अति, kŕit aff. क्त.

atiitakaala|अतीतकाल
