atiitvarii|अतीत्वरी
f. (-री) (ved.) A disloyal or unchaste woman. E. अतीत्वन् (a masc. form not in use, from इ with अति, kŕit or uń. aff. क्वनिप्, with ágama तुट्), fem. aff. ङीप् and र् instead of न्; or अतीत्वर Tatpur. (अति and इत्वर), fem. aff. ङीप्. See इत्वरी.

atiindriya|अतीन्द्रिय
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Going beyond the senses, unattainable by the senses, imperceptible. <BR>II. m. (-यः) (In the Sánkhya philosophy.) The same as Purusha or soul. <BR>III. n. (-यम्)<BR> ^1 (In the Vedánta philosophy.) The same as Manas q. v.<BR> ^2 (In the Sánkhya.) The same as Pradhána or nature. E. अति (sc. क्रान्त) and इन्द्रिय (in the sense of the accusative).

atiireka|अतीरेक
m. (-कः) See अतिरेक.

atiiva|अतीव
Tatpur. ind. Much, very much, much indeed. (Sometimes अतीव may be explained as representing the two distinct words अति (the preposition) and इव which through Sandhi form अतीव but which are not then to be considered as an inseparable Tatpur. compound.) E. अति and इव.

atiisaara|अतीसार
m. (-रः) Diarrhœa or dysentery. See अतिसार.

atiisaarakin|अतीसारकिन्
m. f. n. (-की-किनी-कि). See अतिसारकिन्.

atunga|अतुङ्ग
