adRsh|अदृश्
Bahvur. m. f. n. (-दृक्) Blind. E. अ priv. and दृश्.

adRshya|अदृश्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्)<BR> ^1 Invisible, not to be seen.<BR> ^2 Improper to be beheld. E. अ neg. and दृश्य.

adRshyakaraNa|अदृश्यकरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Making invisible. E. अदृश्य and करण.

adRshyat|अदृश्यत्
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्-न्ती-त्) Invisible. <BR>II. f. (-न्ती) The name of the wife of Śakti, the son of Vaśisht́ha, and mother of Paráśara. E. अ neg. and दृश्यत्.

adRShTa|अदृष्ट
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Unseen, unforeseen.<BR> ^2 Unknown, unfelt, not experienced.<BR> ^3 Invisible. <BR>II. n. (-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Casual and unseen danger (as from conflagration, inundation &c.).<BR> ^2 Fortune, destiny, fate.<BR> ^3 (In philosophy.)<BR> ^a. Virtue or vice (धर्म or अधर्म), as the eventual cause of pleasure or pain.<BR> ^b. The remote or unforeseen consequence of an act, e. g. heaven as that of religious rites &c. See अपूर्व. <BR>III. m. (-ष्टः) A kind of poison or poisonous reptile (in the Vedas). E. अ neg. and दृष्ट.

adRShTaja|अदृष्टज
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Produced by destiny &c. See अदृष्ट. E. अदृष्ट and ज.

adRShTanara|अदृष्टनर
Bahuvr. m. (-रः) The same as the following q. v. E. अदृष्ट and नर.

adRShTapuruSha|अदृष्टपुरुष
Bahuvr. m. (-षः) A form of treaty, in which the parties treat direct, without any mediator or surety. Also अदृष्टनर and similar compounds. E. अदृष्ट and पुरुष, sc. सन्धि.

adRShTapuurva|अदृष्टपूर्व
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) Unseen previously, unseen till now. E. अदृष्ट and पूर्व.

adRShTavat|अदृष्टवत्
m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्)<BR> ^1 Enjoying or undergoing good or bad fortune, more usually the former, fortunate. E. अदृष्ट, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

adRShTi|अदृष्टि
Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) A look of displeasure, evil eye. E. अ deter. and दृष्टि.

adRShTikaa|अदृष्टिका
f. (-का) An angry or displeased look, evil eye. E. अदृष्टि, taddh. aff. कन्.

adeya|अदेय
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Improper or unfit to  be given. II. n. (-यम्) (In law.) An object not fit to be given away, either because it does not belong to the person who would give it, or because law forbids its being disposed of. See अदत्त, दत्त, देय. E. अ neg. and देय.

adeyadaana|अदेयदान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Giving what ought not to be given, what is not one's own &c. See the preceding. E. अदेय and दान.

adeva|अदेव
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-वः-वी-वम्)<BR> ^1 Not referring to the gods, not divine.<BR> ^2 Godless, impious. <BR>II. m. (-वः) One who is not a god. E. अ neg. and देव. I. would more probably be a Bahuvr., if it were not accentuated in the Vedas as a Tatpur. See the following.

adevaka|अदेवक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Having no god or divinity, referring to no god or divinity (as an offering &c.). E. अ priv. and देव, samásánta aff. कप्.

adevataa|अदेवता
Tatpur. f. (-ता) One who is not a divinity. E. अ neg. and देवता.

adevatraa|अदेवत्रा
Tatpur. ind. (ved.) Not towards or amongst the gods. E. अ and देवत्रा.

adevayat|अदेवयत्
Tatpur. m. (-न्) (ved.) One who does not care for the gods, not devout, impious. E. अ neg. and देवयत्.

adevayu|अदेवयु
Tatpur. m. (-युः) (ved.) The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and देवयु.

adesha|अदेश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 An improper place, a wrong place, one not congenial with one's nature &c. E. अ deter. and देश.

adeshastha|अदेशस्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Being not in the proper place, being in the wrong place. E. अदेश and स्थ.

adeshya|अदेश्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्)<BR> ^1 What is not proper to be ordered.<BR> ^2 Not present on the spot, not present at a transaction. E. अ neg. and देश्य.

adomaya|अदोमय
m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Made of that, consisting of that, containing that. E. अदस्, taddh. aff. मयट्.

adomuula|अदोमूल
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Rooted in that, founded upon that. E. अदस् and मूल.

adga|अद्ग
m. (-द्गः) The same as पुरोडाश q. v. E. अद्, uń. aff. गन्.

addhaa|अद्धा
ind. (निपात) Tatpur.(?)<BR> ^1 Indeed, truly, verily.<BR> ^2 Clearly. It may enter into composition with कृ (as a गति q. v.). E. अद् ind. and धा (from धा, kŕit aff. विच्); or according to others, but without probability, अद् (to eat), kŕit aff. क्विप्, and हन् (to kill), taddh. aff. डाच्.

addhaatamaam|अद्धातमाम्
ind. (ved.) Most truly, most certainly, most to be relied upon. E. अद्धा, taddh. aff. तमप् (i. e. the superl. of अद्धा in the acc. of the femin.).

addhaati|अद्धाति
m. (-तिः) (ved.) A wise man. E. अद्धा, taddh. aff. तिल्(?).

addhaapuruSha|अद्धापुरुष
Tatpur. m. (-षः) (ved.) A true man, one deserving the name of a man. E. अद्धा and पुरुष.

addhaabodheya|अद्धाबोधेय
Tatpur. m. pl. (-याः) The name of a Śákhá of the white Yajurveda. E. अद्धा and बोधेय(?).

addhyaalohakarNa|अद्ध्यालोहकर्ण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा or -र्णी-र्णम्) (ved.) Having red ears (as a goat). E. अद्ध्यालोह (very red? see लोह) and कर्ण, in the fem. with aff. टाप् or ङीष्.

adbhuta|अद्भुत
Tatpur.(?) I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Surprising, wonderful (according to a vaidik interpretation: not having existed before). <BR>II. m. (-तः)<BR> ^1 Surprise, astonishment. See अद्भुतरस.<BR> ^2 The name of the Indra or chief of the ninth Manwantara. <BR>III. n. (-तम्)<BR> ^1 A prodigy, a wonder, any portentous  or marvellous phenomenon.<BR> ^2 (In architecture.) A kind of temple or vimána, the breadth of which is divided into four parts, seven such parts being given to its height. E. (doubtful) अद् ind. and भू, uń. aff. डुतच्. Compare अनतिद्भुत.

adbhutagandha|अद्भुतगन्ध
Bahvur. m. f. n. (-न्धः-न्धा-न्धम्) Having a wonderful smell. E. अद्भुत and गन्ध.

adbhutatva|अद्भुतत्व
n. (-त्वम्) Wonderfulness. E. अद्भुत, taddh. aff. त्व.

adbhutabraahmaNa|अद्भुतब्राह्मण
Karmadh. n. (-णम्) The name of a Bráhmańa belonging to the Sámaveda; more properly the last portion of the Shad́vinśabráhmańa of the same Veda. E. अद्भुत and ब्राह्मण.

adbhutarasa|अद्भुतरस
Tatpur. m. (-सः) (In rhetoric.) The marvellous, as a prevailing sentiment in poetical composition, one of the nine rasas or characteristic sentiments of poetical composition as described in Hindu works on rhetoric or poetry. See रस. E. अद्भुत and रस.

adbhutaraamaayaNa|अद्भुतरामायण
Karmadh. n. (-णम्) The name of a work ascribed to Válmíki. E. अद्भुत and रामायण.

adbhutaruupa|अद्भुतरूप
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Having a wonderful shape or figure. E. अद्भुत and रूप.

adbhutasaara|अद्भुतसार
Karmadh. m. (-रः) The resin of the खदिर q. v. E. अद्भुत and सार.

adbhutasvana|अद्भुतस्वन
Bahuvr. m. (-नः) A name of Śiva. Another reading of this word is अद्भुतश्वन. E. अद्भुत and स्वन ‘producing a wonderful sound’.

adman|अद्मन्
n. (-द्म) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Food in general.<BR> ^2 A house. E. अद्, kŕit (or uń.) aff. मनिन्.

admani|अद्मनि
m. (-निः) Fire. E. अद्, uń. aff. अनि and ágama मुट्.

admara|अद्मर
m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Gluttonous. E. अद्, kŕit aff. क्मरच्.

admasad|अद्मसद्
Tatpur. f. (-द्) (ved.)<BR> ^1 A cook.<BR> ^2 A mother. E. अद्मन् and सद्; according to the comm. ‘sitting by the food, to cook it; or sitting in the house; or spending food’.

admasadya|अद्मसद्य
n. (-द्यम्) (ved.) Being a cook, the condition of a cook. See the preceding. E. अद्मसद्, taddh. aff. य.

adya|अद्य
I. ind.<BR> ^1 To-day.<BR> ^2 Now, at present. In the Vedas also written अद्या which seems to be the more original form of this word. अद्यापि Even now, still. अद्यपूर्वम् before today, before now. E. अश्, considered as a substitute of इदम्, taddh. aff. द्य; but more probably a Karmadh. compound of अ (the pronom. theme in इदम्) and द्य or द्या (from द्यु or दिव्) = अस्मिन्द्यवि. <BR>II. 1. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Fit to be eaten, eatable. BREAḲ. n. (-द्यम्) Food in general. E. अद्, kŕitya aff. यत्.

adyatana|अद्यतन
I. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Of or belonging to the current day, of to-day. <BR>II. m. (-नः) The period of a current day, from midnight to midnight in the usual acceptation, but sometimes considered to begin and to end with sun-set or to begin with the proper time of rising and to end with the proper time of going to rest. <BR>III. f. (-नी) (In grammar.) The aorist (or लुङ्), as the tense employed in relating what has happened during the current day. E. अद्य, taddh. aff. ट्युल् and ágama तुट्.

adyataniiya|अद्यतनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Of to-day, belonging to the current day. E. अद्यतन, taddh. aff. छ. 

adyaprabhRti|अद्यप्रभृति
Bahuvr. ind. From to-day. E. अद्य and प्रभृति.

adyashviina|अद्यश्वीन
I. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) What may happen to-day or to-morrow, near to any event, at the point of death &c. <BR>II. f. (-ना) A woman or any female animal near the time of delivery. E. अद्य and श्वस्, taddh. aff. ख.

adyaavadhi|अद्यावधि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धिः-धिः-धि) Beginning or ending with the current day; from or till to-day. E. अद्य and अवधि.

adyuutya|अद्यूत्य
(ved.) Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) Not gained by playing, not gained imporperly, obtained honestly. E. अ neg. and द्यूत्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. n. (-त्यम्) The last watch of the night, that preceding the dawn, at which time the Aświns are especially to be worshipped. E. अ and द्यूत्य (from द्युत्, kŕit aff. ण्यत् and ऊ instead of उ) ‘without light’. Both explanations of this word belong to different commentaries but refer to the same passage in which it occurs.

adrava|अद्रव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Not liquid, solid. E. अ neg. and द्रव.

adravya|अद्रव्य
Tatpur. n. (-व्यम्) A worthless or good-for-nothing object. E. अ deter. and द्रव्य.

adri|अद्रि
m. (-द्रिः)<BR> ^1 A stone.<BR> ^2 The thunderbolt.<BR> ^3 A mountain.<BR> ^4 A cloud.<BR> ^5 A tree.<BR> ^6 The sun.<BR> ^7 The name of a measure.<BR> ^8 A proper name of the son of Viśwagaśwa and father of Yuvanáśwa.<BR> ^9 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the numeral 7. E. अद्, uń. aff. क्रिन्; but more probably, a Tatpur. composed of अ and द्रि (from दॄ or द्रा?). Compare अग. The meanings 1. 2. 4. belong exclusively to the Vedas.

adrikarNii|अद्रिकर्णी
Bahuvr. f. (-र्णी) The name of a plant (Clitoria ternatea). See अपराजिता or गिरिकर्णी. E. अद्रि and कर्ण, fem. aff. ङीष्.

adrikaa|अद्रिका
f. (-का) An Apsaras or heavenly nymph, the wife of Amávasu and mother of Satyavatí. E. अद्रि, taddh. aff. कन् and fem. aff. टाप्.

adrikiilaa|अद्रिकीला
Bahuvr. f. (-ला) The earth. E. अद्रि and कील.

adrikRtasthalii|अद्रिकृतस्थली
Bahuvr. f. (-ली) The name of an Apsaras. E. अद्रि-कृत and स्थल, fem. aff. ङीष्.

adrija|अद्रिज
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Produced or found in the hills. <BR>II. f. (-जा)<BR> ^1 A name of Párvatí or Durgá, the daughter of Himálaya, the ruler of the Himálaya mountain, and hence this her appellation, mountain-born.<BR> ^2 The name of a plant. See सैंहली. <BR>III. n. (-जम्) Red chalk. See शिलाजतु. E. अद्रि and ज.

adrijaa|अद्रिजा
Tatpur. m. (-जाः) (ved.) Produced by the (friction of) stones (an epithet of Agni and हंस q. v.). E. अद्रि and जा.

adrijuuta|अद्रिजूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Moved or hastened by the stones (the sound of the stones); an epithet of the chariot of the Aświns. E. अद्रि and जूत.

adritanayaa|अद्रितनया
Tatpur. f. (-या)<BR> ^1 A name of Párvatí, the daughter of the mountain Himálaya.<BR> ^2 A metre regulated by number and quantity; a variety of the class called विकृति q. v. It consists of four lines, with the following twenty-three syllables to each: {??}, Also called अश्वललित. E. अद्रि and तनया. 

adridugdha|अद्रिदुग्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्धः-ग्धा-ग्धम्) (ved.) Extracted or expressed with stones. E. अद्रि and दुग्ध; literally: milked with stones.

adridviSh|अद्रिद्विष्
Tatpur. m. (-ट्) A name of Indra. E. अद्रि and द्विष्, lit. the enemy of the mountains.

adrinandinii|अद्रिनन्दिनी
Tatpur. f. (-नी) Párvatí. See अद्रितनया. E. अद्रि and नन्दिनी.

adripati|अद्रिपति
Tatpur. m. (-तिः) Hima, lord of mountains: also similar compounds, as अद्रिराज्, अद्रीन्द्र &c.

adribudhna|अद्रिबुध्न
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ध्नः-ध्ना-ध्नम्) (ved.) Produced or originating in mountains. E. अद्रि and बुध्न.

adribhid|अद्रिभिद्
Tatpur. m. (-भित्) A name of Indra. E. अद्रि and भिद्, lit. the splitter of mountains (with his thunderbolt).

adribhuu|अद्रिभू
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-भूः-भूः-भु) Mountaineer, mountain-born. <BR>II. f. (-भूः) A plant (Salvinea cucullata). See आखुकर्णी. E. अद्रि and भू.

adrimuurdhan|अद्रिमूर्धन्
Tatpur. m. (-र्धा) The summit or peak of a mountain. E. अद्रि and मूर्धन्.

adriraaj|अद्रिराज्
Tatpur. m. (-राट्) The king of mountains, the Himálaya mountains; the snowy range on the north of Hindustan, confounded with the mythological ruler of them, and the father of Párvatí. E. अद्रि and राज्.

adriraaja|अद्रिराज
Tatpur. m. (-जः). The same as the preceding. E. अद्रि and राजन्, samásánta aff. टच्.

adrivat|अद्रिवत्
m. (-वान्, voc. in the Vedas -वः) (ved.) Having stones, armed with stones or with the thunderbolt, an epithet of Indra, Soma, Varuńa. E. अद्रि, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

adrivahni|अद्रिवह्नि
Tatpur. m. (-ह्निः) Fire on or in a mountain. E. अद्रि and वह्नि.

adrishayya|अद्रिशय्य
Bahuvr. m. (-य्यः) A name of Śiva. E. अद्रि and शय्या; literally: whose couch is the mountain (Himálaya).

adrishRnga|अद्रिशृङ्ग
Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्) A peak, the horn or summit of a mountain. E. अद्रि and शृङ्ग.

adrisaMhata|अद्रिसंहत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Struck or extracted with stones, pressed with stones (an epithet of Soma). E. अद्रि and संहत.

adrisaara|अद्रिसार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) Iron. E. अद्रि and सार.

adrisaaramaya|अद्रिसारमय
m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Made of iron. E. अद्रिसार, taddh. aff. मयट्.

adriindra|अद्रीन्द्र
Tatpur. m. (-न्द्रः). The same as the following. E. अद्रि and इन्द्र.

adriisha|अद्रीश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 A name of Śiva.<BR> ^2 A name of Himálaya, as king of mountains. E. अद्रि and ईश.

adruh|अद्रुह्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ध्रुक्) (ved.) Harmless, innocuous, void of guile, kind, mild (an epithet of the gods, of heaven and earth &c.) E. अ priv. and द्रुह्.

adruhvan|अद्रुह्वन्
Tatpur. m. (-ह्वा) (ved.) The same as the preceding (an epithet of Mitra and Varuńa). E. अ neg. and द्रुह्वन्.

adrogha|अद्रोघ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-घः-घा-घम्) (ved.) Having no guile, free from deceit, true. E. अ priv. and द्रोघ.

adroha|अद्रोह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) Mildness, moderation, the absence of tyranny or oppression. E. अ neg. and द्रोह.

adrohin|अद्रोहिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ही-हिणी-हि) Innocuous, mild. E. अ neg. and द्रोहिन्.

advaya|अद्वय
I. Tatpur. n. (-यम्)<BR> ^1 Not duality, unity.<BR> ^2 The  identity of Brahman (n.) and the Universe or of the divine essence and the human soul; the real truth. E. अ neg. and द्वय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Without a second, only, alone; esp. in the neuter as an epithet of Brahman (n.) which is not distinct from the Universe. BREAḲ. m. (-यः) A name of Buddha (acc. to a commentary, because wisdom and object of wisdom are identical with him). E. अ priv. and द्वय.

advayat|अद्वयत्
Tatpur. m. (-यन्) (ved.) Free from duplicity, one whose acts are not different from his words and thoughts, upright, honest. E. अ neg. and द्वयत्.

advayavaadin|अद्वयवादिन्
Tatpur. m. (-दी) A Jina or Buddha. E. अद्वय and वादिन्: one who acknowledges but one principle; or who teaches the real truth. See अद्वैतवादिन्.

advayas|अद्वयस्
Tatpur. m. (-याः) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. E. अ neg. and द्वयस्.

advayaananda|अद्वयानन्द
Bahuvr. m. (-न्दः) The same as अद्वैतानन्द. E. अद्वय and आनन्द.

advayaavin|अद्वयाविन्
Tatpur. m. (-वी) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. E. अ neg. and द्वयाविन्.

advayu|अद्वयु
Tatpur. m. (-युः) (ved.) The same as अद्वयत्. E. अ neg. and द्वयु.

advaara|अद्वार
Tatpur. n. (-रम्) An entrance to a house which is other than the door. E. अ neg. and द्वार.

advitiiya|अद्वितीय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्)<BR> ^1 Only, sole, without a second. See अद्वय.<BR> ^2 Unparalleled, unequalled. E. अ priv. and द्वितीय.

adviSheNya|अद्विषेण्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) (ved.) Not detestable or hateful, agreeable, desired. E. अ neg. and द्विषेण्य.

adveSha|अद्वेष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Harmless, not malicious, kind. E. अ priv. and द्वेष.

adveShin|अद्वेषिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षी-षिणी-षि) Harmless, inoffensive. E. अ neg. and द्वेषिन्.

advaita|अद्वैत
I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unity, not duality.<BR> ^2 The identity of Brahman (n.) and the Universe or of the divine essence and the human soul; the real truth.<BR> ^3 The name of an Upanishad of the Atharvaveda. E. अ neg. and द्वैत. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Without a second, only, alone; esp. as an epithet of आत्मन् and ब्रह्मन् (n.) or ब्रह्मलोक. E. अ priv. and द्वैत.

advaitavaadin|अद्वैतवादिन्
Tatpur. m. (-दी) A unitarian, one who maintains the existence of but one principle in the Universe. E. अद्वैत and वादिन्. See अद्वयवादिन्.

advaitaananda|अद्वैतानन्द
Bahuvr. m. (-न्दः) The proper name of one of the founders of the Vaishńava sect in Bengal; he lived about the end of the 15th century. Also अद्वयानन्द. E. अद्वैत and आनन्द.

adha|अध
ind. (निपात) An inceptive particle which occurs only in the Vedas. It is used very much in the same manner as अथ of which it is apparently a variety and corresponds chiefly with<BR> ^1 Now, hereafter.<BR> ^2 Moreover, so much the more.<BR> ^3 Therefore. It occurs frequently in its protracted form अधा which seems to be the more original one. E. See अथ.

adhaHkara|अधःकर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The lower part of the hand, the  metacarpus or the hand from the wrist to the root of the fingers. E. अधस् and कर.

adhaHkaaya|अधःकाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) The lower part of the body, the lower extremities. E. अधस् and काय.

adhaHkhanana|अधःखनन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Undermining. E. अधस् and खनन.

adhaHpadma|अधःपद्म
Tatpur. n. (-द्मम्) (In architecture.) A division of the शिखर (q. v.) or cupola, the lower cima recta. E. अधस् and पद्म.

adhaHpaata|अधःपात
Tatpur. m. (-तः) Falling down, literally and metaphorically. E. अधस् and पात.

adhaHpuShpii|अधःपुष्पी
Bahuvr. f. (-ष्पी)<BR> ^1 A plant (Pimpinella anisun). See अवाक्पुष्पी.<BR> ^2 Another plant (Elephantopus scaber) or perhaps Hieracium. See गोजिह्वा. E. अधस् and पुष्प, fem. aff. ङीष्, lit. having its flowers hanging downwards.

adhaHpravaaha|अधःप्रवाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) Flowing or streaming downwards. E. अधस् and प्रवाह.

adhaHprastara|अधःप्रस्तर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A seat or bed, made of grass, esp. for the use of persons in the state of impurity or आशौच q. v. E. अधस् and प्रस्तर.

adhaHshaya|अधःशय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Sleeping on the ground. E. अधस् and शय.

adhaHshayya|अधःशय्य
I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-य्यः-य्या-य्यम्) Sleeping on the ground, on a kind of couch different from a bed-stead. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-य्या) The sleeping in the manner described. E. अधस् and शय्या.

adhaHshiras|अधःशिरस्
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-राः-राः-रः) and II. n. (-रः) The same as अधोमुख I. and IV. q. v. E. अधस् and शिरस्.

adhaHstha|अधःस्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्)<BR> ^1 Below.<BR> ^2 Inferior. E. अधस् and स्थ.

adhaHsthita|अधःस्थित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Standing beneath. E. अधस् and स्थित.

adhaHsvastika|अधःस्वस्तिक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In astronomy.) The nadir. Also अधरस्वस्तिक. E. अधस् and स्वस्तिक.

adhaupaasana|अधउपासन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Copulation, sexual union. E. अधस् and उपासन.

adhana|अधन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Poor, without wealth. E. अ priv. and धन.

adhama|अधम
I. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्)<BR> ^1 Very low or inferior in place or degree.<BR> ^2 Vile, despicable. (In the vituperative sense it stands often as the latter part of a Tatpur. compound; f. i. पापाधम, नराधम.) <BR>II. m. (-मः) (In rhetoric, according to some.) A paramour of a low description, one without fear, pity or shame &c. <BR>III. f. (-मा) (In rhetoric, according to some.) A mistress of a low description, one ungrateful, whimsical, acting unkindly towards her lover &c. E. अव्, uń. aff. अम, with व् changed to ध; or according to others a Tatpur. composed of अ neg. and धम (from ध्मा); but a preferable etym. is that from अधस्, taddh. aff. म, with elision of स्; or better from अध् (the thematic form common to अधम, अधर, अधस्, अधस्तात्), aff. अम.

adhamabhRta|अधमभृत
Karmadh. m. (-तः). See the following. E. अधम and भृत.

adhamabhRtaka|अधमभृतक
Karmadh. m. (-कः) The lowest order of hired servants, a porter, a bearer of burdens. (See also भृतक, उत्तमभृतक and मध्यमभृतक.) E. अधम and भृतक.

adhamarNa|अधमर्ण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्) A debtor. E. अधम and ऋण.

adhamarNika|अधमर्णिक
m. (-कः) A debtor. E. अधमर्ण, taddh. aff. ठक्. 

adhamaanga|अधमाङ्ग
Karmadh. n. (-ङ्गम्) A foot. E. अधम and अङ्ग.

adhamaachaara|अधमाचार
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Wicked in practice, low, vile. E. अधम and आचार.

adhamaardha|अधमार्ध
Karmadh. n. (-र्धम्) The inferior or lower part. Cf. उत्तमार्ध E. अधम and अर्ध.

adhamaardhya|अधमार्ध्य
m. f. n. (-र्ध्यः-र्ध्या-र्ध्यम्) Belonging to the inferior or lower part. Cf. उत्तमार्ध्य. E. अधमार्ध, taddh. aff. यत्.

adhara|अधर
I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Lower, inferior, in place. (In this sense the word is declined like the sarvanáman यत् &c. (q. v.), but in the abl. and loe. sing. of the mase. and neuter and in the nom. plur. of the mase. it forms optionally अधरस्मात् or अधरात्, अधरस्मिन् or अधरे, अधरे or अधराः; it may form Tatpur. compositions with nouns having the sense of the singular and considered then as depending upon अधर, which is the former part of the compound, in the genitive; for instance अधरकायः is explained, अधरं कायस्य.) Adverbially used are अधरात्, अधरस्मात्, अधरेण; qq. vv.<BR> ^2 Low, vile.<BR> ^3 Speechless, refuted, overcome in abuse or controversy.<BR> ^4 Prior, preceding in time. See अधरेद्युस्. <BR>II. m. (-रः) The lower lip, the lip. <BR>III. f. (-रा)<BR> ^1 The lower region.<BR> ^2 The nadir (?). <BR>IV. m. n. (-रः-रम्) Pudendum muliebre. E. Probably from अध् (see E. of अधम), aff. अर; the derivation given by the native authorities, from अ neg. and धर is not correct.

adharakaNTha|अधरकण्ठ
Tatpur. m. n. (-ण्ठः-ण्ठम्?) The lower part of the throat. E. अधर and कण्ठ. See under अधर.

adharakaaya|अधरकाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) The lower part of the body, the lower extremities. E. अधर and काय. See under अधर.

adharatas|अधरतस्
ind.<BR> ^1 Underneath.<BR> ^2 The lower regions, the nadir, or in the lower regions, in the nadir. (Used in the sense of a nominative or locative, but in the latter with the restriction that the distance must not be far; or governing in the first meaning a noun in the genitive.) See अधरात् and अधरेण. Cf. अधराक्. E. अधर, taddh. aff. अतसुच्.

adharapaana|अधरपान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Kissing. E. अधर II. and पान.

adharastaat|अधरस्तात्
ind. Below, underneath. (The correctness of this form appears doubtful.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. अस्ताति.

adharasvastika|अधरस्वस्तिक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In astronomy.) The nadir. Also अधःस्वस्तिक q. v. E. अधर and स्वस्तिक.

adharaak|अधराक्
Tatpur. ind.<BR> ^1 Downwards, from below.<BR> ^2 Westwards, from or in the west.<BR> ^3 The lower regions or the nadir, from or in the lower regions or the nadir. (Used in the sense of a locative, ablative or nominative; or governing in the two first meanings a noun in the ablative. E. अधर and अञ्च् II. with luk of the taddh. aff. अस्ताति. See अधराञ्च्

adharaachiina|अधराचीन
m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) (ved.) Going or being underneath, westwards, going to or being in the lower regions, in the nadir. E. अधराञ्च्, taddh. aff. ख.

adharaachya|अधराच्य
m. f. n. (-च्यः-च्या-च्यम्) (ved.) The same as the preceding. E. अधराञ्च्, taddh. aff. यत्.

adharaanc|अधराञ्च्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-राङ्-राची-राक्) (ved.) Going or being downwards, westwards, going to or being in the lower regions, in the nadir. E. अधर and अञ्च्.

adharaat|अधरात्
ind. The same as अधरतस्. (Used in the sense of a locative, ablative or nominative.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. आति. 

adharaaraNi|अधरारणि
Tatpur. f. (-णिः) (ved.) The nether piece of the two pieces of wood, which, by attrition, produce the sacrificial fire. See अरणि and उत्तरारणि. E. अधर (q. v.) and अरणि.

adharaavalopa|अधरावलोप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Biting the lip. E. अधर II. and अवलोप.

adhariikRta|अधरीकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Put down, overcome, vanquished.<BR> ^2 Annulled, invalidated (as a document). E. अधर, taddh. aff. च्वि with कृ, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhariiNa|अधरीण
m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Reproached, censured. E. अधर, taddh. aff. ख.

adhariibhuuta|अधरीभूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Refuted, contradicted, invalidated. E. अधर, taddh. aff. च्वि with भू, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhareNa|अधरेण
ind. The same as अधरतस् or अधरात्. (Used in the sense of a locative or nominative, but in the first with the restriction that the distance must not be far; or governing in the first meaning a noun in the accusative or genitive.) E. अधर, taddh. aff. एनप्.

adharedyus|अधरेद्युस्
ind. A previous day, the day before yesterday. E. अधर, irregular aff. एद्युस्; better a Tatpur, compound, from अधर (loc.) and द्युस् from दिव् or द्यु.

adharottara|अधरोत्तर
Dwandwa I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Lower and higher.<BR> ^2 Inferior and better.<BR> ^3 Prior and posterior. <BR>II. n. sing. or plur. (-रम् or -रे)<BR> ^1 The lower and higher, inferior and better, prior and posterior.<BR> ^2 A state of confusion, when things are tupsy-turvy.<BR> ^3 Address and answer. E. अधर and उत्तर.

adharoShTha|अधरोष्ठ
Karmadh. m. (-ष्ठः) The lower lip. Also अधरौष्ठ. E. अधर and ओष्ठ.

adharma|अधर्म
Tatpur. 1. m. (-र्मः)<BR> ^1 Unrighteousness, injustice, all behaviour contrary to the Śruti and Smŕiti, or religious and legal institutions.<BR> ^2 (In philosophy.) According to the Nyáya and Vaiśeshika: moral demerit, the result of doing what is forbidden, the peculiar cause of pain, one of the twenty-four qualities united with substance.--According to the Sánkhya, one of the changeable (वैकृतिक) dispositions (भाव) of the mind, which being the efficient cause, makes the soul migrate into an animal, a deer, a bird, a reptile, a vegetable, a mineral.--According to the Buddhistic doctrine it is the consequence of upádána or exertion of body or speech.--According to the Jainas it is that which causes the soul in general to continue embarrassed with body notwithstanding its capacity for ascent and natural tendency to soar.<BR> ^3 As a personification Adharma occurs in the Puráńas as one of the Prajápatis or mind-born sons of Brahmá; his wife is Hinsá (mischief) on whom he begot Anŕita (falsehood) and Nikŕiti (immorality) or according to others, Mŕishá (falsehood) and his children Dambha (hypocrisy) and Máyá (deceit) who were adopted by Nirŕiti (misfortune).--Adharma is also mentioned as one of the eighteen servants of the sun. BREAḲ. f. (-र्मा) According to the Śáktas a kalá or part of the original or Múla-prakŕiti and personified as the bride of Mŕityu or Death. E. अ neg. and धर्म.

adharmachaarin|अधर्मचारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Unrighteous, wicked. E. अधर्म and चारिन्. 

adharmadaNDana|अधर्मदण्डन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Inflicting punishment without any lawful motive, unjust punishment. E. अधर्म and दण्डन.

adharmamaya|अधर्ममय
m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Consisting of injustice or unrighteousness, thoroughly unjust or unrighteous. E. अधर्म, taddh. aff. मयट्.

adharmaatman|अधर्मात्मन्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्मा-त्मा-त्म) Wicked, unrighteous. E. अधर्म and आत्मन्.

adharmaastikaaya|अधर्मास्तिकाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) The category or predicament of अधर्म, according to the Jainas (see अधर्म,<BR> ^2.). E. अधर्म and अस्तिकाय.

adharmin|अधर्मिन्
m. f. n. (-र्मी-र्मिणी-र्मि) Wicked, sinful, unrighteous. E. अधर्म, taddh. aff. इनि.

adharmiShTha|अधर्मिष्ठ
m. f. n. (-ष्ठः-ष्ठा-ष्ठम्) Very wicked. E. अधर्मिन्, taddh. aff. इष्ठन्.

adharmya|अधर्म्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्म्यः-र्म्या-र्म्यम्) Not conformable or according to justice or morality, wicked, unrighteous. E. अ neg. and धर्म्य.

adhavaa|अधवा
Bahuvr. f. (-वा) A widow. See विधवा. E. अ priv. and धव.

adhashchara|अधश्चर
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Going down or below. <BR>II. m. (-रः) A thief. E. अधस् and चर. See the following.

adhashchaura|अधश्चौर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A house-breaker, a thief. E. अधस् and चौर.

adhas|अधस्
ind.<BR> ^1 Underneath, downwards or from below.<BR> ^2 The lower regions, the nadir, or: from or in the lower regions, the nadir. (In these meanings it is used in the sense of a nominative, ablative or locative; or governs in the first meaning a noun in the genitive, more seldom in the ablative; the reiterated अधो ऽधस् implies proximity and is followed by the noun in the accusative, f. i. अधोऽधो ग्रामम् below the village, but in its neighbourhood; it may occur as the former and as the latter part of Tatpur. compounds.)<BR> ^3 Pudendum muliebre.<BR> ^4 Away, out(?). See अधस्तात्; cf. अधराक्. E. अध् (considered as a substitute of अधर, but more probably the thematic form common to अधम, अधर, अधस् and अधस्तात्), taddh. aff. असि.

adhastana|अधस्तन
m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Below, underneath. E. अधस्, taddh. aff. ट्युल् and ágama तुट्.

adhastaraam|अधस्तराम्
ind. Lower, very low. E. अधस्, taddh. aff. तरप् and आमु (or better the acc. fem. in the comparative of अधस् used as an adverb).

adhastaat|अधस्तात्
ind. The same as अधस् in the three first meanings. It is used, like this word, in its two first meanings in the sense of a nominative, ablative and locative and may in its first meaning govern a noun in the genitive, more seldom in the ablative. See अधस्. E. अध् (considered as a substitute of अधर, but more probably the thematic form common to अधम, अधर, अधस् and अधस्तात्), taddh. aff. अस्ताति.

adhastaaddish|अधस्ताद्दिश्
Tatpur. f. (-क्) The lower region, the nadir. E. अधस्तात् and दिश्.

adhaspada|अधस्पद
Tatpur. n. (-दम्) The place under the feet. E. अधस् and पद.

adhaa|अधा
ind. See अध.

adhaamaargava|अधामार्गव
m. (-वः) A plant (Achyranthes aspera). Also धामार्गव; and see अपामार्ग. E. unknown.

adhaaraNaka|अधारणक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not supporting, not giving or not allowing to gain a livelihood, unprofitable. E. अ priv. and धारण, samásánta aff. कप्. 

adhaarmika|अधार्मिक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Unjust, unrighteous, wicked. See also आधार्मिक. E. अ neg. and धार्मिक.

adhi|अधि
ind. (see निपात, उपसर्ग, गति, कर्मप्रवचनीय) A particle implying superiority in place, power, rank, quality and quantity and generally used as a separable preposition or as a prefix to verbs, but in the Vedas also as an adverb. With nouns it may form Tatpur., Bahuvr. and Avyayíbháva compounds. It means. <BR>1. (as adverb, in the Vedas) very much, excessively. BREAḲ. (as a separable preposition)<BR> ^1 with a noun following or preceding in the locative,<BR> ^a. above (in place),<BR> ^b. over (in the sense of mastership, power &c.),<BR> ^c. under (see अधीन and अधिक 4, cf. अधस्);<BR> ^2 with a noun following or preceding in the accusative,<BR> ^a. on, above (in place),<BR> ^b. concerning, with respect to,<BR> ^c. repeated it implies also proximity; f. i. अध्यधि ग्रामम् above the village but in its neighbourhood;<BR> ^3 with a noun following or preceding in the ablative (in the Vedas),<BR> ^a. on, above,<BR> ^b. from above,<BR> ^c. from (in this meaning it occurs also in the classical language, when it is supposed to be merely an expletive, the preceding ablative implying already the notion ‘from’),<BR> ^d. in consequence of, on behalf of,<BR> ^e. in presence of, before, in front of;<BR> ^4 with a noun following or preceding in the genitive (in the Vedas), amidst, amongst. <BR>3. (as a prefix to verbs) Over, esp. in the sense of taking possession of, mastering &c. literally or metaphorically; but used also as an expletive esp. when followed by another preposition: f. i. with कृ to superintend, with इ to obtain, to study &c.; but it does not alter the meaning of आगम्, when forming with the latter अध्यागम्. BREAḰ. (in composition)<BR> ^1 (with Tatpur. or Bahuvr.) it implies superiority in place, rank, quantity &c.,<BR> ^2 (with Avyayíbh.)<BR> ^a. concerning, with respect to,<BR> ^b. over. E. unknown.

adhi|अधि
1. m. (-धिः) Anxiety, mental pain; more usually आधि q. v. of which it seems to be an incorrect reading. E. see आधि. BREAḲ. f. (-धिः) A woman in her courses. See also अवि. E. अद्, kŕit aff. इ and ध् substituted for द् or a Tatpur. अ neg. and धि (from धा). (The first etym. doubtful.)

adhika|अधिक
I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्)<BR> ^1 Exceeding, in addition to (the reverse of न्यून; between both साधारण).<BR> ^2 More, more than, superior (in place, power, rank, quality or quantity).<BR> ^3 Very much, excessive, excellent.<BR> ^4 Less, smaller, inferior (cf. अधि 2. 1. c.). अधिकम् used as adverb. (If अधिक has the first of these meanings, that by which the excess is caused, stands in the instrumental or (but seldom) in the locative or forms the first part of a Tatpur. compound of which अधिक is the latter; if it has the second meaning, the object compared with, stands in the instrumental, the ablative or in the genitive; if it has the last meaning, the object compared with stands in the ablative. Cf. अध्यारूढ. With numerals अधिक may form Bahuvr. compounds, usually in the plural, if it is the former part of the compound; for instance अधिकचत्वारिंशाः (sc. संख्याः) i. e. more than fourty. It is considered as dropped in Dwandwa compounds of numerals f. i. in पञ्चविंशति, equal to पञ्चाधिकविंशति.)<BR> ^5 Embolismic, intercalary (only in composition with and prefixed to the name or numeral of a luni-solar year, to the name of a month and to the name of a day;  f. i. अधिकाश्विन. See also अधिकतिथि, अधिकदिन, अधिकमास, अधिकसंवत्सर, and compare क्षय).<BR> ^5 Subsequent, following (as a day, a chapter or a passage in a book &c.; used very much in the same manner as ऊर्ध्व). <BR>II. n. (-कम्)<BR> ^1 The surplus, that which is exceeding.<BR> ^2 (In Nyáya.) Superfluity in reasons or instances, giving more reasons or instances than are required or relevant in a syllogism.<BR> ^3 (In rhetoric.) Hyperbole (of which two kinds are enumerated: hyperbole concerning the recipient (substance, subject &c.) and hyperbole concerning that which is to be received (accidents, predicate &c.). E. अधि, taddh. aff. कन्.

adhikataa|अधिकता
f. (-ता) Excess, addition; also अधिकत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधिक, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

adhikaxayakaarin|अधिकक्षयकारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Causing excessive loss, wasting too much. E. अधिक-क्षय and कारिन्.

adhikatithi|अधिकतिथि
Karmadh. m. f. (-थिः-थिः) An intercalary lunar day. When no tithi (q. v.) begins or ends in a solar day, the numeral of the preceding is repeated in the calendar, the first tithi being accounted the intercalated and the second the proper one. Compare क्षयतिथि. E. अधिक and तिथि.

adhikadanta|अधिकदन्त
Karmadh. m. (-न्तः) A tooth growing over another. See अधिदन्त and वर्धन. E. अधिक and दन्त.

adhikadina|अधिकदिन
Karmadh. n. (-नम्) An intercalated day. See अधिकतिथि. Also अधिदिन. E. अधिक and दिन.

adhikamaaMsaarman|अधिकमांसार्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म). See अधिमांसार्मन्. E. अधिक-मांस and अर्मन्.

adhikamaasa|अधिकमास
Karmadh. m. (-सः) An intercalated month. Also अधिमास. Compare क्षयमास. E. अधिक and मास.

adhikaraNa|अधिकरण
I. Tatpur. n. (-णम्)<BR> ^1 Superiority, supremacy, government.<BR> ^2 Title, right.<BR> ^3 Town meeting, court of justice.<BR> ^4 Support, receptacle.<BR> ^5 Substance (द्रव्य, as the recipient of qualities &c.).<BR> ^6 (In grammar.) Comprehension, location, generally the sense of the seventh or locative case, but occasionally also that of the third or instrumental and of the sixth or genitive case.<BR> ^7 (In grammar.) Government, regimen; see एकाधिकरण, युगपदधिकरण, समानाधिकरण.<BR> ^8 (In philosophy.) A case or topic; esp. in the Mímánsá and Vedánta; in the former it comprehends usually five parts or members, the subject (विषय), the doubt (संशय), the first side (or objectionable) argument (पूर्वपक्ष), the following (or right) argument (उत्तरपक्ष) and the conclusion (सिद्धान्त or राद्धान्त). Sometimes, however, the second part is inherent in the third and the fifth in the fourth. In both philosophies an adhikarańa is a subdivision of a páda, which is the division of an adhyáya. E. कृ with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. (-णः-णी). See अधिकार II. E. अधि and करण; in the fem. with aff. ङीप्.

adhikaraNamaNDapa|अधिकरणमण्डप
Tatpur. m. n. (-पः-पम्) A hall of the town council, a hall of justice(?). E. अधिकरण and मण्डप.

adhikaraNasiddhaanta|अधिकरणसिद्धान्त
Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) (In the Nyáya philosophy.) A truth or conclusion which implies another truth or conclusion; one of the four kinds of सिद्धान्त. See also सर्वतन्त्रसिद्धान्त, प्रतितन्त्रसिद्धान्त and अभ्युपगमसिद्धान्त. E. अधिकरण and सिद्धान्त, a paramount truth. 

adhikaraNika|अधिकरणिक
See आधिकरणिक.

adhikaraNaitaavattva|अधिकरणैतावत्त्व
Tatpur. n. (-त्त्वम्) Quantity. E. अधिकरण (substance) and एतावत्त्व ‘the fixed measure of a substance’.

adhikarddhi|अधिकर्द्धि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्द्धिः-र्द्धिः-र्द्धि) Prosperous, every way happy. E. अधिक and ऋद्धि.

adhikarmakara|अधिकर्मकर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The same as the following. E. अधि and कर्मकर.

adhikarmakRt|अधिकर्मकृत्
Tatpur. m. (-त्) A servant who is set over or superintends the working men; one of the four kinds of servants called कर्मकार or कर्मकर qq. vv. See also शुश्रूषक. E. अधि and कर्मकृत्.

adhikarmakRta|अधिकर्मकृत
Tatpur. m. (-तः) The master or chief of a family, one who superintends all family affairs. E. अधिकर्मन् and कृत.

adhikarman|अधिकर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) Superintendence, supervision. E. कृ with अधि, kŕit aff. मनिन्.

adhikarmika|अधिकर्मिक
m. (-कः) Clerk or prefect of the market or fair. E. अधिकर्मन्, taddh. aff. ठन्.

adhikalpin|अधिकल्पिन्
Tatpur. m. (-ल्पी) (ved.) An exceedingly shrewed gambler, one skilled in superior tricks or combinations(?). E. अधि and कल्पिन्.

adhikavaakyokti|अधिकवाक्योक्ति
Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः) Exaggeration, hyperbole. E. अधिक-वाक्य and उक्ति.

adhikaShaaShTika|अधिकषाष्टिक
m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Bought with, made of &c. more than sixty. E. अधिक-षष्टि, taddh. aff. ठञ्.

adhikasaMvatsara|अधिकसंवत्सर
Karmadh. m. (-रः) An intercalated year. E. अधिक and संवत्सर.

adhikasaaptatika|अधिकसाप्ततिक
m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Bought with, made of &c. more than seventy. E. अधिक-सप्तति, taddh. aff. ठञ्.

adhikaanga|अधिकाङ्ग
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गी or -ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Having more members than natural or common. <BR>II. n. (-ङ्गम्) The girdle over the coat of mail, worn as a kind of scarf. E. अधिक and अङ्ग; in the fem. with aff. ङीष् or टाप्.

adhikaara|अधिकार
I. Tatp. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Superintendence, supremacy, authority.<BR> ^2 Rule, government.<BR> ^3 Duty, office.<BR> ^4 Right, title, ownership.<BR> ^5 The use of royal insignia.<BR> ^6 (In the Mímánsá philosophy.) The right of action, i. e. the right to institute a sacrifice and to claim the results which are derived from it; it is subject to different regulations and restrictions and forms the subject of the sixth adhyáya of the Mímánsá. See also कर्माधिकार.<BR> ^7 A topic in a book; especially in grammatical works where it means a precept, rule or word, heading and applying to a number of particular rules which follow. Also written अधीकार. E. कृ with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. (-रः-री) One who has many duties to perform, very busy. E. अधि and कार; in the fem. with aff. ङीष्.

adhikaarastha|अधिकारस्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Established in an office or charge. E. अधिकार and स्थ.

adhikaaritaa|अधिकारिता
f. (-ता)<BR> ^1 Ownership, lordship.<BR> ^2 Right, title &c. See अधिकारिन्. Also अधिकारित्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधिकारिन्, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

adhikaarin|अधिकारिन्
I. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) (In law.) Possessing a right or title. <BR>II. m. (-री)<BR> ^1 A superintendent, a ruler, a director. <BR> ^2 One holding an office.<BR> ^3 A master, an owner.<BR> ^4 (In the Mímánsá.) One entitled to institute a sacrifice; see अधिकार.<BR> ^5 (In the Vedánta.) A person who is perfect in the principles and practice of the Vedánta.<BR> ^6 Man (in general). E. अधिकार, taddh. aff. इनि.

adhikaarthavachana|अधिकार्थवचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Exaggeration, hyperbole. E. अधिक-अर्थ and वचन.

adhikaarma|अधिकार्म
Tatpur. n. (-र्मम्). Perhaps the name of a place or country. E. अधिक and अर्म.

adhikRta|अधिकृत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Superintended, governed.<BR> ^2 Claimed or held as a right.<BR> ^3 Set as a rule or authority.<BR> ^4 Set over, superintendent. <BR>II. m. (-तः)<BR> ^1 A superintendent in general.<BR> ^2 Inspector of receipts and disbursements, an auditor of public accompts. E. कृ with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhikRti|अधिकृति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) A possession, a right, a privilege. See अधिकरण. E. कृ with अधि, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

adhikrama|अधिक्रम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) Invasion, assailing. E. क्रम् with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhixit|अधिक्षित्
Tatpur. m. (-त्) (ved.) Lord, ruler. E. क्षि with अधि, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

adhixipta|अधिक्षिप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्)<BR> ^1 Censured, reviled, detracted from.<BR> ^2 Thrown or cast down.<BR> ^3 Dismissed, sent, dispatched.<BR> ^4 Placed, fixed. E. क्षिप् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhixepa|अधिक्षेप
Tatpur. m. (-पः)<BR> ^1 Detraction, censure.<BR> ^2 Dismissal, dispatch. E. क्षिप् with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhigata|अधिगत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Obtained.<BR> ^2 Gone through or over, lit. or fig. as read, studied. E. गम् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhigantavya|अधिगन्तव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be reached, attainable, acquirable, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

adhigantR|अधिगन्तृ
Tatpur. m. (-न्ता) One who obtains or acquires. E. गम् with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्.

adhigama|अधिगम
Tatpur. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 Obtaining, attaining, acquiring.<BR> ^2 Attainment, apprehension, going through or over, lit. or fig.<BR> ^3 Profit, gain, interest on capital or risk. E. गम् with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhigamana|अधिगमन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Obtaining, attaining, acquiring.<BR> ^2 Attainment, apprehension, going through or over, lit. or fig. as reading, studying. E. गम् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhigamaniiya|अधिगमनीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be reached, attainable, acquirable, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

adhigamya|अधिगम्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्यः-म्या-म्यम्) Attainable, to be reached or acquired, lit. or fig. E. गम् with अधि, kŕitya aff. यत्.

adhigava|अधिगव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वी-वम्) (ved.) On the cow, coming from the cow (as milk &c.). E. अधि and गो, samásánta aff. टच्.

adhiguNa|अधिगुण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Of superior qualities. E. अधि and गुण.

adhija|अधिज
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्)<BR> ^1 Superior by birth.<BR> ^2 Born from, produced on(?). E. जन् with अधि, kŕit aff. ड.

adhijanana|अधिजनन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Birth. E. जन् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhijihva|अधिजिह्व
Bahuvr. m. (-ह्वः) One of the diseases of the throat, described as ‘a swelling at the root of the tongue like a second tongue’ (probably a swelling of the epiglottis)--therefore  called also द्विजिह्व--and produced by the phlegm and blood; when it suppurates, considered as incurable. Also अधिजिह्विका. E. अधि and जिह्वा.

adhijihvikaa|अधिजिह्विका
Bahuvr. f. (-का) The same as the preceding. E. अधिजिह्व, samásánta aff. कप्.

adhijya|अधिज्य
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ज्यः-ज्या-ज्यम्) Strung (as a bow). E. अधि and ज्या.

adhijyotiSham|अधिज्योतिषम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning or relating to the luminous part of creation; a chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon, comprises the following subjects: fire, sun, water and the substance of lightning. E. अधि and ज्योतिष.

adhityakaa|अधित्यका
f. (-का) Land on the upper part of a mountain. E. अधि, taddh. aff. त्यकन्.

adhidanta|अधिदन्त
Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) A tooth growing over another. See अधिकदन्त and वर्धन. E. अधि and दन्त.

adhidina|अधिदिन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The same as अधिकदिन. E. अधि and दिन.

adhideva|अधिदेव
I. Tatpur. m. (-वः)<BR> ^1 A supreme or tutelary deity. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-वम्) Concerning the gods. (In derivatives with a taddh. aff. which has an anubandha ञ्, ण् or क्, both parts of this word have vŕiddhi, f. i. आधिदैविक q. v.) E. अधि and देव.

adhidevatam|अधिदेवतम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning the divinities or the gods. E. अधि and देवता.

adhidevataa|अधिदेवता
Tatpur. f. (-ता) A tutelary or presiding divinity. E. अधि and देवता.

adhidevana|अधिदेवन
n. (-नम्) The ground in a hall, on which gambling with dice takes place. E. दिव्, with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhidaiva|अधिदैव
I. Tatpur. n. (-वम्) and <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-वम्). See the following. E. अधि and दैव.

adhidaivata|अधिदैवत
I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्)<BR> ^1 The supreme or tutelary deity.<BR> ^2 The active principle in creation, the regulating power which resides in water, fire, sky, air, the regions &c. See also अधिभूत, अध्यात्म. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-तम्) Concerning<BR> ^1 the deity or<BR> ^2 the active principle in creation. E. अधि and दैवत.

adhipa|अधिप
Tatpur. m. (-पः)<BR> ^1 An owner, a lord or master.<BR> ^2 A king.<BR> ^3 (In astrology.) The regent of a sign of the zodiac. E. पा with अधि, kŕit aff. क.

adhipati|अधिपति
Tatpur. m. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 A master, an owner, a ruler.<BR> ^2 A king. (A noun depending upon it in these meanings stands in the gen. or loc., f. i. गवामधिपति or गोष्वधिपति.)<BR> ^3 (In medicine.) ‘That part of the trunk which is inside of the upper part of the head, at the passage of the vessel along the lateral sinus; wounds inflicted there produce instantaneous death’. E. पा with अधि, uń. aff. डति.

adhipativatii|अधिपतिवती
f. (-ती) The name of certain female divinities (in the Vedas). See पत्नी. E. अधिपति, taddh. aff. मतुप्, the change of म् in the affix to व् being restricted, in this word, to the vaidik meaning of it.

adhipatnii|अधिपत्नी
Tatpur. f. (-त्नी) A mistress, a protectress. E. अधिपति, fem. aff. ङीप्, and न् ádeśa for the final इ.

adhipatham|अधिपथम्
Avyayíbh. Over or across a road. E. अधि and पथिन्, samásánta aff. अ.

adhipaa|अधिपा
Tatpur. m. (-पाः) (ved.) A master, a lord, a protector. E. पा with अधि, kŕit aff. विच्. 

adhipaaMshula|अधिपांशुल
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Where dust is lying on or has risen from, dusty. Also written अधिपांसुल. E. अधि and पांसुल.

adhipuruSha|अधिपुरुष
Tatpur. m. (-षः) The supreme or presiding spirit. E. अधि and पुरुष.

adhiprajam|अधिप्रजम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning or relating to the continuation of the world by procreation; a chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon comprises the subjects: mother, father, posterity and generation. E. अधि and प्रजा.

adhipraShTi|अधिप्रष्टि
Avyayíbh. (ved.) Over the Prasht́i (q. v.). See the following. E. अधि and प्रष्टि.

adhipraShTiyuga|अधिप्रष्टियुग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) (ved.) The yoke over the Prasht́i horse, to which a fourth horse was put (in a ceremony connected with the Vájapeya sacrifice; two horses being put before a cart and a third in front of the two, so as to form with them a kind of triangle or tripod (प्रष्टि q. v.), wherefore the third horse was called metaphorically the Prasht́i). E. अधिप्रष्टि and युग.

adhibhuu|अधिभू
Tatpur. m. (-भूः) A master, a ruler. E. भू with अधि, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

adhibhuuta|अधिभूत
I. Tatpur. n. (-तम्) A subtile or invisible element, one which is the cause of the gross or visible elements (also as an attribute of the supreme soul that pervades and regulates all elements or existence). <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-तम्) Concerning or relating to the bhúta or elements; a chapter in the Upanishads includes under this topic, earth, atmosphere, material heaven, regions, intermediate regions, fire, air, sun, moon, lunar mansions, water, annual plants, trees, ether, soul. (In derivatives with a taddh. aff. which has an anubandha ञ्, ण् or क्, both parts of this word assume vŕiddhi, f. i. आधिभौतिक.) E. अधि and भूत.

adhimantha|अधिमन्थ
Tatpur. m. (-न्थः) (In medicine.) Severe ophthalmia which is described as having the following symptoms: ‘acute pains as if the eyes were torn; throbbing which extends to half of the head’; it consists of four varieties according to its being produced by derangement of the air, bile, phlegm or blood. Also अधीमन्थ. E. अधि and मन्थ.

adhimanthana|अधिमन्थन
Tatpur. m. n. (-नः-नम्) (ved.) A piece of wood from the paring of the sacrificial post, placed over the arańi (q. v.) to kindle a fire by attrition. E. मन्थ् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्; seil. शकल.

adhimanthita|अधिमन्थित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Affected with the disease called अधिमन्थ q. v. E. अधिमन्थय् (अधिमन्थ, denom. aff. णिच्), kŕit aff. क्त.

adhimaaMsa|अधिमांस
Tatpur. m. (-सः) (In medicine.) A disease of the gums, described as ‘a great and painful swelling round the wisdom-tooth with the discharge of saliva; produced by diseased phlegm’. Also अधिमांसक. E. अधि and मांस.

adhimaaMsaka|अधिमांसक
m. (-कः). The same as the preceding. E. अधिमांस, taddh. aff. कन्.

adhimaaMsaarman|अधिमांसार्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) (In medicine.) A disease of the white part on the conjunctiva of the eye; it is described as ‘a large, soft (fleshy growth), either liver-coloured or brown’. Also अधिकमांसार्मन्. E. अधिमांस (scil. ज) and अर्मन्; ‘the disease अर्मन् produced by the fleshy excrescence’. 

adhimaatra|अधिमात्र
I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Excessive, above measure. Cf. अतिमात्र. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-त्रम्) Above syllabic measurement. (In the doctrine of the Upanishads the mysterious syllable ओम् is said to be exempt from the general rules of prosody. See also अध्यक्षर.) E. अधि and मात्रा.

adhimaatrakaaruNika|अधिमात्रकारुणिक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) The name of a Mahábrahman (q. v.) according to the mythology of the Buddhists. E. अधिमात्र and कारुणिक, lit. ‘excessively kind or compassionate’.

adhimaasa|अधिमास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) An intercalary month, formed of the aggregate days omitted in reckoning the lunar year, in comparison with the solar. See also अधिकमास. E. अधि and मास.

adhimukti|अधिमुक्ति
Tatpur. f. (-क्ति) (In Buddhistic literature.) Comprehension, intelligence, natural disposition (of the soul). E. मुच् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

adhimuktika|अधिमुक्तिक
m. (-कः) A name of Mahákála (q. v.), according to the mythology of the Buddhists. E. अधिमुक्ति, taddh. aff. कन्(?).

adhimuktisaara|अधिमुक्तिसार
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) (In Buddhistic literature.) Being quite comprehension, being thoroughly addicted to comprehending. E. अधिमुक्ति and सार.

adhimuhya|अधिमुह्य
Tatpur. m. (-ह्यः) A name of Śákyamuni in one of his thirty-four anterior births. E. मुह् with अधि, kŕitya aff. यत्(?) or अधि and मुह्य. The word is doubtful.

adhiyaJNa|अधियज्ञ
I. Tatpur. m. (-ज्ञः)<BR> ^1 The supreme sacrifice, the sacrifice .<BR> ^2 An influence superior to or presiding over sacrifice. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-ज्ञम्) Concerning or with respect to sacrifice. E. अधि and यज्ञ.

adhiyaanga|अधियाङ्ग
Tatpur.(?) n. (-ङ्गम्). The same as अधिकाङ्ग of which it is given as a various reading. E. doubtful, perhaps instead of अध्याङ्ग (अधि and आङ्ग), or of अधिकाङ्ग, with य् in the place of क्.

adhiratha|अधिरथ
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-थः-था-थम्) Being on or above a car. <BR>II. m. (-थः)<BR> ^1 A charioteer.<BR> ^2 The proper name of a charioteer who was a prince and descendant of Anu and of Anga, a son of Satyakarman and foster father of Karńa. E. अधि and रथ.

adhirathi|अधिरथि
m. (-थिः). See उदरथि of which it occurs as a various reading.

adhiraaj|अधिराज्
Tatpur. m. (-राट्) A supreme king or ruler. E. अधि and राज्.

adhiraaja|अधिराज
Tatpur. m. (-जः). The same as the preceding. E. अधि and राजन्, samásánta aff. टच्.

adhiraajan|अधिराजन्
Tatpur. m. (-जा). The same as अधिराज्. E. अधि and राजन्.

adhiraajya|अधिराज्य
Tatpur. n. (-ज्यम्)<BR> ^1 Supreme sway.<BR> ^2 Empire.<BR> ^3 The name of a country, also read अधिराष्ट्र and अधिवाज्य. E. अधि and राज्य.

adhiraajyabhaaj|अधिराज्यभाज्
Tatpur. m. (-क्) An emperor, a paramount sovereign. E. अधिराज्य and भाज्.

adhiraaShTra|अधिराष्ट्र
Tatpur. n. (-ष्ट्रम्). See अधिराज्य. E. अधि and राष्ट्र.

adhirukma|अधिरुक्म
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्मः-क्मा-क्मम्) Wearing gold. E. अधि and रुक्म. 

adhiruuDha|अधिरूढ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Ascended or gone over, lit. or fig., act. or pass., person. or impersonally. E. रुह् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhiropaNa|अधिरोपण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Causing to ascend, placing over. E. रुह् with अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhiropita|अधिरोपित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Placed over, lit. or fig. E. रुह् with अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. क्त.

adhiroha|अधिरोह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) Surmounting, ascending, overtopping. E. रुह् with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhirohaNa|अधिरोहण
Tatpur. I. n. (-णम्) Ascending, surmounting, overtopping. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A ladder, a staircase. See also अधिरोहिणी. E. रुह् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhirohin|अधिरोहिन्
Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-ही-हिणी-हि) Who rises on or above. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A ladder, a staircase. See अधिरोहणी. E. रुह् with अधि, kŕit aff. णिनि(?).

adhilokam|अधिलोकम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning or relating to the world. A chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon comprises the subjects: earth, sky, æther, wind. E. अधि and लोक.

adhivaktR|अधिवक्तृ
Tatpur. m. (-क्ता) I. A partisan, an advocate. E. वच् with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्. <BR>II. One who speaks in a superior manner, very eloquent. E. अधि and वक्तृ.

adhivachana|अधिवचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) I. Advocating, speaking in favour of another. E. वच् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II. A name, an appellation. E. अधि and वचन.

adhivastra|अधिवस्त्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्त्रः-स्त्रा-स्त्रम्) Wearing cloth or raiment. E. अधि and वस्त्र.

adhivaajya|अधिवाज्य
n. (-ज्यम्) The name of a country; see अधिराज्य which seems to be the more correct reading of this word.

adhivaasa|अधिवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) I.<BR> ^1 One who dwells above others.<BR> ^2 One who dwells near others, a neighbour.<BR> ^3 An inhabitant.<BR> ^4 An abode, a place or situation. E. वस् (to dwell &c.) with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्. <BR>II. A cover, an upper garment. Also अधीवास. E. वस् (to cover with dress) with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्. <BR>III. Continuance, perseverance, esp. fig.: fixing one's self at a person's door in order to enforce compliance with some demand. E. वस् (वसु) with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्. <BR>IV.<BR> ^1 Perfuming or dressing the person &c.; (as materials and objects of toilet by which this is done, are enumerated the following: मृत्तिका, गन्धः, शिला, धान्यम्, दूर्वा, पुष्पम्, फलम्, दधि, घृतम्, स्वस्तिकम्, सिन्दूरम्, शङ्खः, कज्जलम्, रोचना, श्वेतसर्षपः, स्वर्णम्, रौप्यम्, ताम्रम्, चामरम्, दर्पणम्, दीपः, प्रशस्तपात्रम्).<BR> ^2 See अधिवासन. E. वास् with अधि, kŕit aff. अच्.

adhivaasana|अधिवासन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) I.<BR> ^1 Perfuming or dressing the person &c. (see अधिवास IV. 1.).<BR> ^2 A religious ceremony, preliminary to any great Hindu festival: touching a vessel containing perfumes, flowers and other things previously presented to an idol, or offering perfumes &c. to it. E. वास् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्. <BR>II.<BR> ^1 A summoning and fixing of the presence of a divinity upon an image &c., when he is wanted for any solemnity.<BR> ^2 The placing of a new image in water &c. the day before the divinity is to be summoned to inhabit it.<BR> ^3 The same as अधिवास III. E. वस् (वसु) with अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. युच्(?). 

adhivaasabhuumi|अधिवासभूमि
Tatpur. f. (-मिः) A dwelling place. E. अधिवास and भूमि.

adhivaasita|अधिवासित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) I. Invested with. E. वस् (to cover with dress) with अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. क्त. <BR>II. Perfumed, scented. E. वास् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhivaasitaa|अधिवासिता
f. (-ता) Residence, staying or abiding in one place. Also अधिवासित्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधिवासिन्, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

adhivaasin|अधिवासिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Staying or abiding in one place. E. वस् with अधि, kŕit aff. णिनि(?).

adhivaahana|अधिवाहन
Bahuvr. m. (-नः) A proper name; acc. to some, a son of Anga. E. अधि and वाहन.

adhividyam|अधिविद्यम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning or relating to knowledge. A chapter in the Upanishads treating thereon comprises the subjects: teacher, pupil, science and expounding. E. अधि and विद्या.

adhivinnaa|अधिविन्ना
Tatpur. f. (-न्ना) (In law.) A wife whose husband has subsequently married others; a superseded wife. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त, or according to another etym. a Bahuvr. of अधि and विन्न, taken either in the sense of विन्ना or विन्नम्.

adhivettavyaa|अधिवेत्तव्या
Tatpur. f. (-व्या) A wife deserving or proper to be superseded by her husband marrying another. Also अधिवेद्या or अधिवेदनीया. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

adhivettR|अधिवेत्तृ
Tatpur. m. (-त्ता) A man marrying another than his first wife. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्.

adhivedana|अधिवेदन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Marrying again, whilst a former wife is living. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhivedaniiyaa|अधिवेदनीया
Tatpur. f. (-या). The same as अधिवेत्तव्या. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

adhivedam|अधिवेदम्
Avyayíbh. Concerning or with respect to the Veda. E. अधि and वेद.

adhivedyaa|अधिवेद्या
Tatpur. f. (-द्या). The same as अधिवेत्तव्या. E. विद् (विदॢ) with अधि, kŕitya aff. यत्.

adhishayita|अधिशयित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Lain or slept over or upon; used either in an active or passive sense, personally or impersonally. E. शी with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhishrayaNa|अधिश्रयण
Tatpur. I. n. (-णम्) Placing over the fire a pot &c. (the reverse of अवश्रयण q. v.); also as a sacrificial act which occurs in several sacrifices, the Darśapúrńamása, Vájapeya &c. <BR>II. f. (-णी) A furnace or fire-place. E. श्रि with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्, in the fem. with ङीप्.

adhishrayaNiiya|अधिश्रयणीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Relating to the अधिश्रयण q. v. E. अधिश्रयण, taddh. aff. छ.

adhishrita|अधिश्रित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Placed over the fire. E. श्रि with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhiShavaNa|अधिषवण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (ved.) The name of two wooden boards, on which the juice of the Soma plant was expressed and where the Somábhishava (q. v.) was placed, in sacrifices as the Jyotisht́oma or those sharing in the principal rites of it. E. सू with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhiShThaatR|अधिष्ठातृ
Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-ता-त्री-तृ) Governing, directing, ruling. <BR>II. m. (-ता)<BR> ^1 A ruler, a governor, a superintendent.<BR> ^2 (According to the doctrine of the Páśupatas) Íśwara, the superintending or ruling providence. (In the feminine esp. in conjunction with देवता, a ruling or tutelary divinity.) E. स्था with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्.

adhiShThaana|अधिष्ठान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Abiding, resting upon.<BR> ^2 Site,  situation.<BR> ^3 A town.<BR> ^4 (In architecture.) Base, basement.<BR> ^5 Power, dignity, superintendence.<BR> ^6 Prescribed rule, fixed practice.<BR> ^7 A wheel.<BR> ^8 Approaching.<BR> ^9 (In Buddhistic literature.) Benediction. E. स्था with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhiShThaanashariira|अधिष्ठानशरीर
Karmadh. n. (-रम्) (In Sánkhya phil.) According to some, an intermediate body between the लिङ्गशरीर and स्थूलशरीर (qq. vv.), one that is supposed to enable the subtle body to assume the corporeity of gross body. E. अधिष्ठान and शरीर.

adhiShThaayaka|अधिष्ठायक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यकः-यिका-यकम्) Superintending, governing. E. स्था with अधि, kŕit aff. ण्वुल् and ágama युक्.

adhiShThita|अधिष्ठित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Fixed, determined, established; literally or figuratively, as a house or a practice.<BR> ^2 Inhabited, occupied.<BR> ^3 Supervised, superintended, guarded.<BR> ^4 Appointed.<BR> ^5 Superintending, inhabiting, occupying. Used act. or pass., person. or impersonally. E. स्था with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhistrii|अधिस्त्री
I. Tatpur. f. (-स्त्री) A superior or excellent woman. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-स्त्रि) Used in the same sense as the locative of स्त्री. E. अधि and स्त्री.

adhihari|अधिहरि
Avyayíbh. Used in the same sense as the locative of हरि. E. अधि and हरि.

adhiikaara|अधीकार
Tatpur. m. (-रः). See अधिकार.

adhiigartha|अधीगर्थ
Bahuvr. m. (-र्थः) (In grammatical terminology.) A radical having the sence of remembering. E. इक् (the technical form of इ in the sense of remembering) with अधि, and अर्थ; scil. धातु.

adhiita|अधीत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Read, obtained &c. E. इ (इङ् or इक्) with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhiitaveda|अधीतवेद
Bahuvr. m. (-दः) A Brahman, who has read the Vedas; a student who has finished his course of study. E. अधीत and वेद.

adhiiti|अधीति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Study, perusal.<BR> ^2 (ved.) Recollection, desire. E. इ (^1 इङ्,<BR> ^2 इक्) with अधि, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

adhiitin|अधीतिन्
m. f. n. (-ती-तिनी-ति) Well read in, conversant with, versed in (with a noun in the locative; f. i. अधीती व्याकरणे, versed in grammar). E. अधीत, taddh. aff. इनि.

adhiina|अधीन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 Dependant.<BR> ^2 Docile. E. अधि and इन ‘having a master over one's self’. This word and the etymology as mentioned, are given by the native lexicographers; but according to the best grammatical authorities अधीन would not exist as a real word. Words as राजाधीन, ब्राह्मणाधीन and the like, are explained by them as coming from राजाधि (राजन् and अधि), ब्राह्मणाधि (ब्राह्मण and अधि) with taddh. aff. ख, or by others as derived from राजन्, ब्राह्मण with taddh. aff. सधीनन्; it would seem therefore that the use of अधीन as an independant word is grammatically not correct. But see अध्यधीन and अनधीनक.

adhiinataa|अधीनता
f. (-ता) Subjection, dependance, slavery: so अधीनत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधीन, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व. The grammatical correctness of this word is questionable; see the E. of the preceding.

adhiimantha|अधीमन्थ
Tatpur. m. (-न्थः). The same as अधिमन्थ q. v.; the vowel in अधि being lengthened.

adhiiyat|अधीयत्
Tatpur. I. m. (-यन्) A student who reads the Veda &c. with facility or ease. See अधीयान. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. शतृ. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-यन्-यती-यत्) Remembering. E. इ (इक्) with अधि, kŕit aff. शतृ. 

adhiiyaana|अधीयान
m. (-नः) A student, one going over or reading the Vedas &c. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. शानच्.

adhiira|अधीर
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Unsteady, unstable (lit. or met.).<BR> ^2 Perplexed, confused, not possessed of selfcommand.<BR> ^3 Unwise. <BR>II. f. (-रा)<BR> ^1 Lightning.<BR> ^2 (In rhetoric.) A cross or capricious mistress, one not possessed of self-command; with two varieties, the मध्या or adolescent dame who will ‘assail her lover with harsh speeches’ and the प्रगल्भा or प्रौढा or mature dame who will ‘scold and beat him’. See also धीरा and धीराधीरा. E. अ neg. and धीर.

adhiirataa|अधीरता
f. (-ता) Fickleness, unsteadiness; also अधीरत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अधीर, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

adhiivaasa|अधीवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः). The same as अधिवास II., the इ in अधि being made long.

adhiisha|अधीश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) A master, a lord. E. अधि and ईश.

adhiishvara|अधीश्वर
Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 An emperor, a king paramount over all the neighbouring princes.<BR> ^2 An Arhat, according to the Jainas. E. अधि and ईश्वर.

adhiiShTa|अधीष्ट
Tatpur. I. m. (-ष्टः) One requested or honourably engaged to assume a duty, as a teacher &c. (not one hired for money). <BR>II. n. (-ष्टम्) An honourable occupation. E. इष् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhunaa|अधुना
ind. Now, at present. E. अश् (i. e. अ, considered as a substitute of इदम्), taddh. aff. अधुना.

adhunaatana|अधुनातन
m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Of or belonging to the present. E. अधुना, taddh. aff. ट्यु and ágama तुट्.

adhura|अधुर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having no load (as a cart). E. अ priv. and धुर्, samásánta aff. अ.

adhRta|अधृत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unheld, undetained. <BR>II. m. (-तः) A name of Vishńu. E. अ neg. and धृत.

adhRti|अधृति
I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Laxity, want of firm hold.<BR> ^2 Want of steadiness or firmness. (In rhetoric described as one of the conditions connected with the Rasa Śŕingára q. v.) E. अ neg. and धृति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Having no steadiness or firmness. E. अ priv. and धृति.

adhRShTa|अधृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Ashamed, modest, humble.<BR> ^2 Not overcome, invincible. E. अ neg. and धृष्ट.

adhRShya|अधृष्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्)<BR> ^1 Proud, vain.<BR> ^2 Irresistible, invincible. <BR>II. f. (-ष्या) The name of a river. E. अ neg. and धृष्य.

adhenu|अधेनु
Tatpur. f. (-नुः) A cow that does not yield milk. E. अ deter. and धेनु.

adhairya|अधैर्य
I. Tatpur. n. (-र्यम्) Instability, want of firmness. E. अ neg. and धैर्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Unsteady, feeble, irresolute. E. अ priv. and धैर्य.

adhoshuka|अधोशुक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) A lower garment. E. अधस् and अंशुक.

adhoaxa|अधोअक्ष
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) (ved.) Being under the axle of a car or under a car. See अधोऽक्ष. E. अधस् and अक्ष.

adhoxa|अधोक्ष
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्). The same as अधोअक्ष. E. अधस् and अक्ष.

adhoxaja|अधोक्षज
Tatpur. m. (-जः)<BR> ^1 A name of Kŕishńa.<BR> ^2 The sign Śravańá. Also written अधोक्षज. E. अधस्-अक्ष and ज; ‘Kŕishńa, as a child, killed, when lying under a car, Pútaná,  a female fiend who was hovering over it in the shape of a bird, and thus, as it were, was born again (under the car)’; or according to others, from अधोक्ष, the name of a Ŕishi, and ज, ‘a son of Adhoksha’; or, ‘because he is produced by or to such as have subdued or cast down their passions, i. e. because he becomes visible to them’; or a Bahuvr. from अधस् and अक्षज (n. knowledge derived from the senses; m. pl. living beings), ‘because he has subdued all untrue knowledge or because he is superior to all living beings’.

adhogata|अधोगत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Descended, gone down, lit. or fig. E. अधस् and गत.

adhogati|अधोगति
I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Going downwards, lit. or fig. as degradation, going into hell &c. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Descending, going downwards, lit. or fig. E. अधस् and गति. In the same sense अधोगम Tatpur. m. (-मः) and अधोगमन Tatpur. n. (-नम्).

adhogaamin|अधोगामिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Descending, going downwards. See the preceding. E. अधस् and गामिन्.

adhoghaNThaa|अधोघण्ठा
Bahuvr. f. (-ण्टा) A plant (Acheranthes aspera). See अपामार्ग. E. अधस् and घण्टा.

adhonga|अधोङ्ग
Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्)<BR> ^1 The anus.<BR> ^2 Pudendum muliebre; also written अधोङ्ग. E. अधस् and अङ्ग.

adhojaanu|अधोजानु
Avyayíbh. Under the knee, lower than the knee. E. अधस् and जानु.

adhojihvikaa|अधोजिह्विका
Tatpur. f. (-का) The uvula or soft palate. E. अधस् and जिह्विका.

adhodaaru|अधोदारु
Tatpur. m. n. (-रुः-रु) The under timber (of a pillar &c.). E. अधस् and दारु.

adhodish|अधोदिश्
Tatpur. f. (-दिक्)<BR> ^1 The lower region.<BR> ^2 The Nadir. E. अधस् and दिश्.

adhodRShTi|अधोदृष्टि
I. Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) A downcast look. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्टिः-ष्टिः-ष्टि) Downcast, one who looks down. E. अधस् and दृष्टि.

adhodesha|अधोदेश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 The bottom, the lowest part.<BR> ^2 The lower part of the body. E. अधस् and देश.

adhodvaara|अधोद्वार
Tatpur. n. (-रम्)<BR> ^1 The anus.<BR> ^2 Pudendum muliebre. E. अधस् and द्वार.

adhonaabham|अधोनाभम्
Avyayíbh. Under the navel. E. अधस् and नाभि, samásánta aff. अ.

adhopahaasa|अधोपहास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) Copulation, coition. E. This word occurs only in the Upan. and seems to be an irregular compound formed of the phrase अध उप ह आस, ‘she was or lay under (him)’.

adhobandhana|अधोबन्धन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) An under girth or strap. E. अधस् and बन्धन.

adhobhakta|अधोभक्त
Tatpur. n. (-क्तम्) (In medicine.) A medicament which is to be taken after eating; one of the ten kinds of medicaments classified according to the time of their application; see besides निर्भक्त, प्राग्भक्त, मध्येभक्त, अन्तराभक्त, सभक्त, सामुद्ग, मुहुर्मुहुर्ग्रास (which is twofold) and ग्रासान्तर. E. अधस् and भक्त, scil. औषध.

adhobhava|अधोभव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Placed below, inferior. E. अधस् and भव.

adhobhaaga|अधोभाग
Tatpur. m. (-गः)<BR> ^1 The bottom, the lowest part.<BR> ^2 The lower part of the body. E. अधस् and भाग.

adhobhaagadoShahara|अधोभागदोषहर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Removing or  curing diseases of the lower part of the body (as a medicine). E. अधोभाग-दोष and हर.

adhobhuvana|अधोभुवन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The world below, the regions below the earth. E. अधस् and भुवन.

adhobhuumi|अधोभूमि
Tatpur. f. (-मिः) A place or land below (such as land at the foot of a mountain &c.). E. अधस् and भूमि.

adhomarman|अधोमर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) The anus. E. अधस् and मर्मन्.

adhomukha|अधोमुख
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-खः-खा or खी-खम्)<BR> ^1 Downlooked, looking downwards.<BR> ^2 Inverted, turned upside down, headlong. <BR>II. m. (-खः) A name of Vishńu. <BR>III. f. (-खा) A plant (Premna esculenta). See गोजिह्वा. <BR>IV. n. (-खम्) A division of Naraka or hell. See अधःशिरस्. E. अधस् and मुख; in the fem. with aff. टाप् or ङीष्.

adhoyantra|अधोयन्त्र
Tatpur. n. (-न्त्रम्) A still, or the lower of two vessels luted together for distilling, sublimation &c. E. अधस् and यन्त्र.

adhoraktapitta|अधोरक्तपित्त
Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्) (In medicine.) See अधोऽस्रपित्त. E. अधस् and रक्तपित्त.

adhoraama|अधोराम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) (ved.) White--(or according to others, dark)--coloured on the lower part of the body, an epithet of the goat, one of the twelve ऐकादशिन (q. v.) animals in the Aśwamedha sacrifice. E. अधस् and राम.

adholamba|अधोलम्ब
Tatpur. m. (-म्बः) The perpendicular. Also अवलम्ब, वलम्ब and लम्ब. E. अधस् and लम्ब.

adholoka|अधोलोक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) The regions below the earth. E. अधस् and लोक.

adhovadana|अधोवदन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्). The same as अधोमुख q. v. E. अधस् and वदन.

adhovasha|अधोवश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 The bottom of a thing.<BR> ^2 Pudendum muliebre. E. अधस् and वश.

adhovaayu|अधोवायु
Tatpur. m. (-युः)<BR> ^1 The vital air that passes downwards, one of the five vital airs.<BR> ^2 Ventris crepitus. E. अधस् and वायु.

adhosrapitta|अधोस्रपित्त
Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्) (In medicine.) A kind of plethora, ‘when blood is discharged from the anus and urethra’. Also written अधोस्रपित्त. E. अधस् and अस्रपित्त.

adhyaxa|अध्यक्ष
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्)<BR> ^1 Perceptible, present to the senses.<BR> ^2 Superintending, presiding over. <BR>II. m. (-क्षः)<BR> ^1 A superintendent in general, one of receipts and disbursements.<BR> ^2 A plant (a species of Mimusops). See क्षीरिका and फलाध्यक्ष. E. अधि and अक्ष, or more correctly, as also mentioned in the native etym., अक्ष् with अधि, kŕit aff. अच्.

adhyaxaram|अध्यक्षरम्
Avyayíbh. Above all other letters (in importance or in place; being often put at the head of various writings, as the mysterious syllable ओम्). E. अधि and अक्षर.

adhyagni|अध्यग्नि
Avyayíbh. (In law.) Property given to the wife at the time of her marriage, one of the six items of woman's peculiar property. See स्त्रीधन. E. अधि and अग्नि; lit. (presented) over the (nuptial) fire.

adhyagnikRta|अध्यग्निकृत
Tatpur. n. (-तम्). The same as the preceding. E. अध्यग्नि and कृत; sc. स्त्रीधन (q. v.).

adhyagnyupaagata|अध्यग्न्युपागत
Tatpur. n. (-तम्). The same as the preceding. E. अध्यग्नि and उपागत; sc. स्त्रीधन (q. v.).

adhyanc|अध्यञ्च्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ध्यङ्-धीची-ध्यक्) Superior, best. E. अञ्च् (I. 1.) with अधि, kŕit aff. क्विन्, in the fem. with aff. ङीप्. For the declension of this word see अञ्च् II.

adhyaNDaa|अध्यण्डा
Bahuvr. f. (-ण्डा)<BR> ^1 Cowach. See अव्यङ्गा and कपिकच्छु. <BR> ^2 According to others a synonyme of भूम्यामलकी. E. अधि and अण्ड ‘having excellent seed’(?).

adhyadhixepa|अध्यधिक्षेप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Excessive censure. E. अधि and अधिक्षेप.

adhyadhiina|अध्यधीन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Very dependant, slave by birth. E. अधि and अधीन, or अध्यधि, taddh. aff. ख; see the E. of अधीन.

adhyayana|अध्ययन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Study, reading, especially of the sacred books; one of the six duties of a Brahman. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyayanatapas|अध्ययनतपस्
Dwandwa n. du. (-सी) Study and penance. (Only used in the dual.) E. अध्ययन and तपस्.

adhyayanapuNya|अध्ययनपुण्य
Tatpur. n. (-ण्यम्) Religions merit or purity which is in the study of the sacred works. E. अध्ययन (in the sense of the locative) and पुण्य.

adhyayaniiya|अध्ययनीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be read or studied. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

adhyardha|अध्यर्ध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्धः-र्धा-र्धम्) One and a half, having an extra half. See also सार्ध. (In derivatives of compounds the first part of which is अध्यर्ध and which have the meaning of ‘measuring or weighing, worth, containing, bought for, produced from, consisting of &c.’, the affix which would be required, is dropped in many instances; see f. i. अध्यर्धकंस, अध्यर्धशूर्प &c.) E. अधि and अर्ध.

adhyardhaka|अध्यर्धक
m. f. n. (-र्धकः-र्धिका-र्धकम्) Bought for or worth, containing, produced from &c. one and a half. E. अध्यर्ध, taddh. aff. कन्.

adhyardhakaMsa|अध्यर्धकंस
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-सः-सम्) One Kansa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-सः-सी-सम्) Containing, measuring, consisting of, bought for &c. one Kansa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and कंस; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. टिठन् is considered as dropped.

adhyardhakaakiNiika|अध्यर्धकाकिणीक
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Kákińí (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-काकिणी (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. ईकन्.

adhyardhakaarShaapaNa|अध्यर्धकार्षापण
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-णः-णम्) One Kárshápańa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-णः-णी-णम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Kárshápańa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and कार्षापण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. टिठन् is considered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धकार्षापणिक.

adhyardhakaarShaapaNika|अध्यर्धकार्षापणिक
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-कीकम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Kárshápańa (q. v.) and a half. See also अध्यर्धकार्षापण II. E. अध्यर्धकार्षापण (I.), taddh. aff. टिठन्.

adhyardhakhaariika|अध्यर्धखारीक
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Measuring, containing, consisting of, bought for &c. one Khárí (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-खारी (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. ईकन्.

adhyardhapaNya|अध्यर्धपण्य
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) Measuring or weighing, consisting of, bought for &c. one Pańa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-पण (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

adhyardhapaadya|अध्यर्धपाद्य
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्)  Measuring &c. one foot and a half. E. अध्यर्ध-पाद (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

adhyardhapratika|अध्यर्धप्रतिक
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्). The same as अध्यर्धकार्षापण II. E. अध्यर्ध-प्रति (acc. to some, Dwigu) (considered as a substitute of कार्षापण), taddh. aff. टिठन्.

adhyardhamaaShya|अध्यर्धमाष्य
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) Weighing, consisting of, bought for &c. one Másha (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्धमाष (accord. to some, Dwigu), taddh. aff. यत्.

adhyardhaviMshatikiina|अध्यर्धविंशतिकीन
m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. twenty and a half (i. e. thirty). E. अध्यर्ध-विंशतिक, taddh. aff. ख.

adhyardhashata|अध्यर्धशत
I. Dwandwa(?) n. (-तम्) Hundred and fifty. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. hundred and fifty. E. अध्यर्ध and शत; in the meaning II. the aff. यत् is considered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धशत्य.

adhyardhashatamaana|अध्यर्धशतमान
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-नः-नम्) One Śatamána (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śatamána (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and शतमान; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अण् is considered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धशातमान.

adhyardhashatya|अध्यर्धशत्य
m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. hundred and fifty. See also अध्यर्धशत. E. अध्यर्धशत (I.), taddh. aff. यत्.

adhyardhashaaNa|अध्यर्धशाण
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. (-णः) One Śáńa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-णः-णी-णम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śáńa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and शाण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. ठञ् is considered as dropped. See also the following.

adhyardhashaaNya|अध्यर्धशाण्य
(acc. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-ण्यः-ण्या-ण्यम्) Weighing, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śáńa (q. v.) and a half. See also the preceding. E. अध्यर्धशाण (I.), taddh. aff. यत्.

adhyardhashaatamaana|अध्यर्धशातमान
(accord. to some) Dwigu m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śatamána and a half. See also अध्यर्धशतमान. E. अध्यर्धशतमान (I.), taddh. aff. अण्, with Vŕiddhi in the latter part of the compound.

adhyardhashuurpa|अध्यर्धशूर्प
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-र्पः-र्पम्) One Śúrpa and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-र्पः-र्पी-र्पम्) Measuring, worth, consisting of, bought for &c. one Śúrpa and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and शूर्प; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अञ् or ठक् is considered as dropped.

adhyardhasahasra|अध्यर्धसहस्र
I. Dwandwa(?) n. (-स्रम्) Thousand and a half (i. e. thousand five hundred). <BR>II. m. f. n. (-स्रः-स्रा-स्रम्) Measuring, consisting of, worth, bought fort &c. thousand five hundred. E. अध्यर्ध and सहस्र; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. अण् is considered as dropped. See also अध्यर्धसाहस्र.

adhyardhasaahasra|अध्यर्धसाहस्र
m. f. n. (-स्रः-स्री-स्रम्) Measuring, consisting of, worth, bought for &c. thousand five hundred. E. अध्यर्धसहस्र (I.), taddh. aff. अण् with Vŕiddhi in the latter part of the compound.

adhyardhasuvarNa|अध्यर्धसुवर्ण
(accord. to some) Dwigu I. m. n. (-र्णः-र्णम्) One Suvarńa (q. v.) and a half. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णी-र्णम्) Weighing, consisting of, worth,  bought for &c. one Suvarńa (q. v.) and a half. E. अध्यर्ध and सुवर्ण; in the meaning II. the taddh. aff. ठक् is considered as dropped. See also the following.

adhyardhasauvarNika|अध्यर्धसौवर्णिक
m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Weighing, produced from, worth, bought for &c. one Suvarńa (q. v.) and a half. See also the preceding. E. अध्यर्धसुवर्ण (I.), taddh. aff. ठक्, with Vŕiddhi in the latter part of the compound.

adhyarbuda|अध्यर्बुद
Tatpur. n. (-दम्) An indolent swelling, the growth of which begins in the embryo and which is considered incurable. According to the native commentaries it is a hereditary disease and in so far always also द्विरर्बुद (q. v.), though the latter is distinct from it in some respects. E. अधि and अर्बुद; ‘an Arbuda or indolent swelling which reaches beyond (scil.) birth’, i. e. which takes place prior to birth.

adhyavasaana|अध्यवसान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Determining, ascertaining.<BR> ^2 Effort, energy.<BR> ^3 (In rhetoric.) The simple enuntiation of elliptic or figurative speech without qualifying it by epithets &c., as it were, leaving it on its own effort; such sentences as श्वेतो धावति ‘the white (horse) gallops’, कुन्ताः प्रविशन्ति ‘(men with) lances enter’ (see also under अजहत्स्वार्था), or कलिङ्गः साहसिकः ‘the (inhabitant of) Kalinga is impetuous’ (see also under जहत्स्वार्था) would be lakshańás or elliptic expressions by अध्यवसान, while अश्वः श्वेतो धावति the white horse gallops, एते कुन्ताः प्रविशन्ति these (men with) lances enter, कलिङ्गः पुरुषो युध्यते the man (inhabitant of) Kalinga fights would be qualified or lakshańás by आरोप q. v. (See also under लक्षणा.) Or मुखं द्वितीयश्चन्द्रः, (her) face is another moon, would be an अतिशयोक्ति (q. v.) or hyperbole in virtue of अध्यवसान, the comparison as it were resting on its own merit. E. सो with अव and अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyavasaaya|अध्यवसाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः)<BR> ^1 Ascertainment, determining.<BR> ^2 Assiduous application, effort, energy.<BR> ^3 (In philosophy.) The specific function of बुद्धि or intellect (q. v.), apprehension by intellect, its taking hold of an object either by ascertainment or volition.<BR> ^4 (In rhetoric.) The same as अध्यवसान. E. सो with अव and अधि, kŕit aff. ण and ágama युक्.

adhyavasaayita|अध्यवसायित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Undertaken, attempted as a difficult task. E. सो with अव and अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyavasaayin|अध्यवसायिन्
m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Resolute, determined. E. अध्यवसाय, taddh. aff. इनि.

adhyavasita|अध्यवसित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Determined, ascertained.<BR> ^2 Apprehended by intellect. See अध्यवसाय. E. सो with अव and अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyashana|अध्यशन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Eating too often, taking food before that previously eaten is digested. E. अधि and अशन.

adhyasta|अध्यस्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्)<BR> ^1 Placed over.<BR> ^2 Substituted, supposed erroneously, misconceived: as a snake when that so perceived is actually a piece of rope. E. अस् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyasthi|अध्यस्थि
Tatpur. n. (-स्थि) A bone grown over another bone. E. अधि and अस्थि.

adhyaatma|अध्यात्म
I. Tatpur. n. (-त्मम्) The supreme soul or आत्मन्  (q. v.), sometimes considered as identical with प्राण (q. v.) and, in the sectarian doctrine, especially with Náráyańa or Vishńu. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-त्मम्) Concerning or relating to soul, life &c.; see आत्मन्. A chapter in the Upan. treating thereon contains the following subjects: the lower jaw, the upper jaw, speech and tongue; another passage comprises under this topic<BR> ^1 the vital airs: práńa, apána, vyána, udána, samána,<BR> ^2 the organs of sensation: eyes, ears, manas, speech, skin (tvach) and<BR> ^3 the elementary parts of the body: skin (charman), flesh, tendons, bones, marrow. E. अधि and आत्मन्, samásánta aff. टच्.

adhyaatmaJNaana|अध्यात्मज्ञान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The knowledge of the supreme spirit or of the nature of átman or soul. E. अध्यात्म (I. or II.) and ज्ञान.

adhyaatmadRsh|अध्यात्मदृश्
Tatpur. m. (-दृक्) A holy sage, one who knows the nature of or what concerns átman or the soul. E. अध्यात्म (II.) and दृश्.

adhyaatmarati|अध्यात्मरति
Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) An anchorite, one who delights in meditating on the nature of or what concerns átman or the soul. E. अध्यात्म (II.) and रति.

adhyaatmavid|अध्यात्मविद्
Tatpur. m. (-त्) One who knows the supreme spirit or the nature of átman or soul. E. अध्यात्म (I. or II.) and विद्.

adhyaatmavidyaa|अध्यात्मविद्या
Tatpur. f. (-द्या). The same as अध्यात्मज्ञान. E. अध्यात्म and विद्या.

adhyaatmika|अध्यात्मिक
m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्). See आध्यात्मिक which is the more correct form of this word.

adhyaapaka|अध्यापक
Tatpur. m. (-कः)<BR> ^1 A teacher, esp. one who instructs in the sacred books.<BR> ^2 (According to a legend in the Calcutta edition of the Harivanśa.) One of the sixteen Ŕitvijs (q. v.) or priests, who was produced together with the Nesht́ŕi from the thighs of Purushottama. The reading of the commentary, however, is अच्छावाक (q. v.) and the list of priests mentioned there is differently given in the manuscripts; अध्यापक does not usually occur as the name of a Ŕitvij. (In the first meaning अध्यापक may be the latter part of Tatpur. compounds, the former of which stands in the sense of the genitive (f. i. ब्राह्मणाध्यापक one who instructs a Bráhmana) and as the latter part of several Karmadh. compounds; see f. i. कुमाराध्यापक, कठाध्यापक.) E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, in the caus., kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

adhyaapakodita|अध्यापकोदित
Karmadh. m. (-तः) One who is called or spoken of as a teacher. E. अध्यापक and उदित.

adhyaapana|अध्यापन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Instructing, teaching the sacred books, one of the six duties of a Brahman. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि; in the caus., kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyaapayitR|अध्यापयितृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता). The same as अध्यापक<BR> ^1. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्.

adhyaapya|अध्याप्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्) Fit to, capable of being instructed (esp. in the sacred writings). E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, in the caus., kŕitya aff. यत्.

adhyaaya|अध्याय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) I.<BR> ^1 A section of a book (f. i. of the Ŕigveda, Yajurveda, Aitareyabráhmańa, Pánińis grammar &c.).<BR> ^2 Reading, studying. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्. <BR>II. One who reads or studies (in this sense only as the  latter part of a compound; f. i. वेदाध्यायः one who reads the Veda). E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. अण्.

adhyaayin|अध्यायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Reading, studying. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. णिनि.

adhyaaruuDha|अध्यारूढ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्)<BR> ^1 Mounted on, placed above; used either in an active or passive sense, person. or impersonally.<BR> ^2 Exceeding, more (with a noun in the instrum.)<BR> ^3 Inferior, less (with a noun in the ablative). E. रुह् with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyaaropa|अध्यारोप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Fixing in or upon, transferring; but more especially used in philosophy, in the sense of transferring or attributing erroneously the predicates, nature &c. of one object to another, as those of a serpent to those of a rope &c. See अध्यास. E. रुह्, in the caus., with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhyaaropana|अध्यारोपन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्). The same as the preceding. E. रुह्, in the caus., with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyaaropita|अध्यारोपित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Transferred or attributed erroneously.<BR> ^2 Hyperbolical, exaggerated. E. रुह्, in the caus., with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyaavaapa|अध्यावाप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Throwing or casting upon. E. वप् with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhyaavaahana|अध्यावाहन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A second calling, a second invitation. See the following word of which it is the thematic form. E. अधि and आवाहन.

adhyaavaahanika|अध्यावाहनिक
n. (-कम्) An item of a married woman's property. See स्त्रीधन. It is explained as the gift she takes home from her father's house, when paying a visit to her friends. E. अध्यावाहन, taddh. aff. ठन्.

adhyaasa|अध्यास
Tatpur. m. (-सः)<BR> ^1 Putting, throwing in or upon.<BR> ^2 (In philosophy.) Transferring or attributing erroneously the predicates, nature &c. of one object to another, as of a serpent to a rope &c. See अध्यारोप.<BR> ^3 (In vaidik grammar.) The appendage to a vaidik verse; according to some the same as एकपदा q. v. E. अस्, to throw, in the caus., with अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhyaasana|अध्यासन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Sitting on or upon.<BR> ^2 Presiding over, ruling, inhabiting as chief. E. आस् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyaasayoga|अध्यासयोग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) In Buddhistic doctrine, one of the 108 धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.), perhaps: excessive or profound meditation. E. अध्यास and योग.

adhyaasita|अध्यासित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Seated in or on.<BR> ^2 Presiding over.<BR> ^3 Inhabited. E. आस्, in the caus., with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyaasin|अध्यासिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Sitting on or upon. E. आस् with अधि, kŕit aff. णिनि.

adhyaaharaNa|अध्याहरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as अध्याहार. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyaaharaNiiya|अध्याहरणीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्). The same as अध्याहार्य q. v. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

adhyaahartavya|अध्याहर्तव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्). The same as अध्याहार्य q. v. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

adhyaahaara|अध्याहार
Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Adding a word or words to complete a sentence, supplying an ellipsis.<BR> ^2 Reasoning, discussing. See अध्याहरण. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. घञ्.

adhyaahaarya|अध्याहार्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्)<BR> ^1 To be discussed or argued.<BR> ^2 To be added in order to complete a sentence, to  supply an ellipsis, as a word or words. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्.

adhyaahRta|अध्याहृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Discussed, argued.<BR> ^2 Added to complete a sentence, to supply an ellipsis, as a word or words. E. हृ with आ and अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyuShita|अध्युषित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Inhabited.<BR> ^2 Arrived at, obtained. (See समयाध्युषित.) E. वस् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त and ágama इट्.

adhyuShTa|अध्युष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Bound or tied over, coiled up. See the following. E. उच्छ् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त.

adhyuShTavalaya|अध्युष्टवलय
Bahuvr. m. (-यः) Having the ringlets coiled, wound into rings. This word occurs in the poem Ánandalaharí as the epithet of a serpent, to indicate that it is in profound sleep, forming, then, three ringlets and a half; the god Śiva is likened to a serpent coiled up in this manner, its half ringlet being compared to his Śakti or female energy and the three others to the god as representing the Trimúrti. E. अध्युष्ट and वलय.

adhyuShTra|अध्युष्ट्र
Bahuvr. m. (-ष्ट्रः) A litter drawn or carried by a camel. E. अधि and उष्ट्र.

adhyuuDha|अध्यूढ
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्)<BR> ^1 Borne or placed over, elevated.<BR> ^2 Very prosperous, thriving.<BR> ^3 Much, excessive. <BR>II. m. (-ढः) A name of Śiva. <BR>III. f. (-ढा) A superseded wife, one whose husband has married others. E. वह् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्त. The commentaries explain I. 2. as derived from अधि, in the sense of अधिक and ऊढ; II. as the god by whom the world has been upheld ‘first’ and III. also as derived from अधि, in the sense of ‘first’ and ऊढा married.

adhyuudhnii|अध्यूध्नी
Bahuvr. f. (-ध्नी) The penis (or according to another interpretation perhaps, the urethra). This word occurs esp. in the ritual works, in passages treating on the Agnishomíyapaśu (q. v.) and the ceremonies connected with it. E. अधि and ऊधस्, samásánta ádeśa अनङ् and fem. aff. ङीष्, scil. इडा; literally: the tubular vessel above the scrotum.

adhyuuShitaashva|अध्यूषिताश्व
Bahuvr. m. (-श्वः) The name of a prince, a descendant of Daśaratha. According to others his name would be अभ्युत्थिताश्व or दूषिताश्व or विधृति. E. अध्यूषित (very diseased, from अधि and ऊषित) and अश्व.

adhyuuShivas|अध्यूषिवस्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षिवान्-षुषी-षिवस्) Having inhabited (in the sense of लुङ्, लङ् and लिट् qq. vv.). E. वस् with अधि, kŕit aff. क्वसु.

adhyuuhana|अध्यूहन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Covering over, esp. with ashes and coals. (Used principally in ritual works.) E. ऊह् with अधि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

adhyetavya|अध्येतव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्). The same as अध्ययनीय. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

adhyetR|अध्येतृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) A student, one who reads or studies. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕit aff. तृच्.

adhyeya|अध्येय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्). The same as अध्येतव्य. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, kŕitya aff. यत्.

adhyeShaNa|अध्येषण
Tatpur. f. n. (-णा-णम्) Solicitation, asking, request. E. इष् with अधि, kŕit aff. युच्.

adhyeShyamaaNa|अध्येष्यमाण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Parposing or beginning to read, to study. E. इ (इङ्) with अधि, in the future (ऌट्), kŕit aff. शानच् and ágama मुक्. 

adhri|अध्रि
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ध्रिः-ध्रिः-ध्रि) (ved.) Unrestrained, irresistible. See the following. E. अ neg. and ध्रि.

adhrigu|अध्रिगु
Bahuvr. m. (-गुः--n. pl. -गावः) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Of unrestrained or irresistible course; esp. as an epithet of Indra, Agni, Soma, the Rudras and the Aświns.<BR> ^2 The name of a heavenly śamitŕi (q. v.) or killer of the sacrificial animal.<BR> ^3 The name of a Praishamantra (q. v.) used in the ceremony of the killing of the Agníshomíyapaśu (q. v.), and beginning with the words दैव्याः शमितार आरभध्वमुत मनुष्या उपनयत मेध्याः &c. E. अध्रि and गो.

adhrija|अध्रिज
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) (ved.) Irresistible. E. doubtful; perhaps अ neg. and ध्रिज (from ध्रिज्).

adhripuShkalikaa|अध्रिपुष्कलिका
Bahuvr.(?) f. (-का) The name of a plant, a species of Nágavalli (Piper betel). E. अध्रि and पुष्कलिका.

adhriyamaaNa|अध्रियमाण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्)<BR> ^1 Not held &c. See धृ.<BR> ^2 (In law.) Not alive, not surviving. E. अ neg. and ध्रियमाण.

adhruva|अध्रुव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्)<BR> ^1 Not permanent, not fixed, transient, perishable.<BR> ^2 Uncertain, doubtful.<BR> ^3 Not vital, not essential for life (as a limb or part of the body). E. अ neg. and ध्रुव.

adhruSha|अध्रुष
Tatpur.(?) m. (-षः) (In medicine.) A disease of the palate (see तालुरोग), described as ‘a hard swelling, of a red colour, produced by (diseased) blood and accompanied with pain and fever’. E. unknown.

adhva|अध्व
See अध्वन्.

adhvaga|अध्वग
Tatp. I. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Travelling, being on the road. <BR>II. m. (-गः)<BR> ^1 A traveller.<BR> ^2 A camel.<BR> ^3 The sun. <BR>III. f. (-गा)<BR> ^1 A traveller.<BR> ^2 A name of the river Ganges. E. अध्वन् and ग.

adhvagat|अध्वगत्
Tatpur. m. (-गत्) A traveller. E. अध्वन् and गत्.

adhvagatyanta|अध्वगत्यन्त
Tatpur. m. (-न्तः) The same as the following, of which it occurs as a various reading. E. अध्वन् and गतिअन्त (sc. क्रोश or योजन &c.).

adhvagantavya|अध्वगन्तव्य
Karmadh. m. (-व्यः) Measure of distance, as a Krośa, a Yojana &c. E. अध्वन् and गन्तव्य; an irregular compound, instead of गन्तव्याध्वन्.

adhvagabhogya|अध्वगभोग्य
Tatpur. m. (-ग्यः) The name of a tree (Spondias mangifera). See आम्रात. E. अध्वग and भोग्य; lit. ‘to be enjoyed by travellers’.

adhvagamana|अध्वगमन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Journeying, travelling. E. अध्वन् and गमन.

adhvagaamin|अध्वगामिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Travelling. E. अध्वन् and गामिन्.

adhvajaa|अध्वजा
Tatpur. f. (-जा) The name of a plant. See स्वर्णुली. E. अध्वन् and ज.

adhvan|अध्वन्
m. (-ध्वा)<BR> ^1 Sky, atmosphere (only in the Vedas).<BR> ^2 A road.<BR> ^3 Time.<BR> ^4 A place (perhaps, a place where four roads meet).<BR> ^5 A branch or school of the Vedas or sacred literature.--In some Tatpurusha compounds the former part of which is an उपसर्ग (q. v.), this word occurs in the form of अध्व; i. e. the compound assumes the samásánta aff. अच्; e. g. प्राध्व, निरध्व, प्रत्यध्व.--(The two last meanings of this word are rather unsettled through the variety of readings in the native dictionaries from which they are taken; some read अध्वा…संस्थाने स्यादवस्कन्धे,  others संस्थाने साश्रवस्कन्धे; the best reading, however, that which has been adopted in the present translation, seems to be this: संस्थाने शास्त्रवत्स्कन्धे.) E. doubtful; according to some, अद्, uń. aff. क्वनिप्, with ध् substituted for द् ‘because it eats up the strength of the traveller’; or according to others, अत्, uń. aff. क्वनिप्, with ध् instead of त्.

adhvaniina|अध्वनीन
m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 Marching fast or fleet.<BR> ^2 (m.) A traveller. E. अध्वन्, taddh. aff. ख. According to some used in all the three genders.

adhvanya|अध्वन्य
m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्)<BR> ^1 Marching fast or fleet.<BR> ^2 (m.) A traveller. E. अध्वन्, taddh. aff. यत्. According to some used in all the three genders.

adhvapati|अध्वपति
Tatpur. m. (-तिः) An epithet of the sun, in the Vedas. Literally: ‘the lord of the roads’ or perhaps better ‘the lord of the atmosphere’. E. अध्वन् and पति.

adhvara|अध्वर
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Not crooked, honest proper (ved.)<BR> ^2 Not perishable, lasting (in its consequences, as a sacrifice; ved.).<BR> ^3 Intent, attentive. (It is doubtful whether this word in the two meanings ‘not crooked’ and ‘not perishable’, occurs in the femin. gender, as it is used in the Vedas either absolutely as a neuter or as epithet of यज्ञ in the mascul. Nor is the latter meaning ‘intent, attentive’, a usual one, though it is given in several of the native dictionaries.) <BR>II. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Sacrifice in general, but in the ritual works mostly used as the denomination of the greater sacrifices or those performed with the juice of the Soma plant; see also सौम्याध्वर and अध्वरकाण्ड.<BR> ^2 The name of a Vasu (q. v.).<BR> ^3 The proper name of the chief of a renowned family. See आध्वरायण. <BR>III. n. (-रम्) Sky, atmosphere (ved.). E. अ priv. and ध्वर ‘having no crookedness, dishonesty &c.’ or according to others ‘preventing, not allowing of injury’; another etym. makes this word, but erroneously, a Tatpur. from अध्वन् and र ‘giving or affording the road (scil. to heaven)’.

adhvarakarman|अध्वरकर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्मः) The proceedings with an Adhwara-sacrifice (ved.). See the preceding. E. अध्वर and कर्मन्.

adhvarakalpaa|अध्वरकल्पा
Tatpur. f. (-ल्पा) One of the Kámyesht́is (q. v.) or voluntary isht́is with three yágas (q. v.) in the morning, in the middle of the day and in the evening, which may be instituted by a man of either of the three first classes. E. अध्वर and कल्प.

adhvarakaaNDa|अध्वरकाण्ड
Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) The book on the Adhwaras; the name of the third book of the Śatapat́habráhmańa (q. v.) which treats on the Adhwaras or the greater sacrifices performed especially with the juice of the Soma plant, the Agnisht́oma &c. E. अध्वर and काण्ड.

adhvarakRt|अध्वरकृत्
Tatpur. m. (-त्) Making an Adhwara-sacrifice; also used as a vaidik epithet of स्प्य (q. v.) in the sense of ‘instrumental for the performing of the sacrifice’. E. अध्वर and कृत्.

adhvaraga|अध्वरग
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Belonging or appropriated to an Adhwara-sacrifice, as the Soma. E. अध्वर and ग.

adhvaratha|अध्वरथ
Tatpur. m. (-थः) A travelling carriage or cart. E. अध्वन् and रथ. 

adhvaradiixaNiiyaa|अध्वरदीक्षणीया
Tatpur. f. (-या) That part of an Adhwara-sacrifice which is called दीक्षणीया q. v. E. अध्वर and दीक्षणीया.

adhvarapraayashchitti|अध्वरप्रायश्चित्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) The penance connected with an Adhwara-sacrifice. E. अध्वर and प्रायश्चित्ति.

adhvarayu|अध्वरयु
Tatpur. m. (-युः) Joining or performing the sacrifice. This word occurs as a grammatical explanation of अध्वर्यु q. v. E. अध्वर and यु.

adhvarashrii|अध्वरश्री
Tatpur. m. (-श्रीः) (ved.) Serving or honouring the sacrifice, an epithet of Agni, the Aświns, the Maruts. E. अध्वर and श्री (serving).

adhvarasamiShTayajus|अध्वरसमिष्टयजुस्
Tatpur. n. (-जुः) The offerings called समिष्टयजुस् q. v., connected with the Adhwara-sacrifice. E. अध्वर and समिष्टयजुस्.

adhvarastha|अध्वरस्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Standing for an Adhwara-sacrifice. E. अध्वर and स्थ.

adhvariiy|अध्वरीय्
denom. par. (अध्वरीयति) To be desirous of having a sacrifice instituted for one's self. (ved.) Comp. अध्वर्य्. E. अध्वर, denom. aff. क्यच्.

adhvareShThaa|अध्वरेष्ठा
Tatpur. m. (-ष्ठाः) (ved.) Engaged in a sacrifice. E. अध्वर (in the locative) and स्था.

adhvary|अध्वर्य्
denom. par. (अध्वर्यति) To be desirous of having a sacrifice instituted for one's self (used in this sense in the Rigveda). Comp. अध्वरीय्. E. अध्वर, denom. aff. व्यच् with elision of the final vowel.

adhvaryu|अध्वर्यु
m. (-र्युः)<BR> ^1 One desirous of having a sacrifice instituted for one's self (used in this sense in the Rigveda).<BR> ^2 A priest in general (ved.)<BR> ^3 (In the ritual and the epic literature.) A special priest, one conversant with and performing the ritual observances connected with the Yajurveda; he is one of the sixteen Ŕitvijs required for the performing of the great Soma sacrifices (see ऋत्विज्) and, amongst them, one of the four leading priests (see besides ब्रह्मन्, उद्गातृ and होतृ) who receive the whole dakshińá (q. v.); his purushas or assistant priests are the प्रतिप्रस्थातृ, नेष्ट्ट and उन्नेतृ who are called, like himself, the दीक्षयितृ (q. v.) because they initiate, viz. the अध्वर्यु the three other leading priests, the प्रतिप्रस्थातृ the अर्धिन्- (q. v.), the नेष्टृ the तृतीयिन्- (q. v.) and the उन्नेतृ the पादिन्- (q. v.) priests. The Mimánsá decides in doubtful cases, viz. whenever a sacrifice mentioned in and making part of the ritual of the Yajurveda, is mentioned also and forms part of another Veda, whether the Adhwaryu has another priest to share in his functions or whether he has to abstain from the proceedings altogether. The ten चमसाध्वर्यु (q. v.), who, are also assistants or purushas of the Adhwaryu, are distinct from and do not bear the name of Ŕitvij.--According to a legend in the Harivanśa, Náráyańa created the first Adhwaryu from his arms. The dual अध्वर्यु is the collective denomination of the अध्वर्यु and प्रतिप्रस्थातृ, his principal assistant; the plur. अध्वर्यवः of the अध्वर्यु and his three assistants, and in general of those devoted to the study or the practice of the Yajurveda.<BR> ^4 The Yajurveda (also in the plur. अध्वर्यवः). E. अध्वर्य्, kŕit aff. उ.

adhvaryukaaNDa|अध्वर्युकाण्ड
Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) A collection of mantras or prayers for the special use of the Adhwaryu (q. v.). Also called आध्वर्यवकाण्ड. E. अध्वर्यु and काण्ड. 

adhvaryukratu|अध्वर्युक्रतु
Tatpur. m. (-तुः) The Kratu (q. v.)--sacrifices contained in the Yajurveda or to be performed by the Adhwaryu. E. अध्वर्यु (in the meanings of 3. or 2.) and क्रतु.

adhvaryuveda|अध्वर्युवेद
Karmadh. or Tatpur. m. (-दः) The Yajurveda. E. अध्वर्यु (in the meanings of 4. or 3.) and वेद.

adhvashalya|अध्वशल्य
Tatpur. m. (-ल्यः) A tree (Achyranthes aspera). See अपामार्ग. E. अध्वन् and शल्य.

adhvasman|अध्वस्मन्
Bahuvr. m. (f.?) n. (-स्मा-म) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Not perishing, not falling, everlasting.<BR> ^2 Not causing to perish or to fall. E. अ priv. and ध्वस्मन्.

adhvaanta|अध्वान्त
Tatpur. n. (-न्तम्) Gloom, twilight. E. अ neg. and ध्वान्त.

adhvaantashaatrava|अध्वान्तशात्रव
Tatpur. m. (-वः) A plant (Bignonia Indica). See पत्रोर्ण and श्योनाक. E. अध्वान्त and शात्रव, blossoming in the shade.

an|अन्
See अ III.

an|अन्
Considered as a substitute of इद् in इदम् in some cases, viz. अनेन, अनया and अनयोः. See इदम् and अन.

an|अन्
I. (अन-अदादि-रुदादि-उदात्त-परस्मैपदिन्) r. 2d cl. par. (अनिति- imp. आनीत् or आनत्-आन-अनिता-अनिष्यतिआनीत्.--Desid. अनिनिषति.--Caus. आनयति) and <BR>II. (अन-दिवादि-उदात्त-अनुदात्तेत्) r. 4th cl. átm. (अन्यते &c.) Also read अण् q. v.<BR> ^1 To breathe, to live.<BR> ^2 (ved.) To go. (In composition with परा and प्र, the न् of the radical is changed to ण्.) With अप- To breathe away (in farting), to produce the action of the vital air अपान (q. v.); अभ्यप- The same (अभि implying moreover the direction towards); अव- To breathe out, to breathe forth; उद्- To breathe up, to produce the action of the vital air उदान (q. v.); अभ्युद्- The same (अभि implying also the direction towards); परा-(पराणिति-पराणिणत्-पराणिणिषति)(?); परि-(पर्यनिति)(?); प्र- (प्राणिति. Des. प्राणिणिषति.)<BR> ^1 To breathe, to respire, to produce the action of the vital air प्राण q. v.<BR> ^2 To live.<BR> ^3 (In the Upanishads, but doubtful.) To smell (see also प्राण and अतिग्रह). Caus. (प्राणयतिप्राणिणत्) To revive; अनुप्र- To breathe or to live in conformity with (a following noun depends upon it in the accusative); अभिप्र- To breathe into, to make one's breath enter into (the mouth of another); वि- To breathe, to produce the action of the vital air व्यान (q. v.); अभिवि- The same with the meaning of ‘towards’; सम्-<BR> ^1 To breathe, to live.<BR> ^2 To produce the action of the vital air समान (q. v.).

ana|अन
ind. Not. E. g. अनोपमा ते बुद्धिः, explained by a commentator: ‘thy intellect is unequalled’. See also अना, and comp. अनानुकृत्य, अनानुद &c.

ana|अन
Considered by some as a substitute of इदम् in some cases; viz. अनेन, अनया and अनयोः. See इदम् and अन्.

ana|अन
m. (-नः) Spiration; it is explained as the action which is common to the five vital airs प्राण, अपान, उदान, व्यान and समान (qq. vv.). Compare अनिल. E. अन्, kŕit aff. अच्.

anaMsha|अनंश
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्)<BR> ^1 Portionless, not entitled to a share or portion.<BR> ^2 (In law.) One excluded from participation in an inheritance viz. a eunuque, a degraded man, a blind or deaf person, a fool, an idiot, a dumb  person or one deprived of one of his limbs or senses, a cripple &c. See also अनंशिन् and निरंशक.

anaMshatva|अनंशत्व
n. (-त्वम्) (In law.) The not being entitled to a share &c. See the preceding. Also अनंशता f. (-ता). E. अनंश, taddh. aff. त्व or तल्.

anaMshin|अनंशिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शी-शिनी-शि). The same as अनंश q. v. E. अ neg. and अंशिन्.

anaMshitva|अनंशित्व
n. (-त्वम्) or अनंशिता f. (-ता). The same as अनंशत्व. E. अनंशिन्, taddh. aff. त्व or तल्.

anaMshumatphalaa|अनंशुमत्फला
Tatpur. f. (-ला) A plantain (Musa paradisiaca). See अंशुमत्फला and कदली. E. अ compar.(?) and अंशुमत्फला.

anaka|अनक
m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Inferior, low. See अणक of which it is given as a various reading. E. See that of अणक; another is that from अण (अण् to sound, kŕit aff. अच्) and the taddh. aff. of depreciation कन्.

anakadundubha|अनकदुन्दुभ
Bahuvr. m. (-भः) The name of the father of Vasudeva. E. अनक and दुन्दुभ. (This word is doubtful and perhaps formed only by the commentaries, to explain the patronymic आनकदुन्दुभि q. v. See also the following.)

anakadundubhi|अनकदुन्दुभि
Bahuvr. m. (-भिः) A name of Vasudeva, the father of Kŕishńa. More usually written आनकदुन्दुभि, but given also with the short initial by some commentators of the Amarakosha. E. अनक (instead of आनक) and दुन्दुभि ‘because the gods beat the Anaka-drums in his house when Kŕishńa was born’.

anakasmaat|अनकस्मात्
Tatpur. ind.<BR> ^1 Not without a cause.<BR> ^2 Not immediately, not instantly.<BR> ^3 Not suddenly, not at once. E. अ neg. and अकस्मात्.

anax|अनक्ष्
Bahuvr. m. (-नक्) (ved.) Blind. E. अ priv. and अक्ष् (from the denomin. of अक्षि, with kŕit aff. क्विप्).

anaxa|अनक्ष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षी-क्षम्) Eyeless, blind. E. अ priv. and अक्षि, samásánta aff. षच्.

anaxara|अनक्षर
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Containing, uttering &c. what is blamable or what aught not to be said. <BR>II. n. (-रम्) Blamable or improper speech. E. अ deter. and अक्षर.

anaxi|अनक्षि
Tatpur. n. (-क्षि) A bad or disfigured eye. E. अ neg. and अक्षि.

anagaara|अनगार
Bahuvr. m. (-रः) An anchorite, a man who has retired from the world. See अग्रह. E. अ priv. and अगार ‘having no house i. e. living in the wood’.

anagaarikaa|अनगारिका
f. (-का) A wandering life, the life of a mendicant. E. अनगार, taddh. aff. ठच्(?); scil. वृत्ति.

anagna|अनग्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्नः-ग्ना-ग्नम्) Not naked. E. अ neg. and नग्न.

anagnataa|अनग्नता
f. (-ता) The not being naked. E. The former, taddh. aff. तल्.

anagni|अनग्नि
I. Tatpur. m. (-ग्निः) Any thing not or different from fire. E. अ neg. and अग्नि. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ग्निः-ग्निः-ग्नि)<BR> ^1 Having no sacrificial fire or being deprived of the arrangement of a sacrificial fire place (see अग्निचयन), as a sacrifice.<BR> ^2 Impious, irreligious (as one not performing the observances which require a sacrificial fire; also an epithet of the Manes अग्निष्वात्त q. v.).<BR> ^3 Unmarried(?).<BR> ^4 Having no domestic fire, no fire  for worldly purposes (as an anchorite who has given up his house and retired to the wood).<BR> ^5 Having a bad digestion. E. अ priv. or (in 5.) deterior. and अग्नि.

anagnitra|अनग्नित्र
Tatpur. m. f. (-त्रः-त्रा) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Not having Agni or the divinity of fire as protector, unprotected by Agni. Or according to another interpretation,<BR> ^2 not maintaining a sacrificial fire, impious, wicked. E. अ neg. and अग्नि-त्र.

anagnidagdha|अनग्निदग्ध
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ग्धः-ग्धा-ग्धम्)<BR> ^1 Not burnt in or with fire.<BR> ^2 Not burnt on the funeral pyre, not having received the obsequies in conformity with the religious rites. <BR>II. m. pl. (-ग्धाः) The name of a particular class of Pitŕis or Manes, of those apparently who when alive did not observe religious rites. See अग्निदग्ध and the following. E. अ neg. and अग्निदग्ध.

anagniShvaatta|अनग्निष्वात्त
Tatpur. m. pl. (-त्ताः) The name of a particular class of Pitŕis or Manes. This word is explained by a commentator of the Yajurveda: ‘not tasted by (स्वात्त) i. e. not burnt by fire, not having received the obsequies in conformity with the religious rites’ and it appears therefore as a synonyme of अनग्निदग्ध, as well as the converse of अग्निष्वात्त which, according to the same commentator, would be a synonyme of अग्निदग्ध. Anagnishwátta does not occur in the list of the Pitŕis which are given in the law books and in the Puráńas, while अग्निदग्ध and अग्निष्वात्त (qq. vv.) are named there as distinct classes and explained in a different manner. The etymology given, which identifies स्वात्त and स्वादित, seems moreover objectionable. E. अ and अग्निष्वात्त.

anagha|अनघ
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-घः-घा-घम्)<BR> ^1 Sinless, pure.<BR> ^2 Clean, clear.<BR> ^3 Handsome, pleasing. <BR>II. m. (-घः)<BR> ^1 A name of Śiva.<BR> ^2 The name of a Gandharva.<BR> ^3 The name of a Sádhya.<BR> ^4 The name of a prince, son of Surodha and Upadánaví.<BR> ^5 The name of a son of Vasisht́ha and Úrjá.<BR> ^6 White mustard; see गौरसर्षप. A less correct reading of this word in the latter sense is अनद्य. E. अ priv. and अघ.

anankusha|अनङ्कुश
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Unruly, licentious. E. अ priv. and अङ्कुश.

ananga|अनङ्ग
I. Tatpur. n. (-ङ्गम्) What is different from or other than the अङ्ग q. v. E. अ neg. and अङ्ग. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Bodiless, incorporeal. BREAḲ. m. (-ङ्गः) A name of Káma, the god of Love; so called, ‘because he was reduced to ashes, by the eye of Śiva, for having disturbed his devotions and rendered him enamoured of Párvatí’. <BR>3. n. (-ङ्गम्)<BR> ^1 Sky, æther.<BR> ^2 The same as मनस् q. v. E. अ priv. and अङ्ग.

anangaka|अनङ्गक
Bahuvr. n. (-कम्). The same as मनस् q. v. E. अ priv. and अङ्ग, samásánta aff. कप्. See अनङ्ग II. 3. 2.; or अनङ्ग, taddh. aff. कन्.

anangakriiDaa|अनङ्गक्रीडा
Tatpur. f. (-डा) A metre regulated by quantity; it is a species of the द्विच्छन्दिक (q. v.) and consists of a couplet with sixteen long syllables in the first and thirty two short syllables in the second verse. Also called सौम्या. E. अनङ्ग and क्रीडा.

anangadevii|अनङ्गदेवी
Tatpur. f. (-वी) The proper name of a wife of Mahlańa, a king of Kashmir. E. अनङ्ग and देवी.

anangapaala|अनङ्गपाल
Tatpur. m. (-लः) The proper name of a chamberlain of Ananta, king of Kashmir. E. अनङ्ग and पाल.

anangamejaya|अनङ्गमेजय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not shaking the body. E. अ neg. and अङ्गमेजय (अङ्ग and एज् caus., kŕit aff. खश्).

anangalekhaa|अनङ्गलेखा
Tatpur. f. (-खा) A proper name: the daughter of Baláditya, a king of Kashmir, and wife of Durlabavardhana, his successor. E. अनङ्ग and लेखा.

anangashekhara|अनङ्गशेखर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The name of a metre regulated by number and quantity, a species of the class Dand́aka (q. v.) and consisting of four verses with fifteen Iambi in each verse. E. अनङ्ग and शेखर.

anangasenaa|अनङ्गसेना
Tatpur. f. (-ना) The proper name of a courtesan in a drama. E. अनङ्ग and सेना.

anangaapiiDa|अनङ्गापीड
Tatpur. m. (-डः) The proper name of a king of Kashmir, the sixteenth king of the dynasty of Karkota. E. अनङ्ग and आपीड.

anangaasuhRd|अनङ्गासुहृद्
Tatpur. m. (-हृत्) A name of Śiva. E. अनङ्ग and असुहृद् ‘the foe of Káma’; see अनङ्ग.

anachCha|अनच्छ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-च्छः-च्छा-च्छम्) Turbid, muddy. E. अ neg. and अच्छ.

anajakaa|अनजका
Tatpur. f. (-का) A bad or miserable young female goat. Also अनजिका. E. अ deter. and अजका.

anajikaa|अनजिका
Tatpur. f. (-का). See the preceding. E. अ deter. and अजिका.

ananjana|अनञ्जन
