anaDujjihvaa|अनडुज्जिह्वा
Tatpur. f. (-ह्वा) The name of a plant (Elephantopus scaber). See गोजिह्वा. E. अनडुह् and जिह्वा.

anaDutka|अनडुत्क
m. f. n. (-त्कः-त्का-त्कम्) Having bulls or oxen (^1 as a country (according to others the reading would then be आनडुहक q. v., from आनडुह);<BR> ^2 seemingly the latter part of the thematic form of a Bahuvríhi compound, concluding with अनडुह्, f. i. प्रियानडुत्क). E. अनडुह्,<BR> ^1 taddh. aff. क,<BR> ^2 the compound with samásánta aff. कप्.

anaDudda|अनडुद्द
Tatpur. m. (-द्दः) The donor of a bull or ox. E. अनडुह् and द.

anaDuh|अनडुह्
Tatpur. m. (sing. -ड्वान्, -ड्वन्, -ड्वाहम्, -डुहा, -डुहे, -डुहः, -डुहि; du. -ड्वाहौ, -डुद्भ्याम्, -डुहोः; plur. -ड्वाहः, -डुहः, -डुद्भिः, -डुद्भ्यः, -डुत्सु) f. (-डुही or -ड्वाही)<BR> ^1 A bull or ox, especially one fit to draw a cart or to bear a weight.<BR> ^2 The sign of the zodiac, Taurus.<BR> ^3 (According to a vaidik commentator also used in the adjective sense:) fit or able to draw a cart, as an epithet of a goat; but this explanation seems doubtful.--(The use of the femin. अनड्वाही would be restricted, according to one authority, to the Vedas, while others do not make any distinction between this form and अनडुही. In Avyayíbh. compounds, the compound terminating with अनडुह् assumes the samásánta aff. टच् (see अनडुह) and in Bahuvr. compounds, the samásánta aff. कप् (see अनडुत्क); in the latter, however, it  may also retain its original form, with the following declension in the neuter: sing. अनडुत्, du. अनडुही and plur. अनड्वांहि.) E. अनस्, with स् changed to ड्, and वह् (from वह्, kŕit aff. क्विप्) with samprasárańa of व्; in the fem. with aff. ङीष्.

anaDuha|अनडुह
I. m. (-हः) The proper name of the chief of a gotra or family. See आनडुह्य. E. अनडुह्, taddh. aff. अच्(?). <BR>II. Seemingly the latter part of the thematic form of an Avyayíbh. compound concluding with अनडुह्, f. i. प्रत्यनडुहम्; such a compound assuming the samásánta aff. टच्.

anaDuhii|अनडुही
Tatpur. f. (-ही) A cow. Also अनड्वाही. E. See अनडुह्.

anaDvaahii|अनड्वाही
Tatpur. f. (-ही) A cow. Also अनडुही. E. See अनडुह्.

anaNu|अनणु
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-णुः-णुः or -ण्वी-णु) Not minute, not atomic, coarse (the reverse of अणु or अस्थूल). <BR>II. m. (-णुः) Coarse grain, as chiches (Cicer arietinum) &c. or, according to others, as wheat, barley &c.; (the reverse of अणु q. v.). E. अ neg. and अणु.

anata|अनत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Erect, not bowed down, stiff.<BR> ^2 Proud, haughty. E. अ neg. and नत.

anatikrama|अनतिक्रम
Tatpur. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 Not overstepping certain limits, not surpassing certain qualities &c., moderation.<BR> ^2 Propriety, decorum. E. अ neg. and अतिक्रम.

anatikramaNiiya|अनतिक्रमणीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not to be surpassed, overstepped or transgressed, inviolable, inevitable, unavoidable. E. अ neg. and अतिक्रमणीय.

anatikraanta|अनतिक्रान्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्)<BR> ^1 Unsurpassed, unexceeded.<BR> ^2 Untransgressed &c. See अतिक्रान्त. E. अ neg. and अतिक्रान्त.

anatidRshya|अनतिदृश्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) (ved.) Not pellucid, untransparent. E. अ and अतिदृश्य (from दृश् with अति, kŕitya aff. यत्); but more probably, ‘very invisible, very indiscernible’ from अ neg. and अति-दृश्य, instead of अत्यदृश्य. A similar transposition occurs in the vaidik word अनत्युद्य.

anatidbhuta|अनतिद्भुत
Tatpur. m. (-तः) (ved.) Not surpassed, not excelled. E. अ neg. and अतिद्भुत; the latter part of the compound apparently being a synonyme of अतिभूत and resembling, as regards its formation, the word अद्भुत (q. v.).

anatiprashnya|अनतिप्रश्न्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्न्यः-श्न्या-श्न्यम्) Not belonging or referring to a question which goes beyond its proper bounds, to a question concerning a transcendental object. E. अ neg. and अतिप्रश्न्य.

anatiprauDha|अनतिप्रौढ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Not full-grown, young (as a plant &c.). E. अ neg. and अति-प्रौढ.

anatirikta|अनतिरिक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Not exceeded in quantity or quality. E. अ neg. and अतिरिक्त.

anativilambin|अनतिविलम्बिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्बी-म्बिनी-म्बि) Not very dilatory, not very slow. E. अ neg. and अतिविलम्बिन्.

anativRtti|अनतिवृत्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Not going beyond, the being in conformity or in proportion with. See पदार्थानतिवृत्ति. E. अ neg. and अतिवृत्ति.

anatyantagati|अनत्यन्तगति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) (In grammar.) The sense of ‘not completely’, ‘not very much’, the sense of diminutiveness. E. अ neg. अत्यन्त and गति. See अत्यन्तगति. 

anatyaya|अनत्यय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Having no loss, no end &c., eternal, continual. See the meanings of अत्यय. E. अ priv. and अत्यय.

anatyudya|अनत्युद्य
Tatpur. m. (-द्यः) (ved.) Utterly unnameable, quite unfit to be spoken of. E. अ neg. and अति-उद्य; as it appears, a transposition of अत्यनुद्य, similar to that which has probably taken place in अनतिदृश्य (q. v.).

anadat|अनदत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दन्-दती-दत्) Not eating. E. अ neg. and अदत् I.

anaddhaa|अनद्धा
Tatpur. ind. (ved.) Not clearly, not truly, perhaps. Also with the particles उ and इव, अनद्धो and अनद्धेव. E. अ neg. and अद्धा.

anaddhaapuruSha|अनद्धापुरुष
Tatpur. m. (-षः) (ved.) No man in the true sense of the word, ‘one who does not serve the ends of the gods, of the pitŕis, or of men’. E. अनद्धा and पुरुष.

anadya|अनद्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Not fit to be eaten. <BR>II. m. (-द्यः) White mustard. See अनघ which is the more correct reading of this word. E. अ neg. and अद्य.

anadyatana|अनद्यतन
Bahuvr. m. (-नः) (In grammar.) The time which does not belong to the current day. See अद्यतन. It is either भूतानद्यतनः the past or भविष्यदनद्यतनः the future time, if such a period does not include the current day. E. अ priv. and अद्यतन, sc. काल.

anadhikaara|अनधिकार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) Absence of right, claim, interest or concern. E. अ neg. and अधिकार.

anadhikaaracharchaa|अनधिकारचर्चा
Tatpur. f. (-र्चा) Officiousness, meddling with other people's business. E. अनधिकार and चर्चा.

anadhikaarin|अनधिकारिन्
Tatpur. m. (-री) One who has no right or claim &c. See the meanings of अधिकारिन्. E. अ neg. and अधिकारिन्.

anadhikRta|अनधिकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not set over, or appointed &c. See the meanings of अधिकृत. E. अ neg. and अधिकृत.

anadhigata|अनधिगत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not acquired.<BR> ^2 Not learnt or studied. E. अ neg. and अधिगत.

anadhiinaka|अनधीनक
m. f. n. (-नकः-निका-नकम्) Independant. E. अअधीन, taddh. aff. कन्.

anadhyaxa|अनध्यक्ष
m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) I. Tatpur. Imperceptible, unperceived, absent. See अप्रत्यक्ष. E. अ neg. and अध्यक्ष. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Having no superintendent. E. अ priv. and अध्यक्ष.

anadhyayana|अनध्ययन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Want or intermission of reading or study, especially of the Vedas. E. अ neg. and अध्ययन.

anadhyaaya|अनध्याय
Bahuvr. m. (-यः) Time on which it is improper and forbidden to read or to study the Vedas; also used in the sense of ‘a holy-day’ or ‘vacation’. E. अ priv. and अध्याय, sc. काल.

anadhyaayadivasa|अनध्यायदिवस
Karmadh. m. (-सः) A day on which it is improper to study. See the preceding. E. अनध्याय and दिवस.

anana|अनन
n. (-नम्) Breathing, living. E. अन्, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

ananangamejaya|अननङ्गमेजय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not allowing the body to remain unshaken or quiet. E. अ neg. and अनङ्गमेजय.

ananubhaaShaNa|अननुभाषण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In the Nyáya philosophy.) Not repeating the argument for discussion, i. e. a tacit agreement with it or assent to the assertion of the person  who has proposed it; viz. if, after the argument for discussion has been announced, it has not been repeated by any one--the sign of taking it up--the proposer has to proclaim it three times; if then it does not meet with the anubháshana, it is considered as proved or as accepted as such. E. अ neg. and अनुभाषण.

ananuShangin|अननुषङ्गिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ङ्गी-ङ्गिणी-ङ्गि) Not attached to, indifferent (as to pleasure &c.). E. अ neg. and अनुषङ्गिन्.

ananuShThaana|अननुष्ठान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Non-observance (of duties &c.), neglect, want of propriety. See the meanings of अनुष्ठान. E. अ neg. and अनुष्ठान.

ananuukta|अननूक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्)<BR> ^1 Not spoken-after or accordingly.<BR> ^2 Not read or studied (as the Veda). E. अ neg. and अनूक्त.

ananta|अनन्त
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Endless in time and space: eternal, unbounded, innumerable &c. <BR>II. m. (-न्तः)<BR> ^1 A name of Vishńu or Kŕishńa.<BR> ^2 A name of Baladeva, the elder brother of Kŕishńa.<BR> ^3 A name of Śiva.<BR> ^4 A name of Rudra, in an Upanishad of the Atharvaveda.<BR> ^5 A name of Śesha, the chief of the Nágas or serpent race that inhabit the infernal regions: the couch and constant attendant of Vishńu.<BR> ^6 A name of Vásuki, another king of the serpents, the brother of the former.<BR> ^7 A name of one of the Viśwadevas.<BR> ^8 The name of the fourteenth of the twenty-four Arhats or Jaina deified saints of the present Avasarpińí; see also अनन्तजित्.<BR> ^9 The name of a king of Kashmir; see also अनन्तदेव.<BR> ^10 A proper name common to several authors &c.<BR> ^11 The name of a plant, Vitex trifolia (Lin.); see सिन्दवार.<BR> ^12 Talc (see अभ्रक; in this sense the word is given by some as a neuter).<BR> ^13 (In arithmetic.) Infinite quantity: a fraction having a cypher for its denominator; see also अनन्तराशि and खहर.<BR> ^14 The name of the twenty-third of the lunar asterisms; see श्रवण.<BR> ^15 A silken cord with fourteen knots which the Hindus tie round the right arm at the festival of Anantachaturdaśí. <BR>III. f. (-न्ता)<BR> ^1 The earth.<BR> ^2 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denominate) the numeral one.<BR> ^3 A name of Párvatí, the wife of Śiva.<BR> ^4 A name of Tárá, a Buddhist deity.<BR> ^5 The proper name of the wife of Janamejaya.<BR> ^6 The name of the following plants:<BR> ^a. Hedysarum alhagi; see यवास or रोदनी.<BR> ^b. Echytes frutescens; see श्यामा or गोपी.<BR> ^c. A sort of potherb; see विशल्या or शक्रपुष्पी.<BR> ^d. Agrostis linearis (Koen.) or Panicum dactylon; see दूर्वा or भार्गवी, श्वेतदूर्वा and नीलदूर्वा.<BR> ^e. Phyllanthus emblica (emblic myrobolan); see आमलकी.<BR> ^f. Menispermum glabrum or cordifolium; see गुडूची.<BR> ^g. Gloriosa superba; see लाङ्गली.<BR> ^h. See हेममानी.<BR> ^i. Premna spinosa; see असिमन्थ.<BR> ^k. Piper longum (Long pepper); see पिप्पली or कणा.<BR> ^l. Terminalia chebula (yellow myrobolan); see हरीतकी.<BR> ^m. Asclepias pseudosarsa; see शारिवा.<BR> ^n. Justicia adhatoda(?).<BR> ^o. Bromelia Ananas(?).<BR> ^p. Echytes dichotoma(?).<BR> ^q. According to some also the same as अनन्तमूल q. v. <BR>IV. n. (-न्तम्)<BR> ^1 Sky, atmosphere, æther.<BR> ^2 Talc; (also given in the latter sense as a masculine). E. अ priv. and अन्त. 

anantaka|अनन्तक
I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Endless, eternal, unlimited. <BR>II. n. (-कम्) (In the Jaina doctrine.) The collective expression for what is eternal viz. matter and soul; but including also, according to a commentary, planets or according to another, æther, regions &c. E. अनन्त, taddh. aff. कन्, or rather a Bahuvr. composed of अ neg. and अन्त, samásánta aff. कप्.

anantakara|अनन्तकर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Making endless or unlimited. E. अनन्त and कर.

anantaga|अनन्तग
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Going continually, moving perpetually. E. अनन्त and ग.

anantachaturdashii|अनन्तचतुर्दशी
Tatpur. f. (-शी) The fourteenth lunation of the light half i. e. the day of the full moon of the month Bhádra (August-September), when Vishńu under the form of the serpent Ananta is worshipped. E. अनन्त and चतुर्दशी.

anantachaaritra|अनन्तचारित्र
Bahuvr. m. (-त्रः) The proper name of a Bodhisattva, Mahásattva, or a superior Bauddha saint. E. अनन्त and चारित्र.

anantajit|अनन्तजित्
Tatpur. m. (-जित्) The name of the fourteenth of the twenty-four Arhats or Jaina deified saints of the present Avasarpińí; also called अनन्त. E. अनन्त and जित् ‘who conquers, who gains eternity’.

anantataa|अनन्तता
f. (-ता) Eternity: also अनन्तत्व n. (-त्वम्). E. अनन्त, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anantadRShTi|अनन्तदृष्टि
Bahuvr. m. (-ष्टिः) A name of Śiva. E. अनन्त and दृष्टि.

anantadeva|अनन्तदेव
Karmadh. m. (-वः) The proper name of a king of Kashmir, the son of Harirája; also a proper name belonging to several authors &c. See also अनन्त. E. अनन्त and देव.

anantanemi|अनन्तनेमि
Bahuvr.(?) m. (-मिः) The proper name of a king of Málava, a contemporary of Śákyamuni. E. अनन्त and नेमि.

anantapaala|अनन्तपाल
Tatpur. m. (-लः) The proper name of a warrior chief serving under Harsha, king of Kashmir. E. अनन्त and पाल.

anantamati|अनन्तमति
Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) The proper name of a Bodhisattva or Bauddha saint, the son of the Tathágata Chandrasúryapradípa. E. अनन्त and मति.

anantamuula|अनन्तमूल
Bahuvr. m. (-लः) The name of a plant (Periploca Indica or Asclepias pseudosarsa or Asclepias asthmatica); see also अनन्ता and शारिवा. E. अनन्त and मूल.

anantara|अनन्तर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Having nothing intermediate, having no interval or defect, uninterrupted, entire; in the Upanishads also as an epithet of Brahman (n.) or the supreme soul, of which it is said that it has nothing before it nor after it, nor between ‘before’ and ‘after’ it nor besides it, or that it exists without interruption or defect, entire.<BR> ^2 Next, immediately following or preceding.<BR> ^3 Next of kin, in succession, in caste.<BR> ^4 Close, compact.--अनन्तरम् immediately, afterwards; it is followed or preceded sometimes by a noun depending upon it in the ablative or genitive. E. अ priv. and अनन्तर.

anantaraja|अनन्तरज
Tatpur. m. (-जः) The son of a man of the three first castes, married to a woman of a caste inferior in order  to his own, but not to a Súdra woman viz. of a Bráhmańa by a Kshatriyá or Vaiśyá and of a Kshatriyá by a Vaiśyá. The three kinds of sons got by parents of the same caste are called सजातिज and both, comprising six kinds, have the privileges of a Dvija or twice-born man. (This is the explanation given by a commentator of Manu and, according to him, अनन्तरज would have a different meaning than अनन्तरजात, though both words appear to be synonymes.) E. अनन्तर and ज.

anantarajaata|अनन्तरजात
Tatpur. m. (-तः) The son of a father married to a woman of a caste next in order to his own, viz. of a Bráhmańa by a Kshatriyá, of a Kshatriya by a Vaiśyá, of a Vaiśya by a Súdrá. E. अनन्तर and जात.

anantaraayam|अनन्तरायम्
Bahuvr. ind. Without interruption. E. अ priv. and अन्तराय.

anantaraashi|अनन्तराशि
Karmadh. m. (-शिः) (In arithmetic.) Infinite quantity: a fraction having a cypher for its denominator. See also अनन्त II. 13. and खहर. E. अनन्त and राशि.

anantarita|अनन्तरित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Uninterrupted, not separated by. E. Denom. of अनन्तर, kŕit aff. क्त.

anantariiya|अनन्तरीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Belonging to what is next, next in succession, caste &c. See the meanings of अनन्तर. E. अनन्तर, taddh. aff. छ.

anantaruupa|अनन्तरूप
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Having innumerable forms or shapes, multiform. E. अनन्त and रूप.

anantarhita|अनन्तर्हित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not separated, not interposed.<BR> ^2 Not concealed, not hidden. E. अ neg. and अन्तर्हित.

anantavat|अनन्तवत्
I. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Endowed with infinity, eternal. <BR>II. m. (-वान्) A name or epithet of one of the four pádas or feet of Brahman (in the symbolical language of the Upanishads), consisting of four Kalás or parts, viz. earth, intermediate space, heaven and ocean. The other three feet are called प्रकाशवत्, ज्योतिष्मत् and आयतनवत् (qq. vv.).

anantavarman|अनन्तवर्मन्
Bahuvr. m. (-र्मा) The proper name of a king. E. अनन्त and वर्मन्.

anantavaata|अनन्तवात
Karmadh. m. (-तः) (In medicine.) One of the diseases of the head (see शिरोरोग). It is described in the following manner: ‘when the three humours (air, bile and phlegm) are deranged in the vessels of the back of the neck they make it very feverish and painful and it suppresses the humours particularly in the region of the eyes, eyebrows and temples; it then produces shaking in the sides of the cheeks, cramp of the jaws and morbid affections of the eyes’. E. अनन्त and वात.

anantavikramin|अनन्तविक्रमिन्
m. (-मी) The proper name of a Bodhisattva or Bauddha saint. E. अनन्त-विक्रम, taddh. aff. इनि.

anantavijaya|अनन्तविजय
Bahuvr. m. (-यः) The name of the shell of Yudhisht́hira. E. अनन्त and विजय.

anantaviirya|अनन्तवीर्य
Bahuvr. m. (-र्यः) The proper name of the twentythird Jaina Arhat or deified saint of a future age or Utsarpińí. E. अनन्त and वीर्य.

anantavrata|अनन्तव्रत
Tatpur. n. (-तम्) The name of a festival observed on the day of the full moon in Bhádra (August September) in honour of Vishńu under the form of the serpent Ananta (q. v.). See अनन्तचतुर्दशी. E. अनन्त and व्रत.

anantashakti|अनन्तशक्ति
Bahuvr. m. (-क्तिः) The proper name of a son of the king Amaraśakti. E. अनन्त and शक्ति.

anantashayana|अनन्तशयन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The name of Travancore. E. अनन्त and शयन.

anantashiirShaa|अनन्तशीर्षा
Bahuvr. f. (-र्षा) The proper name of the wife of Vásuki, a king of the serpents. E. अनन्त and शीर्ष; literally: ‘having innumerous heads’.

anantashuShma|अनन्तशुष्म
Bahuvr. m. (-ष्मः) (ved.) Of infinite power or strength; an epithet of the Maruts. E. अनन्त and शुष्म.

anantya|अनन्त्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्त्यः-न्त्या-न्त्यम्) Infinite, eternal, unbounded. <BR>II. n. (-न्त्यम्) Infinity, eternity, immortality. cf. आनन्त्य. E. अ priv. and अन्त्य.

ananda|अनन्द
Bahuvr. m. pl. (-न्दाः) (In the Upanishads) the name of a world where those are doomed to reside after their death, who have not acquired spiritual knowledge or who have made to a priest a sacrificial gift of an old or defective cow &c. E. अ priv. and नन्द; literally: ‘having or giving no pleasure or joy’.

ananna|अनन्न
Tatpur. n. (-न्नम्) No-food, no-corn, bad food, bad corn &c. See the meanings of अन्न. E. अ deter. and अन्न.

ananya|अनन्य
m. f. n. (-न्यः-न्या-न्यम्) I. Tatpur. Not different, same, identical. E. अ neg. and अन्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr.<BR> ^1 Without another, one, sole.<BR> ^2 Fixed on one object, having no other object or occupation. E. अ priv. and अन्य.

ananyagati|अनन्यगति
I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः) No other refuge, asylum or hope, one only refuge &c. E. अ neg. and अन्य-गति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Having but one refuge, asylum or hope. E. अ priv. and अन्य-गति.

ananyagatika|अनन्यगतिक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Having but one refuge, asylum or hope. E. अनन्यगति II, samásánta aff. कप्.

ananyachinta|अनन्यचिन्त
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Having the thoughts fixed on one only object. E. अनन्य and चिन्ता.

ananyaja|अनन्यज
Tatpur. m. (-जः) A name of Káma or Love. E. अ neg. and अन्य-ज ‘produced by nothing else than the manas or heart’.

ananyataa|अनन्यता
f. (-ता) or अनन्यत्व n. (-त्वम्)<BR> ^1 Sameness, identity.<BR> ^2 Singleness. E. अनन्य I. and II., taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

ananyadeva|अनन्यदेव
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Having no other gods. E. अ priv. and अन्य-देव.

ananyaniShpaadya|अनन्यनिष्पाद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) What cannot be done or accomplished by any one else. E. अ neg. and अन्य-निष्पाद्य.

ananyapuurva|अनन्यपूर्व
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) Intact, never in the prior possession of another. <BR>II. f. (-र्वा) A girl not previously wedded, a virgin. E. अ neg. and अन्य-पूर्व. Also with taddh. aff. कन्, अनन्यपूर्वक m. f. n. (-र्वकः-र्विका-र्वकम्).

ananyapratikriya|अनन्यप्रतिक्रिय
Bahuvr. m. (-यः-या-यम्) Having no other remedy. E. अ priv. and अन्य-प्रतिक्रिया.

ananyabhava|अनन्यभव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Produced or effected  by no one or nothing else, by one particular person or thing. E. अनन्य and भव.

ananyamanas|अनन्यमनस्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नाः-नाः-नः) Intent, attentive, having the mind fixed on one subject, not absent. E. अनन्य and मनस्.

ananyamanaska|अनन्यमनस्क
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्कः-स्का-स्कम्). The same as the preceding. E. अनन्यमनस्, samásánta aff. कप्.

ananyamaanasa|अनन्यमानस
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-सः-सी-सम्). The same as अनन्यमनस्. E. अनन्य and मानस.

ananyavRtti|अनन्यवृत्ति
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तिः-त्तिः-त्ति) Having the mind fixed on one object, intent, attentive. E. अनन्य and वृत्ति.

ananyahRta|अनन्यहृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not stolen or taken, safe. E. अ neg. and अन्य-हृत.

ananyaadRsha|अनन्यादृश
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शः-शी-शम्) Not like another, unusual, extraordinary. E. अ neg. and अन्यादृश.

ananyaartha|अनन्यार्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) What exists or is done &c. not for any one or any thing else, what exists &c. on its own behalf, principal, absolute (e. g. a sacrifice). The reverse of अन्यार्थ. E. अ and अन्यार्थ.

ananyaashrita|अनन्याश्रित
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not supported by or dependant upon another, independant. <BR>II. n. (-तम्) (In law.) Unencumbered property. E. अ and अन्य-आश्रित.

ananvaya|अनन्वय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) (In rhetoric.) One of the Álankáras or figures of speech: comparing an object to itself, with respect to its being the only one of its class as to the qualities expressed and therefore not liable to comparison with any thing else; e. g. the moon shines like a moon i. e. like a very moon, a moon indeed. E. अ neg. and अन्वय, literally: ‘want of connexion sc. with other objects’.

ananvita|अनन्वित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unconnected with, inconsistent, incoherent.<BR> ^2 Devoid of, not possessing. E. अ neg. and अन्वित.

anapa|अनप
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Destitute of water. E. अ priv. and अप्, samásánta aff. अ.

anapakaraNa|अनपकरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as the following. E. अ neg. and अपकरण.

anapakarman|अनपकर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) 1. Not doing ill, evil &c. (The reverse of अपकर्मन् q. v.) 2. (In law.)<BR> ^1 Not delivering (a gift).<BR> ^2 Not paying or acquitting (debts, wages). See also अनपकरण, अनपक्रिया, अनपाकरण, अनपाकर्मन्. E. अ neg. and अपकर्मन्.

anapakaara|अनपकार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) Harmlessness, freedom from hatred &c. (The reverse of अपकार q. v.) E. अ neg. and अपकार.

anapakaarin|अनपकारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Innocuous &c. (The reverse of अपकारिन्.) E. अ neg. and अपकारिन्.

anapakriyaa|अनपक्रिया
Tatpur. f. (-या). The same as अनपकर्मन् q. v. E. अ neg. and अपक्रिया.

anapaga|अनपग
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Not departing, not being separated from. E. अ neg. and अपग.

anapachyuta|अनपच्युत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Not fallen off, not diminished in power &c., irresistible; as an epithet of Soma, Indra &c. E. अ neg. and अपच्युत.

anapajayya|अनपजय्य
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-य्यः-य्या-य्यम्) (ved.) What has no possibility of being made un-conquered or un-victorious  (as a victory). अनपजय्यम् used also adverbially: so as not to become un-victorious (e. g. to conquer so as not to have a barren victory, as not to have the ennemy rising again). E. अ priv. and अपजय्य.

anapatya|अनपत्य
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्)<BR> ^1 Childless, having no progeny.<BR> ^2 (ved.) Prejudicial to progeny.<BR> ^3 (ved. Tatpur.) What causes to fall, unpropitious(?). E. अ priv. and अपत्य.

anapatyaka|अनपत्यक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्). The same as अनपत्य. E. अनपत्य, samásánta aff. कप्.

anapatyataa|अनपत्यता
f. (-ता) Childlessness, want of progency. E. अनपत्य, taddh. aff. तल्.

anapatyavat|अनपत्यवत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Childless, having no progeny. E. अ neg. and अपत्यवत्.

anapanihita|अनपनिहित
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Having suffered no loss, entire, complete. E. अ priv. and अपनिहित.

anapayati|अनपयति
Tatpur.(?) ind. Early in the morning. E. अ neg. and अपयति (? the locative of अपयत्, from इ with अप, kŕit aff. शतृ), meaning perhaps: ‘when the sun has not yet gone far’.

anapara|अनपर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having nothing that follows or comes after; esp. as an epithet of the neuter Brahman; opposed to अपूर्व. E. अ priv. and अपर.

anaparaaddha|अनपराद्ध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Having suffered no injury; अनपराद्धम् also used adverbially: without injury. E. अ priv. and अपराद्ध.

anaparaadha|अनपराध
I. Tatpur. m. (-धः) Not doing ill, innocuousness, innocence, sinlessness. E. अ neg. and अपराध. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्)<BR> ^1 Innocuous, sinless.<BR> ^2 Uninjured, complete. E. अ priv. and अपराध.

anaparaadhatva|अनपराधत्व
n. (-त्वम्) Sinlessness, want of fault or defect. E. अनपराध II., taddh. aff. त्व.

anaparaadhin|अनपराधिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धी-धिनी-धि) Innocent, sinless. E. अ neg. and अपराधिन्.

anapalaaShuka|अनपलाषुक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not thirsty. E. अ neg. and अपलाषुक.

anapavRjya|अनपवृज्य
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ज्यः-ज्या-ज्यम्) (ved.) Free from impurity (hairs &c.), as a road. E. अ priv. and अपवृज्य what is to be shunned.

anapavyayat|अनपव्ययत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यन्-यन्ती-यत्) (ved.) Unremitting, able, powerful. E. अ neg. and अपव्ययत् (from व्यय् with अप, kŕit aff. शतृ).

anapasara|अनपसर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Having no valid reason, acting in an unjustifiable manner. E. अ priv. and अपसर, literally: having no way-out.

anapasphur|अनपस्फुर्
Tatpur. f. (-स्फूः) (ved.) Not going or running away; an epithet of a cow. E. अ neg. and अपस्फुर्.

anapasphura|अनपस्फुर
Tatpur. f. (-रा) (ved.) The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and अपस्फुर.

anapasphurat|अनपस्फुरत्
Tatpur. m. f. (-रन्-रन्ती) (ved.) The same as अनपस्फुर्; also as an epithet of the udder of the cow &c. E. अ neg. and अपस्फुरत्.

anapahatapaapman|अनपहतपाप्मन्
Tatpur. m. (-प्मा) (ved.) Not freed from sin or evil; an epithet of the Manes. E. अ neg. and अपहतपाप्मन्.

anapahRta|अनपहृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not taken away, not stolen. E. अ neg. and अपहृत. 

anapaakaraNa|अनपाकरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In law.)<BR> ^1 Not delivering (a gift).<BR> ^2 Not paying or acquitting (debts, wages). See अनपकर्मन्, अनपक्रिया and the following. E. अ neg. and अपाकरण.

anapaakarman|अनपाकर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) (In law.) The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and अपाकर्मन्.

anapaaya|अनपाय
I. Tatpur. m. (-यः) Absence of loss or diminution, permanence. E. अ neg. and अपाय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Undiminished, unceasing. 2. m. (-यः) A name or epithet of Śiva. E. अ priv. and अपाय.

anapaayin|अनपायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि)<BR> ^1 Firm, constant.<BR> ^2 Durable, imperishable. E. अ neg. and अपायिन्.

anapuMsaka|अनपुंसक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) (In grammar.) Not a neuter i. e. the masculine or feminine gender or a noun in these two genders. E. अ neg. and नपुंसक.

anapuupiiya|अनपूपीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not fit for cakes. E. अ neg. and अपूपीय.

anapuupya|अनपूप्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्). The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and अपूप्य.

anapexa|अनपेक्ष
I. Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) Carelessness, indifference, disregard. E. अ neg. and अपेक्षा. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्)<BR> ^1 Disregarding.<BR> ^2 Unheeding, careless.<BR> ^3 Not requiring another thing, not referring to another thing or word in a sentence &c., independent or absolute. See निरपेक्ष. E. अ priv. and अपेक्षा.

anapexatva|अनपेक्षत्व
n. (-त्वम्) The being अनपेक्ष (II.), but more especially in the sense 3. E. अनपेक्ष, taddh. aff. त्व.

anapexita|अनपेक्षित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Disregarded.<BR> ^2 Unheeded. E. अ neg. and अपेक्षित.

anapexin|अनपेक्षिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षी-क्षिणी-क्षि)<BR> ^1 Disregarding.<BR> ^2 Unheeding, careless. E. अ neg. and अपेक्षिन्.

anapeta|अनपेत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Present, not passed or gone.<BR> ^2 Not devoid of, possessed of. E. अ neg. and अपेत.

anapnas|अनप्नस्
Bahuvr. m. (-प्नाः) (ved.) Devoid of (pious) action, impious or (according to another interpretation) devoid of shape or form. E. अ priv. and अप्नस्.

anaphaa|अनफा
f. (-फा) A certain configuration of the planets; a transcription of the greek word .

anabhiJNa|अनभिज्ञ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ज्ञः-ज्ञा-ज्ञम्) Unacquainted, ignorant, unwise. E. अ neg. and अभिज्ञ.

anabhidruh|अनभिद्रुह्
Tatpur. m. (-ध्रुक्) (ved.) Not doing injury; an epithet of the Aświns. E. अ neg. and अभिद्रुह्.

anabhibhuuta|अनभिभूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unsubdued, unsurpassed.<BR> ^2 Unobstructed. E. अ neg. and अभिभूत.

anabhimata|अनभिमत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Disliked, disagreeable, unpleasant &c. (The reverse of अभिमत.) E. अ neg. and अभिमत.

anabhimlaatavarNa|अनभिम्लातवर्ण
Tatpur. m. (-र्णः) (ved.) Of unwithered colour, very bright or splendent; an epithet of Apánnapát. E. अ neg. and अभिम्लातवर्ण.

anabhimlaana|अनभिम्लान
Tatpur. m. (-नः) The proper name of a gotraor family-chief. E. अ priv. and अभिम्लान. See आनभिम्लान. 

anabhiruupa|अनभिरूप
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Not handsome, not pleasing. E. अ neg. and अभिरूप.

anabhilaaSha|अनभिलाष
Tatpur. m. (-षः)<BR> ^1 Absence of desire, indifference.<BR> ^2 Want of appetite, indigestion. E. अ neg. and अभिलाष.

anabhilaxita|अनभिलक्षित
Tatpur. m. (-तः) Not marked, not bearing sings or symbols (e. g. of knowledge, of astrology or of other learned acquirements, as a Vánaprastha when asking for alms). E. अ neg. and अभिलक्षित.

anabhilaaShin|अनभिलाषिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षी-षिणी-षि) Not desirous, indifferent. E. अ neg. and अभिलाषिन्.

anabhivyakta|अनभिव्यक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Indistinct, dim. E. अ neg. and अभिव्यक्त.

anabhishasta|अनभिशस्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) (ved.) Blameless, irreproachable. E. अ neg. and अभिशस्त.

anabhishasti|अनभिशस्ति
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्तिः-स्तिः-स्ति) (ved.) Blameless, irreproachable; an epithet of ájya or clarified butter. E. अ priv. and अभिशस्ति.

anabhishastenii|अनभिशस्तेनी
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नीः-नीः-नि) (ved.) Leading to what is blameless, to heaven &c. (The form अनभिशस्तेन्यम् which is explained as the acc. masc. singul. with the meaning of the nom. neuter sing. is rather to be considered as an irregular formation of the neuter with the addition of अम् to the terminating नि.) E. अनभिशस्त (loc.) and नी.

anabhishastya|अनभिशस्त्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्त्यः-स्त्या-स्त्यम्) (ved.) Blameless, irreproachable. E. अ neg. and अभिशस्त्य.

anabhiShanga|अनभिषङ्ग
Tatpur. m. (-ङ्गः) Detachment, disconnection, freedom from affection or attachment. E. अ neg. and अभिषङ्ग.

anabhisandhikRta|अनभिसन्धिकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Done unintentionally, or by mistake. E. अ neg. and अभिसन्धि-कृत.

anabhihita|अनभिहित
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not named, not designated.<BR> ^2 (ved.) Not tied with, not fastened with. <BR>II. m. (-तः) A proper name of a gotraor family-chief. His descendants are called अनभिहिताः or आनभिहितयः. Acc. to others the proper name aught to be अभिहित q. v. E. अ neg. and अभिहित.

anabhiishu|अनभीशु
Bahuvr. m. (-शुः) (ved.) Without reins (more esp. without the rein called अभीशु q. v.), unrefrained; an epithet of the sun. E. अ priv. and अभीशु.

anabhyaaruuDha|अनभ्यारूढ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढः-ढा-ढम्) Not ascended, not reached. E. अ neg. and अभ्यारूढ.

anabhyaasa|अनभ्यास
Tatpur. I. m. (-सः) Want of practise, exercise &c.; see अभ्यास. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्) Not near, far, far away. Also written अनभ्याश. E. अ neg. and अभ्यास.

anabhyaasamitya|अनभ्यासमित्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) What must not be approached, what must be shunned from afar. Also written अनभ्याशमित्य. E. अनभ्यास with ágama मुम् (or taken adverbially) and इत्य.

anabhraka|अनभ्रक
Bahuvr. m. pl. (-काः) A class of Bauddha gods who reside in the first or lowest stage of the fourth sphere of the Bauddha heaven. E. अ priv. and अभ्र, samásánta aff. कप्, literally ‘without clouds’.

anama|अनम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) A Brahman, one who does not salute a Brahman, making obeisance to the gods only, and returning salutations with his blessing. E. अ neg. and नम who salutes(?). 

anamasya|अनमस्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्यः-स्या-स्यम्) Unworthy of being saluted. E. अ neg. and नमस्य.

anamitampacha|अनमितम्पच
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-चः-चा-चम्) Miserly, niggardly. E. अ neg. and अ-मितम्पच. Others read instead of this word, where it occurs in the Amarak., मितम्पच.

anamitra|अनमित्र
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Free from enemies, without enemies. <BR>II. n. (-त्रम्) The being free from or without enemies. <BR>III. m. (-त्रः) A proper name of<BR> ^1 A prince of the solar race, a descendant of Sagara, son of Nighna and brother of Raghu, the fifty-second king of Ayodhyá.<BR> ^2 A son of the king Krosht́u or Kroshtŕi by Gándhári and father of Śini or, according to others, a grandson of Vŕishńi, son of Sumitra by Mádrí and brother to Śini; or, again, a grandson of Dhŕisht́a, son of Sumitra &c. E. अ priv. and अमित्र.

anamiiva|अनमीव
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Free from disease, healthy.<BR> ^2 Removing diseases, healthy (as food, plants, fire). <BR>II. n. (-वम्) Freedom from disease, good health. E. अ priv. and अमीवा.

anambara|अनम्बर
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Naked, unclad, unclothed. <BR>II. m. (-रः) A Bauddha mendicant, going naked. See दिगम्बर. E. अ priv. and अम्बर.

anaya|अनय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) I. Bad or improper conduct, as gambling &c. (see व्यसन). E. अ deter. and नय. <BR>II.<BR> ^1 Ill-luck, bad fortune.<BR> ^2 Calamity, distress. E. अ deter. and अय.

anayangata|अनयङ्गत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Fallen into misfortune. E. अनय II., ágama मुम् and गत.

anaraNya|अनरण्य
Bahuvr. m. (-ण्यः) The proper name of a king of Ayodhyá, of the solar race; according to one authority, a son of Vána and father of Pŕithu, according to others, a son of Sambhúta and father of Pŕishadaśwa or, again, a son of Sarwakarman and father of Nighna. Those who make him a son of Sambhúta, relate that he was slain by Rávańa.

anarus|अनरुस्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रुः-रुः-रु) (ved.) Not sore, not wounded, sound, healed. (As a Tatpur. this word occurs only in the Vedas; it would be a Bahuvr. according to the use of अरुस् in the classic language.) E. अ neg. and अरुस्, sore, wounded; (or as a Bahuvr. अ priv. and अरुस्, sore, wound).

anargala|अनर्गल
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Unrestrained, selfwilled. E. अ priv. and अर्गल.

anargha|अनर्घ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्घः-र्घा-र्घम्) Invaluable, priceless. E. अ priv. and अर्घ.

anargharaaghava|अनर्घराघव
Tatpur. n. (-वम्) The name of a drama of Murári, the subject of which are the events in the life of Ráma, the descendant of Raghu. E. अनर्घ and राघव, sc. नाटक.

anarghya|अनर्घ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्घ्यः-र्घ्या-र्घ्यम्)<BR> ^1 Priceless, invaluable, not to be bought.<BR> ^2 Different from what is valuable or respectable. (In the first of these meanings the word is an oxytonon, in the latter a proparoxytonon; the first meaning, however, is the usual one.) E. अ neg. and अर्घ्य. 

anarghyataa|अनर्घ्यता
f. (-ता) or अनर्घ्यत्व n. (-त्वम्) Absence of price or cost, invaluableness. E. अनर्घ्य, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anartha|अनर्थ
I. Tatpur. m. (-र्थः)<BR> ^1 Want of meaning, nonsense.<BR> ^2 A thing that is useless or obnoxious.<BR> ^3 Disadvantage, misfortune, calamity. E. अ neg. and अर्थ. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्)<BR> ^1 Meaningless, unmeaning, nonsensical.<BR> ^2 Fruitless, vain, unprofitable.<BR> ^3 Unhappy, unlucky. E. अ priv. and अर्थ.

anarthaka|अनर्थक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थकः-र्थका-र्थकम्)<BR> ^1 Not having the sense or meaning (of).<BR> ^2 Not-significative (as a particle &c.).<BR> ^3 Unmeaning, meaningless, nonsensical.<BR> ^4 Fruitless, vain, unprofitable.<BR> ^5 Unhappy, unlucky. E. अनर्थ II., samásánta aff. कप्.

anarthakara|अनर्थकर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्)<BR> ^1 Following unprofitable or idle pursuits.<BR> ^2 Doing mischief, causing calamities. E. अ neg. and अर्थकर or अनर्थ and कर.

anarthanaashin|अनर्थनाशिन्
Tatpur. m. (-शी) A name or epithet of Śiva. E. अनर्थ and नाशिन् ‘destroying or removing calamity’.

anarthya|अनर्थ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्थ्यः-र्थ्या-र्थ्यम्) Devoid of substance, useless, fit for no purpose &c.; the reverse of अर्थ्य q. v. E. अ neg. and अर्थ्य.

anarva|अनर्व
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Not decaying, not passing away, imperishable, permanent.<BR> ^2 Without impediment, not thwarted, unobstructed. See the following. E. अ priv. and अर्व.

anarvan|अनर्वन्
Bahuvr. m. (-र्वा) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Not moving, fixed.<BR> ^2 Not passing away, permanent.<BR> ^3 Without an impediment, not thwarted, unobstructed.<BR> ^4 Without an enemy or foe. See the preceding. (The declension of this word differs from that of अर्वन् in so far, as it does not assume the ádeśa तृ (i. e. त्) which is said to be the substitute of the न् in अर्वन् q. v.; e. g. अनर्वाणम्, अनर्वाणौ, अनर्वाणः.) E. अ priv. and अर्वन्.

anarvish|अनर्विश्
Tatpur. m. (-ट्) (ved.) I. A car-man, one going with or on a cart. E. अनस्, with र् instead of स्, and विश्. (Or according to another explanation, which appears, however, to be an artificial one), <BR>II. One who does not arrive where he is to go to, one not attaining the end or aim of his journey. E. अ neg. and अर् (from ऋ, kŕit aff. विच्) and विश् II.

anarshani|अनर्शनि
Tatpur. m. (-निः) (ved.) The name of a demon slain by Indra. E. doubtful; probably अ neg. and अर्शनि.

anarsharaati|अनर्शराति
Tatpur. m. (-तिः) (ved.) One whose gifts are not inauspicious or wicked, whose offerings do not cause pain. A various reading of this word in the Sámaveda is अलर्षिराति q. v. E. अ neg. and अर्श-राति (Bahuvr.).

anarha|अनर्ह
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्हः-र्हा-र्हम्)<BR> ^1 Not deserving.<BR> ^2 Unworthy.<BR> ^3 Not fit, unsuitable. E. अ neg. and अर्ह.

anala|अनल
m. (-लः)<BR> ^1 Fire.<BR> ^2 A name of Agni or the god of fire.<BR> ^3 The name of one of the eight Vasus.<BR> ^4 A name of Vasudeva.<BR> ^5 The proper name of a Muni.<BR> ^6 The proper name of a monkey (in the Rámáyańa).<BR> ^7 The fire of the stomach, digestive faculty.<BR> ^8 Bile.<BR> ^9 The name of several plants, viz.<BR> ^a. Plumbago zeylanica (see चित्रक),<BR> ^b. Plumbago rosea (see रक्तचित्रक),<BR> ^c. Semicarpus anacardium (see भल्लातक).<BR> ^10 Wind.<BR> ^11 (In astronomy.) The name of the fiftieth year  of Bŕihaspati's cycle of sixty years.<BR> ^12 (In astronomy.) The name of the third lunar mansion or Kŕittiká(?).<BR> ^13 (In arithmetic sometimes used to denote) the numeral three; see अग्नि(9.). E. अन्, in the causative, uń. aff. कलच्; (अनल belongs to the वृषादि).

analankariShNu|अनलङ्करिष्णु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्णुः-ष्णुः-ष्णु)<BR> ^1 Not fond of ornaments, dress &c.<BR> ^2 Not making show of ornaments, not ornamented. E. अ neg. and अलङ्करिष्णु.

analadiipana|अनलदीपन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Producing appetite, stomachic. See अग्निदीपन. E. अनल and दीपन.

analaprabhaa|अनलप्रभा
Tatpur. f. (-भा) The name of a plant (Halicacabum cardiospermum); see ज्योतिष्मती. E. अनल and प्रभा ‘fire-shine’.

analapriyaa|अनलप्रिया
Tatpur. f. (-या) The wife of Agni. E. अनल and प्रिया.

analam|अनलम्
Tatpur. ind. Not enough, insufficient, unequal, unable. E. अ neg. and अलम्.

analavaaTa|अनलवाट
Tatpur. m. (-टः) The name of ancient Pattana. E. अनल and वाट.

analasa|अनलस
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्)<BR> ^1 Not indolent or lazy.<BR> ^2 Diligent, industrious. E. अ neg. and अलस.

analasaada|अनलसाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) Decrease of digestive faculty, loss of appetite; lit. decay of the stomachic fire. E. अनल 7. and साद.

anali|अनलि
m. (-लिः) The name of a tree (Sesbana grandiflora); see अगस्तिद्रु. E. अनल, taddh. aff. इ(?).

analpa|अनल्प
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ल्पः-ल्पा-ल्पम्) Not a little, much. E. अ neg. and अल्प.

analpaghoSha|अनल्पघोष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Making much noise, vociferous. E. अनल्प and घोष.

anavakaasha|अनवकाश
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्)<BR> ^1 Having no opportunity &c.; see अवकाश.<BR> ^2 Having no proper place, irrelevant, unessential; (as words of an instance &c. which have no bearing on the rule to be illustrated, opposed to those words of it which are essential for the purpose). E. अ priv. and अवकाश.

anavakaashataa|अनवकाशता
f. (-ता) or अनवकाशत्व n. (-त्वम्) The being irrelevant or unessential. E. अनवकाश, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anavagraha|अनवग्रह
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) Not to be obstructed or impeded, resistless. E. अ priv. and अवग्रह.

anavachChinna|अनवच्छिन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्)<BR> ^1 Not cut, not separated, uninterrupted.<BR> ^2 Unbounded.<BR> ^3 Immoderate, excessive.<BR> ^4 (In Nyáya phil.) Undiscriminated. E. अ neg. and अवच्छिन्न.

anavachChinnahaasa|अनवच्छिन्नहास
Karmadh. m. (-सः) Uninterrupted or excessive laughter. See अतिहास. E. अनवच्छिन्न and हास.

anavatapta|अनवतप्त
Tatpur. m. (-प्तः) (In Buddhist mythology and legends.)<BR> ^1 The name of a serpent-king.<BR> ^2 The name of a renowned lake where the disciples of Śákyamuni held several of their meetings; probably the same as Rávańahrada. E. अ neg. and अवतप्त.

anavat|अनवत्
See the E. of the following.

anavattva|अनवत्त्व
n. (-त्त्वम्) The being endowed with life, the property or quality of what is living. E. अनवत् (endowed with life, breathing, living, from अन III., taddh. aff. मतुप्, but occurring only as the thematic form of this word),  taddh. aff. त्व; used in a vaidik commentary, to explain one meaning of the word असुरत्व.

anavadya|अनवद्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्)<BR> ^1 Blameless, irreproachable.<BR> ^2 Unobjectionable, allowable. <BR>II. f. (-द्या) The proper name of an Apsaras, the daughter of Prádhá.

anavadyaruupa|अनवद्यरूप
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Of faultless form, beautiful. E. अनवद्य and रूप.

anavadyaanga|अनवद्याङ्ग
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गी or ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Of faultless form, beautiful. E. अनवद्य and अङ्ग, fem. ङीष् or टाप्.

anavadhaana|अनवधान
I. Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Inadvertence, inattention, carelessness. See also अनवधानता and अनवहितत्व. E. अ neg. and अवधान. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Inattentive, careless. E. अ priv. and अवधान.

anavadhaanataa|अनवधानता
f. (-ता) Inadvertence, inattention, carelessness. E. अनवधान II., taddh. aff. तल्.

anavadhi|अनवधि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धिः-धिः-धि) Illimited, infinite. E. अ priv. and अवधि.

anavadhRShya|अनवधृष्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) Not to be hurt or overcome, invincible, uninjurable. E. अ neg. and अवधृष्य.

anavana|अनवन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Affording no help or protection. E. अ priv. and अवन.

anavanaamitavaijayanta|अनवनामितवैजयन्त
Bahuvr. m. (-न्तः) The name of a Buddhist future universe; one in which Ánanda is to reappear under the name of Ságaravaradharabuddhivikríd́ita. E. अनवनामित and वैजयन्त, literally: with banners unprostrate i. e. always victorious(?).

anavapRgNa|अनवपृग्ण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्णः-ग्णा-ग्णम्) (ved.) Not mixed, not kept together (an epithet of the lustre of the sun which is not kept together, on a limited space, but shed over the world). E. अ neg. and अवपृग्ण.

anavabrava|अनवब्रव
Bahuvr. m. (-वः) (ved.) One whose words are not thrown away, whose commands are not idle or given in vain, who commands respect. E. अ priv. and अवब्रव.

anavabhra|अनवभ्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-भ्रः-भ्रा-भ्रम्) (ved.) Having suffered no loss or diminution, undiminished. E. अ priv. and अवभ्र. See the following.

anavabhraraadhas|अनवभ्रराधस्
Bahuvr. m. (-धाः) (ved.) With undiminished riches, in the fulness of wealth; esp. in the plural, as an epithet of the Maruts, the riches of which consist, according to the commentators, in the clarified butter &c. they receive in the sacrifice. E. अनवभ्र and राधस्.

anavama|अनवम
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) Not low, high, illustrious. E. अ neg. and अवम.

anavamarsham|अनवमर्शम्
Tatpur. ind. Without touching. E. अ neg. and अवमर्शम्.

anavara|अनवर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Not inferior, not less.<BR> ^2 Excellent, superior. E. अ neg. and अवर.

anavarata|अनवरत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Uninterrupted, continual, eternal.--अनवरतम् used adv., continually, eternally. E. अ neg. and अवरत.

anavaratha|अनवरथ
Bahuvr.(?) m. (-थः) The name of a prince, descendant from Krosht́ŕi, the son of Madhu and father of Kuruvatsa; his grandson is Anuratha. E. अ priv. and अवरथ(?).

anavaraardhya|अनवरार्ध्य
m. f. n. (-र्ध्यः-र्ध्या-र्ध्यम्) Chief, principal, best. E. अ neg. and अवरार्ध (forming a Tatpur.), taddh. aff. यत्. 

anavalamba|अनवलम्ब
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-म्बः-म्बा-म्बम्) Without support, dependance &c.; see अवलम्ब. E. अ priv. and अवलम्ब.

anavalobhana|अनवलोभन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) One of the संस्कार q. v., a purificatory rite observed in the third month after conception. E. अ neg. and अवलोभन.

anavasa|अनवस
Bahuvr. m. (-सः) (ved.) Without food while travelling. (See अवस.) E. अ priv. and अवस.

anavasara|अनवसर
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Want of leisure or opportunity.<BR> ^2 Unseasonableness, inopportuneness. E. अ neg. and अवसर. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Having no leisure, occupied, busy.<BR> ^2 Unseasonable, inopportune. E. अ priv. and अवसर.

anavasaana|अनवसान
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 Without conclusion, endless.<BR> ^2 Free from death. E. अ priv. and अवसान.

anavasita|अनवसित
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not terminated &c. See अवसित. <BR>II. f. (-ता) The name of a metre regulated by number and quantity, a species of the class called Trisht́ubh (q. v.); it consists of a stanza of four lines with the following eleven feet in each line: {??} E. अ neg. and अवसित.

anavaskara|अनवस्कर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Freed from dirt, cleansed. E. अ priv. and अवस्कर.

anavastha|अनवस्थ
I. Tatpur. f. (-स्था)<BR> ^1 An unsettled state, want of fixedness, unsteadiness, uncertainty.<BR> ^2 Incontinence, dissoluteness.<BR> ^3 Indeterminateness, unboundedness; esp. in the Nyáya philosophy: an endless series (of causes and effects), the regressus in infinitum; e. g. in arguing that the lamp is the cause which reveals the existence of a jar, the eye  the cause which reveals that of the lamp, and so on. E. अ neg. and अवस्था. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्)<BR> ^1 Not fixed, not permanent, unstable, not lasting. E. अ priv. and अवस्था.

anavasthaana|अनवस्थान
I. Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Instability, want of fixedness, unsteadiness.<BR> ^2 Incontinence, misconduct. E. अ neg. and अवस्थान. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Unsteady, mutable, variable, not lasting. 2. m. (-नः) Wind. E. अ priv. and अवस्थान.

anavasthaayin|अनवस्थायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Unstable, transitory. E. अ neg. and अवस्थायिन्.

anavasthita|अनवस्थित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unfixed, unstable, unsteady, inconstant, uncertain.<BR> ^2 Loose, abandoned, violating moral and legal restraint. E. अ neg. and अवस्थित.

anavasthitachitta|अनवस्थितचित्त
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Unsteadyminded. E. अनवस्थित and चित्त.

anavasthitataa|अनवस्थितता
f. (-ता) or अनवस्थितत्व n. (-त्वम्). The same as the following. E. अनवस्थित, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anavasthiti|अनवस्थिति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Unsteadiness, instability.<BR> ^2 Misconduct, incontinence, dissoluteness.

anavahita|अनवहित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Inattentive, careless. E. अ neg. and अवहित.

anavahitatva|अनवहितत्व
