anavahvara|अनवह्वर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) (ved.) Not crooked, straight, upright, honest. E. अ neg. and अवह्वर.

anavaach|अनवाच्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्) Not dumb, eloquent. E. अ neg. and अवाच्. 

anavaanc|अनवाञ्च्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ङ्-ची-क्) Not downlooked, looking upwards or in front of. E. अ neg. and अवाञ्च्.

anavaanam|अनवानम्
Tatpur. ind. Without breathing, in one breath, without interruption. E. अ neg. and अवानम् (अन् with अव, kŕit aff. णमुल्).

anavaanataa|अनवानता
f. (-ता) Close contiguity, uninterruptedness. E. अनवान (अनवानम् with elision of the म् of the kŕit aff. णमुल्), taddh. aff. तल्.

anavaapta|अनवाप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) Not obtained, not received. E. अ neg. and अवाप्त.

anavaapti|अनवाप्ति
Tatpur. f. (-प्तिः) Not obtaining, not receiving, not getting. E. अ neg. and अवाप्ति.

anavaayam|अनवायम्
Bahuvr. ind. (ved.) Without interruption, continually. E. अ priv. and अवाय.

anavithya|अनविथ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-थ्यः-थ्या-थ्यम्) Not fit for or suited to a sheep. E. अ neg. and अविथ्य.

anavexa|अनवेक्ष
I. Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) Want of attention, want of regard, regardlessness. E. अ neg. and अवेक्षा. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षा-क्षम्) Taking no regard, regardless.--अनवेक्षम् used also as adv.; without paying attention or taking regard. E. अ priv. and अवेक्षा; अनवेक्षम् may be however also a Tatpur. from अ neg. and अवेक्षम् (ईक्ष् with अव, kŕit aff. णमुल्).

anavrata|अनव्रत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not destitute of meritorious acts of devotion; especially. <BR>II. m. (-तः) A Jaina devotee who only partially conforms to the rules of his order. E. अ neg. and अव्रत.

anashana|अनशन
I. Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A fast, fasting. In law, fasting of a creditor or of a Brahman employed by him to enforce payment of a debt, the debtor incurring the guilt of Brahmanicide, if the person should die of inanition. E. अ neg. and अशन. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) One who fasts. E. अ priv. and अशन.

anashanataa|अनशनता
f. (-ता) Fasting. E. अनशन II., taddh. aff. तल्.

anashanaaya|अनशनाय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not hungry. E. अ priv. and अशनाया.

anashita|अनशित
Tatpur. n. (-तम्) Fasting; esp. in composition with अशित; e. g. अशितेनानशितेन जीवति he lives now eating now fasting. E. अ neg. and अशित.

anashnat|अनश्नत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्नन्-श्नती-श्नत्) Not eating, not enjoying. E. अ neg. and अश्नत्.

anashnantsaangamana|अनश्नन्त्साङ्गमन
Tatpur. m. (-नः) (ved.) The name of the sacrificial fire in the Sabhá, so called because it is approached early in the morning before breakfast. E. अनश्नत् and साङ्गमन ‘the fire approached by those who have not yet eaten any thing’.

anashru|अनश्रु
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-श्रुः-श्रुः-श्रु) Without tears, not shedding tears. E. अ priv. and अश्रु.

anashva|अनश्व
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-श्वः-श्वा-श्वम्) Without a horse or horses. E. अ priv. and अश्व.

anashvadaa|अनश्वदा
Tatpur. m. (-दाः) (ved.) Not giving horses. E. अ neg. and अश्वदा.

anashvan|अनश्वन्
Tatpur.(?) m. (-श्वा) The proper name of a prince, the son of Vidúratha by Sampriyá and father of Paríkshit. E. unknown. 

anashvara|अनश्वर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Imperishable, eternal. E. अ neg. and नश्वर.

anaShTa|अनष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Not lost, not destroyed. E. अ neg. and नष्ट.

anas|अनस्
n. (-नः)<BR> ^1 A cart, esp. one made of wood and tied over with cloth.<BR> ^2 Boiled rice (cf. अन्न and अन्धस्).<BR> ^3 A mother.<BR> ^4 Birth.<BR> ^5 A living being, an animal. (The final स् of this word is changed sometimes to र् or ड्; see अनर्विश्, अनडुह्.-Avyayíbháva compounds, or according to others, also other compounds, the latter part of which is अनस्, assume the samásánta aff. टच्, e. g. उपानसम्, महानस (qq. vv.). E. अन्, uń. aff. असुन्.

anasuuya|अनसूय
I. Tatpur. f. (-या) Want of detractiveness, the not lowering maliciously other's merits, good qualities &c. E. अ neg. and असूया. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Free from detractiveness, not lowering maliciously other's merits, good qualities &c. BREAḲ. f. (-या) A proper name of<BR> ^1 a daughter of Daksha, the wife of Atri (q. v.) and mother of Durvásas,<BR> ^2 a friend of Śakuntalá (in the drama Śak.). E. अ priv. and असूया.

anasuuyaka|अनसूयक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) The same as अनसूय II. 1. E. अनसूय II. 1., samásánta aff. कप्.

anasuuyu|अनसूयु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-युः-युः-यु) Free from detractiveness, not lowering maliciously other's merits, good qualities &c. E. अ neg. and असूयु.

anasuuri|अनसूरि
Tatpur. m. (-रिः) Not unwise, wise, not unintelligent. E. अ neg. and असूरि.

anastamita|अनस्तमित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not set (as the sun).<BR> ^2 Not ceasing, not perishing, imperishable. E. अ neg. and अस्तमित.

anastha|अनस्थ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) (ved.) Boneless. E. अ priv. and अस्थि, samásánta aff. अ(?).

anasthi|अनस्थि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-स्थिः-स्थिः-स्थि) Boneless. (For the declension of this word see अस्थि.) E. अ priv. and अस्थि.

anasthika|अनस्थिक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Boneless. E. अनस्थि, taddh. aff. कप्.

anasthimat|अनस्थिमत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मान्-मती-मत्) Boneless. E. अ neg. and अस्थिमत्.

anasvat|अनस्वत्
m. f. n. (-स्वान्-स्वती-स्वत्) Having a cart, with a cart. E. अनस्, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

anahankaara|अनहङ्कार
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Absence of the sense of self.<BR> ^2 Absence of the pride of individuality, humility. E. अ neg. and अहङ्कार. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Free from the pride of individuality, not proud, humble.

anahankaarin|अनहङ्कारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि). The same as अनहङ्कार II. E. अ neg. and अहङ्कारिन्.

anahankRta|अनहङ्कृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not having the pride of individuality, not proud, humble. E. अ neg. and अहङ्कृत.

anahankRti|अनहङ्कृति
I. Tatpur. f. (-तिः). The same as अनहङ्कार I. E. अ neg. and अहङ्कृति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति). The same as अनहङ्कार II. E. अ priv. and अहङ्कृति.

anahan|अनहन्
Tatpur. n. (-हः) No-day, a bad day, an unlucky day. (For the declension of this word see अहन्.) E. अ deter. and अहन्. 

anaa|अना
ind. (ved.) Certainly, indeed. (A commentator of the Amarakosha considers this particle as a synonyme of the negative न; his opinion rests, however, only on an artificial interpretation of the word अनावृष्टि (q. v.) and is refuted by others who explain it as derived, not from अना and वृष्टि, but from अ neg. and आवृष्टि.) E. unknown; probably an obsolete third case of the pronominal theme अ (q. v.).

anaakaara|अनाकार
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Shapeless, without form. E. अ priv. and आकार.

anaakaarita|अनाकारित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not demanded, not exacted. E. अ neg. and आकारित.

anaakaala|अनाकाल
Tatpur. m. (-लः)<BR> ^1 Unfit or improper time.<BR> ^2 Hard time, as famine &c. See the following word. E. अ neg. and आकाल.

anaakaalabhRta|अनाकालभृत
Tatpur. m. (-तः) (In law.) One of the fifteen kinds of slaves (see दास): a man who has become a slave voluntarily, for the sake of sustenance at a season of famine. (The less correct reading of this word is अन्नाकालभृत.) E. अनाकाल and भृत, scil. दास.

anaakaasha|अनाकाश
I. Tatpur. m. n. (-शः-शम्) No-æther, any thing different from æther or atmosphere. E. अ neg. and आकाश. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Having no æther, destitute of the properties of æther. E. अ priv. and आकाश.

anaakula|अनाकुल
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्)<BR> ^1 Unperplexed, collected, composed.<BR> ^2 Not contradicting one's self, consistent with one's self. E. अ neg. and आकुल.

anaakRta|अनाकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unchecked, unrestrained; (according to the explanation of a vaidik commentator). E. अ neg. and आकृत.

anaakraanta|अनाक्रान्त
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) The reverse of आक्रान्त q. v. <BR>II. f. (-न्ता) A sort of prickly nightshade (Solanum jacquini Wild.). See अग्निदमनी and कण्टकारिका. E. अ neg. and आक्रान्त.

anaaga|अनाग
I. Bahuvr. m. (-गः) (ved.) Without fault or sin. E. an abbreviated form of अनागस्. <BR>II. Tatpur.(?) f. (-गा) The name of a river; (the reading of this word, however, is doubtful). E. uncertain.

anaagata|अनागत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not arrived, not approached.<BR> ^2 Not acquired, not learnt, not obtained.<BR> ^3 Unknown, undistinguished.<BR> ^4 Not yet come, future. <BR>II. n. (-तम्) The future time. E. अ neg. and आगत.

anaagatavat|अनागतवत्
m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Full with future events, much engaged with what will come (as thoughts &c.). E. अनागत, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

anaagatavidhaatR|अनागतविधातृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) One who makes his dispositions for the future, forecasting, cautious. E. अनागत and विधातृ.

anaagataabaadha|अनागताबाध
Karmadh. m. (-धः) Future pain or illness. E. अनागत and आबाध.

anaagataartavaa|अनागतार्तवा
Bahuvr. f. (-वा) A young girl, one not arrived at puberty; according to a commentary, a girl eight years old (the same as गौरी q. v.). E. अनागत and आर्तव.

anaagataavexaNa|अनागतावेक्षण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Looking or referring to what is to come or follows (e. g. in a book &c.). E. अनागत and अवेक्षण. 

anaagama|अनागम
I. Tatpur. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 Non-arrival.<BR> ^2 Non-acquisition. E. अ neg. and आगम. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्)<BR> ^1 Not arrived, not present.<BR> ^2 (In law.) Without legal acquisition, without title deeds, from time immemorial (used of estates, privileges &c.). See also निरागम. E. अ priv. and आगम.

anaagamopabhoga|अनागमोपभोग
Karmadh. m. (-गः) The use or enjoyment of estates &c. without legal acquisition, without title deeds, from time immemorial. See also निरागमोपभोग. E. अनागम and उपभोग.

anaagamya|अनागम्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-म्यः-म्या-म्यम्)<BR> ^1 Unapproachable, inaccessible.<BR> ^2 Unobtainable. E. अ neg. and आगम्य.

anaagas|अनागस्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-गाः-गाः-गः)<BR> ^1 Free from fault or sin, pious, virtuous.<BR> ^2 Removing fault or sin, conferring happiness. E. अ priv. and आगस्. Comp. अनाग.

anaagaamin|अनागामिन्
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि)<BR> ^1 Not arriving, not coming.<BR> ^2 Not future. <BR>II. m. (-मी) The third of the four orders of the Buddhists, generally termed Áryás; (see besides श्रोतआपन्न, सकृदागामिन् and अर्हत्): literally, one who does not return, but it means one who has only to pass through forty thousand kalpas and then is freed from transmigration. E. अ neg. and आगामिन्.

anaagaamuka|अनागामुक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not arriving or coming frequently, not disposed to come habitually. E. अ neg. and आगामुक.

anaagaastva|अनागास्त्व
n. (-त्वम्) (ved.) Exemption from fault or sin, sinlessness. E. अनागस्, taddh. aff. त्व.

anaacharaNa|अनाचरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Improper or immoral conduct. E. अ neg. and आचरण.

anaachaara|अनाचार
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः) Impropriety, misconduct, violation of moral or civil laws. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Ill behaved, indecent. immoral.

anaachaarin|अनाचारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Ill behaved, indecent, immoral. E. अ neg. and आचारिन्.

anaachaaryabhogiina|अनाचार्यभोगीन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not fit to be eaten or enjoyed by a spiritual teacher. E. अ neg. and आचार्यभोगीन.

anaaJNapta|अनाज्ञप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) Not ordered, not commanded. E. अ neg. and आज्ञप्त.

anaaJNaptakaarin|अनाज्ञप्तकारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Doing what is not ordered, acting without order. E. अनाज्ञप्त and कारिन्.

anaaJNaata|अनाज्ञात
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not known, unheard of. (This word may form, as a term of praise, the first part of Karmadh. compounds e. g. अनाज्ञाताध्यापक.) E. अ neg. and आज्ञात.

anaaDhya|अनाढ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ढ्यः-ढ्या-ढ्यम्) Not rich, poor. E. अ neg. and आढ्य.

anaaDhyambhaviShNu|अनाढ्यम्भविष्णु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्णुः-ष्णुः-ष्णु) Not becoming rich or wealthy. E. अ neg. and आढ्यम्भविष्णु.

anaatata|अनातत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not strung (as a bow). (According to a vaidik commentary also: not placed on a bow, as an arrow; this latter meaning, however, seems doubtful.) E. अ neg. and आतत. 

anaatapa|अनातप
Tatpur. m. (-पः)<BR> ^1 Coolness.<BR> ^2 Shade, shadow. E. अ neg. and आतप.

anaatura|अनातुर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Free from sickness or disease, well, vigorous. E. अ neg. and आतुर.

anaatmaka|अनात्मक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Void of substance or reality (as the phenomena of this world, according to the Bauddha doctrine). E. अ priv. and आत्मन्, samásánta aff. कप्.

anaatman|अनात्मन्
I. Tatpur. m. (-त्मा)<BR> ^1 No-soul, other than spirit or soul.<BR> ^2 Not self, other. E. अ neg. and आत्मन्. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्मा-त्मा-त्म) Without spirit or soul. E. अ priv. and आत्मन्.

anaatmaniina|अनात्मनीन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not suitable, not fit for one's self. E. अ neg. and आत्मनीन.

anaatmapratyavexaa|अनात्मप्रत्यवेक्षा
Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) In Buddhist doctrine, one of the 108 धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.): the reflection that there is no soul or self. E. अनात्मन् and प्रत्यवेक्षा.

anaatmavat|अनात्मवत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Not self possessed, without self-control. E. अ neg. and आत्मवत्.

anaatmya|अनात्म्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्म्यः-त्म्या-त्म्यम्) Impersonal (as Brahman. n.). E. अ neg. and आत्म्य.

anaatyantika|अनात्यन्तिक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) Not final, not permanent. E. अ neg. and आत्यन्तिक.

anaatyantikatva|अनात्यन्तिकत्व
n. (-त्वम्) Absence of finality, reoccurrence (e. g. of pains). E. अनात्यन्तिक, taddh. aff. त्व.

anaatha|अनाथ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-थः-था-थम्)<BR> ^1 Without a lord or protector (as an orphan, one without a सपिण्ड (q. v.) &c.), without a master.<BR> ^2 Helpless, poor. E. अ priv. and नाथ.

anaathapiNDada|अनाथपिण्डद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) The name of a celebrated merchant, the owner of the garden Jetavana near Śrávasti, where the Buddha Sákyamuni used to explain his doctrine to his disciples. He was also called अनाथपिण्डिक. E. अनाथ and पिण्ड-द ‘giving food to the poor’.

anaathapiNDika|अनाथपिण्डिक
m. (-कः) The same as the preceding. E. अनाथपिण्डिन्, taddh. aff. कन्.

anaathasabhaa|अनाथसभा
Tatpur. f. (-भा) A poor-house. E. अनाथ and सभा.

anaadara|अनादर
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः) Disrespect, contempt. E. अ neg. and आदर. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) (According to the commentary of an Upanishad.) Not bewildered, not agitated (an epithet of आत्मन् or the soul; but perhaps also: ‘not zealous, not making any effort, calm, quiet’). E. अ priv. and आदर.

anaadaraNa|अनादरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Not having regard, treating with disrespect or contempt. E. अ neg. and आदरण.

anaadarin|अनादरिन्
m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Wanting in respect or regard, disrespectful, disregardful. E. अनादर, taddh. aff. इनि.

anaadi|अनादि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दिः-दिः-दि) Without any beginning, unborn, uncreate, eternal. E. अ priv. and आदि.

anaaditaa|अनादिता
f. (-ता) or अनादित्व n. (-त्वम्) Exemption from commencement, eternity. E. अनादि, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anaadin|अनादिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दी-दिनी-दि) Who or what does not sound. E. अ neg. and नादिन्.

anaadinidhana|अनादिनिधन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Without beginning and termination, eternal. E. अ priv. and आदि-निधन (Dwandwa). 

anaadimat|अनादिमत्
m. f. n. (-मान्-मती-मत्). The same as अनादि. E. अनादि, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

anaadimattva|अनादिमत्त्व
n. (-त्त्वम्) The being without any beginning, the being eternal. E. अनादिमत्, taddh. aff. त्व.

anaadiShTa|अनादिष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Not assigned, not appointed, not fixed.<BR> ^2 Not commanded, not directed.<BR> ^3 Not allowed. E. अ neg. and आदिष्ट.

anaadRta|अनादृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not respected.<BR> ^2 Disrespected, disregarded, despised. E. अ neg. and आदृत.

anaadeya|अनादेय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्)<BR> ^1 Not to be taken or received, unacceptable.<BR> ^2 Not admissible, inadmissible (as a law suit, a plaint). E. अ neg. and आदेय.

anaadya|अनाद्य
m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) I. Tatpur. Not to be eaten, not edible. E. अ neg. and आद्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Without a beginning, unborn, uncreate, eternal. E. अ priv. and आद्य.

anaadyananta|अनाद्यनन्त
Dwandwa m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Without a beginning and end, eternal. E. अनादि and अनन्त.

anaadyanta|अनाद्यन्त
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Without a beginning and end, eternal. <BR>II. m. (-न्तः) A name of Śiva. E. अ priv. and आदिअन्त (Dwandwa).

anaadhRShTa|अनाधृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) (ved.) Not overcome, not vanquished, unconquered. E. अ neg. and आधृष्ट.

anaadhRShTi|अनाधृष्टि
Bahuvr. m. (-ष्टिः)<BR> ^1 The proper name of<BR> ^a. a prince, the son of Śura by Bhojyá, or according to others by Márishá, and brother of Vasudeva; his wife is Aśmakí and his son Ninartaśatru or according to another reading, Nirvŕittiśatru;<BR> ^b. a son of Ugrasena and chief of the Yádavas.<BR> ^2 A name or epithet of Ŕicheyu, the son of Raudráśwa. E. अ priv. and आधृष्टि, ‘suffering no defeat, invincible’.

anaadhRShya|अनाधृष्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) (ved.) Unconquerable, indomitable. E. अ neg. and आधृष्य.

anaanata|अनानत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Not bent, not depressed, unimpaired, superior. <BR>II. m. (-तः) The name of a Ŕishi, the son of Paruchhepa and author of a vaidik hymn. E. अ neg. and आनत.

anaanukRtya|अनानुकृत्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्) (ved.) Not to be done again, unparalleled. E. अ neg. and अनुकृत्य, the first syllable of the latter part of the compound being made long, or perhaps अन neg. and अनुकृत्य.

anaanuda|अनानुद
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दः-दा-दम्) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Having no follower, unaided, alone.<BR> ^2 Unsurpassed in liberality (lit. without any one who could give after, i. e. in a similar manner). Both meanings of this word, as given according to the comm., seem doubtful; it occurs as an epithet of Indra and Brihaspati. E. अ priv. and अनुद, the first syllable of the latter part of the compound being lengthened, or perhaps अन priv. and अनुद.

anaanudiShTa|अनानुदिष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) (ved.) Unasked. E. अ neg. and अनुदिष्ट, the first syllable of the latter part of the compound being made long, or perhaps अन neg. and अनुदिष्ट.

anaanubhuuti|अनानुभूति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः; occurs only in the plur. -तयः) (ved.) Inattentiveness, neglect; esp. personified: those who are neglectful in holy acts or worship (sc. प्रजाः). Cf. अनाभू.  E. अ neg. and अनुभूति, the अ of the latter part of the compound being made long, or perhaps, अन neg. and अनुभूति.

anaapad|अनापद्
Tatpur. f. (-त्) Absence of calamity or misfortune. E. अ neg. and आपद्.

anaapanna|अनापन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) Unobtained, unattained. E. अ neg. and आपन्न.

anaapaana|अनापान
Bahuvr. m. (-नः) The proper name of a prince; according to one authority, the son of Anga, a descendant of Anu. E. अ priv. and आपान.

anaapi|अनापि
Bahuvr. m. (-पिः) (ved.) Without relations, without equals(?); an epithet of Indra. E. अ priv. and आपि, relation (equal?).

anaapuuyita|अनापूयित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not infected with stench or putrefaction. E. अ neg. and आपूयित.

anaapta|अनाप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्)<BR> ^1 Not obtained, not gained.<BR> ^2 Not having obtained, not having attained.<BR> ^3 Unskilful, unapt. E. अ neg. and आप्त.

anaapti|अनाप्ति
Tatpur. f. (-प्तिः) Not obtaining, not attaining. E. अ neg. and आप्ति.

anaapya|अनाप्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्) Not obtainable. E. अ neg. and आप्य.

anaabaadha|अनाबाध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) Without obstruction or vexation, unobstructed, unmolested. See also निराबाध. E. अ priv. and आबाधा.

anaabhayin|अनाभयिन्
Tatpur. m. (-यी) (ved.) Fearless; an epithet of Indra. E. अ neg. and आभयिन्(?).

anaabhuu|अनाभू
Tatpur. m. (-भूः, esp. in the plur. -भुवः) (ved.) One who is neglectful in worship or holy acts. Cf. अनानुभूति. E. अ neg. and आभू.

anaamaka|अनामक
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्)<BR> ^1 Nameless.<BR> ^2 Having a bad name. <BR>II. m. (-कः) An intercalary month. See मलमास. <BR>III. n. (-कम्) Piles or hœmorrhoids. E. अ priv. or deter. and नामन्, samásánta aff. कप्.

anaaman|अनामन्
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-मा-मा-म)<BR> ^1 Nameless.<BR> ^2 Having a bad name. <BR>II. f. (-मा) The ring finger. See अनामिका. E. अ priv. and नामन्, ‘because the head of Brahmá having being cut off with this finger, it has become unworthy of a name’.

anaamaya|अनामय
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्)<BR> ^1 Free from disease or sickness, healthy.<BR> ^2 Not producing disease. <BR>II. m. (-यः) A name of Śiva. <BR>III. n. (-यम्)<BR> ^1 Health.<BR> ^2 A medicament or drug(?). E. अ priv. and आमय.

anaamayat|अनामयत्
Tatpur. n. (-यत्) (ved.) Health. E. अ neg. and आमयत्, lit.: absence of what makes or allows to be sick.

anaamayitnu|अनामयित्नु
m. f. n. (-त्नुः-त्नुः-त्नु) (ved.) Freeing from disease. E. अनामय् (denom. from अनामय), uń. aff. इत्नुच्.

anaamikaa|अनामिका
Bahuvr. f. (-का) The ring finger. See अनामन्. E. अ priv. and नामन्, samásánta aff. कप् (the insertion of इ before the aff. is irregular).

anaamin|अनामिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) (ved.) Unbending. E. अ neg. and नामिन्.

anaamiSha|अनामिष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Without flesh, without enjoyment, bootless, profitless &c. See आमिष. E. अ priv. and आमिष. 

anaamRNa|अनामृण
Bahuvr. m. (-णः) (ved.) Free from foes or such as can do injury; an epithet of Indra. E. अ priv. and आमृण.

anaamRta|अनामृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) No where perishable, everlasting. E. अ neg. and आमृत.

anaayaka|अनायक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Without a leader, without a ruler or chief. E. अ priv. and नायक.

anaayata|अनायत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unchecked, unrestrained.<BR> ^2 Close, continuous, unseparated.<BR> ^3 Unextended, having no length. E. अ neg. and आयत.

anaayatana|अनायतन
I. Tatpur. n. (-नम्) No-altar, no-abode. E. अ neg. and आयतन. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Having no abode, no altar. E. अ priv. and आयतन.

anaayatanavat|अनायतनवत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्)<BR> ^1 Having no abode.<BR> ^2 Having no altar. E. अ neg. and आयतनवत्.

anaayatta|अनायत्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Independent, uncontrolled. E. अ neg. and आयत्त.

anaayattavRtti|अनायत्तवृत्ति
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तिः-त्तिः-त्ति) Having an independent subsistence or livelihood. E. अनायत्त and वृत्ति.

anaayattavRttitaa|अनायत्तवृत्तिता
f. (-ता) Independence, self subsistence. E. अनायत्तवृत्ति, taddh. aff. तल्.

anaayasaagra|अनायसाग्र
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्रः-ग्रा-ग्रम्) Having no iron point (as an arrow). E. अ neg. and आयसाग्र.

anaayaasa|अनायास
I. Tatpur. m. (-सः)<BR> ^1 Exemption from pain or difficulty, facility, ease.<BR> ^2 Absence of exertion, idleness, neglect. E. अ neg. and आयास. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-सः-सा-सम्) Easy, not difficult. E. अ priv. and आयास.

anaayaasakRta|अनायासकृत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Done easily, readily, without effort. <BR>II. n. (-तम्) (In medicine.) An infusion made by simply putting the plant into water without any other preparations and extracting in such a manner its juice or essence; f. i. myrobalan (त्रिफला)--infusions &c. E. अनायास and कृत.

anaayuShaa|अनायुषा
Bahuvr. f. (-षा) A proper name: one of the daughters of Daksha and wives of Káśyapa, the mother of Bala and Vŕitra. See अनायुस्. E. अ priv. and आयुस्, fem. aff. टाप्; (the formation is irregular).

anaayuShya|अनायुष्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्यः-ष्या-ष्यम्) Not giving long life, destructive of life, fatal. E. अ neg. and आयुष्य.

anaayus|अनायुस्
Bahuvr. f. (-युः) A proper name: the same as अनायुषा. E. अ priv. and आयुस्.

anaarata|अनारत
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Continual, eternal. अनारतम् continually, eternally. E. अ priv. and आरत.

anaarabhya|अनारभ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-भ्यः-भ्या-भ्यम्) What cannot or aught not to be begun or attempted. E. अ neg. and आरभ्य.

anaarabhyavaada|अनारभ्यवाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) An injunction (concerning sacrifices or vaidik rites) not connected with the books or chapters which treat authoritatively on sacrifices &c. in the regular order. See आरभ्यवाद and the following. E. अ neg. and आरभ्यवाद.

anaarabhyaadhiita|अनारभ्याधीत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not read in connexion with chapters or books treating authoritatively on vaidik rites or sacrifices; said of passages, esp. in the Bráhmańas, which treat on rites, sacrifices &c. not to be connected with other passages with which they may happen  to be found together, the injunctions of the latter not being applicable to those of the former. A ceremonial, for instance, taught in an anárabhyádhíta, would not be considered as the essential part of another ceremonial, treated in passages, called árabhyádhíta, which may precede or follow it, nor share in the general rules concerning these; and it is, therefore, always the object of special rules which define its position amongst the other parts of the ritual and its applicability. E. अ neg. and आरभ्याधीत.

anaarambaNa|अनारम्बण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) (ved.) Without support, unsupported. See अनालम्बन. E. अ priv. and आरम्बण.

anaarambha|अनारम्भ
I. Tatpur. m. (-म्भः) Non-commencement, not attempting or undertaking. E. अ neg. and आरम्भ. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-म्भः-म्भा-म्भम्) Without beginning or commencement. E. अ priv. and आरम्भ.

anaarambhaNa|अनारम्भण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) (ved. according to the comm.) Without support, unsupported (see अनालम्बन); but it may mean also: without a point of touch, not palpable, as æther, darkness. E. अ priv. and आरम्भण.

anaarogya|अनारोग्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-ग्यः-ग्या-ग्यम्) Unhealthy, not salubrious, unwholesome. <BR>II. n. (-ग्यम्) Want of health, sickness. E. अ neg. and आरोग्य.

anaarogyakara|अनारोग्यकर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Causing sickness, unwholesome. E. अनारोग्य and कर, fem. ङीप्.

anaarjava|अनार्जव
Tatpur. n. (-वम्)<BR> ^1 Crookedness, moral or physical.<BR> ^2 Disease. E. अ neg. and आर्जव.

anaartava|अनार्तव
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वः-वी-वम्) Not seasonable, as plants &c. E. अ neg. and आर्तव.

anaartvijiina|अनार्त्विजीन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not fit for a priest, not fit to be a priest. E. अ neg. and आर्त्विजीन.

anaarya|अनार्य
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Not respectable, not venerable, unworthy, inferior, bad, vile. BREAḲ. m. (-र्यः) Other than an Árya, a barbarian, a Súdra, a Mlechchha, a Kiráta &c. E. अ neg. and आर्य. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Having no Áryas, inhabited by Mlechchhas &c. as a country. E. अ priv. and आर्य.

anaaryaka|अनार्यक
Bahuvr. n. (-कम्) Agallochum or aloe wood (Aquila agallocha). See also अनार्यज. E. अनार्य II., samásánta aff. कप्.

anaaryakarmin|अनार्यकर्मिन्
m. (-र्मी) One doing the work of a Súdra or a non-Árya. E. अनार्य-कर्म, taddh. aff. इनि.

anaaryaja|अनार्यज
Tatpur. n. (-जम्). The same as अनार्यक q. v. E. अनार्य and ज ‘produced in the country of the Mlechchhas or barbarians’.

anaaryataa|अनार्यता
f. (-ता) or अनार्यत्व n. (-त्वम्) Vileness, unworthiness, baseness. E. अनार्य, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anaayatikta|अनायतिक्त
Tatpur. m. (-क्तः) A medicinal plant, a kind of gentian (Gentiana cherayta, Rox.) See also किराततिक्त. E. अनार्य I. 2. and तिक्त.

anaarSha|अनार्ष
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्षः-र्षी-र्षम्)<BR> ^1 Not relating or belonging to a Ŕishi (to his name &c.).<BR> ^2 Not relating to the vaidik hymns (considered as the inspirations of the Ŕishis). E. अ neg. and आर्ष. 

anaarSheya|अनार्षेय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-यी-यम्) Not relating or belonging to a Ŕishi. E. अ neg. and आर्षेय.

anaalamba|अनालम्ब
I. Tatpur. m. (-म्बः)<BR> ^1 Want of support.<BR> ^2 Despondency, heart-brokenness. E. अ neg. and आलम्ब. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-म्बः-म्बा-म्बम्) Without support or stay, unsupported. E. अ priv. and आलम्ब.

anaalambana|अनालम्बन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 Without stay or support, unsupported.<BR> ^2 Despondent, heart-broken. E. अ priv. and आलम्बन.

anaalambanataa|अनालम्बनता
f. (-ता)<BR> ^1 Unsupportedness.<BR> ^2 Despondency, heart-brokenness. E. अनालम्बन, taddh. aff. तल्.

anaalambii|अनालम्बी
Tatpur. f. (-म्बी) The Víńá or lute of Śiva. E. अ neg. and आलम्बी.

anaalambukaa|अनालम्बुका
Tatpur. f. (-का). See the following.

anaalambhukaa|अनालम्भुका
Tatpur. f. (-का) A woman during menstruation. This word occurs only in ritual works and is sometimes, though less correctly written अनालम्बुका. E. अ neg. and आलम्भुका.

anaalaapa|अनालाप
I. Tatpur. m. (-पः) Taciturnity, silence. E. अ neg. and आलाप. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्) Silent, taciturn. E. अ priv. and आलाप.

anaalochita|अनालोचित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unseen, unbeheld.<BR> ^2 Unweighed, unconsidered, rash, imprudent. E. अ neg. and आलोचित.

anaaviddha|अनाविद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Not pierced, not wounded, not hurt. E. अ neg. and आविद्ध.

anaavila|अनाविल
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Clear, clean, pure. E. अ neg. and आविल.

anaavRta|अनावृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Uncovered, unhidden.<BR> ^2 Open, uninclosed (as a field &c.). E. अ neg. and आवृत.

anaavRtta|अनावृत्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्)<BR> ^1 Not turned round.<BR> ^2 Not retreating.<BR> ^3 Not approached, not visited. E. अ neg. and आवृत्त.

anaavRtti|अनावृत्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Not-returning, literally and metaphorically (as after death into this world). E. अ neg. and आवृत्ति.

anaavRShTi|अनावृष्टि
Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) Drought. E. अ neg. and आ-वृष्टि (explained with समन्ताद्वृष्टि). See also under अना.

anaavedita|अनावेदित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not made known, not announced. E. अ neg. and आवेदित.

anaasha|अनाश
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) I. Without hope, hopeless. E. अ priv. and आशा. <BR>II. Not dead, living. E. अ priv. and नाश. The latter meaning is artificial.

anaashaka|अनाशक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) Fasting. E. अ neg. and आशक.

anaashakanivRtta|अनाशकनिवृत्त
Tatpur. m. (-त्तः) One who desists from fasting (as a Sannyásin who returns to his home &c.). E. अनाशक and निवृत्त.

anaashakaayana|अनाशकायन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The penitence of fasting. E. अनाशक and अयन.

anaashasta|अनाशस्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) Not excellent, not praiseworthy; (according to a vaidik commentary). E. अ neg. and आशस्त.

anaashin|अनाशिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शी-शिनी-शि) Not perishing, not being lost. E. अ neg. and नाशिन्. 

anaashu|अनाशु
m. f. n. (-शुः-शुः-शु) I. Tatpur. Not quick, slow. E. अ neg. and आशु. <BR>II. Bahuvr. (ved.) Without destruction, indestructible, unchecked (as horses going extremely fast). This meaning seems doubtful. E. अ priv. and नाशु(?).

anaashya|अनाश्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) Indestructible. E. अ neg. and नाश्य.

anaashramavaasa|अनाश्रमवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः). See अनाश्रमेवास. E. अ neg. and आश्रमवास.

anaashramin|अनाश्रमिन्
Tatpur. m. (-मी) One not belonging to one of the áśramas (q. v.) or religious orders. E. अ neg. and आश्रमिन्.

anaashramevaasa|अनाश्रमेवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) Not staying in or belonging to one of the áśramas (q. v.) or religious orders. E. अ neg. and आश्रमवास.

anaashraya|अनाश्रय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Without an asylum or refuge, unprotected. E. अ priv. and आश्रय.

anaashrita|अनाश्रित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not connected with, not resorting to, esp. not belonging to one of the áśramas (q. v.) or religious orders.<BR> ^2 (In philosophy.) Not inherent in, not requiring any thing else, self-dependent, absolute; as in the Sánkhya philosophy, pradhána or matter, which is complete or absolute in itself, unlike the produced principles mahat, ahamkára &c., which are आश्रित relative or resorting to one another. E. अ neg. and आश्रित.

anaashvas|अनाश्वस्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्वान्-शुषी-श्वः) Not having eaten, fasting. E. अ neg. and आश्वस् (from अश् to eat).

anaaShTra|अनाष्ट्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्ट्रः-ष्ट्रा-ष्ट्रम्) (ved.) Free from enemies, free from mischievous beings. E. अ priv. and नाष्ट्र.

anaasika|अनासिक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Noseless. E. अ priv. and नासिका.

anaasthaa|अनास्था
Tatpur. f. (-स्था)<BR> ^1 Want of fixity or condition.<BR> ^2 Disregard, want of consideration. E. अ neg. and आस्था.

anaasthaana|अनास्थान
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Without a fixed site, without a basis or foundation. E. अ priv. and आस्थान.

anaahata|अनाहत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unhurt, unbeaten, unwounded.<BR> ^2 Unwashed, new (as cloth).<BR> ^3 (In music.) Not beat or struck, not produced in the ordinary way (as a sound). See अनाहतनाद. <BR>II. n. (-तम्)<BR> ^1 A new garment (see आहत).<BR> ^2 The fourth of the six mystical Chakras or circles of the body. E. अ neg. and आहत.

anaahatanaada|अनाहतनाद
Karmadh. m. (-तः) A sound not produced in the ordinary manner; the mysterious sound (om) which is heard in consequence of religious meditation and which is said ‘not to give pleasure, but eternal bliss’; unlike the आहतनाद (q. v.) or the real musical sound. E. अनाहत and नाद.

anaahaara|अनाहार
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Abstinence, starvation.<BR> ^2 Nonseizure. E. अ neg. and आहार. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not taking food. E. अ priv. and आहार.

anaahitaagni|अनाहिताग्नि
Tatpur. m. (-ग्निः) A householder who has not performed the ceremony of the अग्न्याधान q. v. E. अ neg. and आहिताग्नि.

anaahitaagnitaa|अनाहिताग्निता
f. (-ता) or अनाहिताग्नित्व n. (-त्वम्) The condition of an अनाहिताग्नि q. v. E. The preceding, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व. 

anaahuti|अनाहुति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Not-sacrificing.<BR> ^2 A bad or improper sacrificing. E. अ neg. or deter. and आहुति.

anaahuuta|अनाहूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Uncalled, unbidden. E. अ neg. and आहूत.

aniketa|अनिकेत
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Without a house. E. अ priv. and निकेत.

aniketana|अनिकेतन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Without a house. E. अ priv. and निकेतन.

anixiptadhuura|अनिक्षिप्तधूर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The proper name of a Bodhisattva or Bauddha deified saint. E. अ neg. and निक्षिप्तधूर(?).

anixu|अनिक्षु
Tatpur. m. (-क्षुः) A sort of long grass or reed (Saccharum spontaneum). E. अ comp. and इक्षु sugar-cane. Cf. इक्षुतुल्या.

anigiirNa|अनिगीर्ण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्)<BR> ^1 Not swallowed.<BR> ^2 (In rhetoric.) Not to be supplied, not being the object of an ellipsis. E. अ neg. and निगीर्ण.

anigraha|अनिग्रह
I. Tatpur. m. (-हः)<BR> ^1 Want of restraint &c. See निग्रह.<BR> ^2 (In Nyáya phil.) No-failure in argument, not perceiving one's self having failed in argument. E. अ neg. and निग्रह. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) Unrestrained, unconfined. E. अ priv. and निग्रह.

anigrahasthaana|अनिग्रहस्थान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) (In Nyáya phil.) No-failure in argument. E. अ neg. and निग्रहस्थान.

anighaateShu|अनिघातेषु
Bahuvr. m. (-षुः) Probably a proper name or surname implying blame; lit. one whose arrows do no harm. E. अ priv. and निघात-इषु.

anichi|अनिचि
See आनिचेय.

anichCha|अनिच्छ
I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-च्छः-च्छा-च्छम्) Undesirous, indifferent, disliking. E. अ priv. and इच्छा. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-च्छा) Absence of wish or desire, indifference, dislike. E. अ neg. and इच्छा.

anitya|अनित्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्)<BR> ^1 Transient, not everlasting (as the body, or in the Sánkhya philosophy the discrete principles mahat, ahankára &c. or in the Nyáya the sound &c.<BR> ^2 Occasional, not peremptory, not obligatory as a rule &c. (see also काम्य; as in the Jyotisht́oma the six samsthás: अत्यग्निष्टोम, उक्थ्य, षोडशिन्, अतिरात्र, अप्तोर्याम and वाजपेय &c.).<BR> ^3 Not necessary, not immutable. See अनित्यसमास.<BR> ^4 Unstable, inconstant.<BR> ^5 Unusual, irregular. (अनित्यम् not always.) E. अ neg. and नित्य.

anityakarman|अनित्यकर्मन्
Karmadh. n. (-र्म) An act of worship which is not peremptory, but voluntary and occasional. See काम्यकर्मन्. E. अनित्य and कर्मन्.

anityakriyaa|अनित्यक्रिया
Karmadh. f. (-या). The same as the preceding. E. अनित्य and क्रिया.

anityataa|अनित्यता
f. (-ता) or अनित्यत्व n. (-त्वम्)<BR> ^1 Impermanence, transient existence.<BR> ^2 The being occasional, not peremptory.<BR> ^3 The being not necessary.<BR> ^4 Unstableness, inconstance.<BR> ^5 Unusual occurrence. See the meanings of अनित्य. E. अनित्य. taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anityadatta|अनित्यदत्त
Tatpur. m. (-त्तः) (In law.) A son given away by his natural parents temporarily or for a term. The adoption of such a son is performed without the homas or burnt offerings required at the adoption of a nityadatta (q. v.). Also अनित्यदत्तक and अनित्यदत्रिम. E. अनित्य and दत्त, temporarily given, scil. पुत्र.

anityadattaka|अनित्यदत्तक
m. (-कः) (In law.) The same as अनित्यदत्त q. v. E. The preceding, taddh. aff. कन्. 

anityadatrima|अनित्यदत्रिम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) (In law.) The same as अनित्यदत्त q. v. E. अनित्य and दत्रिम.

anityapratyavexaa|अनित्यप्रत्यवेक्षा
Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) In Buddhist doctrine, one of the 108 धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.): the reflection that (every thing) is transitory. E. अनित्य and प्रत्यवेक्षा.

anityabhaava|अनित्यभाव
Tatpur. m. (-वः) The state or condition of what is transient or perishable, perishableness. E. अनित्य (in the sense of the genitive) and भाव.

anityasama|अनित्यसम
Tatpur. m. f. (-मः-मा) (In the Nyáya philosophy.) Wrongly generalizing the predicament of perishableness i. e. a sophism on perishableness; viz. arguing perishableness from the reason that every thing is perishable because it shares in some qualities with other things which are perishable. E. अनित्य and सम (in the sense of जाति, sophism); the masc. form of this word is explained according to some, by the ellipsis of प्रतिषेध or contradiction, as a Sútra in the Nyáya treating on a sophism is always followed by another containing the refutation; or, according to others, by the ellipsis of विकल्प (in the sense of विविधः कल्पः i. e. प्रकारः or variousness), there being various sophisms, viz. twenty-four; or according to others, by the ellipsis of प्रयोग i. e. a (logical) proceeding which likens or produces the plausibility of perishableness; or the word is taken as a Bahuvr. with the ellipsis of प्रयोग i. e. a logical proceeding in which perishableness is likened (viz. made plausible).-As a feminine, ºसमा is taken in the sense of जाति, sophism.

anityasamaprakaraNa|अनित्यसमप्रकरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) The chapter in the Nyáya philosophy which treats on the sophism अनित्यसम q. v. E. अनित्यसम and प्रकरण.

anityasamaasa|अनित्यसमास
Karmadh. m. (-सः) (In grammar.) A compound which may be dissolved into its constituent parts without undergoing a material change of sense; e. g. राजपुरुषः, which may be dissolved into राज्ञः पुरुषः. The converse of नित्यसमास q. v.

anidra|अनिद्र
I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्रः-द्रा-द्रम्) Sleepless, awake. E. अ priv. and निद्रा. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-द्रा) Want of sleep. E. अ neg. and निद्रा.

anidhi|अनिधि
Bahuvr. See आनिधेय.

anidhRShTa|अनिधृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Not defeated, not overcome. Cf. अनिभृष्ट. E. अ neg. and निधृष्ट.

anidhma|अनिध्म
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ध्मः-ध्मा-ध्मम्) Without fuel. E. अ priv. and इध्म.

anina|अनिन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Without a master, independent. E. अ priv. and इन.

anindita|अनिन्दित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Irreproachable, blameless, virtuous, good. E. अ neg. and निन्दित.

anindya|अनिन्द्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्द्यः-न्द्या-न्द्यम्) Irreproachable, blameless. E. अ neg. and निन्द्य.

anindra|अनिन्द्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-न्द्रः-न्द्रा-न्द्रम्)<BR> ^1 Deprived of Indra.<BR> ^2 (ved.) Not paying regard to Indra, not holding Indra in esteem. E. अ priv. and इन्द्र.

anindriya|अनिन्द्रिय
Tatpur. n. (-यम्). The same as अन्तःकरण q. v. E. अ neg. and इन्द्रिय, ‘no-indriya (q. v.), different from the indriyas’.

anipadyamaana|अनिपद्यमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not falling down, not dejected, untiring. (ved.) E. अ neg. and निपद्यमान.

anipaata|अनिपात
Tatpur. m. (-तः) Not dying, remaining alive. E. अ neg. and निपात. 

anipuNa|अनिपुण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Unskilled, unlearned, not conversant. Comp. आनैपुण्य. E. अ neg. and निपुण.

anibaddha|अनिबद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Not attached, not bound, not connected, incoherent. E. अ neg. and निबद्ध.

anibaddhapralaapin|अनिबद्धप्रलापिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पी-पिनी-पि) Talking incoherently, talking without regard to the subject in question. E. अनिबद्ध and प्रलापिन्.

anibaadha|अनिबाध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) Unconfined, unrestricted, extended. E. अ priv. and निबाध.

anibhRta|अनिभृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not modest, bold.<BR> ^2 Not lonely, not private. E. अ neg. and निभृत.

anibhRShTa|अनिभृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) (ved.) Not defeated, not overcome, unhurt. E. अ neg. and निभृष्ट.

anibhRShTataviShi|अनिभृष्टतविषि
Bahuvr. m. (-षिः) (ved.) Of unhurt power, of unabated strength. E. अनिभृष्ट and तविषी.

anibhya|अनिभ्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-भ्यः-भ्या-भ्यम्) Not wealthy, not opulent. E. अ neg. and इभ्य.

animantrita|अनिमन्त्रित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Uninvited, uncalled. E. अ neg. and निमन्त्रित.

animantritabhojin|अनिमन्त्रितभोजिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जी-जिनी-जि) Eating without having being invited. E. अनिमन्त्रित and भोजिन्.

animaana|अनिमान
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Measureless, immense, boundless. E. अ priv. and निमान.

animitta|अनिमित्त
I. Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्) No cause, want of cause. E. अ neg. and निमित्त. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Having no cause or motive. (अनिमित्तम् from no cause, without a cause.) E. अ priv. and निमित्त.

animittatas|अनिमित्ततस्
ind. From no cause, without a cause. E. अनिमित्त (Tatpur.), taddh. aff. तसिल्.

animittalinganaasha|अनिमित्तलिङ्गनाश
Karmadh. m. (-शः) (In medicine.) A disease of the pupil of the eye, when the whole crystalline lens is affected; it is described as being produced ‘by the sight of the divine Ŕishis, the Gandharvas, the great Serpents and luminous bodies’ and causing the entire loss of vision. See also लिङ्गनाश and सनिमित्तलिङ्गनाश. E. अनिमित्त and लिङ्गनाश.

animiSh|अनिमिष्
Tatpur. f. (only in the acc. -षम् and instrum. -षा) (ved.)<BR> ^1 The not twinkling.<BR> ^2 Attentiveness, watchfulness.<BR> ^3 Uninterruptedness. अनिमिषम् and अनिमिषा<BR> ^1 Attentively, watchfully.<BR> ^2 Uninterruptedly, continually. E. अ neg. and निमिष्.

animiSha|अनिमिष
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्)<BR> ^1 Not twinkling, having the eyes fixed.<BR> ^2 Attentive, watchful. <BR>II. m. (-षः)<BR> ^1 A god.<BR> ^2 A fish. See also अनिमेष. E. अ priv. and निमिष. <BR>III. Tatpur. m. (-षः). The same as अनिमिष्. E. अ neg. and निमिष्.

animiSham|अनिमिषम्
Tatpur. (ved.) See अनिमिष् and अनिमेषम्.

animiShaa|अनिमिषा
Tatpur. (ved.) See अनिमिष्.

animiShaaxa|अनिमिषाक्ष
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-क्षः-क्षी-क्षम्) One whose eyes are fixed (as in disease). E. अनिमिष and अक्षि, samásánta aff. षच्.

animiShaachaarya|अनिमिषाचार्य
Tatpur. m. (-र्यः) A name of Vŕihaspati. E. अनिमिष and आचार्य, ‘the preceptor of the gods’.

animiShiiya|अनिमिषीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Relating to the gods. E. अनिमिष, taddh. aff. छ. [Pagetittle-I+ 21]

animeSha|अनिमेष
I. Tatpur. m. (-षः) The not-twinkling. E. अ neg. and निमेष. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-षः-षा-षम्) Not twinkling. BREAḲ. m. (-षः)<BR> ^1 A god.<BR> ^2 A fish. E. अ priv. and निमेष.

animeSham|अनिमेषम्
Tatpur. ind. (ved.)<BR> ^1 Without twinkling.<BR> ^2 Attentively, watchfully, without interruption. See also अनिमिषम्. E. अ and निमेषम् (from मिष् with नि, kŕit aff. णमुल्).

aniyata|अनियत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not restrained, not fastened.<BR> ^2 Not necessarily connected.<BR> ^3 Not inevitable, not certain, not always occurring.<BR> ^4 Not positive, not definite, undefined, undetermined. (The अनियता धर्माः or ‘undetermined rules’ of the Buddhists, are the topic of one of the chapters of their Phátimokkha, and treat on transgressions that involve exclusion, suspension and penance, but not permanent exclusion, of a Bauddha priest.) E. अ neg. and नियत.

aniyatapuMskaa|अनियतपुंस्का
Tatpur. f. (-स्का) An unsteady or unchaste woman. E. अ neg. and नियत-पुम् (Bahuvr. samásánta aff. कप्).

aniyatavRtti|अनियतवृत्ति
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तिः-त्तिः-त्ति) One who has no fixed profession or livelihood. E. अ neg. and नियत-वृत्ति.

aniyataanka|अनियताङ्क
Karmadh. m. (-ङ्कः) (In Arithmetic.) An indeterminate digit. E. अनियत and अङ्क.

aniyataatman|अनियतात्मन्
Tatpur. m. (-त्मा) Not exercising self-control, not subduing one's mind. E. अ neg. and नियत-आत्मन्.

aniyama|अनियम
1. Tatpur. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 Absence of a restriction or fixed rule.<BR> ^2 Absence of moral or religious obligation.<BR> ^3 Indecorous or improper conduct. E. अ neg. and नियम. BREAḲ. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) Without restriction, undertermined, undefined, unprovided for, by any rule or law. E. अ priv. and नियम.

aniyukta|अनियुक्त
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Not authorised, not called, not appointed &c. See नियुक्त. BREAḲ. m. (-क्तः) (In Law.) A Bráhmańa who attends a court without having been appointed a member of it, whose vote is therefore not binding, and who is at liberty to attend the court meetings and to debate in them, or not. (See, on the contrary, सभासद्.)

anira|अनिर
(ved.) I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Without food, without an offering (of clarified butter). E. अ priv. and इरा. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-रा) Want of food, famine, calamity, distress. E. अ neg. and इरा.

aniraakariShNu|अनिराकरिष्णु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्णुः-ष्णुः-ष्णु)<BR> ^1 Not disposed to or in the habit of throwing obstacles in the way, of being obstructive.<BR> ^2 Not in the habit of disdaining, of dispising. E. अ neg. and निराकरिष्णु.

aniraakRta|अनिराकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unchecked, unobstructed. E. अ neg. and निराकृत.

anirukta|अनिरुक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्)<BR> ^1 Not spoken out, not declared.<BR> ^2 Not explained, not defined (e. g. the divinity, if spoken of in general terms, or Brahma (n.) that is without qualities, or an invocation, not containing the special name of the god addressed, one addressed to the gods in general &c.).<BR> ^3 Obscure, incomprehensible, literally and metaphorically; e. g. Prajápati, Brahman (n.) or a hymn uttered inaudibly, so as not being comprehensible to the by-standers. E. अ neg. and निरुक्त. 

aniruktagaana|अनिरुक्तगान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) One of the modes of chanting the hymns of the Sámaveda. See गान. E. अनिरुक्त and गान.

aniruddha|अनिरुद्ध
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्)<BR> ^1 Unobstructed, unrestrained.<BR> ^2 Self-willed, ungovernable, headstrong.<BR> ^3 Moveable, unsteady(?). BREAḲ. m. (-द्धः)<BR> ^1 The name of the son of Pradyumna or Kámadeva by Śubhángí or, according to others, Kakudwatí, the daughter of Rukmin; his wife is Ushá, the daughter of Vána, or, according to others, Subhadrá, the granddaughter of Rukmin, and his son Vajra.--The Vaishńava sect, called Páncharátra or Bhágavatas, consider him as an incarnation or part of Vishńu and identify him with Ahankára, self-consciousness.--^2 A name of Śiva.<BR> ^3 The name of a celebrated Bauddha Arhat and contemporary of Śákyamuni.<BR> ^4 The name of a member of the Vŕishńi tribe, the descendants of Vŕishńi. See also आनिरुद्ध and आनिरुद्धायनि.<BR> ^5 A spy(?). <BR>3. n. (-द्धम्) A rope for fastening cattle. E. अ neg. and निरुद्ध. (It is doubtful whether the meaning 1. 3. (moveable) or the meaning 2. 4. (spy) is the correct one, the translation being founded on the word चर, given as one of the meanings of अनिरुद्ध, but without any further indication as to the gender. From the place, however, चर occupies in the explanation of some of the native dictionaries, the meaning ‘spy’ is likely to be preferable to the meaning ‘moveable’.)

aniruddhapatha|अनिरुद्धपथ
Bahuvr. n. (-थम्) Atmosphere, æther. E. अनिरुद्ध and पथिन्, samásánta aff. अ; lit. having an unobstructed path.

aniruddhabhaavinii|अनिरुद्धभाविनी
Tatpur. f. (-नी) The wife of Aniruddha, Ushá (q. v.). E. अनिरुद्ध and भाविनी.

anirjita|अनिर्जित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unsubdued, unconquered. E. अ neg. and निर्जित.

anirNaya|अनिर्णय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) Uncertainty. E. अ neg. and निर्णय.

anirNiita|अनिर्णीत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unascertained, undetermined. E. अ neg. and निर्णीत.

anirdasha|अनिर्दश
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Not out of, i. e. within, the ten days of impurity which follow after a case of birth or death. अनिर्दशम् also used adverbially. See the following. E. अ neg. and निर्दश; scil. अहन्.

anirdashaaha|अनिर्दशाह
