anirdesha|अनिर्देश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 Absence of rule or direction.<BR> ^2 A bad or imperfect direction, a rule not conveying exactly the bearing or sense it is intended to have. E. अ neg. or deter. and निर्देश.

anirdhaarita|अनिर्धारित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unascertained, undetermined, undefined. E. अ neg. and निर्धारित.

anirmala|अनिर्मल
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्) Unclean, dirty. E. अ neg. and निर्मल.

anirmaalyaa|अनिर्माल्या
Tatpur. f. (-ल्या) A plant (Trigonella corniculata or Medicago esculenta, Rox.). Also निर्माल्या, लङ्क, पिका, पृक्का, पिशुना, and ranging amongst the महौषध. E. अ neg. and निर्माल्य, according to a commentary ‘because no garland can be made of it’. 

anirlochita|अनिर्लोचित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not considered, not reflected. E. अ neg. and निर्लोचित.

anirvachaniiya|अनिर्वचनीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Not explainable, indescribable. E. अ neg. and निर्वचनीय.

anirvaachya|अनिर्वाच्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-च्यः-च्या-च्यम्) Not explainable, indescribable. E. अ neg. and निर्वाच्य.

anirvaaha|अनिर्वाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः)<BR> ^1 Want of completion.<BR> ^2 Want of logical connexion (in a sentence &c.).<BR> ^3 Want of means of subsistence. E. अ neg. and निर्वाह.

anirvRta|अनिर्वृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unaccomplished, unterminated.<BR> ^2 Unhappy, discontented, ill at ease. E. अ neg. and निर्वृत.

anirvRti|अनिर्वृति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Incompleteness, want of completion.<BR> ^2 Discontent, unhappiness.<BR> ^3 Poverty. E. अ neg. and निर्वृति.

anirveda|अनिर्वेद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) Undauntedness, hopefulness, selfconfidence. E. अ neg. and निर्वेद.

anila|अनिल
m. (-लः)<BR> ^1 Wind, viz.<BR> ^a. (in its usual acceptation) the motion of air;<BR> ^b. the deity of wind;<BR> ^c. one of the eight Maruts, and in this sense distinct from मारुत, वायु &c. (see मरुत्);<BR> ^d. one of the eight Vasus (see वसु);<BR> ^e. (in the plural अनिलाः) a class of the Gańadevatás, comprising forty-nine Anilas;<BR> ^f. (in medicine) one of the three Rasas or temperamental elements of the body (see रस), subdivided into प्राण, उदान, समान, व्यान and अपान; in this sense used synonymously with मारुत, वात, वायु, समीरण and other words meaning wind;<BR> ^g. (in the terminology of the Upanishads) the exterior wind or the surrounding air, in distinction from वायु or प्राण, the vital air of the body.<BR> ^2 A proper name of<BR> ^a. a son of Tansu and father of Dushwanta;<BR> ^b. a Rákshasa;<BR> ^c. a Ŕishi, author of a vaidik hymn;<BR> ^d. (in the mythology of the Jainas) the seventeenth Arhat of the past Utsarpińí.<BR> ^3 (In arithmetic, sometimes used to denote) the numeral 49 (there being forty-nine Anilas).<BR> ^4 A mystic denomination of the letter य. E. अन्, uń. aff. इलच्.

anilakumaara|अनिलकुमार
Tatpur. m. pl. (-राः) (In the mythology of the Jainas.) One of the ten kinds of Bhavanapatis (q. v.) or Bhavanádhíśas (q. v.), the first of the four classes of Jaina divinities. E. अनिल and कुमार.

anilaghna|अनिलघ्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-घ्नः-घ्नी-घ्नम्) Removing disorders from wind (see अनिल 1. f.), as a medicine &c. Also वातघ्न, वायुघ्न &c. E. अनिल and घ्न.

anilaghnaka|अनिलघ्नक
m. (-कः) A large tree (Terminalia belerica). See also विभीतक. E. अनिलघ्न, taddh. aff. कन्.

anilaparyaaya|अनिलपर्याय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) (In Medicine.) An inflammation affecting the whole eye, described as produced from the vitiated Rasa wind (see अनिल 1. f.) ‘which pervades the eyelids, eye and eyebrows and makes them diseased one after the other’. The less correct reading of this word is अनिलपयय. See also मारुतपर्याय and वातपर्याय. E. अनिल and पर्याय.

anilaprakRti|अनिलप्रकृति
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-तिः-तिः-ति) Of airy or windy nature; an epithet of the planet Saturn. E. अनिल and प्रकृति.

anilambhasamaadhi|अनिलम्भसमाधि
Karmadh. f. (-धिः) A fanciful name of a Buddhistic samádhi or profound meditation. E. अनिलम्भ and समाधि, meaning perhaps ‘a meditation that sur passes all impediments or limits, one which nothing can resist’.

anilayana|अनिलयन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) No-resting place, no-support (an epithet of the neuter Brahman, in an Upanishad, because it is devoid of qualities, impersonal &c.). E. अ neg. and निलयन.

anilavyaadhi|अनिलव्याधि
Tatpur. f. (-धिः) (In Medicine.) Derangement of the Rasa wind (see अनिल 1. f.), produced, according to the native theory, by the continued use of dry, cold or light articles of food, taken in unusually small quantities &c. and causing, according to some authorities, eighty varieties of nervous diseases. See also अनिलामय and वातव्याधि. E. अनिल and व्याधि.

anilasakha|अनिलसख
Tatpur. m. (-खः) A name of Fire. Cf. अग्निसख. E. अनिल and सखि, samásánta aff. टच्, ‘the friend of Wind’.

anilahan|अनिलहन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-हा-घ्नी-ह) The same as अनिलघ्न q. v. E. अनिल and हन्.

anilahRt|अनिलहृत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्-त्-त्) The same as अनिलघ्न q. v. E. अनिल and हृत्.

anilaatmaja|अनिलात्मज
Tatpur. m. (-जः)<BR> ^1 A name of Hanumat.<BR> ^2 A name of Bhíma. See also वायुपुत्र and similar synonymes. E. अनिल and आत्मज.

anilaantaka|अनिलान्तक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) The name of a plant. See इङ्गुदी or अङ्गारपुष्प. E. अनिल and अन्तक, in the same sense as अनिलघ्न.

anilaapaha|अनिलापह
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) The same as अनिलघ्न q. v. E. अनिल and अपह.

anilaamaya|अनिलामय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) The same as अनिलव्याधि q. v. E. अनिल and आमय.

anilaashin|अनिलाशिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शी-शिनी-शि) Feeding on the wind, fasting. E. अनिल and आशिन्.

anivartitva|अनिवर्तित्व
n. (-त्वम्)<BR> ^1 The not returning.<BR> ^2 The not turning back, not running away, not flying. E. अनिवर्तिन्, taddh. aff. त्व.

anivartin|अनिवर्तिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्ती-र्तिनी-र्ति)<BR> ^1 Not coming back, not returning.<BR> ^2 Not turning back, not flying.

anivaarita|अनिवारित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unchecked, unimpeded, unopposed, unforbidden. E. अ neg. and निवारित.

anivaarya|अनिवार्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्) Not to be prevented or forbidden, necessary, unavoidable. E. अ neg. and निवार्य.

anivishamaana|अनिविशमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not reposing, not resting, restless. (ved.) E. अ neg. and निविशमान.

anivRta|अनिवृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unchecked, unimpeded, unopposed. E. अ neg. and निवृत.

anivedita|अनिवेदित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not told, not mentioned, not pointed out. E. अ neg. and निवेदित.

aniveditaviJNaata|अनिवेदितविज्ञात
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Known without having been told or pointed out. E. अनिवेदित and विज्ञात.

aniveshana|अनिवेशन
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Without a resting place, without an abode, restless. E. अ priv. and निवेशन.

anisha|अनिश
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Continual, incessant. अनिशम् used adv. continually, without interruption. E. अ priv. and निशा, according to some, implying here merely the period of time, according to others, the want of occupation or rest i. e. literally ‘without a night’ or ‘without rest’. 

anishita|अनिशित
m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Restless, incessant(?). E. अनिशि (a denom. from अनिश), kŕit aff. क्त(?). (Meaning and etymology of this word are doubtful. According to the native commentaries it would be a Tatpur. compounded of अ neg. and निशित, sharpened, sharp, and would mean either:<BR> ^1 not sharp, not injurious, or:<BR> ^2 not difficult, easy, or<BR> ^3 not slender, not little; but these explanations, when applied to the passages to which they refer, seem artificial.

anishitasarga|अनिशितसर्ग
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्गः-र्गा-र्गम्) (ved.) Of continual effusion, continually flowing (an epithet of the waters)(?). (This meaning is doubtful; according to the comm. it would be: of strong or abundant effusion. See the preceding.) E. अनिशित and सर्ग.

aniShanga|अनिषङ्ग
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ङ्गः-ङ्गा-ङ्गम्) Without a quiver. (According to the vaidik comm.: not connected with or impeded by, scil. the Rákshasas; this interpretation seems artificial.) E. अ priv. and निषङ्ग.

aniShiddha|अनिषिद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Not prohibited, not forbidden. E. अ neg. and निषिद्ध.

aniShu|अनिषु
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-षुः-षुः-षु) Having no arrow or having bad arrows. E. अ priv. and इषु.

aniSheddhra|अनिषेद्ध्र
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्ध्रः-द्ध्रा-द्ध्रम्) (ved.) Without impediment, unchecked, unimpeded. E. अ priv. and निषेद्ध्र.

aniShkRta|अनिष्कृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not completed, not accomplished, not perfect. E. अ neg. and निष्कृत.

aniShTa|अनिष्ट
Tatpur. I. 1. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Unwished, undesirable, bad, wrong.<BR> ^2 Bad, evil.<BR> ^3 Unlucky. BREAḲ. n. (-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Bad luck, evil occurrence, misfortune.<BR> ^2 Evil deed, crime. <BR>3. f. (-ष्टा) The name of a plant (Sida alba). See नागवला. E. अ neg. and इष्ट (इष्, kŕit aff. क्त). <BR>II. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Not sacrificed.<BR> ^2 Not honoured with a sacrifice (as a god). E. अ neg. and इष्ट (यज्, kŕit aff. क्त).

aniShTaduShTadhii|अनिष्टदुष्टधी
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धीः-धीः-धि) Of a bad and wicked disposition or mind. (Another and apparently more correct reading of this word is अरिष्टदुष्टधी q. v.) E. अनिष्टदुष्ट (Dwandwa) and धी.

aniShTaprasanga|अनिष्टप्रसङ्ग
Tatpur. m. (-ङ्गः) Connexion or association with what is undesirable, incongruous or wrong connexion, as that of a Yogin with worldly objects; or (in Nyáya) that of an inference with wrong premises, the former tending to prove the absurdity of the argument advanced; or (in grammatical literature) connecting one rule with an other rule which has no relation to it. E. अनिष्ट and प्रसङ्ग.

aniShTaphala|अनिष्टफल
Karmadh. n. (-लम्) Evil consequence, evil result. E. अनिष्ट and फल.

aniShTashankaa|अनिष्टशङ्का
Tatpur. f. (-ङ्का) Apprehension of an unpleasant or unlucky occurrence, apprehension of danger; (in rhetoric one of the व्यभिचारिभाव (q. v.) of the rasa वत्सल (q. v.). E. अनिष्ट and शङ्का.

aniShTahetu|अनिष्टहेतु
Tatpur. m. (-तुः) An evil omen. E. अनिष्ट and हेतु.

aniShTaapaadana|अनिष्टापादन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) 1. Obtaining or getting what is not desirable. See प्राप्तिसम. E. अनिष्ट and आपादन. BREAḲ. Not obtaining what is desirable. See अप्राप्तिसम. E. अ neg. and इष्ट-आपादन. 

aniShTaapti|अनिष्टाप्ति
Tatpur. f. (-प्तिः) The same as the preceding. E. 1. अनिष्ट and आप्ति, 2. अ neg. and इष्ट-आप्ति.

aniShTaashaMsin|अनिष्टाशंसिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Boding ill or evil. E. अनिष्ट and आशंसिन्.

aniShTin|अनिष्टिन्
Tatpur. m. (-ष्टी) One who has not performed a sacrifice. E. अ neg. and इष्टिन्.

aniShTRta|अनिष्टृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (ved.) Not hurt, not injured. E. अ neg. and निष्टृत.

aniShTotprexaNa|अनिष्टोत्प्रेक्षण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Apprehension of an unpleasant or unlucky occurrence, apprehension of danger, fear. E. अनिष्ट and उत्प्रेक्षण.

aniShThura|अनिष्ठुर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Not contumelious.<BR> ^2 Not harsh. E. अ neg. and निष्ठुर.

aniShNaata|अनिष्णात
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unskilful, ignorant. E. अ neg. and निष्णात.

aniShpatti|अनिष्पत्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Non-completion, non-termination. E. अ neg. and निष्पत्ति.

aniShpatram|अनिष्पत्रम्
Tatpur. ind. (Wounding) so as not to make the arrow come out on the other side of the body, i. e. not too violently. E. अ neg. and निष्पत्र.

aniShpanna|अनिष्पन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) Not accomplished, incomplete, imperfect. E. अ neg. and निष्पन्न.

anisarga|अनिसर्ग
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्गः-र्गा-र्गम्) Unnatural, unnaturally elated or depressed. E. अ priv. and निसर्ग.

anistabdha|अनिस्तब्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ब्धः-ब्धा-ब्धम्)<BR> ^1 Not paralyzed, not overpowered.<BR> ^2 Not stopped, not fixed. E. अ neg. and निस्तब्ध.

anistiirNa|अनिस्तीर्ण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्)<BR> ^1 Not got over.<BR> ^2 (In law.) Not refuted, not answered (as a plaint, a charge). See the following. E. अ neg. and निस्तीर्ण.

anistiirNaabhiyoga|अनिस्तीर्णाभियोग
Bahuvr. m. (-गः) (In law.) A defendant who has not or not yet refuted the charge brought against him. E. अनिस्तीर्ण and अभियोग.

aniika|अनीक
m. n. (-कः-कम्)<BR> ^1 The face (ved.).<BR> ^2 The fore part, front, the principal or conspicuous part (ved.).<BR> ^3 The point (e. g. of an arrow) (ved.).<BR> ^4 Multitude, assemblage, quantity (ved.).<BR> ^5 An army, a host, forces (according to some, also: part of an army).<BR> ^6 War, combat. E. अन्, to breathe (in 1. 2. 3.) and to go (in 4. 5. 6.), uń. aff. ईकन्, the radical being कित्.

aniikavat|अनीकवत्
m. (-वान्) (ved.) Having or occupying the prominent or principal place, principal, superior, first, an epithet of Agni, used chiefly when the god receives the first offerings in certain sacrifices, his name then also occurring as the first in the list of the gods invoked. E. अनीक, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

aniikavidaaraNa|अनीकविदारण
Tatpur. m. (-णः) A proper name: a brother of Jayadratha. E. अनीक and विदारण ‘destroyer of hosts’.

aniikastha|अनीकस्थ
Tatpur. m. (-स्थः)<BR> ^1 A warrior, a combattant.<BR> ^2 A royal body guard.<BR> ^3 A trainer of an elephant, an elephant driver.<BR> ^4 A large military drum.<BR> ^5 A mark, a sign, a signal.<BR> ^6 (According to one authority: अश्वल q. v.) E. अनीक and स्थ.

aniikinii|अनीकिनी
f. (-नी)<BR> ^1 An army, a host, forces.<BR> ^2 A certain force; three chamús or one-tenth of an Akshauhińí, containing two thousand, one hundred and eighty-seven elephants, and as many cars, six thousand, five hundred and  sixty-one horses, and ten thousand, nine hundred and thirtyfive foot. E. अनीक, taddh. aff. इनि.

aniixaNa|अनीक्षण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Not seeing, not looking at (e. g. the rising or the setting sun, as one of the प्रजापतिव्रत q. v.). E. अ neg. and ईक्षण.

aniicha|अनीच
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-चः-चा-चम्)<BR> ^1 Not low, respectable, decent.<BR> ^2 (In grammar.) Not pronounced with the low or anudátta accent (as a syllable). E. अ neg. and नीच.

aniichaanuvartin|अनीचानुवर्तिन्
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-र्ती-र्तिनी-र्ति) Not keeping low or improper company. 2. m. (-र्ती) A faithful lover or husband. E. अ neg. and नीच-अनुवर्तिन्.

aniichidarshin|अनीचिदर्शिन्
Tatpur. m. (-र्शी) The name of a Bauddha saint. E. अनीचि(?) and दर्शिन्. (The reading of this word is doubtful, and the correct form is probably अवीचिदर्शिन्; from अवीचि the last of the eight fiery hells of the Buddhists and दर्शिन्, ‘seeing’; as an Arhat, who has made himself conversant with the whole doctrine of Sákyamuni, is promised to penetrate with his sight all the worlds, ‘from the highest summit of existence, down to the great hell Avíchi’.)

aniiDa|अनीड
I. Tatpur. m. (-नीडः) (ved.) Not nesting, not resting, restless; an epithet of Agni. Also written अनीळ. E. अ neg. and नीड. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-डः-डा-डम्) Having no nest or repose; metaphorically applied to the highest divinity which is without an abode i. e. without a body. E. अ priv. and नीड.

aniiti|अनीति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) I.<BR> ^1 Impropriety, immorality.<BR> ^2 Impolicy, ill conduct. E. अ neg. and नीति. <BR>II. Freedom from calamities of season, as excessive rain &c. E. अ neg. and ईति.

aniitiJNa|अनीतिज्ञ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ज्ञः-ज्ञा-ज्ञम्)<BR> ^1 Indiscreet, immoral.<BR> ^2 Impolitic. E. अ neg. and नीतिज्ञ.

aniitivid|अनीतिविद्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्-त्-त्) The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and नीतिविद्.

aniidRsha|अनीदृश
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-शः-शी-शम्) Unlike, dissimilar. E. अ neg. and ईदृश.

aniipsita|अनीप्सित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not desirable. E. अ neg. and ईप्सित.

aniisha|अनीश
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Not ruling, not being master over, without power, powerless, unable. BREAḲ. f. (-शा) (In the Upanishads.) Want of power, impotence, insufficiency. E. अ neg. and 1. ईश, 2. ईशा. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Without a lord or superior. And see अनीश्वर II. BREAḲ. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 A name of Vishńu.<BR> ^2 A name of Śiva. E. अ priv. and ईश.

aniishataa|अनीशता
f. (-ता) or अनीशत्व n. (-त्वम्) The condition or state of not being a master or ruler. E. अनीश I., taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

aniishvara|अनीश्वर
I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not ruling, not being master over, without power, powerless, unable. E. अ neg. and ईश्वर. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Without a lord or superior.<BR> ^2 Unchecked, uncontrolled.<BR> ^3 Not belonging to the supreme deity.<BR> ^4 Not acknowledging a supreme deity, atheistic. E. अ priv. and ईश्वर. 

aniishvarataa|अनीश्वरता
f. (-ता) or अनीश्वरत्व n. (-त्वम्)<BR> ^1 Want of power, impotence, insufficiency.<BR> ^2 The being without a lord.<BR> ^3 The being unchecked.<BR> ^4 Atheism. E. 1. अनीश्वर I.; 2. 3. 4. अनीश्वर II., taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

aniishvaravaadin|अनीश्वरवादिन्
Tatpur. m. (-दी) An atheist, one who denies a supreme ruler of the universe. E. अनीश्वर and वादिन्.

aniiha|अनीह
I. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) Without a desire, indifferent. BREAḲ. m. (-हः) The proper name of a king of Ayodhyá, father of Párijátra; (according to other authorities the same king is called Ahínagu and is father of Párijátra or Sahaśráswa). E. अ priv. and ईहा. <BR>II. Tatpur. f. (-हा)<BR> ^1 Want of desire, indifference.<BR> ^2 Want of energy, apathy. E. अ neg. and ईहा.

aniihita|अनीहित
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unwished for, disagreeable. 2. n. (-तम्) Displeasure. E. अ neg. and ईहित.

aniiळ|अनीळ
see अनीड.

anu|अनु
ind. (see निपात, उपसर्ग, गति, कर्मप्रवचनीय). A particle implying the notion of ‘after’ in its literal and metaphorical acceptations; it is used either as a separable preposition or as a prefix to verbs, but, in the latter capacity, in the Vedas and in archaic passages of the epic literature, also detached from the verb, very much in the same manner as German prepositions when connected with verbs; in the Vedas it is sometimes also used adverbially. With nouns it may form Avyayíbh., Tatpur. and Bahuvr. compounds. It means: <BR>1. (as a separable preposition, with a noun following or preceding in the accusative)<BR> ^1 After;<BR> ^a. in space (literally),<BR> ^b. in time, implying successiveness,<BR> ^c. in rank or order, implying inferiority.<BR> ^2 Along, lengthwise (in this sense also with a noun in the genitive).<BR> ^3 With, together with (in this meaning, however, only in conventional phrases; e. g. पर्वतमनु or नदीमन्ववसिता सेना ‘the army was (so placed as to be) in communication with a mountain or with a river’.<BR> ^4 To the part or share of; e. g. यदत्र मामनु स्यात् ‘what there may fall to my share’.<BR> ^5 By (implying distribution); e. g. वृक्षं वृक्षमनु सिञ्चति ‘he throws water tree by tree i. e. he waters every tree.<BR> ^6 After, in the sense of to, towards, in the direction of; e. g. वृक्षमनु विद्योतते विद्युत् ‘the lightning flushes after i. e. towards, in the direction of the tree’.<BR> ^7 In regard to, in consequence of, on behalf of (only in conventional phrases), e. g. जपमनु प्रावर्षत् ‘it rained in consequence of prayers’ or शाकल्यस्य संहितामनु or अनुडुद्यज्ञमनु प्रावर्षत् ‘it rained in consequence of the hymns of Sákalya (having been recited) or in consequence of an ox having being sacrificed’.<BR> ^8 In accordance with, agreeably to, like, similar.<BR> ^9 According to the statement of, e. g. साधुर्देवदत्तो मातरमनु ‘Devadatta is an excellent man, according to what his mother tells’. BREAḲ. (as a prefix to verbs, undetached or detached)<BR> ^1 After, in space or time, literally and metaphorically, e. g. गम्, सज्ज्, शी &c. with अनु qq. vv.<BR> ^2 Similarly, likewise (implying imitation); in accordance with, agreeably to, lit. and met., see f. i. कृ, वच्, ज्ञा with अनु &c. <BR>3. (as adverb, in the Vedas) Afterwards.  BREAḰ. (in composition with nouns) I. (In Avyayíbh. compounds.)<BR> ^1 After,<BR> ^a. in space (literally), e. g. अनुरथम्, after, behind the cart;<BR> ^b. in order or rank, e. g. अनुज्येष्ठम्, after, next to the eldest.<BR> ^2 Along, lengthwise, on, e. g. अनुगङ्गं वाराणसी ‘Benares is situated along, i. e. on the Ganges’.<BR> ^3 Near to; e. g. अनुवनमशनिर्गतः ‘it lightens near the forest’.<BR> ^4 According to, agreeably to, like; e. g. अनुक्रमम् ‘according to order, in due order’.<BR> ^5 Severally, by; e. g. अनुदिनम् ‘day by day, daily’. <BR>II. (In Tatpur. compounds.)<BR> ^1 After (in order or rank), subsequent, inferior, secondary; see f. i. अनुकनीयस्, अनुकल्प, अनुनायिका.<BR> ^2 According to, in conformance with, similar, like to; e. g. अनुकूल, अनुलोम, अनुब्राह्मण.<BR> ^3 Again; e. g. अनुलाप. <BR>III. (In Bahuvr. compounds.) In conformity with, similar, like, e. g. अनुगुण, अनुरूप &c. E. unknown; the native etym. अन्, uń. aff. उ, is not plausible; अनु is probably connected in origin with आ, towards, in its oldest form आंँ = अंँस्. See s. v. आ and the Preface.

anu|अनु
m. (-नुः)<BR> ^1 (in the Vedas; esp. in the plural अनवः) Man in general; but it seems that this word is in the Vedas the name of a tribe or family, the meaning ‘men’ being an etymological interpretation of the commentaries.<BR> ^2 The proper name of a king in the North, the fourth son of Yayáti by Śarmisht́á; according to others, a son of Kuruvaśa or of Kuru. E. अन्, uń. aff. उ.

anuka|अनुक
m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Desirous, lustful, libidinous. E. अनु (the particle), taddh. aff. कन्; acc. to others, a Tatpur., E. कम् with अनु, kŕit aff. ड.

anukathana|अनुकथन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Telling according to (what has been said), report, account. E. कथ् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anukaniiyas|अनुकनीयस्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यान्-यसी-यः) The next youngest, the youngest in succession. Comp. अनुज्येष्ठ. E. अनु and कनीयस्.

anukampaka|अनुकम्पक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) The name of a king, who lived, accord. to the Mahábh., in the Kŕita-yuga. E. कम्प्, with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anukampana|अनुकम्पन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Compassion, commiseration. E. कम्प् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anukampaa|अनुकम्पा
Tatpur. f. (-म्पा) Compassion, tenderness. E. कम्प् with अनु, kŕit aff. अ, and fem. aff. टाप्.

anukampya|अनुकम्प्य
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-प्यः-प्या-प्यम्) Worthy of tenderness or compassion. <BR>II. m. (-म्प्यः)<BR> ^1 A courier, an express, a runner.<BR> ^2 An ascetic, keeping the vow of rigorous penance. E. कम्प् with अनु, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्.

anukara|अनुकर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Doing any thing like another, imitating. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्.

anukaraNa|अनुकरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्)<BR> ^1 Making or doing like or in imitation of another, imitating.<BR> ^2 Resemblance, similarity. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anukartR|अनुकर्तृ
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-र्ता-र्त्री-तृ) Imitating. 2. m. (-र्ता) A performer, an actor. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. तृच्.

anukarman|अनुकर्मन्
Tatpur. n. (-र्म) A subsequent rite or ceremony. E. अनु and कर्मन्. See अनुक्रिया.

anukarSha|अनुकर्ष
Tatpur. m. (-र्षः)<BR> ^1 Attracting.<BR> ^2 (In Grammar.) Including  a preceding in a subsequent rule.<BR> ^3 Invoking, summoning by incantations.<BR> ^4 Deferred performance of a duty: performance at a period posterior to that for which it is prescribed (opp. to अपकर्ष q. v.).<BR> ^5 The bottom of a carriage (so called, because it is, as it were, dragged after by the wheel which is under it). E. कृष् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anukarShaNa|अनुकर्षण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as अनुकर्ष 1. 2. 3. E. कृष् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anukarShan|अनुकर्षन्
Tatpur. m. (-र्षा) The bottom of a carriage. See अनुकर्ष. E. Probably a further developement of the partic. अनुकर्षत्, from कृष् with अनु, conformably to the general origin of bases in अन्; the native dict. consider it as अनुकर्ष with an additional न्, but अनुकर्ष is more likely the curtailed अनुकर्षन् as most bases in अ probably originate in a fuller form on अस्, अत्, अन्.

anukalpa|अनुकल्प
Tatpur. m. (-ल्पः) A secondary or succedaneous injunction: an injunction of what is to be done, if the original injunction cannot be acted upon; f. i. to make offerings with nívára, if vríhi--the dravya originally required<BR> --cannot be had; but used also in a more general sense with regard to other duties. E. अनु and कल्प.

anukaankShaa|अनुकाङ्क्षा
Tatpur. f. (-ङ्क्षा) Wish, desire after. E. काङ्क्ष् with अनु, kŕit aff. अ and fem. aff. टाप्.

anukaama|अनुकाम
I. Tatpur. 1. m. (-मः) (ved.) Wish, desire. E. कम् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्. BREAḲ. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) Consistent with one's desire, agreeable, liked. E. अनु and काम. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-मम्)<BR> ^1 According to wish or desire.<BR> ^2 After (i. e. past) one's wish or desire(?).<BR> ^3 Desire by desire, every desire(?). E. अनु and काम.

anukaamakRt|अनुकामकृत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कृत्) (ved.) Fulfilling desire or wish. E. अनुकाम and कृत्.

anukaamiina|अनुकामीन
m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्)<BR> ^1 One who goes where he pleases.<BR> ^2 One who acts as he pleases. E. अनुकाम, taddh. aff. ख.

anukaamiinataa|अनुकामीनता
f. (-ता)<BR> ^1 Going according to wish or inclination.<BR> ^2 Acting according to wish or inclination. E. अनुकामीन, taddh. aff. तल्.

anukaara|अनुकार
Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 Imitation.<BR> ^2 Resemblance. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anukaarin|अनुकारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Imitating (also as an actor). Comp. अनुकर्तृ. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anukaarya|अनुकार्य
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-र्यः-र्या-र्यम्)<BR> ^1 To be imitated.<BR> ^2 To be performed (as the character in a play). E. कृ with अनु, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्. BREAḲ. n. (-र्यम्) A subsequent duty or business. E. अनु and कार्य.

anukaalam|अनुकालम्
Avyayíbh. In due time. E. अनु and काल.

anukiirNa|अनुकीर्ण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्) Filled, thronged, crowded. E. कॄ with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anukiirtana|अनुकीर्तन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Proclaiming, publishing. E. कॄत् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anukuncita|अनुकुञ्चित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Inflected, curved. E. कुञ्च् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त with ágama इट्.

anukuula|अनुकूल
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-लः-ला-लम्)<BR> ^1 Conformable to.<BR> ^2 Well disposed to, friendly, favourable. BREAḲ. m. (-लः) (In Rhetoric.) See अनुकूलनायक.  <BR>3. f. (-ला)<BR> ^1 The name of a medicinal plant (Croton polyandrum). See दन्ती.<BR> ^2 The name of a metre regulated by number and quantity; it belongs to the class, called त्रिष्टुभ् q. v. and consists of a stanza of four lines with the following eleven syllables in each: {??} Also called कुद्मलदन्ती, मौक्तिकमाला and श्री. BREAḰ. n. (-लम्) (In Rhetoric.) An alankára or mode of writing or speaking elegantly, viz. representing an act, unpleasant in itself, as arising out of kindness or affection; e. g. when ‘an ill-humoured mistress embraces her lover and apparently out of excess of love wounds him with her nails’. E. अनु and कूल literally ‘along or according to the bank (of a river)’.

anukuulataa|अनुकूलता
f. (-ता) and अनुकूलत्व n. (-त्वम्)<BR> ^1 Conformity, consistency.<BR> ^2 Concord, good will, consent. E. अनुकूल, taddh. aff. तल् or त्व.

anukuulanaayaka|अनुकूलनायक
Karmadh. m. (-कः) (In Rhetoric.) One of the forty-eight characters of a hero or principal personage in a poetical composition; he is described as a lover attached only to one mistress and as one of the four varieties (see also दक्षिण, धृष्ट and शठ) of either of the four principal divisions of the नायक (q. v.), viz. of the धीरोदात्त, धीरोद्धत, धीरललित and धीरप्रशान्त (qq. vv.). The अनुकूलनायक may again be उत्तम, मध्यम or अधम (qq. vv.). E. अनुकूल and नायक.

anukuuli|अनुकूलि
Denom. (अनुकूलयति) To act kindly, to show favour. E. अनुकूल, denom. aff. णिच्.

anukRta|अनुकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Imitated, made like or done in like manner. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anukRti|अनुकृति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Making or doing any thing like or in imitation of another, imitating.<BR> ^2 Resemblance, similarity. E. कृ with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anukRtya|अनुकृत्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्यः-त्या-त्यम्). The same as अनुकार्य. E. कृ with अनु, kŕitya aff. क्यप् and ágama तुक्.

anukRShTa|अनुकृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Attracted.<BR> ^2 (In Grammar.) Included in a subsequent rule (as a preceding one). E. कृष् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anukta|अनुक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्)<BR> ^1 Not spoken, not expressed.<BR> ^2 Unheard of, unthought of, extraordinary (esp. in Karmadh. compositions, implying praise, e. g. अनुक्ताध्यापक an unheard of i. e. a very excellent teacher). E. अ neg. and उक्त.

anuktanimitta|अनुक्तनिमित्त
I. Tatpur. n. (-त्तम्)<BR> ^1 A reason not expressed.<BR> ^2 An extraordinary, unthought of reason. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्)<BR> ^1 Being without an apparent reason.<BR> ^2 Having or owing its origin to an extraordinary, unthought of reason. See विभावना and विशेषोक्ति. E. अनुक्त and निमित्त.

anukti|अनुक्ति
Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः)<BR> ^1 The not speaking, not saying.<BR> ^2 The not having been said or mentioned. E. अ neg. and उक्ति.

anuktha|अनुक्थ
Bahuvr. m. (-क्थः) (ved.) Without hymns, not praising (the divinity) in hymns. E. अ priv. and उक्था.

anukakacha|अनुककच
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-चः-चा-चम्) Serrated, dentated. E. अनु and क्रकच.

anukrama|अनुक्रम
I. Tatpur. m. (-मः) Order, arrangement, regular and methodical disposal or succession.--अनुक्रमेण and अनुक्रमात् in the order. E. क्रम् with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्.  <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-मम्) According to order, in due order. E. अनु and क्रम.

anukramaNa|अनुक्रमण
Tatpur. 1. n. (-णम्)<BR> ^1 Following.<BR> ^2 Arranging, disposing methodically. BREAḲ. f. (-णी) An explanatory table of contents, esp. of vaidik writings. E. क्रम् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्; 2. with fem. aff. ङीप्.

anukramaNikaa|अनुक्रमणिका
f. (-का). The same as अनुक्रमणी. E. अनुक्रमणी, taddh. aff. कन् and fem. aff. टाप्.

anukraanta|अनुक्रान्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Done or arranged methodically, passed over &c. in due order. E. क्रम् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anukriyaa|अनुक्रिया
Tatpur. f. (-या) A subsequent rite or ceremony. See अनुकर्मन्. E. अनु and क्रिया.

anukrosha|अनुक्रोश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) Tenderness, compassion. E. क्रुश् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuxaNam|अनुक्षणम्
Avyayíbh. Momentarily, perpetually. E. अनु and क्षण.

anuxattR|अनुक्षत्तृ
Tatpur. m. (-क्षत्ता) (ved.)<BR> ^1 The follower or servant of a charioteer.<BR> ^2 The follower or servant of a doorkeeper. E. अनु and क्षत्तृ.

anuxapam|अनुक्षपम्
Avyayíbh. Night by night, every night. E. अनु and क्षपा.

anuxetra|अनुक्षेत्र
Tatpur. n. (-त्रम्) (A modern term.) A charitable allowance made to the native servants of certain temples in Orissa, by the Marathas and continued by the British Government. E. अनु and क्षेत्र.

anukhanja|अनुखञ्ज
Tatpur. m. (-ञ्जः) The name of a country (as a king of which Paurava is mentioned). E. अनु and खञ्ज.

anukhyaati|अनुख्याति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Reporting, revealing. E. ख्या with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anukhyaatR|अनुख्यातृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) Reporter, revealer. E. ख्या with अनु, kŕit aff. तृच्.

anuga|अनुग
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्)<BR> ^1 Following, lit. and met.<BR> ^2 Corresponding with. BREAḲ. m. (-गः)<BR> ^1 A follower, a companion.<BR> ^2 A servant, an attendant. <BR>3. f. (-गा) The proper name of an Apsaras. E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. ड.

anugangam|अनुगङ्गम्
Avyayíbh. Along the Ganges, on the Ganges. See I. अनु 4. E. अनु and गङ्गा.

anugaNita|अनुगणित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Reckoned over, calculated over. E. गण् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त and ágama इट्.

anugaNitin|अनुगणितिन्
m. f. n. (-ती-तिनी-ति) One who has reckoned over, calculated over (with a noun following in the locative). E. अनुगणित, taddh. aff. इनि.

anugata|अनुगत
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Following, pursuing.<BR> ^2 Followed, pursued.<BR> ^3 Acquired, obtained, lit. and met.<BR> ^4 Gone out, extinguished (as fire). BREAḲ. n. (-तम्) (In Music.) The middle measure, neither quick nor slow; the same as घन q. v. E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anugataartha|अनुगतार्थ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) Having an obvious meaning, one easily inferred from the etymon (as a word), e. g. the words गर्भाधान, अन्नप्राशन, उदयगिरि &c. E. अनुगत and अर्थ.

anugantavya|अनुगन्तव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be followed (also  in a special sense: at funeral obsequies). E. गम् with अनु, kŕitya aff. तव्य or तव्यत्.

anugandhikaa|अनुगन्धिका
f. (-का) A river of mount Mályavat. E. अनु-गन्ध, taddh. aff. क(?).

anugama|अनुगम
Tatpur. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 Following, going or coming after. See also अनुगमन.<BR> ^2 (In Philosophy.) The comprehension mentally of the essence of an object.<BR> ^3 The going out, extinction (of fire). E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्.

anugamana|अनुगमन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Following, going or coming after (also in a special sense: at funeral obsequies).<BR> ^2 Following in death, the self-immolation of a widow on the funeral pile. See also अनुमरण. E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anugavam|अनुगवम्
Avyayíbh. Of a cow's breadth, as wide as is required for a cow (said of a cart). E. अनु and गो, samásánta aff. अच्.

anugaviina|अनुगवीन
m. (-नः) A cowherd. E. अनुगु, taddh. aff. ख.

anugaadin|अनुगादिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दी-दिनी-दि) Speaking the same as or like another. E. गद् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anugaamin|अनुगामिन्
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-मी-मिनी-मि) Going behind or after, following. BREAḲ. m. (-मी)<BR> ^1 A follower, a companion.<BR> ^2 A servant, an attendant. E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anugaamuka|अनुगामुक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Always following, always connected with. E. गम् with अनु, kŕit aff. उकञ्.

anugiram|अनुगिरम्
Avyayíbh. On the mountain (= गिरौ). E. अनु and गिरि, samásánta aff. टच्.

anugiiti|अनुगीति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) The name of a metre regulated by feet and belonging to the class called गणच्छन्दस् or गणवृत्त qq. vv. It consists of a couplet of two verses with twentyseven syllables in the first, and with thirty-two syllables in the second verse; it is measured by feet, denominated गण or मात्रागण which are equivalent to two long syllables or to four short; its odd feet (the first, third, fifth and seventh) must never be amphibrachys, the sixth foot of the first verse consists of a single short syllable and that of the second verse of an Amphibrachys or Proceleusmaticus. The pause is commonly restricted to the close of the third foot. If the long verse precede the short one, the metre is called सुगीति. E. अनु and गीति (another metre).

anugu|अनुगु
Avyayíbh. After the cow or the cows. E. अनु and गो.

anuguNa|अनुगुण
I. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Of similar qualities, congenial with, corresponding with, suitable to. <BR>II. Tatpur. m. (-णः) (In Rhetoric.) An alankára or mode of writing elegantly, representing the natural properties of a thing as more intense through contact with another thing. <BR>III. Avyayíbh. (-णम्) According to the quality or natural property (of an object). E. अनु and गुण.

anugRhiita|अनुगृहीत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Favoured, obliged. E. ग्रह with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त and ágama इट् lengthened.

anugra|अनुग्र
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्रः-ग्रा-ग्रम्) Not violent, calm, gentle, mild. E. अ neg. and उग्र.

anugraha|अनुग्रह
Tatpur. m. (-हः)<BR> ^1 Promoting good and preventing ill or (according to another interpretation) promoting good by preventing ill.<BR> ^2 The conferring benefits, favour.<BR> ^3 Aid, assistance.<BR> ^4 Instructing in the mystical verses or incantations of the Vedas(?).<BR> ^5 See अनुग्रहसर्ग. E. ग्रह् with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्. 

anugrahaNa|अनुग्रहण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्). The same as अनुग्रह 1. 2. 3. E. ग्रह् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anugrahasarga|अनुग्रहसर्ग
Tatpur. m. (-र्गः) (In the Sánkhya philosophy.) The creation of mental conditions; in some of the Puráńas it is considered as an eigth creation, in others as a fifth, and subdivided into विपर्यय, अशक्ति, सिद्धि and तुष्टि qq. vv. See also प्रत्ययसर्ग. E. अनुग्रह (perhaps in the sense of ‘feeling’ in general) and सर्ग.

anugrahin|अनुग्रहिन्
m. (-ही) One instructed in the mystical verses or incantations of the Vedas(?). E. अनुग्रह, taddh. aff. इनि.

anugraamam|अनुग्रामम्
Avyayíbh. Village for village, according to or in every village. E. अनु and ग्राम.

anugraasaka|अनुग्रासक
m. (-कः) A mouthful or a quantity equivalent to a mouthful of boiled rice. E. अनु-ग्रास, taddh. aff. क.

anugraahaka|अनुग्राहक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-हकः-हिका-हकम्)<BR> ^1 Manifesting grace or favour towards; e. g. आदित्यपुरुषो वा चक्षुषोऽनुग्राहकः.<BR> ^2 A supporter, an assistant (also in evil deeds). E. ग्रह् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anugraahin|अनुग्राहिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ही-हिणी-हि) Gracious, favourable. E. ग्रह् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anugraahya|अनुग्राह्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ह्यः-ह्या-ह्यम्) To be treated with graciousness or favour, to be favoured. E. ग्रह् with अनु, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्.

anuchara|अनुचर
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Going or coming after, following. BREAḲ. m. f. (-रः-री)<BR> ^1 A follower, a companion.<BR> ^2 A servant, an attendant. (The fem. form अनुचरा, if not the latter part of a Bahuvr. compound, is grammatically incorrect. E. चर् with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्; चर being टित् or, according to some, चर् with अनु, kŕit aff. ट.

anuchaaraka|अनुचारक
Tatpur. m. f. (-रकः-रिका)<BR> ^1 A follower, a companion.<BR> ^2 A servant, an attendant. E. चर् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anuchaarin|अनुचारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Following, attending. E. चर् with अनु, kŕit aff. घिणुन्.

anuchita|अनुचित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not proper, not suitable, not convenient, wrong.<BR> ^2 Not known, not understood. E. अ neg. and उचित.

anuchitaartha|अनुचितार्थ
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्थः-र्था-र्थम्) Having an unknown or an unusual meaning (as a word; in rhetoric considered as one of the पददोष q. v.; e. g. if the word पशु, animal, is used in the sense of sacrificial animal, in a poetical passage, while it has this sense only in the ritual literature, or with the intention of implying timidity which it does not imply). E. अनुचित and अर्थ.

anuchintana|अनुचिन्तन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Thinking of, recollecting, recalling. E. चिन्त् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuchintaa|अनुचिन्ता
Tatpur. f. (-न्ता) Thinking of, recollecting, recalling. E. चिन्त् with अनु, kŕit aff. अङ्.

anuchchaara|अनुच्चार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) Non-utterance, omission (of a word). E. अ neg. and उच्चार.

anuchChaada|अनुच्छाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) A cloth or garment, that hangs down; different from पर्यास, a cloth that is thrown round q. v., from नीवि q. v. &c. (ved.). E. छद् with अनु (along, scil. the body), kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuchChitti|अनुच्छित्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Non-destruction, indestructibility, eternity. E. अ neg. and उच्छित्ति. 

anuchChittidharman|अनुच्छित्तिधर्मन्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्मा-र्मा-र्म) Having the property of eternity, of indestructibility (an epithet of आत्मन् in the Upan.). E. अनुच्छित्ति and धर्मन्.

anuchChinna|अनुच्छिन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) Not cut off, not destroyed. E. अ neg. and उच्छिन्न.

anuchChiShTa|अनुच्छिष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Not rejected, pure. E. अ neg. and उच्छिष्ट.

anuchCheda|अनुच्छेद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) Non-destruction, indestructibility, eternity. E. अ neg. and उच्छेद.

anuchChedya|अनुच्छेद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्)<BR> ^1 Not divisible.<BR> ^2 Indestructible, permanent. E. अ neg. and उच्छेद्य.

anuja|अनुज
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Born after or later. BREAḲ. m. (-जः) A younger brother. <BR>3. f. (-जा)<BR> ^1 A younger sister.<BR> ^2 The name of a medicinal plant. See त्रायमाणा. BREAḰ. n. (-जम्) A small herbaceous plant used in medicine and as a perfume. See प्रपौण्डरीक. E. जन् with अनु, kŕit aff. ड.

anujanam|अनुजनम्
Avyayíbh. According to people, according to every body. E. अनु and जन.

anujanman|अनुजन्मन्
Bahuvr. m. (-न्मा) A younger brother or younger born. E. अनु and जन्मन्.

anujaata|अनुजात
Tatpur. I. 1. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Born after. Used actively, passively and impersonally; when actively with a noun depending in the accusative; e. g. अनुजातो माणवको माणविकाम् or अनुजाता माणविका माणवकेन ‘the boy is born after the girl’ or अनुजातं माणवकेन ‘the boy is later born’. BREAḲ. m. (-तः) A younger brother. <BR>3. f. (-ता) A younger sister. E. जन् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 After teething (as a child; the word is explained so by a commentator of Manu, where it appears as an elliptical expression instead of अनुदन्तजात, the word दन्तजात preceding immediately; this meaning is therefore restricted to the passage alone alluded to (book 5 verse 58) and not generally applicable).<BR> ^2 Born like or with similar qualities as (another). E. अनु and जात.

anujaavara|अनुजावर
See आनुजावर. (The form आनुयाजावर which occurs in the existing edition of Páńini V. 4. 36. v. 5., is wrong.)

anujighRxaa|अनुजिघृक्षा
Tatpur. f. (-क्षा) The desire of conferring favours, of acting kindly. E. ग्रह् in the desid., with अनु, kŕit aff. अ.

anujiirNa|अनुजीर्ण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्णः-र्णा-र्णम्) Grown old after, decayed after, or in consequence of, on behalf of. (Used actively, passively and impersonally; when actively with a noun depending in the accusative; e. g. अनुजीर्णो वृषलीं चैत्रः or अनुजीर्णा वृषली चैत्रेण; अनुजीर्णं चैत्रेण. Compare the construction of अनुजात.) E. जॄ with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anujiivin|अनुजीविन्
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-वी-विनी-वि) Living upon, getting a livelihood by or through, dependant. BREAḲ. m. (-वी)<BR> ^1 A servant, a dependant.<BR> ^2 A companion, a follower. (It occurs as the proper name of a crow in a fable.) E. जीव् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anujiivisaat|अनुजीविसात्
ind. See the following. E. अनुजीविन्, taddh. aff. साति.

anujiivisaatkRta|अनुजीविसात्कृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Made subservient, become entirely one's own. E. अनुजीविसात् and कृत. 

anujiivya|अनुजीव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be lived upon or after, in conformance with. E. जीव् with अनु, kŕitya aff. तव्यत्.

anuJNapti|अनुज्ञप्ति
Tatpur. f. (-प्तिः) Ordering, commanding, enjoining. The same as अनुज्ञापन. E. ज्ञप् with अनु (or perhaps better ज्ञा, in the caus., with अनु, with ágama पुक् and the vowel of the radical shortened), kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anuJNaa|अनुज्ञा
Tatpur. f. (-ज्ञा)<BR> ^1 Assent, permission.<BR> ^2 Order, command(?).<BR> ^3 (In Rhetoric.) An alankára or mode of writing elegantly viz. taking a favourable view of another's faults and, as it were, assenting to them. E. ज्ञा with अनु, kŕit aff. अङ्.

anuJNaata|अनुज्ञात
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Assented to, permitted, allowed, accepted, acknowledged.<BR> ^2 Ordered, directed.<BR> ^3 Dismissed.<BR> ^4 Honoured. E. ज्ञा with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuJNaana|अनुज्ञान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Assenting, permitting. E. ज्ञा with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuJNaapaka|अनुज्ञापक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पकः-पिका-पकम्) Commanding. E. ज्ञा in the caus., with अनु, with ágama पुक्, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anuJNaapana|अनुज्ञापन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्). The same as अनुज्ञप्ति. E. ज्ञा in the caus., with अनु, with ágama पुक्, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuJNaapraarthanaa|अनुज्ञाप्रार्थना
Tatpur. f. (-ना) Asking permission. E. अनुज्ञा and प्रार्थना.

anuJNaiShaNaa|अनुज्ञैषणा
Tatpur. f. (-णा) Asking permission. E. अनुज्ञा and एषणा.

anujyeShTha|अनुज्येष्ठ
I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्ठः-ष्ठा-ष्ठम्) Following the eldest, the next eldest, eldest but one. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-ष्ठम्)<BR> ^1 After the eldest.<BR> ^2 According to seniority. E. अनु and ज्येष्ठ.

anuta|अनुत
See E. of आनुति.

anutapta|अनुतप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) Filled with regret or repentance, repentant, remorseful. E. तप् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anutara|अनुतर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) Fare, freight. E. तॄ with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्.

anutarSha|अनुतर्ष
Tatpur. m. (-र्षः)<BR> ^1 Thirst.<BR> ^2 Wish, desire.<BR> ^3 A drinking vessel, one used to drink spirituous liquors from.<BR> ^4 Spirituous liquor. See अनुतर्षण. E. तृष् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anutarShaNa|अनुतर्षण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्)<BR> ^1 A vessel (according to some, of crystal), from which spirituous liquor is drunk.<BR> ^2 Serving up or distributing liquor. (Some authorities admit only the first, some only the second meaning; neither both together. A later compilation makes this word a synonyme of अनुतर्ष also in its other meanings.) E. तृष् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anutaapa|अनुताप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Repentance. E. तप् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anutaapana|अनुतापन
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्) Making remorseful or penitent, afflicting. E. तप् with अनु, in the caus., kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anutaapin|अनुतापिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पी-पिनी-पि) Penitent, regretting. E. अनुताप, taddh. aff. इनि.

anutilam|अनुतिलम्
Avyayíbh. According or like a seed of sesamum; (probably used in the same manner as तिलतुल्य in negative phrases answering ‘a single grain, a pin's head, an iota, a whit &c.’). E. अनु and तिल.

anutuuli|अनुतूलि
Denom. (अनुतूलयति). E. तूल, denom. aff. णिच्, with अनु. See under तूलि.

anutkarSha|अनुत्कर्ष
Tatpur. m. (-र्षः) Want of excellence or superiority, inferiority. E. अ neg. and उत्कर्ष.

anutta|अनुत्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Not thrown, not over powered, invincible (ved.). E. अ neg. and नुत्त. (According to others: not wetted, not moistened. E. अ neg. and उत्त; this interpretation, however, seems erroneous.)

anuttama|अनुत्तम
m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) I. Tatpur. Very best, chief, principal. E. अ compar. or expl. and उत्तम, or perhaps a compound framed after the analogy of अनुत्तर. <BR>II. Bahuvr. (In grammar.) Without the first person, used in any but the first person, i. e. in the second or third person (viz. a verb). E. अ priv. and उत्तम.

anuttamanyu|अनुत्तमन्यु
Bahuvr. m. (-न्युः) (ved.) Of invincible wrath, an epithet of Indra. E. अनुत्त and मन्यु.

anuttamaambhas|अनुत्तमाम्भस्
Tatpur. n. (-म्भः) A technical term in the Sánkhya philosophy denoting one of the five sorts of external acquiescence or indifference (see तुष्टि), viz. that condition of mind in which a man abstains from sensual enjoyments on the ground that there is no repose for the senses when attachment to sensual pleasures prevails. Some call this indifference नारीक; compare also अम्भस्, सलिल, ओघ, वृष्टि, सुतमस्, पार, सुनेत्र, सुपार, अपार, पारापार, उत्तमाम्भस् and the following. E. अ neg. and उत्तमाम्भस्(?).

anuttamaambhasika|अनुत्तमाम्भसिक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) A technical term in the Sánkhya philosophy denoting one of the five sorts of external acquiescence or indifference (see तुष्टि), viz. that condition of mind in which a man abstains from sensual enjoyments on the ground that it is sinful to injure created things, enjoyment however being impossible without doing so. Some call this indifference उत्तमाम्भस्. Compare the preceding and the terms named there. E. अनुत्तम and आम्भसिक(?).

anuttara|अनुत्तर
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Low, nether.<BR> ^2 South, southern.<BR> ^3 Low, inferior, vile. BREAḲ. n. (-रम्)<BR> ^1 No-answer.<BR> ^2 A bad or evasive reply and held therefore to be no-answer (e. g. of the defendant, in a law-suit). E. अ neg. and उत्तर. <BR>II. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्)<BR> ^1 Best, excellent, supreme, chief, principal (literally: than which there is no higher or better).<BR> ^2 Fixed, firm.<BR> ^3 Unable to answer or to give a proper answer. BREAḲ. m. pl. (-राः) In Jaina mythology, one of the two divisions (see also ग्रैवेयक) of the gods called कल्पातीत (q. v.) which are one of the two divisions (see also कल्पभव) of the gods called वैमानिक (q. v.); the अनुत्तराः comprise five classes. See विजय, वैजयन्त, जयन्त, अपराजित and सर्वार्थसिद्धि. See also अनुत्तरोपपातिक. E. अ priv. and उत्तर.

anuttarayogatantra|अनुत्तरयोगतन्त्र
Tatpur. n. (-न्त्रम्) The name of the last of the four Bauddha Tantras, the Tantra of the supreme Yoga. (The other three are called क्रियातन्त्र, आचारतन्त्र and योगतन्त्र qq. vv.) E. अनुत्तर-योग and तन्त्र.

anuttaropapaatika|अनुत्तरोपपातिक
m. pl. (-काः) Apparently the same as अनुत्तर m. pl.: the name of the Jaina gods so called. According to a commentary it would mean literally ‘those who have the highest origin i. e. who are born in the five Vimánas’ from which the five classes of the अनुत्तराः derive their appellations. E. अनुत्तरोपपातिन् (अनुत्तर and उपपात, taddh. aff. इनि), taddh. aff. कन्(?).

anuttaropapaatikadashaa|अनुत्तरोपपातिकदशा
Bahuvr. f. pl. (-शाः) The name of the ninth of the twelve sacred writings of the Jainas: that  treating on the अनुत्तरोपपातिकाः (q. v.). E. अनुत्तरोपपातिक and दशा (acc. to a comm. in the sense of अध्ययन); but more probably अनुत्तº and दशन्, samásánta aff. डच्, like आसन्नदश &c.

anutpatti|अनुत्पत्ति
I. Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) The not taking origin or birth, the not being produced, the not arising (as in philosophy, e. g. of all knowledge at once, or of Prakŕiti &c.). See also अनुत्पत्तिसम. E. अ neg. and उत्पत्ति. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्तिः-त्तिः-त्ति) Having no origin or birth, not being produced. E. अ priv. and उत्पत्ति.

anutpattika|अनुत्पत्तिक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-की-कम्) (In Bauddha literature.) Having no origin or birth, not or not yet being produced. (The fem. -की belongs to Bauddha writings; in the classic language, it would be -का.) See the following. E. अनुत्पत्ति II., samásánta aff. कप्.

anutpattikadharmaxaanti|अनुत्पत्तिकधर्मक्षान्ति
Tatpur. f. (-न्तिः) (In Bauddha literature.) Enduring conditions which have not yet taken place i. e. reconciling one's mind to the conditions of a future life; one of the hundred-eight धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.) or means to comprehend the doctrine of Śákyamuni; ‘it leads to the reception of revelations’ i. e. it enables an enquirer to get possessed of the mysteries of the Bauddha doctrine. E. अनुत्पत्तिक-धर्म and क्षान्ति.

anutpattisama|अनुत्पत्तिसम
Tatpur. m. f. (-मः-मा) (In the Nyáya philosophy.) The sophism of the impossibility of origin or birth; viz. arguing that a thing cannot take origin, because a thing exists in consequence of an immaterial cause; as the latter, however, does not exist before the material cause and the instance proving the existence of such material cause, and as the material cause again depends upon what exists, and the instance upon the material cause, the thing itself can never come into existence: or origin in general is impossible. E. अनुत्पत्ति and सम. (With respect to the gender of this word and the ellipsis required to explain it, see the E. of अनित्यसम.)

anutpanna|अनुत्पन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्) Not born, not produced &c. See उत्पन्न. E. अ neg. and उत्पन्न.

anutpaada|अनुत्पाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) The not taking origin or birth, the not arising. E. अ neg. and उत्पाद.

anutpaadaxaanti|अनुत्पादक्षान्ति
Tatpur. f. (-न्तिः) (In Bauddha literature.) Enduring non-birth i. e. reconciling one's mind to not being born again; one of the hundred-eight धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.) or means to comprehend the doctrine of Śákyamuni; it is conducive to a clear apprehension of all that may impede (sc. the attainment of this desirable end). E. अनुत्पाद and क्षान्ति.

anutpaadana|अनुत्पादन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Not producing, not bringing forth. E. अ neg. and उत्पादन.

anutpaadya|अनुत्पाद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Not producible, eternal (e. g. प्रकृति or पुरुष in the Sánkhya philosophy). E. अ neg. and उत्पाद्य.

anutsaaha|अनुत्साह
I. Tatpur. m. (-हः) Want of effort or energy, in difference, unconcernedness. E. अ neg. and उत्साह. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-हः-हा-हम्) Without energy, indifferent, unconcerned. E. अ priv. and उत्साह.

anutsuka|अनुत्सुक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Not strongly attached to, not longing for &c. See उत्सुक. E. अ neg. and उत्सुक. 

anuda|अनुद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) (ved.) 1. A companion, a follower. E. दो with अनु, kŕit aff. क. Comp. अनुदेयी. BREAḲ. Giving like, liberal in a similar manner. E. दा with अनु, kŕit aff. क. In both meanings only in composition with अ priv. See अनानुद.

anudaka|अनुदक
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Without water, waterless. E. अ priv. and उदक.

anudatta|अनुदत्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Given back, returned. Also अनूत्त q. v. E. दा with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anudara|अनुदर
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Thin, lank. E. अ priv. and उदर.

anudarshana|अनुदर्शन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Looking after, considering. E. दृश् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anudarshin|अनुदर्शिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्शी-र्शिनी-र्शि) Looking after, considering, foreseeing. E. दृश् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anudaatta|अनुदात्त
Tatpur. (In Grammar.) 1. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Not elevated, not being pronounced with the accent called उदात्त (q. v.) or स्वरित (q. v.) (as the syllable of a word). BREAḲ. m. (-त्तः) The not elevated accent, the accent (see स्वर and वाह्यप्रयत्न) which is neither उदात्त (q. v.) nor स्वरित (q. v.) and which by the depression of the voice, it requires, prepares, as it were, for the greater effort in the pronunciation of the syllables accented with the उदात्त or स्वरित. This depression being the greatest when the syllable having the अनुदात्त accent, is immediately followed by a syllable accented with the उदात्त or स्वरित, the अनुदात्त is called in this case अनुदात्ततर ‘a very anudátta’. The mode of marking the अनुदात्त, is restricted, as is also the case with the other two accents, to the vaidik Sanhitás (Sanhitá-Pát́has) and Bráhmańas, and varies according to the different Vedas. In the Sanhitá, Pada and the Bráhmańas of the Ŕigveda, in the Sanhitá and Pada of the Yajurand Sanhitá of the Atharvaveda the Anudátta is marked with a horizontal line under the syllable so accented (thus becoming comparable also in graphic value to the sign of the Viráma, the horizontal line representing as it were the repose in accentuation); in the Bráhmańas of the White Yajurveda, it is not marked at all; and in the Sanhitá of the Sámaveda the anudátta syllable when anudáttatara before an udátta, or before a svarita syllable bearing the figures २ or ३, is marked with the figure ३ over it, except when it is preceded in the beginning of a verse by other anudátta syllables, in which case only the first anudátta syllable bears the figure ३, while the following anudátta syllables are left unmarked. If the anudáttatara is followed by a svarita syllable bearing the sign २र, the syllable so accented is marked with ३क. In the Pada-text of the Sámaveda the sign ३ denotes the anudáttatara before an udátta, if the latter occupies the second syllable from the beginning, or the syllable before an anudáttatara, if the latter is followed by a svarita, or lastly the anudátta accentuation of a syllable so marked and of all the syllables following it until an udátta or svarita syllable comes; the sign ३क or क denotes the anudáttatara immediately followed by a svarita. Compare also the terms नीच, निहत, न्यस्त, न्यस्ततर, नियत, निघात, न्यास, नियम and the radd. हन् with नि and यम् with नि.--In the native  lists of radicals, the Dhátupáthas, certain radicals have the anudátta accent as an इत् (q. v.) or अनुबन्ध (q. v.) connected with them i. e. as a technical sign for certain rules they are subject to with respect to derivation &c. See also अनुदात्तेत् and अनुदात्तोपदेश. E. अ neg. and अनुदात्त.

anudaattatara|अनुदात्ततर
m. (-रः) The अनुदात्त accent (or स्वर) or a syllable so accented when immediately preceding a syllable having the उदात्त or स्वरित accent. See under अनुदात्त. E. अनुदात्त, taddh. aff. तरप्.

anudaattatva|अनुदात्तत्व
n. (-त्वम्) The having or being the accent अनुदात्त. E. अनुदात्त, taddh. aff. त्व.

anudaattasvarita|अनुदात्तस्वरित
Karmadh. See नीचस्वरित. E. अनुदात्त and स्वरित.

anudaattaadi|अनुदात्तादि
Bahuvr. n. (-दि) (In Grammar.) A nominal base which is अनुदात्त (q. v.) in the first syllable. E. अनुदात्त and आदि; scil. प्रातिपदिक.

anudaattet|अनुदात्तेत्
Bahuvr. m. (-त्) (In Grammar.) A radical having in the Dhátupát́ha or the native list of radicals, the अनुदात्त accent as अनुबन्ध i. e. as a technical sign for certain rules of derivation &c. See the Appendix. E. अनुदात्त and इत् (the technical denomination of अनुबन्ध); scil. धातु.

anudaattodaya|अनुदात्तोदय
Bahuvr. n. (-यम्) (In Grammar.) A syllable followed by an अनुदात्त (q. v.) syllable. E. अनुदात्त and उदय; scil. अक्षर.

anudaattopadesha|अनुदात्तोपदेश
Bahuvr. m. (-शः). The same as अनुदात्तेत्. See s. v. उपदेश. E. अनुदात्त and उपदेश; scil. धातु.

anudaara|अनुदार
I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-रा-रम्) Not liberal, not generous, niggardly, mean. E. अ neg. and उदार. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. (-रः) Adhered to or followed by a wife. E. अनु and दार.

anudita|अनुदित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) I. Unrisen. II. Unsaid, unuttered. E. अ neg. and उदित.

anudinam|अनुदिनम्
Avyayíbh. Daily, every day. E. अनु and दिन.

anudivasam|अनुदिवसम्
Avyayíbh. Daily, every day. E. अनु and दिवस.

anudisham|अनुदिशम्
Avyayíbh. In every quarter, in every direction. E. अनु and दिश्, samásánta aff. टच्.

anudRShTi|अनुदृष्टि
Bahuvr.(?) f. (-ष्टिः) The proper name of the mother or ancestress of आनुदृष्टिनेय. E. अनु and दृष्टि ‘having her eyes after i. e. provident’.

anudeya|अनुदेय
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be given back, to be returned. (ved.) BREAḲ. f. (-यी) (ved.)<BR> ^1 Restitution, restoration(?).<BR> ^2 A female friend or companion. Comp. अनुद. E. दा with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anudesha|अनुदेश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 (In Grammar.) A rule or injunction relating to a preceding rule or injunction, to an उद्देश q. v. If there are several उद्देशाः followed by an equal number of अनुदेशाः, the first अनुदेशः is to be connected with the first उद्देश, the second अनुदेशः with the second उद्देशः and so on.<BR> ^2 Order, injunction in general. E. दिश् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anudeshin|अनुदेशिन्
m. f. n. (-शी-शिनी-शि) (In Grammar.) Being the object of an अनुदेश (q. v.) in distinction from उद्देशिन् (q. v.) the object of an उद्देश (q. v.); ‘समानां समसंख्यानां समपरिपठितानामुद्देशिनामनुदेशिनां च यथाक्रममुद्देशिभिः सहानुदेशिनः संबध्यन्ते।’. E. अनुदेश, taddh. aff. इनि. 

anuddhRta|अनुद्धृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not taken out, not taken away &c. See उद्धृत. (If in ritual books said of the Áhavaníya (q. v.) fire, it means that this fire is not yet taken from the Gárhapatya (q. v.) where it is kept.) E. अ neg. and उद्धृत.

anuddhRtaabhyastamaya|अनुद्धृताभ्यस्तमय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) The setting of the sun, while the Áhavaníya (q. v.) fire is not yet removed from the Gárhapatya (q. v.) where it is kept. E. अनुद्धृत (in the sense of the locative) and अभ्यस्तमय.

anudbhaTa|अनुद्भट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-टः-टा-टम्) Not exalted, lowlyminded, not lofty. E. अ neg. and उद्भट.

anudya|अनुद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) What must or ought not to be said, unspeakable, unutterable. Compare अवद्य. (The reading अनूद्य in the actual edition of Páń. III. 1. 101. is to be corrected to अनुद्य.) E. अ neg. and उद्य.

anudyoga|अनुद्योग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) Absence of exertion or effort, laziness. E. अ neg. and उद्योग.

anudraShTavya|अनुद्रष्टव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be recognised, to be seen, visible. E. दृश् with अनु, kŕit aff. तव्य.

anudruta|अनुद्रुत
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Followed, pursued. E. द्रु with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त. <BR>II. n. (-तम्) A measure of time in music, half a Druta, or one-fourth of a Mátrá or time taken to articulate a short vowel. E. अनु and द्रुत ‘an inferior or minor Druta’.

anudvaaha|अनुद्वाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) Celibacy. E. अ neg. and उद्वाह.

anudvigna|अनुद्विग्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ग्नः-ग्ना-ग्नम्) Easy, free from apprehension or perplexity. E. अन् neg. and उद्विग्न.

anudvega|अनुद्वेग
I. Tatpur. m. (-गः) Freedom from anxiety, the not being discomposed. E. अ neg. and उद्वेग. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-गः-गा-गम्) Free from anxiety. E. अ priv. and उद्वेग.

anudvegakara|अनुद्वेगकर
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रः-री-रम्) Not causing fear, not terrifying sc. by its appearance (e. g. as the staff of a man belonging to the three superior castes, or as a judge ought to be). E. अ neg. and उद्वेगकर.

anudhaavana|अनुधावन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) I.<BR> ^1 Chasing, pursuit, running after.<BR> ^2 (fig.) Pursuit of any object, research, investigation, meditation. II. Cleansing, purifying. E. धाव् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anudhyaana|अनुध्यान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Meditation, religious contemplation. E. ध्यै with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anudhyaayin|अनुध्यायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Meditating, reflecting. E. ध्यै with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anunaya|अनुनय
I. Tatpur. m. (-यः)<BR> ^1 Salutation, courtesy, shewing respect or adoration to a guest or deity, submission, humility.<BR> ^2 Humble supplication, conciliatory entreaty, reconcilement. E. नी with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-यम्) According to propriety, agreeably to what is required, to circumstance; e. g. अब्रवीदनुनयं वचः. E. अनु and नय.

anunayapratighaprahaaNa|अनुनयप्रतिघप्रहाण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In Buddhistic literature.) One of the 108 धर्मालोकमुख (q. v.), (probably) relinquishing what is adverse to respectful conduct or humility. E. अनुनय-प्रतिघ and प्रहाण.

anunayamaana|अनुनयमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Showing respect or adoration, honouring. E. नी with अनु, kŕit aff. शानच्, and ágama मुक्. 

anunayaamantraNa|अनुनयामन्त्रण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) An address marked with conciliation, conciliatory address. E. अनुनय and आमन्त्रण.

anunayin|अनुनयिन्
m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Courteous, humble, submissive. E. अनुनय, taddh. aff. इनि.

anunaada|अनुनाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः) Sound, consequent sound, vibration, echo. E. अनु and नाद.

anunaadin|अनुनादिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दी-दिनी-दि) Sounding after, echoing; e. g. कलानुनादिन् q. v. E. अनु and नादिन्.

anunaayikaa|अनुनायिका
Tatpur. f. (-का) A secondary or inferior female character in a drama, one subordinate to the नायिका or principal female character, such as ‘a friend, a female devotee, a slave, a nurse or female artisans’. E. अनु and नायिका.

anunaasha|अनुनाश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) The name of a country (? this meaning is doubtful). E. अनु and नाश.

anunaasika|अनुनासिक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) (In Grammar.) Uttered through the nose, nasal (see also रक्त), viz.<BR> ^1 A nasal sound in general, it being pronounced through the nose and with the appropriate organ of speech, as ङ् through the nose and the throat, ञ् through the nose and with the palate &c.<BR> ^2 (Conditionally) a vowel or य्, व्, ल्; in this case the nasal nature of the sound is indicated by the sign ंँ. (N. B. य्ंँ or व्ंँ represent the value of य् or व् preceded by म्; ल्ंँ that of ल् preceded by म् or न्. In the pause a final vowel may be anunásika. A short anunásika vowel, when not occurring in a pause, represents apparently always the value of the same vowel and म् or न्; it must be, in general, the last vowel sound of the former part of a compound or of the word itself, followed by a final sibilant, e. g. संँस्कर्ता instead of सम्स्-कर्ता, पुंँश्चली = पुम्स्-चली, तस्मिंँस्त्वा = तस्मिन्स्-त्वा. Only a few exceptions of this rule are mentioned by the vaidik grammarians, e. g. अमिनन्तंँ एवैः, when अ of न्त is anunásika, although it does neither stand in a pause nor represent more than its own sound.--A long anunásika vowel, when not occurring in a pause, may be generally considered as representing the value of its short vowel and an original न्त्स् or of its short vowel and न्त्, provided स् or its substitute has been preserved; e. g. महांँ इन्द्रः = महन्त्स् इन्द्रः, दधन्वांँ यः = दधन्वन्त्स् यः, सर्गांँ इव = सर्गन्त्स् इव or महांँश्चरति = महन्त्स् चरति, दस्यूंँरेकः = दस्युन्त्स् एकः. The material difference that prevails between the anunásika (ंँ) and the anuswára (ं) sound, does not appear to have been kept alive beyond the period of the vaidik literature, when an interchange between both was not deemed legitimate; according to the grammarians of the classical period, in the latter the anunásika may be replaced by the anuswára. The sign of the anunásika (ंँ), however, is but seldom met with in the ordinary Mss. referring to the postvaidik literature; and from the reasons stated, its use in vaidik Mss. is objectionable, when it occurs in words like यशांँसि, धनूंँषि, विश्वेषांँ हितः or in मंँहिष्ठ, वाजंँ सनिषत्, इन्द्रंँ स्तवाम and similar instances in which the long nasal vowel does not represent more than the value of a short vowel and a nasal, or in which the short nasal vowel is not followed by a final sibilant.) E. अनु and नासिका.

anunaasikatva|अनुनासिकत्व
n. (-त्वम्) The being nasal, nasality. E. अनुनासिक, taddh. aff. त्व. 

anunaasikalopa|अनुनासिकलोप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) The dropping or disappearance of a nasal. E. अनुनासिक and लोप.

anunaasikaatva|अनुनासिकात्व
n. (-त्वम्) The nasality of आ. E. अनुनासिकआ, taddh. aff. त्व.

anunaasikaadi|अनुनासिकादि
Bahuvr. m. (-दिः) A combined consonant beginning with a nasal (न् &c.) as न्द् &c. E. अनुनासिक and आदि; scil. संयोग.

anunaasikaanta|अनुनासिकान्त
Bahuvr. m. (-न्तः) A radical ending in a nasal; as तन्, गम् &c. E. अनुनासिक and अन्त; scil. धातु.

anunaasikopadha|अनुनासिकोपध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्)<BR> ^1 Having a nasal penultimate.<BR> ^2 Having a preceding syllable pronounced with nasality (as a विवृत्ति or hiatus between सचांँ इन्द्रः &c.). E. अनुनासिक and उपधा.

anuniniiShu|अनुनिनीषु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-षुः-षुः-षु) Desirous of showing respect, of reconciling, of pleasing. E. नी in the desider., with अनु, kŕit aff. उ.

anunirdesha|अनुनिर्देश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) Telling, describing &c. (see निर्देश) in accordance with, in the same order as something previously told; e. g. भूयसामुपदिष्टानां क्रियाणामथ कर्मणाम्। क्रमशो योऽनुनिर्देशो यथासंख्यं तदुच्यते. E. अनु and निर्देश.

anunirvaapa|अनुनिर्वाप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Subsequently pouring out (e. g. clarified butter); a sacrificial rite occurring in several sacrifices. E. अनु and निर्वाप.

anunirvaapyaa|अनुनिर्वाप्या
f. (-प्या) A religious ceremony referring to the अनुनिर्वाप. E. अनुनिर्वाप, taddh. aff. यत्.

anuniiti|अनुनीति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) The same as अनुनय. E. नी with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anunnatagaatra|अनुन्नतगात्र
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्रः-त्रा-त्रम्) Whose limbs are not too full (one of the eighty secondary signs or अनुव्यञ्जन which characterize a great man according to the Buddhists. E. अ neg. and उन्नतगात्र.

anunmatta|अनुन्मत्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Sane, sober, not wild, not mad. E. अ neg. and उन्मत्त.

anunmaada|अनुन्माद
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-दः-दा-दम्). The same as अनुन्मत्त. E. अ priv. and उन्माद.

anupakaarin|अनुपकारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Not assisting, neglecting, ungrateful. E. अ neg. and उपकारिन्.

anupakRta|अनुपकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Unassisted. E. अ neg. and उपकृत.

anupaxita|अनुपक्षित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not destroyed, not perished. E. अ neg. and उपक्षित.

anupagiita|अनुपगीत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not praised, not made known. (In a vaidik passage, where this word occurs, it means ‘not praised by others’.) E. अ neg. and उपगीत.

anupaghaataarjita|अनुपघातार्जित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) (In Law.) Acquired without injury (to the father's property). E. अ neg. and उपघात-अर्जित.

anupaghnat|अनुपघ्नत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्-न्ती-त्) Not doing injury (e. g. पितृद्रव्यम् to the father's property). E. अ neg. and उपघ्नत्.

anupaja|अनुपज
Tatpur. n. (-जम्). See अनूपज.

anupajiivaniiya|अनुपजीवनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) I. Tatpur. Who does not afford means to live upon. E. अ neg. and उपजीवनीय. <BR>II. Bahuvr. Who has nothing to live upon. E. अ priv. and उपजीवनीय.

anupaThita|अनुपठित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Recited. E. पठ with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त. 

anupaThitin|अनुपठितिन्
m. f. n. (-ती-तिनी-ति) Having recited, with a noun in the locative, e. g. अनुपठिती वेदे ‘having recited the Veda. E. अनुपठित, taddh. aff. इनि.

anupatana|अनुपतन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Falling on or upon.<BR> ^2 Following.<BR> ^3 (In Arithmetic.) Proportion. E. पत् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anupati|अनुपति
Avyayíbh. After the husband. E. अनु and पति.

anupatita|अनुपतित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Fallen, descended.<BR> ^2 Followed. E. पत् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anupatha|अनुपथ
I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-थः-था-थम्) Following the road. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-थः-था-थम्) Having favourable roads (a vaidik epithet of the Maruts). E. अनु and पथिन्, samásánta aff. अ. <BR>III. Avyayíbh. (-थम्) Along the road. E. अनु and पथिन्, samásánta aff. टच्.

anupad|अनुपद्
Tatpur. f. (-द्) Food (according to a vaidik comm. ‘because it is daily searched for). E. पद् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

anupada|अनुपद
I. Bahuvr. m. (-दः) A proper name (explained by a comm. अनुगतं पदमस्य); his descendants are called अनुपदाः or आनुपदयः. <BR>II. Tatpur. n. (-दम्) A burden, a word or passage repeated. <BR>III. Avyayíbh. (-दम्)<BR> ^1 Upon the foot, after, immediately after, with a noun in the genitive case.<BR> ^2 Step by step.<BR> ^3 Word for word. E. अनु and पद.

anupadasuutra|अनुपदसूत्र
Tatpur. n. (-त्रम्) The name of a work which interprets the Shad́vinśabráhmańa word for word. E. अनुपद (III.) and सूत्र.

anupadasvat|अनुपदस्वत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्वान्-स्वती-स्वत्) (ved.) Probably: not diminishing, not decaying. E. अ neg. and उपदस्वत्.

anupadin|अनुपदिन्
m. (-दी) A searcher, an inquirer, one who follows or seeks for, with a noun in the genit., e. g. मृगस्यानुपदी, अनुपद्युष्ट्राणाम्. E. अनुपद (III.), taddh. aff. इनि.

anupadiinaa|अनुपदीना
f. (-ना) A boot, a buskin. E. अनुपद (III.), taddh. aff. ख.

anupadRShTin|अनुपदृष्टिन्
m. (-ष्टी) A proper name. E. अ-उपदृष्ट, taddh. aff. इनि(?).

anupadeShTR|अनुपदेष्टृ
Tatpur. m. (-ष्टा) One who does not advise or instruct; e. g. हितानुपदेष्टा कुत्सितः सखा. E. अ neg. and उपदेष्टृ.

anupadha|अनुपध
Bahuvr. m. (-धः) Not preceded by a letter (liter. having no penultimate; as a sibilant or ह् which may be doubled if they are followed by a consonant and not preceded by a letter; e. g. श्श्चोतन्त्यभितः, ह्ह्वयाम्यग्निम्). E. अ priv. and उपधा; scil. ऊष्मन्.

anupanaaha|अनुपनाह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) (In Buddhistic doctrine.) One of the 108 धर्मालोकमुख q. v.; (perhaps) want of attachment(?). E. अ neg. and उपनाह.

anupanyasta|अनुपन्यस्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्तः-स्ता-स्तम्) Not laid down, not established, not clearly shown. E. अ neg. and उपन्यस्त.

anupanyaasa|अनुपन्यास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) Failure of proof or determination, the not establishing satisfactorily. E. अ neg. and उपन्यास.

anupapatti|अनुपपत्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः)<BR> ^1 The not taking place, failing to be, failure.<BR> ^2 The not being applied or applicable (as a rule in grammar &c.).<BR> ^3 The not being conclusive (as an argument &c. brought to support a doctrine).<BR> ^4 Absence of the means of subsistence(?). E. अ neg. and उपपत्ति. 

anupapanna|अनुपपन्न
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्नः-न्ना-न्नम्)<BR> ^1 Uneffected, unaccomplished.<BR> ^2 Not applicable, not relevant.<BR> ^3 Inconclusive (as an argument).<BR> ^4 Undemonstrated, unsubstantiated.<BR> ^5 Not having means of subsistence(?). E. अ neg. and उपपन्न.

anupapaadaka|अनुपपादक
Bahuvr. m. pl. (-काः) (In the Buddhistic doctrine of Nepal) a class of Buddhas which is of non-material origin, also called ध्यानिबुद्धाः ‘the Buddhas of contemplation’; in contradistinction from the मानुषिबुद्धाः or the seven Buddhas of human origine, the last of which is Śákyamuni. E. अ priv. and उपपादक lit. ‘without a parent’.

anupaplava|अनुपप्लव
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-वः-वा-वम्) Free from misfortune, not distressed. E. अ priv. and उपप्लव.

anupapluta|अनुपप्लुत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्). The same as the preceding. E. अ neg. and उपप्लुत.

anupabaadha|अनुपबाध
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) (ved.) Not obstructed, not injured. E. अ priv. and उपबाधा.

anupama|अनुपम
Bahuvr. I. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) Incomparable, excellent, best. <BR>II. f. (-मा) The female elephant of the south-west (as the wife of the elephant Kumuda) or according to others, of the north-east (as the wife of the elephant Supratíka). E. अ priv. and उपमा.

anupamamati|अनुपममति
Bahuvr. m. (-तिः) The proper name of a contemporary of Śákyamuni, one of those to whom the Buddha expounded his doctrine. E. अनुपम and मति ‘of incomparable intellect’.

anupamardana|अनुपमर्दन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Not refuting a charge. E. अ neg. and उपमर्दन.

anupamita|अनुपमित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Incomparable. E. अ neg. and उपमित.

anupameya|अनुपमेय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Incomparable. E. अ neg. and उपमेय.

anupayukta|अनुपयुक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Useless, unsuitable, unserviceable. E. अ neg. and उपयुक्त (as according to a law book, ‘vaidik writings to fools’).

anupayoga|अनुपयोग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) Unserviceableness, uselessness. E. अ neg. and उपयोग.

anuparata|अनुपरत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not stopped, not ceased. E. अ neg. and उपरत.

anuparidhi|अनुपरिधि
Avyayíbh. Along or near the परिधि q. v. E. अनु and परिधि.

anupalaxita|अनुपलक्षित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Unseen, unperceived.<BR> ^2 Unmarked, undiscriminated. E. अ neg. and उपलक्षित.

anupalabdha|अनुपलब्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ब्धः-ब्धा-ब्धम्)<BR> ^1 Unobtained.<BR> ^2 Unperceived, imperceptible. E. अ neg. and उपलब्ध.

anupalabdhatva|अनुपलब्धत्व
n. (-त्वम्). The same as अनुपलम्भ q. v. E. अनुपलब्ध, taddh. aff. त्व.

anupalabdhi|अनुपलब्धि
Tatpur. m. (-ब्धिः) Not perceiving, non-perception, non-recognition (esp. used in the Sútras of various philos. systems and the writings relating to them. See also अनुपलम्भ and अनुपलब्धिसम). E. अ neg. and उपलब्धि.

anupalabdhisama|अनुपलब्धिसम
Tatpur. m. f. (-मः-मा) (In the Nyáya philosophy.) A sophism on non-perception; viz. arguing: ‘because the non-perception of an object cannot be perceived, therefore the non-perception of the object does not exist  and consequently the non-existence of the object cannot exist i. e. the object itself must exist’. This sophism is attributed by the Nyáya e. g. to those who maintain the eternity of sound on the ground that ‘the non-perception of sound antecedently to pronunciation’--the reason alleged by the Nyáya for its non-eternity--may be refuted in the manner explained. E. अनुपलब्धि and सम (m. scil. प्रतिषेध or विकल्प or प्रयोग; f. scil. जाति; comp. for the meaning of these words the E. of अनित्यसम).

anupalabhyamaana|अनुपलभ्यमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Not being perceived, not being seen. E. अ neg. and उपलभ्यमान.

anupalambha|अनुपलम्भ
Tatpur. m. (-म्भः) The not being perceived, ascertained, or the not being perceptible, ascertainable; e. g. तदनुपलब्धेरनुपलम्भादावरणोपलब्धिः ‘the perception of a covering is from the non-perception there of not being perceptible’. See अनुपलब्धि and अनुपलब्धिसम. E. अ neg. and उपलम्भ.

anupaviitin|अनुपवीतिन्
Tatpur. m. (-ती) One who does not wear the cord of his caste. E. अ neg. and उपवीतिन्.

anupashaya|अनुपशय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) (In Medicine.) Any aggravating thing or circumstance that increases the disease. E. अ neg. and उपशय.

anupashaanta|अनुपशान्त
Tatpur. 1. m. (-न्तः-न्ता-न्तम्) Not calm, not tranquil. BREAḲ. m. (-न्तः) The name of a Bauddha mendicant. E. अ neg. and उपशान्त.

anupashya|अनुपश्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) Looking after, considering attentively. See प्रत्ययानुपश्य. E. दृश् with अनु, kŕit aff. श.

anupasaMhaarin|अनुपसंहारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) (In philosophy.) Non-exclusive, purely affirmative, as an argument of allcomprehensiveness whose subject does not exclude any thing; as such an argument would lead to a conclusion of a purely formal kind, i. e. to no real conclusion, अनुपसंहारिन् is the characteristic of one of the modes of हेत्वाभास (q. v.) or ‘semblance of argument’; compare also अनैकान्तिक. E. अ neg. and उपसंहारिन्.

anupasarga|अनुपसर्ग
I. Tatpur. m. (-र्गः) (In Grammar.) A particle which (or when it) is not an उपसर्ग (q. v.), for instance अन्तर् in compounds like अन्तर्वण, or अभि, परि in formations like अभिसावकीयति, परिसावकीयति, when अभि and परि do not qualify the radical सु but the denom. सावकीयति. E. अ neg. and उपसर्ग. <BR>II. Bahuvr. m. (-र्गः)<BR> ^1 Without an उपसर्ग q. v. (as a radical).<BR> ^2 Without obstruction, free from impediment; an epithet of ईश्वर. E. अ priv. and उपसर्ग.

anupasargatva|अनुपसर्गत्व
n. (-त्वम्) The not being an उपसर्ग q. v. (see the preceding). E. अनुपसर्ग (I.), taddh. aff. त्व.

anupaskRta|अनुपस्कृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not vitiated, not blamed, blameless (e. g. the law of Manu).<BR> ^2 Not ornamented, unfinished; e. g. राजतमनुपस्कृतम् a silver vessel not enchased. E. अ neg. and उपस्कृत.

anupasthaana|अनुपस्थान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Absence. E. अ neg. and उपस्थान.

anupasthaapana|अनुपस्थापन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Not bringing near, not having ready or at hand. E. अ neg. and उपस्थापन.

anupasthaapayat|अनुपस्थापयत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यन्-यन्ती-यत्) Not offering, not having ready or at hand (e. g. money). E. अ neg. and उपस्थापयत्. 

anupasthaapita|अनुपस्थापित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not ready, not at hand, not offered or produced. E. अ neg. and उपस्थापित.

anupasthaayin|अनुपस्थायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Absent, distant. E. अ neg. and उपस्थायिन्.

anupasthita|अनुपस्थित
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not approached &c.<BR> ^2 Not ready, not fresh in memory.<BR> ^3 Sunk into oblivion (as a science &c.). <BR>II. n. (-तम्) (In Grammar.) A word which is not उपस्थित (q. v.) i. e. which is not the word इति as it occurs in the writings referring to the recitation of the vaidik hymns. E. अ neg. and उपस्थित.

anupasthiti|अनुपस्थिति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Absence. E. अ neg. and उपस्थिति.

anupahata|अनुपहत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not injured, not impaired, not obstructed.<BR> ^2 Not polluted, not vitiated, not made impure. E. अ neg. and उपहत.

anupahatakruShTa|अनुपहतक्रुष्ट
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Who has (in his aspect) nothing that indicates injury or anger (one of the eighty secondary signs (or अनुव्यञ्जन) which characterize a great man, acc to the Buddhists. E. अ priv. and उपहत-क्रुष्ट.

anupahuuta|अनुपहूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not summoned, not invoked.<BR> ^2 Not summoned in a loud voice, invoked in a low voice. E. अ 1. neg. 2. deter. and उपहूत.

anupaakRta|अनुपाकृत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Not prepared or made fit for sacrificial purposes (as a victim before the muttering of prayers over it, or as the प्रातरनुवाक before the completion of the ceremonies required for it &c.). E. अ neg. and उपाकृत.

anupaakRtamaaMsa|अनुपाकृतमांस
Karmadh. n. (-सम्) Flesh of an animal which has not been made fit for sacrificial purposes by the recital of vaidik hymns, flesh of an animal which has not been killed at a sacrifice. (A Brahmańa is forbidden to eat such flesh.) E. अनुपाकृत and मांस.

anupaakhya|अनुपाख्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ख्यः-ख्या-ख्यम्) Not clearly perceptible. E. अ neg. and उपाख्य.

anupaata|अनुपात
Tatpur. m. (-तः)<BR> ^1 Falling subsequently upon, alighting or descending upon in succession.<BR> ^2 Following.<BR> ^3 (In arithmetic.) Proportion, the rule of three. E. अनु and पात or पत् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण.

anupaataka|अनुपातक
Tatpur. n. (-कम्) A heinous offence, one similar to the four great crimes (महापातक) which are:<BR> ^a. Causing the death of a Bráhmańa (directly or indirectly).<BR> ^b. Drinking spirits.<BR> ^c. Stealing (acc. to the comm. ‘gold from a Bráhmańa’).<BR> ^d. Committing incest with the wife of a father, natural or spiritual. The अनुपातक mentioned by Manu are the following: 1. False boasting of superiority (as pretending to be a Bráhmańa or conversant with the four Vedas, if one is not); 2. Malignant report, before a king, of crimes (comm.: punishable by death)--omitted by Yájnavalkya--; 3. Falsely accusing a spiritual preceptor; 4. Forgetting the Veda; 5. Showing contempt of the Veda (comm.: by resorting to heretical writings); 6. Giving false evidence (omitted by Yájnav.); 7. Killing a friend (comm.: not a Bráhmańa, this case being the first महापातक); 8. (Knowingly) eating things prohibited (i. e. food fit only for a Śúdra, as garlick &c.) or unfit to be tasted (as excrements &c.); [9. (According to Yájnavalkya) Kissing a woman  while in menstruation; 10. (Acc. to Yájn.) Deceitfulness (i. e. saying one thing and doing another)]; 11. Appropriating a deposit (comm.: not the gold of a Bráhmańa (this case being the third महापातक) or acc. to another author. a deposit not of gold, if it belongs to a Bráhmańa); 12--17. Stealing a man, a horse, silver, a piece of land, a diamond or a gem [acc. to Yájnavalkya, 12--17. a horse, a gem, a man, a woman, a piece of land, and a cow]; 18--22. Sexual intercourse with one's own sister, with little girls before they have attained to puberty, with women of the lowest tribe (comm.: a Cháńdálí), with the wives of a friend or of a son [to which Yájnavalkya adds: 23--30. with a woman of the same gotra or family, the sister of a father or mother, the wife of a maternal uncle, the wife of one's father, the daughter or wife of a spiritual teacher or one's own daughter; Nárada adds moreover: 31--40. with a mother in law, the wife of a paternal uncle or of a pupil, the friend of a sister, one who comes for protection, the wife of one who carries on the government of the country--comm.: if he is not a Kshatriya--, a nurse, a female mendicant, a female devotee and a woman of the Bráhmańa class.]-Similar to the first Mahápátaka are the Anupátakas, acc. to Manu, 1--3, acc. to Yájnavalkya, 3--5 and 7. Similar to the second Mahápátaka are the Anup., acc. to Manu, 4--8; acc. to Yájnav., 1. 8. 9. 10. Similar to the third Maháp. are the Anup., acc. to Manu and Yájnav., 11--17. Similar to the fourth Maháp. are, according to Manu, the Anupát. 18--22, acc. to Yájnav. (and Nárada, Yama &c.), 18-40. E. अनु and पातक.

anupaatam|अनुपातम्
Tatpur. ind. Following, going after, having followed or gone after (used in phrases implying reiteration; for the construction comp. s. v. अनुप्रपातम्); e. g. लतानुपातं कुसुमान्यगृह्लात् ‘following creeper for creeper &c.’, क्रीडन्भुजङ्गेन गृहानुपातं कश्चिद्यथा जीवति संशयस्थः &c. ‘like as a snake-catcher who plays with the snake is always in uncertainty whenever he goes house for house &c.’. E. पत् with अनु, kŕit aff. णमुल्.

anupaatin|अनुपातिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ती-तिनी-ति)<BR> ^1 Following.<BR> ^2 Resulting from e. g. शब्दज्ञानानुपाती वस्तुशून्यो विकल्पः ‘imagination is (a notion) devoid of reality, resulting from knowledge conveyed by words’. E. पत् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anupaana|अनुपान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 (In Medicine.) A fluid vehicle in medicine, drink taken after or with medicine.<BR> ^2 (In a passage of the Chhánd. Upan.) Drink which is near or stands close by. E. अनु and पान.

anupaanatka|अनुपानत्क
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-त्कः-त्का-त्कम्) Without shoes. E. अ priv. and उपानह्, samásánta aff. कप्.

anupaaniiya|अनुपानीय
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be drunk after. E. पा with अनु, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्. BREAḲ. n. (-यम्) Drink which is near (see अनुपान). E. अनु and पानीय. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) What is used as a vehicle (in medicine). E. अनुपान, taddh. aff. छ.

anupaalana|अनुपालन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Preserving, guarding; e. g. विद्यानुपालन keeping to science, studying. E. पा, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्. 

anupaalayat|अनुपालयत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्-न्ती-त्)<BR> ^1 Preserving, taking care of; e. g. अभिवर्षति योऽनुपालयन्विधिवीजानि विवेकवारिणा &c.<BR> ^2 (Accord. to a comm.) Neglecting, disregarding; e. g. अनुपालयतामुदेष्यतीं प्रभुशक्तिं द्विषतामनीहया। अपयान्त्यचिरान्महीभुजां जननिर्वादभयादिव श्रियः (the comm. referring अनुपालयताम् = उपेक्षमाणानाम् not to द्विषताम् but to महीभुजाम्). E. पा, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. शतृ.

anupaalin|अनुपालिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ली-लिनी-लि) Preserving, cherishing, guarding; e. g. विद्यानुपालिन्. E. पा, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anupaalu|अनुपालु
Tatpur. n. (-लु) The name of a plant (wild Calladium escul.). It is doubtful whether the word is genuine Sanskrit. E. unknown.

anupaavRtta|अनुपावृत्त
Tatpur. m. pl. (-त्ताः) The name of a people. E. अ neg. and उपावृत्त.

anupaarshva|अनुपार्श्व
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्श्वः-र्श्वा-र्श्वम्) Lateral. E. अनु and पार्श्व.

anupuruSha|अनुपुरुष
Tatpur. m. (-षः)<BR> ^1 The man spoken of before, the said man.<BR> ^2 A man who follows, a follower. E. अनु and पुरुष.

anupuShpa|अनुपुष्प
Bahuvr.(?) m. (-ष्पः) A kind of read (Saccharum sara). See also शर. E. अनु and पुष्प.

anupuurva|अनुपूर्व
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्वः-र्वा-र्वम्)<BR> ^1 Following what precedes, successive.<BR> ^2 Orderly, in regular or proper order; अनुपूर्वम् used adv., in regular or proper order, successively. Comp. अनुपूर्वशस्.

anupuurvakesha|अनुपूर्वकेश
Bahuvr. m. (-शः) Whose hairs are grown in perfect order; one of the eighty secondary signs or अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. which indicate the ‘great man’, accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and केश.

anupuurvagaatra|अनुपूर्वगात्र
Bahuvr. m. (-त्रः) Whose limbs are regular or symmetrical; one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (compare the preceding), accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and गात्र.

anupuurvaja|अनुपूर्वज
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Born of parents in the regular sequence of the castes. Comp. अनुलोमज. E. अनुपूर्व and ज.

anupuurvatva|अनुपूर्वत्व
n. (-त्वम्). The same as आनुपूर्व्य q. v. E. अनुपूर्व, taddh. aff. त्व.

anupuurvadaMShTra|अनुपूर्वदंष्ट्र
Bahuvr. m. (-ष्ट्रः) Whose (large?) teeth are grown in a regular manner or symmetrically; one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (compare अनुपूर्वकेश); accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and दंष्ट्रा.

anupuurvanaabhi|अनुपूर्वनाभि
Bahuvr. m. (-भिः) Whose navel is regular (acc. to an interpretation, whose navel turns to the right); one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (comp. the preced.); accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and नाभि.

anupuurvapaaNilekha|अनुपूर्वपाणिलेख
Bahuvr. m. (-खः) Whose lines of the hands are regular (acc. to an interpretation: extended); one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (comp. the two preced.), accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and पाणि-लेखा.

anupuurvabhruu|अनुपूर्वभ्रू
Bahuvr. m. (-भ्रूः) Whose eye-brows are regular (acc. to an interpret.: well shaped or with hairs in the proper order); one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (comp. the three preced.); accord. to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and भ्रू.

anupuurvavatsaa|अनुपूर्ववत्सा
Bahuvr. f. (-त्सा) A cow which bears one calf after an other, an excellent cow. E. अनुपूर्व and वत्स. 

anupuurvashas|अनुपूर्वशस्
ind. In regular order or succession, from the first, from above downwards; also followed by a noun in the genitive. E. अनुपूर्व, taddh. aff. शस्.

anupuurvaanguli|अनुपूर्वाङ्गुलि
Bahuvr. m. (-लिः) Whose fingers are grown in a regular or graceful manner; one of the eighty अनुव्यञ्जन q. v. (comp. अनुपूर्वकेश); according to the Buddhists. E. अनुपूर्व and अङ्गुलि.

anupeta|अनुपेत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Not endowed with &c.<BR> ^2 Not invested with the characteristic (caste-)string. E. अ neg. and उपेत.

anupoShaNa|अनुपोषण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Not fasting. E. अ neg. and उपोषण.

anuptashasya|अनुप्तशस्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्यः-स्या-स्यम्) Fallow (meadowground &c.). E. अ neg. and उप्तशस्य.

anuptrima|अनुप्त्रिम
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) Not produced by sowing, grown wild. E. अ neg. and उप्त्रिम.

anupradaana|अनुप्रदान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Giving, gift, donation. E. दा with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuprapaatam|अनुप्रपातम्
Tatpur. ind. Following, going after, having followed or gone after. (Used in phrases which imply reiteration; either in composition with a noun in the sense of an accusative, or when not compounded with a noun, following the noun which then is repeated, or repeated itself after the noun, which then is not repeated; e. g. गेहानुप्रपातमास्ते or गेहं गेहमनुप्रपातमास्ते or गेहमनुप्रपातमनुप्रपातमास्ते ‘having gone house by house he sits down’. Compare अनुपातम्. E. अनु and प्रपातम् (पत् with प्र, kŕit aff. णमुल्).

anuprapaadam|अनुप्रपादम्
Tatpur. ind. The same as the preceding and used in the same manner, e. g. गेहानुप्रपादम् &c. See the preceding. E. पद् with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. णमुल्.

anupramaaNa|अनुप्रमाण
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Of proportionate length (as a surgical instrument). E. अनु and प्रमाण.

anuprayujyamaana|अनुप्रयुज्यमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Added afterwards, joined subsequently (as a word). E. अनु and प्रयुज्यमान.

anuprayoktavya|अनुप्रयोक्तव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be added afterwards or subsequently (as a word). E. अनु and प्रयोक्तव्य.

anuprayoga|अनुप्रयोग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) Adding or joining afterwards, a subsequent addition (as of a word). E. अनु and प्रयोग.

anupraroha|अनुप्ररोह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) Growing or budding in conformity with. E. अनु and प्ररोह.

anupravachana|अनुप्रवचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्). Probably the same as अनुवचन q. v. E. अनु and प्रवचन.

anupravachaniiya|अनुप्रवचनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Referring to, having for its object the अनुप्रवचन. E. अनुप्रवचन, taddh. aff. छ.

anupravesha|अनुप्रवेश
Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 Returning.<BR> ^2 Entering. See अनुप्रवेशम्. E. अनु and प्रवेश.

anupraveshana|अनुप्रवेशन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Returning.<BR> ^2 Entering E. अनु and प्रवेशन.

anupraveshaniiya|अनुप्रवेशनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Referring to the return or entering, having the return or entering for its object. E. अनुप्रवेशन, taddh. aff. छ.

anupravesham|अनुप्रवेशम्
Tatpur. ind.<BR> ^1 Returning.<BR> ^2 Entering; used like अनुप्रपातम् q. v. E. अनु and प्रवेशम् (विश् with प्र, kŕit aff. णमुल्).

anuprashna|अनुप्रश्न
Tatpur. m. (-श्नः) A question referring to what has  been said before (e. g. by the spiritual teacher). E. अनु and प्रश्न, or प्रच्छ् with अनु, kŕit aff. नङ्.

anuprasakti|अनुप्रसक्ति
Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः) Connexion with, esp. logical connexion. E. अनु and प्रसक्ति.

anuprasarpin|अनुप्रसर्पिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्पी-र्पिणी-र्पि) Going after, following. E. सृप् with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anuprastha|अनुप्रस्थ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्थः-स्था-स्थम्) Latitudinal. E. अनु and प्रस्थ.

anupraharaNa|अनुप्रहरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Throwing into. E. हृ with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anupraapta|अनुप्राप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्)<BR> ^1 Obtained, found.<BR> ^2 Reached, arrived. E. आप् with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anupraasa|अनुप्रास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) (In Rhetoric.) Repetition of similar letters, syllables or words, alliteration or rhyme; an अलंकार or mode of writing elegantly, so far as the sound is concerned (see शब्दालंकार) with five varieties; see छेकानुप्रास, वृत्त्यनुप्रास, श्रुत्यनुप्रास, अन्त्यानुप्रास and लाटानुप्रास; see also उद्भटानुप्रास. E. अनु and प्रास or अस् with प्र and अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuplava|अनुप्लव
Tatpur. m. f. (-वः-वी) A companion, a follower. E. प्लु with अनु, kŕit aff. अच् and टित्.

anubaddha|अनुबद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Bound to, connected with. E. बन्ध् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anubandha|अनुबन्ध
Tatpur. I. m. (-न्धः)<BR> ^1 Binding, confining.<BR> ^2 Connexion, association, attachment; close relation; e. g. पूर्वाभ्यस्तस्मृत्यनुबन्धः ‘connexion with the memory of things previously acquired’. नीवारादिषु चोदनानुबन्धः ‘the injunction relates to or concerns wild rice &c. (not व्रीहि).<BR> ^3 An uninterrupted series, e. g. वैरानुबन्धः a series of hostilities or heroic deeds.<BR> ^4 Consequence, result, e. g. पूर्वकृतफलानुबन्धात्तदुत्पत्तिः ‘it (the body) is produced in consequence of the fruits of its former deeds’.<BR> ^5 Cause esp. of a crime &c., e. g. अनुबन्धं परिज्ञाय…दण्डं पातयेत् let (the king) having ascertained the cause (comm.: of the offence) inflict punishment; or of an untoward event &c., e. g. विरात्रे चागतं कस्मात्कोऽनुबन्धश्च तेऽभवत् ‘why hast thou come so late in the night and what was the cause (comm.: of the delay)?’<BR> ^6 Commencement, beginning.<BR> ^7 A child (this meaning seems doubtful, at least as regards its etymol. interpretation; acc. to some it would be qualified as मुख्यानुयायिन् ‘following the chief i. e. the father &c. at the marriage ceremony &c.; the instance given however would not seem to countenance the meaning viz. बालकानुबन्धेन यात्राभङ्गो मा भूत् ‘let the festival not be disturbed by the incumbrance of children’; accord. to others the meaning ‘child’ would imply the tie of affection).<BR> ^8 (In the system of the native grammarians.) An indicatory letter which is annexed to radicals (धातु), nominal bases (प्रातिपदिक), affixes (प्रत्यय), particles (निपात), inserted letters (आगम) and substitutes (आदेश), to mark some peculiarity in the accent, inflection or derivation; for instance an indicatory इ denotes that verbs require the insertion of a nasal before their final consonant; the anubandha may be a vowel (in this case it is अनुनासिक q. v. in the system of Páńini) or a consonant. Being a mere technical element it cannot occur in real language. Instances of anubandhas may be gathered from the etymologies in this  Dictionary. See also इत्.<BR> ^9 Any thing small or little, a part, a small part.<BR> ^10 (In Medicine.) A secondary or symptomatic affection, one supervening on the principal disease.<BR> ^11 (In Arithmetic.) Junction or union; see भागानुबन्ध.<BR> ^12 (In the Vedánta philosophy.) An indispensable element of the study of the Vedánta; it consists of<BR> ^a. the अधिकारिन् or the competent person, one who is well versed in the vaidik writings, observes the ceremonies &c., is purified in his heart &c.;<BR> ^b. the विषय or the object-matter viz. the identity of the individual soul and Brahman (neuter);<BR> ^c. the संबन्ध or the relation viz. between that identity to be proved and the authoritative evidence contained in the Upanishads, and<BR> ^d. the प्रयोजन or the purpose viz. the cessation of ignorance and attainment of eternal bliss. <BR>II. f. (-न्धी)<BR> ^1 Hickup.<BR> ^2 Thirst. E. बन्ध् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्, in the fem. with ङीष्.

anubandhana|अनुबन्धन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Connexion, association. E. बन्ध् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anubandhin|अनुबन्धिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्धी-न्धिनी-न्धि) Connected with, followed as by a consequence; e. g. हितानुबन्धिन् having a salutary result, वैरानुबन्धिन् resulting in enmity. E. बन्ध् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anubandhya|अनुबन्ध्य
I. Tatpur. m. f. (-न्ध्यः-न्ध्या) One of the three principal paśus or sacrificial animals in the Jyotisht́oma sacrifice. (See also अग्नीषोमीयपशु and सवनीयपशु.) It is a cow, and the proceedings with it take place after the Avabhŕitha on the fifth day of the Agnisht́oma (q. v.). But as the sacrifice of a cow is forbidden in the present or Kali-yuga, a substitute for it is an offering of curds of two-milk-whey.-Also written अनूबन्ध्य. E. बन्ध् with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्; with the ellipsis of पशु for the masc. and of गो for the feminine. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-न्ध्यः-न्ध्या-न्ध्यम्) Principal, primary, what may receive an adjunct, as a root, a disease &c. E. अनुबन्ध, taddh. aff. यत्.

anubandhyapashu|अनुबन्ध्यपशु
Karmadh. m. (-शुः) The sacrificial animal called अनुबन्ध्य. See the preceding. E. अनुबन्ध्य and पशु.

anubala|अनुबल
Tatpur. n. (-लम्) An army which follows, an auxiliary force. E. अनु and बल.

anubiidha|अनुबीध
Tatpur. m. (-धः)<BR> ^1 Reviving the scent of a faded perfume.<BR> ^2 Replacing perfumes removed by bathing &c.<BR> ^3 An after-thought. E. अनु and बोध.

anubodhana|अनुबोधन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Recollecting, remembering. E. अनु and बोधन or बुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anubraahmaNa|अनुब्राह्मण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) A work similar to those called Bráhmańa. E. अनु and ब्राह्मण.

anubraahmaNin|अनुब्राह्मणिन्
m. (-णी) One who studies or knows the work Anubráhmańa. E. अनुब्राह्मण, taddh. aff. इनि.

anubhangam|अनुभङ्गम्
Avyayíbh. According to defeat, fear &c.(?). Compare also आनुभङ्ग्य. E. अनु and भङ्ग.

anubhartR|अनुभर्तृ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्ता-र्त्री-तृ) (ved.) Imitating, resembling. (The vaidik passage मरुतोऽनुभर्त्री where the word occurs is marked by the Prátiśákhya on account of the elision of अ after ओ.) E. भृ with अनु (comp. the meaning of हृ with अनु), kŕit aff. तृच्.

anubhava|अनुभव
Tatpur. m. (-वः) Knowledge other than remembrance,  apprehension, notion, understanding. The same as अनुभूति q. v.; e. g. पूर्वजन्मजातमरणदुःखानुभव ‘apprehension of the pains of death produced in a previous life’; or अयथार्थानुभव q. v. E. भू with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्.

anubhavasiddha|अनुभवसिद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Established by perception, resulting from experience, e. g. कृतिचैतन्ययोः सामानाधिकरण्यमनुभवसिद्धम् ‘the common substratum between action and consciousness is &c.’. E. अनुभव and सिद्ध.

anubhavasaara|अनुभवसार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) The name of a treatise on the merits of worshipping Śiva agreeably to the tenets of the Jangamas. E. अनुभव and सार.

anubhaava|अनुभाव
Tatpur. m. (-वः)<BR> ^1 Dignity, authority, power (such as results from wealth, a magisterial position &c.).<BR> ^2 Certainty, resolution (only in the positive sense of a good resolution, e. g. महानुभाव q. v.).<BR> ^3 (In rhetorical terminology.) ‘A symptom which indicated the feeling (भाव) produced by its appropriate causes’. These causes being naturally various from the character (रस) of a poetical composition, the rhetorical works enumerate the anubhávas which are the concomitants of the different sorts of rasas; thus the symptoms of the Erotic (शृङ्गार) are according to them, motion of the eye-brows, side-glances &c.; of the Comic (हास्य), blinking with the eye, smiles &c.; of the Pathetic (करुण), cursing one's fate, falling to the ground, crying &c.; of the Terrible (रौद्र), abuse, fierce looks &c.; of the Heroic (वीर), looking for a companion &c.; of the Fearful (भयानक), change of colour, stammering &c.; of the Disgustful (बीभत्स), spitting, contracting the mouth, shutting the eyes &c.; of the Wonderful (अद्भुत), wide opening of the eyes &c.; of the Quietistic (शान्त), horripilation (sic) &c.; of the Affectionate (वत्सल), horripilation, joy, tears &c.--Compare भाव and विभाव. E. अनु and भाव, lit. ‘following or connected with condition, feeling &c.’.

anubhaavaka|अनुभावक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-वकः-विका-वकम्) Making intelligible. E. भू, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anubhaavana|अनुभावन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) (In rhetoric.) Representing feelings so as to make then the characteristic (शृङ्गार &c. see रस and अनुभाव) of a poetical composition. E. भू, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anubhaavin|अनुभाविन्
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-वी-विनी-वि) Perceiving, knowing (e. g. a witness). BREAḲ. m. (-वी) (In law.) According to some, the same as सपिण्ड q. v., a near kinsman (i. e. ‘one who feels grief at a death in the family’), according to others, the same as ‘a young son’ (i. e. ‘one who is or comes after’). E. भू with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि. <BR>II. m. f. n. (-वी-विनी-वि) Having the symptoms which indicate feeling (see अनुभाव). E. अनुभाव, taddh. aff. इनि.

anubhaaShaNa|अनुभाषण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (In the Nyáya phil.) Repeating an argument proposed for discussion, i. e. taking it up; the contrary (not-repeating it when it has been announced three times besides the first time) being considered as a tacit agreement or avowal of defeat. See अननुभाषण. E. भाष् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anubhaasa|अनुभास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) A kind of crow. (Perhaps the word ought to be read अनुभाष when it might suggest the mean ing of the Pica or Garrulus Argoratensis.) E. भास् (भाष्?) with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्(?).

anubhuu|अनुभू
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-भूः-भूः-भु) Perceiving, knowing. E. भू with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

anubhuuta|अनुभूत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Understood, judged, apprehended.<BR> ^2 Perceiving, understanding.<BR> ^3 Resulted, followed as a consequence. E. भू with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anubhuuti|अनुभूति
Tatpur. m. (-तिः) (In the Vaiśeshika phil.) Apprehension, one of the two essential properties of intellect (बुद्धि); it is four-fold viz. knowledge arising from the senses (see प्रत्यक्ष), inference (see अनुमिति), comparison (see उपमिति) and verbal knowledge (शब्दज). Comp. अनुभव. E. भू with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anubhuutiprakaasha|अनुभूतिप्रकाश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) The name of a work which paraphrases the Upanishads, by Vidyárańyamuni. E. अनुभूति and प्रकाश.

anubhuutisvaruupaachaarya|अनुभूतिस्वरूपाचार्य
Karmadh. m. (-र्यः) The name of the author of the grammar Sáraswatí-prakriyá. E. अनुभूति-स्वरूप ‘being apprehension itself’, and आचार्य.

anubhoga|अनुभोग
Tatpur.(?) n. (-गम्) (A modern law term.) Enjoyment, usufruct, a grant of hereditary land in Malabar, either rent-free or at pepper-corn-rent, in reward of service; also a present of betel or a cocoa nut, from the proprietor at the time of executing a deed of transfer of a garden or plantation to the person to whom the transfer is made, as symbolical of the character of the land made over. E. अनु and भोग.

anubhraatR|अनुभ्रातृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) A younger brother. E. अनु and भ्रातृ.

anumata|अनुमत
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Accepted, assented to.<BR> ^2 Agreeable, pleasant.<BR> ^3 Loved, beloved.<BR> ^4 Concurred with, being of one opinion. BREAḲ. n. (-तम्) Assent. E. मन् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anumati|अनुमति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः)<BR> ^1 Assent, permission, acquiescence.<BR> ^2 Conniving (at a criminal act).<BR> ^3 The fifteenth day of the moon's age, on which she rises one digit less than full. (On this day it was held that the gods and the Manes of departed progenitors were favourable to the prayers of men; gifts made to Bráhmańas on this day were considered therefore to be meritorious. The three other phases of the increasing moon are कुहू, राका and सिनीवाली qq. vv. Compare also पौर्णमासी, अमावास्या, खर्विका and सद्यस्काला.)<BR> ^4 The former personified as a goddess and invoked especially in sacrificial acts connected with the Rájasúya sacrifice and the obsequial rites. The later mythology represents her as a daughter of Angiras and Smŕiti.<BR> ^5 The name of the offering made to the goddess Anumati in the Rájasúya sacrifice and consisting of Purod́áśa fried in eight bowls. E. मन् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anumatipatra|अनुमतिपत्र
Tatpur. n. (-त्रम्) (A modern law term.) A deed expressive of assent or concurrence; especially a deed executed by a husband about to die, authorising his widow to adopt a son. E. अनुमति and पत्र.

anumadhyamam|अनुमध्यमम्
Avyayíbh. After the intermediate, after the nextoldest (मध्यम taken in reference to ज्येष्ठ and कनीयस्). E. अनु and मध्यम. 

anumanana|अनुमनन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Assenting, acquiescing; e. g. स्वाच्छन्द्यानुमन indulging in one's desires, doing as one pleases.<BR> ^2 Conniving (as at a criminal act). E. मन् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anumantR|अनुमन्तृ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्ता-न्त्री-न्तृ)<BR> ^1 Consenting to, acquiescing.<BR> ^2 Conniving (at a criminal act), ‘be it for one's own interest or for the interest of another’. E. मन् with अनु, kŕit aff. तृच्.

anumantraNa|अनुमन्त्रण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Consecrating by the recital of appropriate hymns, e. g. उपांशुयाजानुमन्त्रण consecrating the Upáńśuyája &c. E. मन्त्र् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anumantraNamantra|अनुमन्त्रणमन्त्र
Tatpur. m. (-न्त्रः) A Mantra or hymn used for the consecrating of religious performances. E. अनुमन्त्रण and मन्त्र.

anumantrita|अनुमन्त्रित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Consecrated by the recital of appropriate hymns (e. g. a weapon, thus made efficient). E. मन्त्र् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त and ágama इट्.

anumaraNa|अनुमरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Dying with or following in death; the term usually denotes the cremation of a Hindu widow, whose husband's corpse is not on the spot, and with whose shoes she, therefore, ascends the pile: this is prohibited to Bráhmańa women; or the cremation of a widow with the body of the husband (see सहमरण). E. अनु and मरण.

anumaru|अनुमरु
Tatpur. m. (-रुः) A country or place adjoining a desert, or a country similar to a desert. E. अनु and मरु.

anumaa|अनुमा
Tatpur. f. (-मा). The same as अनुमिति q. v. E. मा with अनु, kŕit aff. अङ्.

anumaadya|अनुमाद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) To be gratified by praise. (ved.) E. मद्, in the caus., with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anumaana|अनुमान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Inferring, as the cause of अनुमिति or of a conclusion drawn from given premises. According to the Sánkhya and Yoga-philosophies it is one of the three means (see प्रमाण) by which true knowledge may be obtained (see also प्रत्यक्ष or दृष्ट and आगम or आप्तवचन); according to the Nyáya and Vaiśeshika phil., one of the four means for this end (see also प्रत्यक्ष, उपमान and शब्द). Inference may be, according to the definitions of Sánkhya and Nyáya philosophers, either one by induction (पूर्ववत्) e. g. that it will rain because clouds have gathered, or one by analogy (सामान्यतो दृष्टम्), e. g. that moon and stars are locomotive because they change their place and that a person therefore who changes his place is locomotive; or one by necessity (शेषवत्), e. g. that the ocean will be salt, because a drop taken from it, is salt. According to the Vaiśeshika philosophers, inference may be either purely consecutive or positive (केवलान्वयिन्), i. e. when the major term is not excluded by any other notion (comp. अनुपसंहारिन्), e. g. all that can be known can be named, because only positive (not negative instances) can be alleged to prove the assertion; or purely exclusive or negative (केवलव्यतिरेकिन्), i. e. when only negative proof can be adduced, e. g. in asserting that earth is distinguished from all the other elements, because it is possessed of the quality of smell, for the argument would be that all that is not distinguished from all the other elements, is not possessed of the quality of  smell; or positive and negative (अन्वयव्यतिरेकिन्), i. e. when there exist positive and negative instances of the major term, e. g. where there is fire there is smoke, because the positive argument would be ‘on the hearth’ and the negative ‘in the lake’. (The Mímánsá and Vedánta philosophies do not discuss these topics, as inference is not considered by them to be a means of arriving at true knowledge.)<BR> ^2 (In rhetoric.) A logical anakolouthon by the way of inference, an अलंकार or mode of writing elegantly, e. g. ‘wherever falls the look of woman, there fall sharpened arrows; I think therefore that the God of Love runs before them while shooting off his arrows’. E. मा with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anumaanakhaNDa|अनुमानखण्ड
Tatpur. n. (-ण्डम्) The name of a work on logical inference by Chintámańi. E. अनुमान and खण्ड.

anumaanaprakaasha|अनुमानप्रकाश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) The name of a work on logical inference by Ruchidatta. E. अनुमान and प्रकाश.

anumaanamaNidiidhiti|अनुमानमणिदीधिति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) The name of a work on logical inference by Raghunátha. E. अनुमान-मणि, and दीधिति.

anumaanokti|अनुमानोक्ति
Tatpur. f. (-क्तिः) Reasoning, logic. E. अनुमान and उक्ति ‘speaking from inference’.

anumaapaka|अनुमापक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पकः-पिका-पकम्) Causing to draw an inference, being the ground of inference (as कार्य or effect). E. मा in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल् and ágama पुक्.

anumaaSham|अनुमाषम्
Avyayíbh. (Probably.) Like or as much as a kidney bean. Compare अनुतिलम्. E. अनु and माष.

anumaasa|अनुमास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) A following month. See मासानुमासिक. E. अनु and मास.

anumita|अनुमित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Inferred. E. मा with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anumiti|अनुमिति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Conclusion, the result of अनुमान q. v.; it is defined as ‘knowledge resulting from syllogizing’. See also s. v. अनुभूति. E. मा with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anumimaana|अनुमिमान
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Concluding, inferring. E. मा with अनु, kŕit aff. शानच्, ágama मुक्.

