Avyayíbh. Every night, night by night. E. अनु and रात्रि, samásánta aff. अच्.

anuraadha|अनुराध
I. Tatpur. 1. Compare अनूराध. E. राध् with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्.  BREAḲ. f. (-धा) The seventeenth Nakshatra (q. v.) or lunar mansion, described as a row of oblations; it consists of four, or according to a different reading, of three stars; its chief and middlemost star is placed by the authorities in 3º or 2º or 1º 45'S. and in 224º or 224º 5'E., and must intend the star near the head of the Scorpion ( Scorpionis) and the asterism probably comprises  and  Scorpionis. Also written अनूराधा. See राधानुराधा and विशाखानुराधा. E. अनु and राधा, the name of the sixteenth Nakshatra. <BR>II. 1. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) Born under the constellation Anurádhá. BREAḲ. m. (-धः) A proper name, the son of Páńd́u-Śákya and founder of the village or town Anurádha (see अनुराधग्राम and अनुराधपुर), the ancient capital of Ceylon. E. अनुराधा with लुक् of the taddh. aff. अण्.

anuraadhagraama|अनुराधग्राम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) The village (later the town) Anurádha; the same as अनुराधपुर q. v. and the  or  of Ptolemæus. E. अनुराध and ग्राम.

anuraadhapura|अनुराधपुर
Tatpur. n. (-पुरम्) The name of the ancient capital of Ceylon, founded according to the legends by Anurádha (q. v.), and the principal place of Buddhistic relics; it was possessed especially of the tooth of Buddha which has played a great part in the history of Ceylon and is still preserved in Kandi. See also अनुराधग्राम. Its geographical position is 8º 15'N. Lat. 98º 14'36'' E. L. E. अनुराध and पुर.

anuru|अनुरु
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रुः-रु or -र्वी-रु) Not large, small. E. अ neg. and उरु.

anuruddha|अनुरुद्ध
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्)<BR> ^1 Checked, opposed.<BR> ^2 Pleased, pacified. <BR>II. m. (-द्धः) A proper name: a cousin of Sákyamuni. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuruddhaka|अनुरुद्धक
m. (-कः). The same as अनुरुद्ध (m.). E. The preceding, taddh. aff. कन्.

anurudh|अनुरुध्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्) Loving, favouring, following. Also read अनूरुध्. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

anuruhaa|अनुरुहा
Tatpur. f. (-हा) The name of a sweet smelling grass (Cyperus pertenius Roxb.) or of a bulb of the root of Cyperus Juncifolius. See नागरमुस्तक. E. रुह् with अनु, kŕit aff. क.

anuruupa|अनुरूप
I. Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-पः-पा-पम्)<BR> ^1 Like, resembling.<BR> ^2 Fit, suitable.<BR> ^3 According to. BREAḲ. m. (-पः) The second of three तृच or stanzas (each consisting of three verses) recited at a sacrificial act; of the three तृच, for instance, in the beginning of the second portion of the Saḿaveda, उपास्मै गायत नराः &c., दविद्युतत्या रुचा &c., and पवमानस्य ते कवे &c. which form the बहिष्पवमानस्तोत्र and are recited e. g. in the द्वादशाह sacrifice, the Tŕicha which begins with the words दविद्युतत्या रुचा is called the अनुरूप. (See besides स्तोत्रीय and पर्यास.) <BR>3. n. (-पम्)<BR> ^1 Conformity, likeness, analogy (अनुरूपेण conformably, agreeably to).<BR> ^2 Fitness, suitableness. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-पम्) Conformably, agreeably to. E. अनु and रूप.

anuruupacheShTa|अनुरूपचेष्ट
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Endeavouring to act becomingly. E. अनुरूप and चेष्टा. 

anurevatii|अनुरेवती
Tatpur. f. (-ती) The name of a plant; the same as लघुदन्ती q. v. E. अनु and रेवती.

anurodha|अनुरोध
Tatpur. m. (-धः)<BR> ^1 The accomplishing of a desired object for another person, obligingness, compliance.<BR> ^2 Conformity.<BR> ^3 Application, bearing (of a rule). Compare अनुवृत्ति. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anurodhaka|अनुरोधक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धकः-धिका-धकम्) Complying with, complaisant. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anurodhana|अनुरोधन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Compliance, complaisance, obligingness. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anurodhitaa|अनुरोधिता
f. (-ता) The being obliging or complaisant. E. अनुरोधिन्, taddh. aff. तल्.

anurodhin|अनुरोधिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धी-धिनी-धि) Compliant, complaisant, acting in conformity with or in regard of. E. रुध् with अनु, kŕit aff. घिनुण्.

anurohaNa|अनुरोहण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) (Probably) the same as अन्वारोहण q. v. E. रुह् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anurohaNiiya|अनुरोहणीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) (Probably) the same as अन्वारोहणीय q. v. E. अनुरोहण, taddh. aff. छ.

anurohat|अनुरोहत्
Tatpur. m. (-न्) A proper name. See आनुरोहति. E. रुह् with अनु, kŕit aff. शतृ.

anulaa|अनुला
Tatpur.(?) f. (-ला) A proper name of<BR> ^1 A female Buddhistic Arhat or Saint who is renowned for having introduced the Buddhistic religion in Lanká or Ceylon in the time of the king Aśoka; she was the wife of Mahánága, the younger brother of Mahendra and received the dignity of a female Arhat from Sanghamitrá, the sister of Mahendra.<BR> ^2 A queen of Ceylon renowned for her profligacy. She was the wife of Koranága, the brother of Mahákúlamahátishya, whom she killed by poison as well as his son Tishya and four paramours whom she married in succession. A second son of Mahákúla, Kálakanatishya revolted at last against her and caused her death in the year 41 before Christ. E. doubtful.

anulaapa|अनुलाप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Repetition. E. अनु and लाप.

anulaasa|अनुलास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) A peacock. E. अनु and लास.

anulaasya|अनुलास्य
Tatpur. m. (-स्यः) A peacock. E. अनु and लास्य.

anulipta|अनुलिप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) Smeared, anointed. E. लिप् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anulepa|अनुलेप
Tatpur. m. (-पः) Unction, anointing. E. लिप् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anulepaka|अनुलेपक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पकः-पिका-पकम्) Anointing, who or what anoints. E. लिप् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anulepana|अनुलेपन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Anointing the body.<BR> ^2 Unguent so used; as such are enumerated the unguents made of कुङ्कुम (Crocus sativus), अग्निशिख (Arthamus tinctorius), काश्मीर (Costus speciosus), चन्दन (Syrium myrtifolium) and श्रीखण्ड (Sandal wood).<BR> ^3 Oily or emollient application (see the former meaning). E. लिप् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anulepikaa|अनुलेपिका
Tatpur. f. (-का). See अनुलेपक; comp. आनुलेपिक. E. the fem. of अनुलेपक.

anulepin|अनुलेपिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पी-पिनी-पि) Anointing the body; e. g. गात्रानुलेपिन्. E. लिप् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि. (In compounds such as ताम्रमृष्टानुलेपिन् the E. is not ताम्र-मृष्ट and अनुलेपिन्, but ताम्र-मृष्ट-अनुलेप, taddh. aff. इनि, since  the taddh. aff. इनि does not belong to the last part of the compound, but to the whole.)

anuloma|अनुलोम
I. Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-मः-मा-मम्) In natural order or direction, regular, successive (liter. with the hair), the reverse of प्रतिलोम; comp. e. g. प्रतिलोमानुलोमपादयमक. BREAḲ. m. (-मः)<BR> ^1 A proper name; his descendants are called अनुलोमाः or आनुलोमयः (plur. of आनुलोमि); according to another authority, however, the name of the descendants ought to be अनुलोमानः or आनुलोमयः (plur. of आनुलोमि).<BR> ^2 (In vaidik grammar; scil. अन्वक्षरसन्धि) One of the two kinds of the Sandhi called अन्वक्षरसन्धि q. v., viz. when a final vowel or the last syllable of एषः, स्यः or सः is followed by a consonant (of a new word; the case in the latter three instances being similar to those of the meeting between a final vowel and a beginning consonant, since their Visarga is dropped). Compare प्रतिलोम. <BR>3. m. plur. (-माः) scil. वर्णाः; mixed tribes or castes; for the special meaning, in which this word is used, see अनुलोमज. BREAḰ. f. (-मा) A woman of a caste inferior to that of the man; e. g. a Kshatriyá woman when spoken of in reference to a Bráhmańa man. Comp. अनुलोमज. <BR>[5. (In Buddhistic literature the word अनुलोम expresses the regular order in which certain ascetic rites are to be performed; e. g. the kasinánuloma consists of the eight first kasinas in their regular order, the dhyánánuloma of the four successive dhyánas.]<BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-मम्) In natural order, regularly, successively. E. अनु and लोमन्, samásánta aff. अच्.

anulomakalpa|अनुलोमकल्प
Karmadh. m. (-पः) The name of the 34th of the Pariśisht́has of the Atharvaveda. E. अनुलोम and कल्प.

anulomakRShTa|अनुलोमकृष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्) Ploughed (as it were) with the grain; e. g. अनुलोमकृष्टं क्षेत्रं पुनः प्रतिलोमं कर्षति ‘he ploughs the field first with and then against its grain’, i. e. first in one and then in its opposite direction. E. अनुलोम (II.) and कृष्ट.

anulomaja|अनुलोमज
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-जः-जा-जम्) Born in due gradation; applied especially to the mixed tribes or offspring of a father superior in caste to the mother, viz. the Múrdhávasikta (son of a Bráhmańa and a Kshatriyá mother), the Ambasht́ha (son of a Bráhmańa and Vaiśyá mother), the Nisháda or Páraśava (son of a Bráhmańa and Śúdrí mother), the Máhishya (son of a Kshatriya and Vaiśya mother), the Ugra (son of a Kshatriya and Śúdrí mother) and the Karańa (son of a Vaiśya and Śúdrí mother). For the offspring of a mother superior in caste to the father see प्रतिलोम and प्रतिलोमज. E. अनुलोम and ज.

anuloman|अनुलोमन्
Tatpur. m. pl. (-मानः) The descendants of अनुलोम (acc. to one authority; acc. to another their name is अनुलोमाः or आनुलोमयः. See अनुलोम I. 2.). E. अनु and लोमन्.

anulomana|अनुलोमन
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-नः-नी-नम्)<BR> ^1 Putting in due order, regulating; e. g. धर्मानुलोमन.<BR> ^2 (In Medicine.) Directing into the proper channel; esp. applied to medicines intended to correct the vitiated air of the body or to obviate urinary and excretory impediments.  BREAḲ. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Regulating.<BR> ^2 Obviating the diseases mentioned before by correcting vitiated air &c. E. अनुलोमि, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anulomapariNiitaa|अनुलोमपरिणीता
Tatpur. f. (-ता) A woman married in the regular gradation of the caste inferior to that of the husband. E. अनुलोम (II.) and परिणीत.

anulomaaya|अनुलोमाय
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Of favourable or well regulated fortune. E. अनुलोम and अय.

anulomi|अनुलोमि
denom. par. (अनुलोमयति--aor. अन्वलुलोमत्)<BR> ^1 To go or touch with the grain.<BR> ^2 (In Medicine.) To direct into the proper channel, as vitiated air of the body, excrements &c. E. अनुलोम, denom. aff. णिच्.

anulvaNa|अनुल्वण
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-णः-णा-णम्) Not excessive. E. अ neg. and उल्वण.

anuvaMsha|अनुवंश
I. Tatpur. m. (-शः)<BR> ^1 A genealogical table, a song embodying such tables or lists. (A comm. renders this word simply with गाथा ‘a song’ and अनुवंश्य with गातव्य; the meaning ‘song’ however seems too general and would not always convey a distinct meaning of अनुवंश.) <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-शम्) According to the families or races. (The word आनुवंश्य is derived from the Avyayíbh., not from the Tatpur.) E. अनु and वंश (the E. of I. 1. however according to the comm. mentioned, would have to be in conformity with that given of वंश, वम् with अनु, kŕit aff. श).

anuvaMshya|अनुवंश्य
m. f. n. (-श्यः-श्या-श्यम्) Being in or referring to the genealogical lists. (A comm., differing from the grammatical authority of the given meaning, renders this word गातव्य ‘to be sung’ thus deriving it as a Tatpur. from वंश् with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्--but without probability.) E. अनुवंश, taddh. aff. यत्.

anuvaktavya|अनुवक्तव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्)<BR> ^1 To be named in reference to what has been said before (compare अनुवाक).<BR> ^2 To be repeated, to be spoken after. E. वच् with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anuvakra|अनुवक्र
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्रः-क्रा-क्रम्) Somewhat oblique (another reading of this word is अतिवक्र q. v.); applied esp. to the diurnal motion of a planet in its orbit (see गति), of which motions eight are enumerated, subdivided again into two classes; the अनुवक्रगति belongs to that class of motions which is called वक्र. E. अनु and वक्र.

anuvakraga|अनुवक्रग
Tatpur. m. (-गः) Moving in a somewhat oblique direction (as a planet); see the preceding. E. अनुवक्र and ग.

anuvachana|अनुवचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Speaking after or in conformity with, repeating, reciting; e. g. वेदानुवचन repeating the words of the Veda in the same manner as the teacher has enounced them, i. e. reading or studying the Veda; सावित्र्यनुवचन reciting the Sávitrí hymn.<BR> ^2 A lecture or chapter (esp. in the Kát́haka recension of the black Yajurveda).<BR> ^3 (In the liturgical literature.) The speaking of and the name of certain vaidik passages or mantras which are addressed by certain priests at sacrifices to the deity in consequence of, and in conformity with, other passages spoken by other priests, esp. by the Adhvaryu, which contain an injunction or प्रैष (q. v. and compare अनुवाचन); the अनुवचन are either connected with the प्रैष immediately (see समस्त), or separated from them by other words (see व्यस्त); e. g. such अनुवचन  as प्र वो वाजा अभिद्यवः । अञ्जन्ति त्वामध्वरे देवयन्तः &c. are separated from प्रैष such as अग्नये समिध्यमानायानुब्रूहि । यूपायाज्यमानायानुब्रूहि, while in the instances होतायक्षदग्निं &c. the अनुवचन is immediately followed by the प्रैष ‘होतुर्यज’, or in the instance मैत्रावरुणः प्रेष्यति चानु चाह, the anuvachana ‘अनु चाह’ follows immediately the praisha मैत्राº. E. वच् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvachaniiya|अनुवचनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Referring to the अनुवचन q. v. E. अनुवचन, taddh. aff. छ.

anuvatsara|अनुवत्सर
Tatpur. m. (-रः)<BR> ^1 A year (comp. वत्सर, इद्वत्सर, उद्वत्सर, परिवत्सर, संवत्सर).<BR> ^2 (In Astronomy.) In the Bŕihaspati (or Jupiter) cycle which consists of five cycles of twelve years, the fifth which is presided over by Brahman (for the other four cycles see इद्वत्सर &c.). E. अनु and वत्सर.

anuvanam|अनुवनम्
Avyayíbh. Along or near the forest. E. अनु and वन.

anuvartana|अनुवर्तन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Following, attending.<BR> ^2 Obliging or serving another.<BR> ^3 Concurring, admitting.<BR> ^4 Consequence, result. E. वृत् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvartin|अनुवर्तिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-र्ती-र्तिनी-र्ति)<BR> ^1 Following.<BR> ^2 Obedient. E. वृत् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anuvartman|अनुवर्त्मन्
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-र्त्मा-र्त्मा-र्त्म) Following. E. अनु and वर्त्मन्.

anuvasha|अनुवश
I. Tatpur. m. (-शः) Obedience, deference. II. Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-शः-शा-शम्) Wishing to please or to fulfill one's desires, obedient. E. अनु and वश.

anuvaShaTkaara|अनुवषट्कार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A second वषट्कार or exclamation at a sacrifice, the first वषट्कार being intended for the principal deity and the अनुवषट्कार for the other deities; in the Jyotisht́oma, for instance, the Chamasas with the juice of the Soma plant are at the वषट्कार offered to Indra, and afterwards at the अनुवषट्कार to the other deities, Mitra and Varuna &c. According to the decision of the Mimánsists, however, Indra the principal deity, would also have to be mentally supplied i. e. to share in the offering made at the Anuvashat́kára. E. अनु and वषट्कार.

anuvaShaTkRta|अनुवषट्कृत
Tatpur. n. (-तम्). The same as अनुवषट्कार. E. अनु and वषट्कृत.

anuvasita|अनुवसित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Tied to, connected with, addicted to; e. g. पापानुवसित. E. सि with अव (in its form व) and अनु. The same as अन्ववसित.

anuvaha|अनुवह
Tatpur. m. (-हः) The seventh of the seven tongues or flames of the sacrificial fire (lit. carrying along), also called निवह (the others are: प्रवह, आवह, उद्वह, संवह, विवह and परिवह. Compare also s. v. अग्निजिह्वा). E. वह् with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्.

anuvaaka|अनुवाक
Tatpur. m. (-कः)<BR> ^1 Reciting, recital, reading; e. g. अनुवाकहता बुद्धिः ‘common sense lost in or by the reading (of the Vedas)’.<BR> ^2 A section, a chapter, esp. of the Ŕig-, Yajuror Atharvaveda and of writings referring to either of these Vedas.<BR> ^3 One who recites (? comp. आनुवाक). E. वच् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuvaakasaMkhyaa|अनुवाकसंख्या
Tatpur. f. (-ख्या) The name of the fourth of the eighteen Pariśisht́as belonging to the Yajurveda. E. अनुवाक and संख्या.

anuvaakaanukramaNii|अनुवाकानुक्रमणी
Tatpur. f. (-णी) The name of an Anukramańí (q. v.) of hymns of the Ŕigveda by Śaunaka. E. अनुवाक and अनुक्रमणी. 

anuvaakyavat|अनुवाक्यवत्
m. f. n. (वान्-वती-वत्) Having an अनुवाक्या, accompanied with an अनुवाक्या. E. अनुवाक्या (with its final vowel shortened), taddh. aff. मतुप्. (This word which occurs in the present edition of the Śatapathabr. is perhaps a misreading for अनुवाक्यावत् which is found elsewhere.)

anuvaakyaa|अनुवाक्या
Tatpur. f. (-क्या) The name of such verses of the Ŕigveda as are recited by the priest Hotŕi (q. v.), when the deity is invoked by him to partake of the Havis or clarified butter. This word is found frequently together with याज्या (q. v.), the name of those hymns of the same Veda which are recited by the Hotŕi when the Havis-oblation is actually made. The Anuvákyás are spoken in a slow or as it were drawling tone, while the Yájyás are recited quickly. According to the Mímánsá no priest but the Hotŕi is allowed to recite either of them. Compare also पुरोऽनुवाक्या and याज्यानुवाक्या. E. वच् with अनु, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्.

anuvaakyaavat|अनुवाक्यावत्
m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्) Having an अनुवाक्या, accompanied with an अनुवाक्या. Compare अनुवाक्यवत्. E. अनुवाक्या, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

anuvaach|अनुवाच्
Tatpur. f. (-वाक्). The same as अनुवचन (but not to be confounded with अनुवाक्या). E. वच् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्, the vowel of the radical being lengthened.

anuvaachana|अनुवाचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Causing to recite; esp. in the liturg. literature, as the effect of a प्रैष (q. v.) or injunction addressed by the Adhvaryu to another priest which causes the latter to invite the god or gods to partake of a sacrifice, by reciting certain passages from the Ŕigveda. (Compare अनुवचन.) E. वच् in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvaachanapraiSha|अनुवाचनप्रैष
I. Tatpur. m. (-षः) An injunction esp. addressed by the Adhvaryu to the Hotŕi (qq. vv.) for the purpose of causing the latter to invite the god or gods by certain mantras to partake of the sacrifice. <BR>II. Dvandva (-षौ) The injunction esp. of the Adhvaryu addressed to the Hotŕi to invite the gods &c. (see the preceding) and that of the Adhvaryu to the Maitŕavaruna (q. v.), to assign to them their respective portions of the sacrifice. E. अनुवाचन and प्रैष.

anuvaachaniiya|अनुवाचनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Referring to or fit for the अनुवाचन q. v. E. अनुवाचन, taddh. aff. छ.

anuvaachita|अनुवाचित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Referred to, mentioned before. E. वच्, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuvaata|अनुवात
Tatpur. m. (-तः) The wind that blows from behind; अनुवाते ‘when the wind blows from behind, to windward’. E. अनु and वात.

anuvaada|अनुवाद
Tatpur. m. (-दः)<BR> ^1 Reference or referring to what has been previously said, not in the way of a mere repetition or tautology, but in that of explanation, detailed comment or emphasis; explanatory and corroborative reference, explanation; e. g. भूपरिधिमानानुवादः ‘a detailed explanation with reference to the measure of the earth's circumference (mentioned before in the Goládhyáya)’; or, in Manu 2. 53. the words खानि संस्पृशेत् are an अनुवाद to निवेद्य &c. 2. 51., because they give a detailed illustration of the general injunction contained in the latter verse. If a word is repeated or an expression used which would seem superfluous, because not conveying a new notion, such repeated word or  such expression is अनुवाद, provided a certain purpose be connected with it, otherwise it would be sipely पुनरुक्त or a meaningless tautology, e. g. घटो घटः or घटः कलसः ‘a jar is a jar’ would be a पुनरुक्त; but the repetition of पश्येत् in Yájnav. 2. 1. from 1. 359. is an अनुवादः because it points to the connexion between both passages and to the detail which is to follow as an illustration of 1. 359.; or in Manu 1. 72. परिसंख्यया might be taken as an अनुवाद to सहस्रं, because it imparts greater emphasis to the bare numeral.<BR> ^2 In the ritual literature अनुवाद designates those passages of the Bráhmańa portion of the Vedas, which point to an injunction given before (विधि q. v.) and illustrate it by the way of comment, or by entering into greater detail, or by adding supplementary rules, but without stating the purpose of the injunction itself as the latter would be the object of the अर्थवाद (q. v.); the अनुवाद being accessory, therefore, to the विधि portion of the Bráhmańa and precluded from giving independent regulations, the supplementary rites they contain are not considered of equal weight and as absolute as those of the विधि; there exists however sometimes a difficulty to decide whether a passage of the Bráhmańas is विधि or अनुवाद, or in other words whether its injunctions are absolute or not, as appears from the discussion of the Mímánsists. (The Nyáya, supported by the commentaries on the Mímánsá, distribute the text of the Bráhmańa under the three heads of विधि, अनुवाद and अर्थवाद qq. vv.; a later division makes अनुवाद one of the three categories of the अर्थवाद.)<BR> ^3 Report, e. g. कुत्सितार्थानुवादः.<BR> ^4 Abuse, reviling (? this meaning is given by several dictionaries on the authority of the Śabdaratnávalí, but, to judge from the Mss. at my disposal, it would seem to proceed from another reading or from a misunderstanding of the passage of this work which contains the synonymes of ‘rumour’: यथार्थानिश्चिता वार्त्ता भवेत्सर्वजनात्मिका । कुत्सितार्थानुवादो वा किंवदन्ती जनश्रुतिः ॥; the same might be said of the meanings ‘abusive reply’ and ‘divulging another's misdeeds’ which occur also in some dictionaries). E. वद् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ् or अनु and वाद.

anuvaadaka|अनुवादक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-दकः-दिका-दकम्) Being or producing an अनुवाद (q. v.), concurrent, corroborative. E. वद् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anuvaadana|अनुवादन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्). Apparently the same as अनुवाचन q. v. E. वद् in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvaadaniiya|अनुवादनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) Apparently the same as अनुवाचनीय q. v. E. अनुवादन, taddh. aff. छ.

anuvaadavachana|अनुवादवचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A passage of the Bráhmańas which contains an अनुवाद q. v. E. अनुवाद and वचन.

anuvaadin|अनुवादिन्
Tatpur. I. m. f. n. (-दी-दिनी-दि)<BR> ^1 Referring to by way of explanation, responding to (comp. अनुवाद).<BR> ^2 Harmonizing with, conformable to. <BR>II. m. (-दी) (In music.) The name of either of the three notes (see स्वर) of the Gamut which comprises four quartertones (see श्रुति), viz. the षड्ज, मध्यम and पञ्चम qq. vv. (Compare also वादिन्, संवादिन् and विवादिन्.) E. वद् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि or अनु and वादिन्.

anuvaadya|अनुवाद्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्यः-द्या-द्यम्) Fit to be the subject  of an अनुवाद (q. v.). (Compare also the following.) E. वद् with अनु, kŕitya aff. ण्यत्.

anuvaadyatva|अनुवाद्यत्व
n. (-त्वम्) The quality of being the subject or the basis of an अनुवाद (q. v.), the being the cause of explanatory injunctions, accessory rites &c. (compare अनुवाद), one of the three properties of the फल or ultimate object of a sacrificial act which is instrumental in fulfilling the wishes of the agent. (For the two other properties of the फल see उद्देश्यत्व and मुख्यत्व or प्रधानत्व, and for those of the sacrificial act उपादेयत्व (the correlate of अनुवाद्यत्व), विधेयत्व (the correlate of उद्देश्यत्व) and गुणत्व (the correlate of मुख्यत्व). E. अनुवाद्य, taddh. aff. त्व.

anuvaaram|अनुवारम्
Avyayíbh. Repeatedly. E. अनु and वार.

anuvaasa|अनुवास
Tatpur. m. (-सः) An oily enema. E. वस् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuvaasana|अनुवासन
Tatpur. 1. m. n. (-नः-नम्) An oily enema; e. g. पिच्छावस्तिर्हितस्तत्र पयसा चैव भोजनम् । सर्पिर्मधुरकैः सिद्धं तैलं चाप्यनुवासनम् ॥ अतितीक्ष्णो निरूहो वा सवाते चानुवासनः । हृदयस्योपसरणं कुरुते चाङ्गपीडनम् ॥. E. वस् cl. 10, kŕit aff. ल्युट्, as a masc. with the ellipsis of वस्ति. BREAḲ. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Administering an oily enema.<BR> ^2 Fumigating, perfuming, scenting in general. E. 1. वस् cl. 10, 2. वास् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvaasaniiya|अनुवासनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्)<BR> ^1 Referring to, fit for an oily enema.<BR> ^2 Referring to or fit for fumigating or scenting. E. अनुवासन, taddh. aff. छ.

anuvaasanopaaya|अनुवासनोपाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) A medicine for an oily enema. E. अनुवासन and उपाय.

anuvaasita|अनुवासित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Prepared or administered as an oily enema.<BR> ^2 Fumigated, perfumed, scented. E. 1. वस् cl. 10, 2. वास् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuvaasin|अनुवासिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Being in the habit of dwelling. E. वस् cl. 1, with अनु, kŕit aff. घिनुण्.

anuvaasya|अनुवास्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्यः-स्या-स्यम्)<BR> ^1 Requiring an oily enema.<BR> ^2 To be fumigated, perfumed, scented. E. 1. वस् cl. 10, 2. वास् with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anuvitta|अनुवित्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Found, obtained. E. विद् (to find) with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuvitti|अनुवित्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः) Finding, obtaining. E. विद् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anuviddha|अनुविद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्)<BR> ^1 Hurt, pierced.<BR> ^2 Obstructed, checked.<BR> ^3 Variegated, ornamented.<BR> ^4 Full of.<BR> ^5 Set (as a jewel). E. व्यध् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuvidhaana|अनुविधान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Acting in conformity with, complaisance, obedience. E. धा with वि and अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvidhaayin|अनुविधायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Conformable, compliant, obedient, attentive to. E. धा with वि and अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि and ágama युक्.

anuvinaasha|अनुविनाश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) Dying after, perishing after; e. g. अग्नेर्दाह्यविनाशानुविनाशवत् ‘as fire dies on the dying of the combustible matter’. E. नश् with वि and अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuvinda|अनुविन्द
Tatpur. m. (-न्दः) A proper name, a son of Jayasena, king of Avanti, by Rájádhideví, and brother of Vinda; according to the Mahábhárata, one of the Kaikeyas slain by Sátyaki. E. अनु and विन्द. 

anuvishva|अनुविश्व
Tatpur.(?) m. pl. (-शाः) (According to Varáhamihira) the name of a people or country in the north-east. E. अनु and विश्व.

anuviShTambha|अनुविष्टम्भ
Tatpur. m. (-म्भः) The being impeded or obstructed in consequence (of what is mentioned previously). E. अनु and विष्टम्भ.

anuviShNu|अनुविष्णु
Avyayíbh. After Vishńu. E. अनु and विष्णु.

anuvii|अनुवी
See अनुव्यम्.

anuvRtta|अनुवृत्त
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-त्तः-त्ता-त्तम्) Following, obedient. 2. n. (-त्तम्) Compliance. E. वृत् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuvRtti|अनुवृत्ति
Tatpur. f. (-त्तिः)<BR> ^1 Acting in conformity with, acting as is required or suitable according to circumstance, e. g. स्वस्थानुवृत्ति doing what is suitable to health, स्नेहानुवृत्ति acting in such a manner as affection would require, behaving affectionately.<BR> ^2 Compliance with another's desires, obliging or serving another.<BR> ^3 Referring or reference to what precedes, supplying, e. g. of a passage or rule, application or bearing of a preceding passage or rule on a following one. Compare अनुरोध.<BR> ^4 Reverting, return, repetition, e. g. वर्णानामनुवृत्तिर्या नातिदूरान्तरश्रुतिः । अनुप्रासः &c.; or दुःखानुवृत्तिः. E. वृत् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anuvRddhi|अनुवृद्धि
Bahuvr. m. f. n. (-द्धिः-द्धिः-द्धि) (ved.) Increasing in accordance with; as mantras which are recited with increasing clearness in measure as the three savanas proceed. E. अनु and वृद्धि.

anuvedi|अनुवेदि
Avyayíbh. Along the sacrificial ground or वेदि q. v. E. अनु and वेदि.

anuvedha|अनुवेध
Tatpur. m. (-धः). The same as अनुव्याध q. v. E. In following the native lexicographical etym. of वेध, this word would come from विध् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्, the radical विध् assuming in this derivative the meaning of व्यध्; it will appear however that the form वेध in the meaning of व्यध, and अनुवेध in that of अनुव्याध are objectionable, from a gramm. point of view, since विध् does not occur otherwise in the meaning “to pierce” and वेध is not mentioned by the best gramm. authorities as a derivative of either विध् or व्यध्.

anuvelam|अनुवेलम्
Avyayíbh. Continually. E. अनु and वेला.

anuvellita|अनुवेल्लित
Tatpur. n. (-तम्) One of the fourteen kinds of bandages used in Hindoo surgery (cf. बन्ध), a roller or bandage to encircle the extremities, used esp. when bones of the hands or feet are fractured. E. वेल्ल् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त and ágama इट्.

anuvesha|अनुवेश
Tatpur. m. (-शः) Entering after (another). The same as अनुप्रवेश. E. विश् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuveshana|अनुवेशन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्). The same as अनुप्रवेशन. E. विश् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuveshaniiya|अनुवेशनीय
m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्). The same as अनुप्रवेशनीय. E. अनुवेशन, taddh. aff. छ.

anuvyanjana|अनुव्यञ्जन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) A secondary mark; (the Buddhists hold that there are 80 secondary marks of beauty, besides the 32 principal marks or लक्षण, which characterize a great man). E. अनु and व्यञ्जन.

anuvyam|अनुव्यम्
Tatpur. (? ved.) ind. After, behind. E. Probably the accus. of अनुवी ‘following’ (वी with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्). 

anuvyavahaara|अनुव्यवहार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A practice in conformance with, e. g. धर्मानुव्यवहार. E. अनु and व्यवहार.

anuvyavasaaya|अनुव्यवसाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) Perception of a judgement or sentiment. E. अनु and व्यवसाय.

anuvyaakhyaana|अनुव्याख्यान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) According to the Bŕihadárańyaka-Upan., one of the eight categories or characteristics of the text of a Bráhmańa; it is defined either as a synonyme of अर्थवाद q. v. or as a passage of a Bráhmańa in which short and obscure dicta (or सूत्र) which have occurred in another portion of the Bráhmańa, are discussed and explained. For the other categories comp. इतिहास, पुराण, विद्या, उपनिषद्, श्लोक, सूत्र and व्याख्यान. E. अनु and व्याख्यान.

anuvyaadha|अनुव्याध
Tatpur. m. (-धः)<BR> ^1 Obstruction, impeding.<BR> ^2 Mixing union. E. व्यध् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuvyaaharaNa|अनुव्याहरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्) Cursing, imprecating. E. हृ with आ, वि and अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvyaahaara|अनुव्याहार
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A curse, an imprecation. E. हृ with आ-वि and अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anuvyaahaarin|अनुव्याहारिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-री-रिणी-रि) Cursing, imprecating. E. हृ with आ-वि and अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anuvrajana|अनुव्रजन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Following, esp. complimentary attendance on a departing guest or guru, following him a little distance. See also अनुव्रज्या. E. व्रज् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuvrajya|अनुव्रज्य
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-ज्यः-ज्या-ज्यम्) To be followed, as a person deceased whose corpse is to be followed by his relatives to the cemetery. BREAḲ. f. (-ज्या). The same as अनुव्रजन. E. व्रज् with अनु, kŕitya aff. क्यप्.

anuvrata|अनुव्रत
Bahuvr. 1. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Acting friendly, devout, faithful. BREAḲ. m. (-तः) A Jaina devotee of the first class (the two other being the महाव्रत and the निर्वाण qq. vv.). “To attain the rank of Anuvrata one must forsake his family, entirely cutting off his hair, throwing away the sacred thread, holding in his hand a bundle of peacock's feathers and an earthen pot (कमण्डलु), and wearing only tawny coloured clothes: be must reside for some time in one of their temples (As. Res. IX. 248).” E. अनु and व्रत.

anushatika|अनुशतिक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) Followed by one or something bought for a hundred. (A derivative of this word with taddh. aff. अण् requires Vŕiddhi in both parts of the compound, see आनुशातिक) E. अनु and शतिक.

anushaya|अनुशय
Tatpur. I. m. (-यः)<BR> ^1 Connexion, attachment; comp. अनुशयिन्.<BR> ^2 (In the Vedánta philos.) That consequence of an act which compels the soul to descend again on earth, after she has enjoyed in the other world those consequences of her acts which allowed her to soar; that consequence, as it were, that cleaves to the soul and does not permit her to enjoy freedom from transmigration (‘आमुष्मिकफले कर्मजाते उपभुक्तेऽवशिष्टमैहिकफलं कर्मान्तरजातमनुशयः’); the अनुशय varies according to its qualities; if it is ‘handsome’ (रमणीय) the soul is reborn as a ‘Bráhmańa, Kshatriya or Vaiśya’; if it is ‘contemptible’ (कपूय) it animates ‘a dog, a hog or a Chánd́ála’.<BR> ^3 Repentance, regret.<BR> ^4 Hatred,  resentment.<BR> ^5 Deep or intense enmity, enmity which goes far in its consequences; e. g. शिशुपालोऽनुशयं परं गतः (comm.: परमनुशयं केवलं न सप्तव्यः किं तु हन्तव्यश्चेति दीर्घद्वेषं गतः).<BR> ^6 A certain country or place (? the meaning thus rendered in a comm. is देशविशेष). <BR>II. f. (-यी) (In Medicine.)<BR> ^1 A disease of the feet, a small abscess on the upper part, ‘deep, causing little pain, and of the natural colour as the limb’.<BR> ^2 (According to another) An abscess on the head (मस्तकोपरि) of the same symptoms as described before. E. शी with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्; the femin. in ई would be an anomaly accord. to this etym.

anushayavat|अनुशयवत्
m. f. n. (-वान्-वती-वत्)<BR> ^1 (In the Vedánta phil.) Having or being fraught with the अनुशय (q. v. 2.); viz. the soul (‘कृतात्ययेऽनुशयवान्दृष्टस्मृतिभ्यां यथेतमनेवं च’).<BR> ^2 Repenting, regretting.<BR> ^3 Feeling hatred.<BR> ^4 Feeling deep animosity. E. अनुशय, taddh. aff. मतुप्.

anushayaana|अनुशयान
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Repenting, regretting. BREAḲ. f. (-ना) One of the female characters described in the rhetorical literature; ‘a mistress who is overcome with sadness because she apprehends the loss of her lover, either on account of the breaking up of their actual meeting place, or for fear of not having one in future, or from the conclusion she has arrived at that her husband might find her in a place which is not that of his family’. <BR>[3. n. (-नम्) This word occurs in a Páli inscription where it would appear to mean ‘repentance’ or ‘confession’.]<BR>E. शी with अनु, kŕit aff. शानच्.

anushayitavya|अनुशयितव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be repented or regretted. E. शी with अनु, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

anushayin|अनुशयिन्
m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि)<BR> ^1 Connected with as with a consequence; e. g. सुखानुशयी रागः । दुःखानुशयी द्वेषः ।.<BR> ^2 (In the Vedánta phil.) The same as अनुशयवत्; e. g. तत्र संशयः । किमस्मिन्नवधौ स्थावरजात्यापन्नाः स्थावरसुखदुःखभाजोऽनुशयिनो भवन्ति । आहोस्वित्क्षेत्रज्ञान्तराधिष्ठितेषु स्थावरशरीरेषु संश्लेषमात्रं गच्छन्तीति ।<BR> ^3 Devotedly attached to, faithful.<BR> ^4 Repentant, penitent. E. अनुशय, taddh. aff. इनि.

anushara|अनुशर
Tatpur. m. (-रः) A Rákshasa, a sort of demon. E. शृ with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्.

anushastra|अनुशस्त्र
Tatpur. n. (-स्त्रम्) (In Medicine.) A subsidiary instrument or surgical means in general, used either in want of the proper instrument or when the patient is afraid of the latter; as such are named: bambu (त्वक्सार), crystal, glass (काच), ruby (कुरुविन्द), leeches, fire, alkali (क्षार), the finger nail, and several plants (गोजी, शेफालिका, शाकपत्र, करीर, बालाङ्गुलि). E. अनु and शस्त्र.

anushaaya|अनुशाय
[This word occurs as a meaning of the particle नु, in the Calc. ed. of Hem. n. 7. 11, but is a bad reading for अनुशय.]

anushaayin|अनुशायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Adhering, closely connected with. E. शी with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anushaasaka|अनुशासक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सकः-सिका-सकम्) Ruling, governing, directing. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anushaasat|अनुशासत्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-न्-ती-त्) Ruling, teaching &c., see शास्. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. शतृ.

anushaasana|अनुशासन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Instruction, order, precept; e. g. तन्मनोरनुशासनम् or भवादृशेषु प्रमदाजनोदितं भवत्य धिक्षेप इवानुशासनम्; the 13th book of the Mahábh. is called the book of precepts ‘अनुशासनपर्वन्’.<BR> ^2 Explanation, comment, explanatory treatise; e. g. योगानुशासन which is thus explained: युक्तिर्योगः समाधानम् । अनुशिष्यते व्याख्यायते लक्षणभेदोपायफलैर्येन तदनुशासनम् ।. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anushaasaniiya|अनुशासनीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be instructed, directed, ruled. E. शास् with अनु, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

anushaasita|अनुशासित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Instructed, directed, governed. E. शास् in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anushaasitR|अनुशासितृ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ता-त्री-तृ) Instructing, ruling, governing, commanding, directing. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. तृच्.

anushaasin|अनुशासिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-सी-सिनी-सि) Punishing. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anushaasya|अनुशास्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-स्यः-स्या-स्यम्) To be instructed, directed, ruled. E. शास् with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anushixin|अनुशिक्षिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्षी-क्षिणी-क्षि) Learning, practising. E. शिक्ष् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anushikha|अनुशिख
Tatpur.(?) The name of a serpent which according to a legend in the Panchavinśa-Bráhmańa officiated as Potŕipriest in a sacrifice performed to conquer Death. E. अनु and शिख, the name of another serpent-priest.

anushivam|अनुशिवम्
Avyayíbh. After Śiva. E. अनु and शिव.

anushishu|अनुशिशु
Bahuvr. f. (-शुः) Followed by her young (as a mare &c.). E. अनु and शिशु.

anushiShTa|अनुशिष्ट
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्टः-ष्टा-ष्टम्)<BR> ^1 Taught, ordered, laid down as a rule; e. g. यद्यपि छन्दःशास्त्रे सानुस्वारस्य गुरुत्वमनुशिष्टं &c.<BR> ^2 Ruled, governed.<BR> ^3 (In Law.) Adjudged, decided, settled, so that the penalty or the punishment may be inflicted; (a lawsuit is तीरित when the cause is properly decided according to evidence but the penalty not yet fixed, and अनुशिष्ट when it is brought up to the point of punishment, the only bar to the carrying out of the sentence then being the appeal). E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anushiShTi|अनुशिष्टि
Tatpur. f. (-ष्टिः) Instruction, order, command. E. शास् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anushiilana|अनुशीलन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Constant study of a Śástra.<BR> ^2 Repeated and devoted service. E. अनु and शीलन.

anushoka|अनुशोक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) Sorrow, repentance, regret. E. शुच् with अनु, kŕit aff. घञ्.

anushochaka|अनुशोचक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-चकः-चिका-चकम्)<BR> ^1 Grieving, one who repents.<BR> ^2 Occasioning repentance. E. शुच् with अनु (2. in the caus.), kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anushochana|अनुशोचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Sorrow, repentance. E. शुच् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anushochita|अनुशोचित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Regretted, repented of. E. शुच् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anushobhin|अनुशोभिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-भी-भिनी-भि) Splendid, shining. E. शुभ् with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि.

anushrava|अनुश्रव
Tatpur. m. (-वः) Sacred tradition, such as is contained in the Veda, Ágamas &c. E. श्रु with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्.

anushruta|अनुश्रुत
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Handed down by sacred tradition (comp. the preceding). E. श्रु with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuShak|अनुषक्
ind. (see निपात)<BR> ^1 In due order, in succession; e. g. अनुषक्प्रविशतीति बन्धुता.<BR> ^2 Consequently. E. सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्. Compare आनुषक्. 

anuShakta|अनुषक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्)<BR> ^1 Adhered to, connected with.<BR> ^2 Supplied (as a word from a preceding passage). E. सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuShanga|अनुषङ्ग
Tatpur. m. (-ङ्गः)<BR> ^1 Connexion, conjunction, association, attachment (lit. and fig.) e. g. (वारिणा) अन्तर्गलितेन मन्मथशिखीसिक्तोऽनुषङ्गोद्भवः (comm. प्रियस्मरणादुत्पन्नः).<BR> ^2 Tenderness, compassion.<BR> ^3 Necessary consequence, the connexion of a subsequent with a previous act.<BR> ^4 Grammatical relation, connexion of, or connecting a word of a preceding with those of a subsequent passage; e. g. कच्चिदित्यस्यानुषङ्गं केचिन्नेच्छन्ति as the Schol. observes with reference to कच्चित् in Bhattik. 6. 67 when commenting on 6. 68, or in the Mímánsá: अनुषङ्गो वाक्यपरिसमाप्तिः सर्वेषु तुल्ययोगित्वात्. Comp. अनुषञ्जन. (Different from अध्याहार.)<BR> ^5 (In Grammar.) Appendage, viz. the nasal which is connected with certain radicals and dropped in certain derivatives; e. g. the nasal in तृम्प्, दृम्प्, शुम्भ्, सञ्ज् &c. E. सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕit aff. अच्.

anuShangin|अनुषङ्गिन्
m. f. n. (-ङ्गी-ङ्गिणी-ङ्गि)<BR> ^1 Addicted or attached to.<BR> ^2 Connected with.<BR> ^3 Embracing. E. अनुषङ्ग, taddh. aff. इनि.

anuShanjana|अनुषञ्जन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Grammatical relation, connecting a word of a preceding with those of a subsequent passage; e. g. या ते अग्ने रजेत्यध्याहारो यद्वानुषञ्जनम्. Comp. अनुषङ्ग. E. सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuShanjaniiya|अनुषञ्जनीय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्)<BR> ^1 To be connected.<BR> ^2 To be supplied (as a word from a preceding in a subsequent passage; comp. अनुषङ्ग); e. g. शक्रं (= इन्द्रं) निर्जित्यानीताः । राक्षसेन्द्रेण इत्यनुषञ्जनीयम् in Bhattik. 7. 94. &c. &c. E. सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕitya aff. अनीयर्.

anuShaT|अनुषट्
ind. (see निपात) Apparently the same as अनुषक् q. v. (It is omitted in some of the Gańa lists, while the Gańaratnamahodadhi mentions आनुषट् as a various reading of अनुषक्.) E. probably सञ्ज् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्.

anuShaNDa|अनुषण्ड
Bahuvr. (?) The name of a place or country. E. (?).

anuShikta|अनुषिक्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-क्तः-क्ता-क्तम्) Re-watered or-sprinkled. E. अनु and सिक्त.

anuShuka|अनुषुक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) Probably the epithet of a divinity; the same as आनुषुक. (Some read instead of this word अनुसूयक which seems to be wrong, others अनुषूक which is doubtful. Compare also आनुसुक.) E. The Gańaratnamahodadhi derives अनुषुक from अनुसू and क (from कै) with a short vowel before कः अनुषुवतीति अनुषू । तं कायतीति अनुषुक । केऽण इति ह्रस्वत्वे; this application, however, of Páń. VII. 4. 13. to the etym. given, seems very objectionable.

anuSheka|अनुषेक
Tatpur. m. (-कः) Watering or sprinkling over again. E. अनु and सेक.

anuShechana|अनुषेचन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Watering or sprinkling over again. E. अनु and सेचन.

anuShTuti|अनुष्टुति
Tatpur. f. (-तिः) Praise, eulogy. E. स्तु with अनु, kŕit aff. क्तिन्.

anuShTubgarbhaa|अनुष्टुब्गर्भा
Bahuvr. f. (-र्भा) The name of a metre in the Vedas; it belongs to the class called उष्णिह् and consists of four Pádas, the first of which contains five and each of the three others eight syllables. E. अनुष्टुभ् and गर्भ.

anuShTubh|अनुष्टुभ्
Tatpur. f. (-ष्टुप्)<BR> ^1 Speech, in general.<BR> ^2 A name of  Saraswatí.<BR> ^3 The name of a class of metres which consists of 32 syllables and, in the Vedas, is regulated by the number of syllables only, in classical poetry by number and quantity. In the Vedas the 32 syllables are distributed either in Tetrastichs of 8 syllables in each line, or in Triplets of either 12 + 8 + 12 or 12 + 12 + 8 or 8 + 12 + 12 syllables. For the varieties of the Anusht́ubh in the classical poetry see चित्रपदा, विद्युन्माला, माणवक or माणवकाक्रीडा, हंसरुत, प्रमाणिका or नगस्वरूपिणी or मतल्लिका, समानिका or मल्लिका, वितान, तुङ्गा, कमल, हंसपदी, मातङ्गी, रम्भा and the metre which is most in use but the quantity of which is not so invariable as that of the named varieties viz. the श्लोक. In a vaidik hymn the Anusht́ubh is represented as one of the primitive creations, that originated together with the moon; according to some Puráńas it was created from the northern mouth of the fourheaded Brahman (m.) together with the Atharvaveda, a portion of the Sámaveda and some hymns as well as the Áptoryáma portion of the Jyotisht́oma sacrifice; accord. to another Puráńa from the tendons of Brahman. (The Kásiká considers the vaidik अनुष्ट्या equivalent to the classical instrum. अनुष्टुभा; but अनुष्ट्या is probably an erroneous reading for अनुष्ट्या q. v.) E. स्तुभ् with अनु, kŕit aff. क्विप्, so called according to the Nirukta ‘because it follows in praise (अनुष्टोभति) with its fourth Páda the Gáyatrí metre which consists only of three Pádas or stanzas’.

anuShTobhana|अनुष्टोभन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Praising after, following in praise. E. स्तुभ् with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuShTra|अनुष्ट्र
Tatpur. m. (-ष्ट्रः) A bad camel &c. E. अ neg. and उष्ट्र.

anuShTha|अनुष्ठ
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-ष्ठः-ष्ठा-ष्ठम्) Standing in succession, one after the other. E. स्था with अनु, kŕit aff. क.

anuShThaatR|अनुष्ठातृ
Tatpur. m. (-ता) One who performs or executes a work. E. स्था with अनु, kŕit aff. तृच्.

anuShThaana|अनुष्ठान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Commencement or course of proceeding.<BR> ^2 Doing or performing in general; e. g. विहितानुष्ठान; सकलानुष्ठान; योगाङ्गानुष्ठान; ‘वेदाध्ययनं ततस्तदर्थजिज्ञासा ततस्तदर्थानुष्ठानम्’.<BR> ^3 Practice, espreligious practice, performance of sacrificial or other ceremonies; e. g. पश्वनुष्ठान, ‘ceremonies connected with the immolation of the sacrificial animal’, अनुष्ठानरूपफलपर्यवसान ‘completion of results by means of sacrificial acts’.<BR> ^4 Concurrence, agreement, conforming to. E. स्था with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuShThaanakrama|अनुष्ठानक्रम
Tatpur. m. (-मः) The order in which religious ceremonies are to be or are performed. E. अनुष्ठान and क्रम.

anuShThaanashariira|अनुष्ठानशरीर
Tatpur. n. (-रम्) (In the Sánkhya philos.) A body which is presumed to be intermediate between the subtle body (लिङ्गशरीर or सूक्ष्मशरीर) and the grosser body (स्थूलशरीर), composed of the five elements but tenuous or refined and the vehicle of the subtle body. Comp. अधिष्ठानशरीर. E. अनुष्ठान and शरीर.

anuShThaanasmaaraka|अनुष्ठानस्मारक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-रकः-रिका-रकम्) Reminding of religious ceremonies; said of certain vaidik passages which properly do not answer the general definition given of a Mantra, but which nevertheless are called so by the liturgical authors, because they remind of duties taught or explained in a more explicit manner by other Mantras. E. अनुष्ठान and स्मारक. 

anuShThaapaka|अनुष्ठापक
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-पकः-पिका-पकम्) Causing to do or to perform an act; e. g. विनियोगोऽनुष्ठापकविधित्वान्मुख्यः ।. E. स्था, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ण्वुल्.

anuShThaapana|अनुष्ठापन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) The causing to do or to perform an act. E. स्था, in the caus., with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anuShThaayin|अनुष्ठायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Doing, performing an act. E. स्था with अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि and ágama युक्.

anuShThi|अनुष्ठि
Tatpur. f. (-ष्ठिः) (ved.) Proper order, succession; this word occurs only in the instrum. अनुष्ठ्या ‘in the order, one by one, successively’. E. स्था with अनु, uń.(?) aff. कि.

anuShThita|अनुष्ठित
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्)<BR> ^1 Done, practised.<BR> ^2 Effected, accomplished.<BR> ^3 Followed, observed.<BR> ^4 Agreed to, conformed to, done accordingly. E. स्था with अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anuShThu|अनुष्ठु
(ved.) I. Tatpur. f. (-ष्ठुः) Proper order, succession; this word occurs only in the instrum. अनुष्ठुया which has the same meaning as the Avyayíbh. E. स्था with अनु, uń. aff. कु. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-ष्ठु) In proper order, in regular succession, properly. E. अनु and स्थु; or अनुष्ठु may be considered, according to the native comm., as a neuter used adverbially, when the etym. would be that of I.

anuShTheya|अनुष्ठेय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) To be effected or accomplished &c. See the meanings of अनुष्ठित and अनुष्ठान. E. स्था with अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anuShNa|अनुष्ण
Tatpur. 1. m. f. n. (-ष्णः-ष्णा-ष्णम्)<BR> ^1 Not hot, cold, chilly.<BR> ^2 Lazy, sluggish. BREAḲ. n. (-ष्णम्) A blue lotus (Nymphæa cærulea). <BR>3. f. (-ष्णा) The name of a river. E. अ neg. and उष्ण.

anuShNaka|अनुष्णक
m. f. n. (-कः-का-कम्) The same as the preceding. E. अनुष्ण, taddh. aff. कन्.

anuShNagu|अनुष्णगु
Bahuvr. m. (-गुः) The moon (lit. having cold rays); e. g. विक्षिप्यते स्वपातेन स्वक्रान्त्यन्तादनुष्णगुः ।. E. अनुष्ण and गो.

anuShNavallikaa|अनुष्णवल्लिका
Tatpur. f. (-का) A dark species of the Dúb (Panicum dactylon); see नीलदूर्वा. E. अनुष्ण and वल्लिका.

anuShNaashiita|अनुष्णाशीत
Dwandwa m. f. n. (-तः-ता-तम्) Neither cold nor hot; e. g. अपाकजोऽनुष्णाशीतः स्पर्शस्तु पवने मतः ।. E. अनुष्ण and अशीत.

anuShvadha|अनुष्वध
(ved.) I. Tatpur. m. f. n. (-धः-धा-धम्) Accompanied with food, viz. clarified butter &c., an epithet of Soma. <BR>II. Avyayibh. (-धम्)<BR> ^1 In consequence of (partaking of) food, through food, viz. Soma &c.<BR> ^2 Food for food, to every food (as clarified butter).<BR> ^3 After every oblation; e. g. पत्नीवतस्त्रिंशतं त्रींश्च देवाननुष्वधमावह मादयस्व. E. अनु and स्वधा.

anusaMvatsaram|अनुसंवत्सरम्
Avyayíbh. Year for year, every year. (In its derivative आनुसांवत्सरिक both parts of the compound assume Vŕiddhi.) E. अनु and संवत्सर.

anusaMvaraNam|अनुसंवरणम्
Avyayíbh. Probably a bad reading for अनुसञ्चरणम् q. v.

anusaMsarpam|अनुसंसर्पम्
Avyayíbh.(?) At each meeting(?). E. अनु and संसर्प, or perhaps a Tatpur., ‘meeting in succession’ from सृप् with सम् and अनु, kŕit aff. णमुल्.

anusaMhitam|अनुसंहितम्
Avyayíbh. According to the Sanhitá-text of the Veda. E. अनु and संहिता.

anusakhi|अनुसखि
Tatpur. m. (-खा) A companion-friend(?); e. g. अनुसखा सयूथ्यः. E. अनु and सखि. 

anusancaraNam|अनुसञ्चरणम्
Avyayíbh. At each meeting; e. g. अनुसंचरणं दीयते. E. अनु and सञ्चरण.

anusandhaatavya|अनुसन्धातव्य
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-व्यः-व्या-व्यम्) To be connected reasonably, to be investigated, to be looked after or inquired into. See अनुसन्धेय. E. धा with सम् and अनु, kŕitya aff. तव्य.

anusandhaana|अनुसन्धान
Tatpur. n. (-नम्)<BR> ^1 Congruous or suitable connexion; e. g. यथा वाक्यद्वयानुसंधानसंपन्नं प्रकरणं पृथक्प्रमाणम् । तथा प्रकरणद्वयानुसंधानसंपन्नः क्रमः कुतो न मानं स्यात्.<BR> ^2 (In the Vaiśeshika phil.) the same as उपनय of the Nyáya phil.; viz. in a syllogism (see न्याय) which according to the native phil. consists of five parts, the fourth part or the application to the terminus major (i. e. the congruous connexion of the application with the latter); e. g. in a syllogism ‘^a. a word is perishable (the प्रतिज्ञा)<BR> ^b. because it is produced artificially (the अपदेश)<BR> ^c. all that is produced artificially is perishable (the निदर्शन)<BR> ^d. now, the word has the properties of what is artificially produced<BR> ^e. therefore it is perishable (the प्रत्याम्नाय or निगमन)--’<BR> ^d. is the अनुसन्धान or in the Nyáya the उपनय.<BR> ^3 Inquiry, investigation, searching.<BR> ^4 Close or narrow inspection. E. धा with सम् and अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anusandhaayin|अनुसन्धायिन्
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यी-यिनी-यि) Investigating, searching. E. धा with सम् and अनु, kŕit aff. णिनि and ágama युक्.

anusandheya|अनुसन्धेय
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-यः-या-यम्) The same as अनुसन्धातव्य; e. g. अत्र (in the Nalodaya) कथोपकथनं भारते ऽनुसन्धेयम्. E. धा with सम् and अनु, kŕitya aff. यत्.

anusandhyam|अनुसन्ध्यम्
Avyayíbh. Every twilight, every evening. E. अनु and सन्ध्या.

anusamaya|अनुसमय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) Necessary association, a connexion which is the result of reasoning; e. g. इत्येवं पदार्थानुसमयो ऽभ्युपेतव्यः । न तु काण्डानुसमयः ‘thus the connexion (between the subjects of discussion) results from the bearing of the words, not from the circumstance that they are named in the same book’. E. अनु and समय.

anusamaapana|अनुसमापन
Tatpur. n. (-नम्) Congruous completion or conclusion. E. अनु and समापन.

anusamudram|अनुसमुद्रम्
Avyayíbh. Near the sea. E. अनु and समुद्र.

anusampraapta|अनुसम्प्राप्त
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-प्तः-प्ता-प्तम्) Arrived, come, arrived in consequence of, happened accordingly; e. g. तदिदं मेऽनुसंप्राप्तं दुःखम्. E. आप् with प्र-सम्-अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anusambaddha|अनुसम्बद्ध
Tatpur. m. f. n. (-द्धः-द्धा-द्धम्) Connected with. E. बन्ध् with सम् and अनु, kŕit aff. क्त.

anusara|अनुसर
I. Tatpur. m. (-रः) A companion, a follower, an attendant. E. सृ with अनु, kŕit aff. अप्. <BR>II. Avyayíbh. (-रम्) Near or on a lake(?). Compare आनुसर्य. E. अनु and सर.

anusaraNa|अनुसरण
Tatpur. n. (-णम्)<BR> ^1 Following, going after, lit. and fig.; e. g. वस्तुतत्त्वानुसरण.<BR> ^2 Conformity to, consequence of. See अनुसार. E. सृ with अनु, kŕit aff. ल्युट्.

anusarpa|अनुसर्प
Tatpur. m. (-र्पः) A reptile, a being like a serpent. E. अनु and सर्प.

anusavanam|अनुसवनम्
Avyayíbh.<BR> ^1 At each savana or sacrifice.<BR> ^2 Every moment; e. g. न कश्चन पुरुषो वाञ्छति…किमपि…भर्तर्यनुसवनं विजृम्भितस्नेहातिशयमन्तरेण । (comm. भर्तरि ऋषभदेवे प्रतिक्षणमुल्लसितस्नेहोद्रेकं विनान्यन्न वाञ्छति ॥). E. अनु and सवन. 

anusaatam|अनुसातम्
Avyayíbh. According to pleasure. E. अनु and सात.

anusaama|अनुसाम
