anuuka|अनूक
Tatpur. 1. m. (-कः)<BR> ^1 The spine (ved.).<BR> ^2 A part of the altar(?) (ved.).<BR> ^3 A former state of existence. BREAḲ. n. (-कम्) Race, family. <BR>3. m. n. (-कः-कम्) Disposition, temperament. E. The native etym. derives it from उच् with अनु, kŕit aff. क or even from कै with अनु, kŕit aff. क with the prolongation of उ; but it comes more probably from अच् with अनु, and stands in the same relation to अन्वच् as प्रतीक to प्रत्यच्, समीक to सम्यच्.

anuukavana|अनूकवन
