anuuchaana|अनूचान
Tatpur. 1. m. (-नः)<BR> ^1 A Bráhmana who is able to repeat, to read and to teach the Veda in the same manner as the teacher has enounced it (compare अनुवचन), one versed in the Vedas and Vedángas; e. g. ब्राह्मणानामनूचानतमः.<BR> ^2 An excellent physician. BREAḲ. m. f. n. (-नः-ना-नम्) Well-behaved, decorous, humble. E. वच् with अनु, kŕit aff. कानच्.

anuuchii|अनूची
