antaHpaTa|अन्तःपट
Tatpur. m. n. (-टः-टम्) A screen of silk or cloth hold up between the bride and bridegroom, or between the  student who is to receive the sacred cord and the spiritual teacher, until the moment deemed auspicious by the astrologer arrives for the parties to see each other in the one case, and in the other of reciting the mystical initiatory words. E. अन्तर् and पट.

