antaHpurasahaaya|अन्तःपुरसहाय
Tatpur. m. (-यः) An assistant belonging to the gynæceum or inner apartments (compare स्थापत्य); such assistants are: ‘dwarfs, eunuchs, Kirátas or mountaineers<BR> --retained as guards--Mlechchhas or barbarians, Abhíras, the mock-brother-in-law of a king--i. e. the brother of his concubine--humpbacks, mutes &c. E. अन्तःपुर and सहाय.

